				"kuvausteksti" : "N-PRO Resources Oy Ltd is a staffing and recruiting company belonging to Nipromec Group focusing mainly on needs of our customers in the fields of energy, industry and offshore.\r\n\r\nWe are looking for Safety Officers for our client working on the Olkiluoto 3 project. Work starts as soon as possible, estimated duration is 12 months.\r\n\r\nSafety Officer's tasks included, but are not limited to:\r\n-Anticipate difficulties (interfaces) and propose alternative ways to work.\r\n-Preliminary review of the risk assessment / Method Statement submitted by the contractors.\r\n-Preliminary review of the risk assessment / method Statement submitted by the client for commissioning activity.\r\n-Check the implementation on site of safety rules and mitigation measure defined in the risk assessment.\r\n-Manage the safety inspection on site with the contractors. Follow up corrective actions defined during the inspection.\r\n-Closely work with the supervisors and commissioning team to have the knowledge of the coming activities (anticipating) and involve them in the daily safety.\r\n-Animate the safety in the Commissioning team, through visit in spot, training, lesson learned.\r\n-Be pro-active to propose safety issues to improve our level and the attitude on site.\r\n\r\nSkills required:\r\n-HSE background on commissioning activities with complex systems. The Safety officer could have a technical experience on a previous nuclear power plant activities like team leader or supervisor.\r\n-Good knowledge of Finnish Occupational Health and Safety Regulations.\r\n-Experienced on running nuclear power plant.\r\n-Experienced on construction site.\r\n-Qualified for OHSAS 1800 referential (set up and follow-up of the safety management system).\r\n-Comfortable in speaking in public, especially when giving training and eventually leading meetings.\r\n-Knowledge or experience in commissioning risks linked to industrial activities is required.\r\n-Fluent English, Finnish is a benefit.\r\n\r\nPositions are filled as soon as suitable candidates are found. To apply please send application and CV with salary request to info@n-pro.fi or fill in an application at www.n-pro.fi",
