				"kuvausteksti" : "Polar is the pioneer of wearable sports and fitness technology and the leader of heart rate monitoring for more than 35 years. We at Polar believe that all people are made to move - this is why we cater for all levels of fitness. We combine leading physiological research with cutting-edge technology solutions and innovative design to create products that help everyone achieve more, whether their goal is to be more active in daily life, boost sports performance or break world records. Our devices are accompanied by Polar Flow, the app and web service that acts as a personalized window into the user's life data. Our wide range of products, apps, services and group solutions reflects Polar's mission: to help everyone live a healthy and happy life.\r\n\r\nAt Polar, you will be working for a global company with an international team of professionals who truly believe in what they do.\r\n\r\nWe are now looking for the following professional\r\n\r\niOS Developers for a permanent position\r\n\r\nPolar Service Development Unit is looking for talented software engineers to join our iOS mobile application development team at Kempele / Oulu, Finland. You will be part of software development team that has full end-to-end responsibility to develop and maintain great user experiences to our next generation Polar service products, such as Polar Flow, Team Pro and Club. \r\n\r\nAs a scrum team member, your main objective is to ensure that you and your team will deliver top quality applications and user experiences to our customers worldwide. You have proven track record of working in modern SW development projects and you have personal passion to develop yourself as part of your daily developer routines. Your daily coding tasks will include all the traditional scrum team activities from code reviews to unit tests but we also appreciate proactive attitude being one of the team builders within the team.\r\n\r\nAs Polar Service Development unit - we offer you a unique opportunity to be part of the team who provides smart coaching solutions to Polar customers from top-athletes and world-class teams to active fitness customers all over the world. Polar Service Products offers comprehensive range of features to help people to track their physical activity including sleep analysis, and that way helping people to learn and make them to understand more about their lifestyle and body. \r\n\r\nYou will be part of Polar ecosystem development and thus we offer you an excellent opportunity to develop yourself not only as iOS coder but getting familiar with the latest system backend and device technologies. Close cooperation with Polar Research unit also offers you a unique opportunity to learn more about the data behind the activity numbers and thus makes your developer day much more extensive.\r\n\r\nWe expect you to have:\r\n- Experience in Objective-C programming and iOS development\r\n- Swift experience is an advantage\r\n- Experience of modern agile software development practices\r\n- Continuous integration and unit testing experience\r\n- Fluent use of Git, JIRA, Confluence and Jenkins\r\n- Pro-active, can-do attitude for daily task\r\n- Team player\r\n- Reference application in Appstore is considered as an advantage\r\n- Good written and spoken English and Finnish\r\n\r\nThe positions are located in Kempele  / Oulu, Finland.\r\n\r\nPositions will be filled when suitable candidates are found.\r\n\r\nFor further information please contact Mr. Timo Vuolteenaho (timo.vuolteenaho@polar.com). Please send your application to recruitment@polar.com with the title of 'Vuolteenaho/ Software Engineers, iOS Applications Development'.",
