				"kuvausteksti" : "Enersense International Oy provides its customers with resourcing solutions which appreciate the fluctuations in their projects. Our company is an ISO 9001:2008/14001:2004-certified actor with more than ten years of experience in operating in close cooperation with large-scale nuclear and construction sites, the Olkiluoto 3 nuclear power plant site being the largest of them. \r\n\r\nWe are currently looking for an SSS Mechanical Engineer for our client in Olkiluoto Nuclear Power Plant, Finland.  We are offering challenging work in an international project environment.\r\n\r\nMain Tasks and Responsibilities\r\n\r\n- Analysis and Closure of Open Points\r\n- Review of supplier documentation\r\n- Accountability for the progress on the open point closure related engineering tasks\r\n- Check/prepare/close CRs/FCRs/DCRs/NCRs (Modification) new orders/open points... Shall close the issues independent (due to technical expertise) or prepare in a way that efficient and fast execution is possible\r\n- Assisting in all other technical issues/clarifications related to SSS Mechanical on Large Cranes\r\n- Support Construction and Commissioning Team in technical issues and is acting as main interface for Large Cranes\r\n- Reporting: Provide input to the different weekly/monthly reports (e.g. 2MLA)\r\n- Report to SSS Task Leader such as priorities according to the Site Installation Needs\r\n- Support time schedule planning in close collaboration with Construction and Commissioning in order to secure finalization on time\r\n- Reporting to SSS EDL\r\n- Clarifications with other departments, subcontractors, back office and client related scope\r\n\r\nRequirements\r\n\r\n- Engineering expertise in the area of Mechanical Engineering\r\n- Good verbal and written communication skills\r\n- Ability to work confidently within large teams\r\n- Ability to express oneself clearly verbally and in writing\r\n- Adapt successfully to changing situations and environments\r\n- Gather information systematically to establish facts and principles\r\n- Problem solving skills\r\n- Good time management skills\r\n- Ability to prioritize and meet deadlines\r\n- Highly motivates to solve problems/issues\r\n- Target oriented\r\n- Good knowledge of Mechanical Engineering, especially for on-site environment\r\n\r\nTechnical\r\n\r\n- At least six years of vast expertise in the are of Mechanical Engineering or Large Cranes or large components\r\n- Knowledge of mechanical calculations\r\n- Good knowledge of NavisWorks and/or AutoCAD or equal CAD tools\r\n\r\nLanguage Skills\r\n\r\n- Fluent in English\r\n- Knowledge of other languages seen as an advantage\r\n\r\nPlease register as a jobseeker and apply for the position through our website.\r\n\r\nIf you have questions regarding the position, please contact Mrs. Sanna Uronen by E-mail, sanna.uronen@enersense.eu.\r\n\r\nDrug test and concise security clearance will be done for the selected person in order to get the permanent access to OL3 site.\r\n\r\nThe post will be filled as soon as a suitable applicant is found.",
