				"kuvausteksti" : "Enersense International Oy provides its customers with resourcing solutions which appreciate the fluctuations in their projects. Our company is an ISO 9001:2008/14001:2004-certified actor with more than ten years of experience in operating in close cooperation with large-scale nuclear and construction sites, the Olkiluoto 3 nuclear power plant site being the largest of them. \r\n\r\nWe are currently looking for a Radiation Protection Engineer for our client in Olkiluoto Nuclear Power Plant. We are offering challenging work in an international project environment.\r\n\r\nMain Tasks and Responsibilities\r\n\r\n- Assessment of the N-16 source term from the measured gamma dose rates\r\n- Prepare methodology\r\n- Perform calculations for the installation of the detectors\r\n- Procure the detectors\r\n- Participate to the installation of the detectors\r\n- Monitor the results (extrapolation) and perform the reporting to the project and customer\r\n- Evaluate potential changes in zoning and predicted service lifetimes to be implemented only after commissioning feedback becomes available\r\n- Confirmation of radiation zoning, including assessment of potential hot spots close to buildings' openings (SCP RAD)\r\n- Initiate corrective actions in case of deviations, the candidate will coordinate the handling of CR/DCR if any related to radiation shielding\r\n- Participate in review and testing of equipment is required during commissioning\r\n- Support the commissioning for execution of the client's part of commissioning dose rate measurements\r\n- Troubleshoot and perform analysis activities during commissioning\r\n- Optional: Review all test reports related to radiation protection\r\n\r\nRequirements\r\n\r\n- Engineering Degree in Nuclear or Radiological Engineering\r\n- Experience in nuclear power plant operations\r\n- At least one significant experience in testing or commissioning activities related to radiation protection\r\n- Knowledge of source term characteristics\r\n- Capacity of organization and managing daily activities involving several disciplines\r\n- Excellent relational and communicational skills\r\n- Analysis and synthesis skills\r\n- Rigorous, especially for adherence to procedures in force on site including configuration management\r\n- Aware of safety and security aspects\r\n- Adherence to access requirements in Controlled Area and Sign Posting\r\n- Use of radiation protection software\r\n- Knowledge of radiation protection products such as MIRION products would be beneficial\r\n- Establishment and/or review of system test procedures\r\n- Knowledge in radiation protection technology\r\n- Experience in nuclear safety and/or system engineering\r\n\r\nLanguage Skills\r\n\r\n- Fluent in English\r\n- Other languages considered beneficial\r\n\r\nPlease register as a jobseeker and apply for the position through our website. \r\n\r\nIf you have questions regarding the position, please contact Mrs. Sanna Uronen by E-mail, sanna.uronen@enersense.eu.\r\n\r\nDrug test and concise security clearance will be done for the selected person in order to get the permanent access to OL3 site.\r\n\r\nThe post will be filled as soon as a suitable applicant is found.",
