				"kuvausteksti" : "Hey there code lover. \r\n\r\nWe've said it before and we'll say it again: people just can't get enough of that magic you do, developers. The demand for that sweet, sweet programming knowledge of yours is higher than ever before. \r\n\r\nThat's why we're looking to add three new system developers to our Vaasa office, but you personally don't have to be all three of them. (wait what?) \r\n\r\nAnyway, this is the stuff we are after:\r\n\r\n- Java, Objective-C, C# experience (PHP, C and C++ are also a big plus plus)\r\n- Angular, JavaScript, HTML5 and CSS3 knowledge\r\n- Front and back-end development, preferably the agile kind\r\n- At least one (1) human language\r\n- Agile development/scrum experience (if you don't have it, there's always scruum for improvement)\r\n- Social skills and a terrible sense of humor (maybe you even enjoyed the awful pun above)\r\n\r\nA little bit about us\r\nAt Gambit, we digitize to make things easier. Our business-oriented IoT solutions, apps and third party integrations make every work day better than the previous one. Our growing team currently consists of fourteen developers, designers and project managers, as well as a bunch of cute dogs. Although they do lack some work morale. The dogs that is, not the humans.\r\n\r\n\r\nWorking at Gambit\r\nWe like to balance hard work with good times. Creating a positive work environment is one of our driving factors. That's why we always meet up every now and then outside of work to barbeque, watch a movie or play Dungeons & Dragons.\r\n\r\nOur office is located in Runsoria Business Park in Vaasa. For this position, remote location is not possible. But honestly: why wouldn't you want to work on-site? We have the best lunch in town, video games, a ping pong table and there's also a gym in the building (or so we've been told).\r\n\r\nStart date for these full time positions are flexible but preferably as soon as possible.",
