				"kuvausteksti" : "Ultimate.ai is a deep tech company building a world class customer service automation platform using state of the art deep learning techniques. We are growing rapidly in Finland and abroad, our team has conquered multiple hackathons with large clients, we were selected as part of the Dubai Future Accelerators (1% acceptance rate) where we are working the with Government of Dubai. We are also part of NVIDIA's Inception program for deep learning startups. This is the right time to join our team and grow your expertise while working at a fast paced startup.\r\n\r\nAs one of the first employees in our Development team you will have a big impact on our general architecture. You will be working closely with our development team and customers to build a world class customer service automation platform. You will move quickly with our customers and build new features in lean sprints.\r\n\r\nResponsibilities\r\n-Take charge of expanding our back-end architecture and APIs\r\n-Implement new features for conversational use cases based on customer needs\r\n-Participate in development of our customer service dashboard and knowledge base\r\n-Building integrations to third party systems\r\n\r\nRequirements\r\n-Experience with server side programming, Python, Nodejs etc.\r\n-Experience of working with (No)SQL databases\r\n-Understanding of programming best practices\r\n-Disciplined approach for writing, testing and documenting code\r\n-Nice to have experience: React, HTML, CSS, ES6\r\n\r\nBenefits\r\n-Freedom to think by yourself and implement your own ideas\r\n-Competitive salary and stock options program\r\n-Place in a small and agile team with \"no bs\" attitude\r\n-Opportunity to develop your skills and role in the company\r\n\r\nYou can work from our offices in Helsinki or Tampere.\r\n\r\nJoin us!\r\nSend us an email jaakko(at)ultimate.ai with your Application and CV. We will get back to you as soon as possible.\r\n\r\np.s. we appreciate the most your own projects so link them (github, stackoverflow etc) in your Application if possible.",
