				"kuvausteksti" : "Job Title : Apps Developer / Intern\r\nSeniority Level : Not Applicable\r\nIndustry : Consumer Electronics, Industry Electronics, Automotive Electronics\r\nEmployment Type : Full-time\r\n\r\nJob description\r\n- Design, develop and verify Apps (e.g. Sensor data logger Android/iOS Apps, Sensor evaluation Windows Apps)\r\n- Investigate, prototype and deliver new and innovative system solutions\r\n- Participate in design reviews for development and documentation\r\n- Work with new technologies that are vital to product development\r\n- Perform tasks including debug, bring-up, Beta and production software development\r\n- Deliver investigation plans and reports, architectural documents, design specs, software and firmware source code, build scripts\r\n- Work in an international environment\r\n- Close collaboration in agile teams, successfully collaborate with hardware product teams\r\nRequirements\r\n- BSc degree in computer science or comparable\r\n- Skill to create an intuitive, efficient and pleasing GUIs\r\n- Experience in Application software design, development and debugging preferably on Android/iOS/Windows platform\r\n- Knowledge of object oriented programming\r\n- SW development skills and experiences (C++, Java)\r\n- SW platform skills and experiences (Android/iOS/Windows or others)\r\n- Good coordination and communication skills\r\n- Ability to efficiently gain an overview on complex technical content\r\n- Ability to work independently\r\n- Fluent English, active usage of the language\r\n\r\n About ROHM Semiconductor\r\n ROHM Semiconductor is an industry leader in system LSI, discrete components and module products, utilizing the latest in semiconductor technology. ROHM's proprietary production system, which includes some of the most advanced automation technology, is a major factor in keeping it at the forefront of the electronic component manufacturing industry. In addition to its development of electronic components, ROHM has also developed its own production system so that it can focus on specific aspects of customized product development. ROHM employs highly skilled engineers with expertise in all aspects of design, development and production. This allows ROHM the flexibility to take on a wide range of applications and projects and the capability to serve valuable clients in the automotive, telecommunication and computer sectors, as well as consumer OEMs.\r\n\r\n About Kionix\r\n Kionix, Inc., a global MEMS inertial sensor manufacturer based in Ithaca, NY, USA, offers high-performance, low-power accelerometers, gyroscopes, and 6-axis combination sensors plus comprehensive software libraries that support a full range of sensor combinations, operating systems and hardware platforms. Leading consumer, automotive, health and fitness and industrial companies worldwide use Kionix sensors and total system solutions to enable motion-based functionality in their products. Kionix is ISO 9001:2008, TS 16949, and TS 14001:2004 certified. Kionix is a wholly owned subsidiary of ROHM Co., Ltd.\r\n\r\n About the ROHM Group Finland Software Development Center:\r\n Address : Kiviharjunlenkki 1E 90220 Oulu, Finland\r\n Date of Establishment : November 1, 2014\r\n Functions:\r\n -Software development and application support of sensor products including\r\n -Sensor algorithm development\r\n -Sensor drivers development for OS/MCU support\r\n\r\n FURTHER INFORMATION\r\n - Company web top - http://www.rohm.com/web/global/\r\n - Sensor products - http://www.rohm.com/web/global/groups/-/group/groupname/Sensors%20&%20MEMS\r\n - koki.okada@fi.rohmeurope.com +358 40 5055300\r\n - mika.laaksonen@fi.rohmeurope.com +358 50 5689919",
