				"kuvausteksti" : "The Company \r\nKlever is a startup company building its dream team.\r\nWe are giving private consumers a super easy way of handling and paying their bills and managing their economy, in the simplest and coolest way.\r\nWe have big plans for the future.\r\n\r\nWork description\r\n\r\nWe are looking for an experienced Financial Office Associate to undertake all aspects of financial management, including corporate accounting, regulatory and financial reporting, budget and forecasts preparation, as well as development of internal control policies and procedures. Financial Office Associate's responsibilities will also include financial risk management.\r\n\r\nResponsibilities\r\n-Manage all accounting operations including Billing, A/R, A/P, GL, Cost Accounting, Inventory Accounting and Revenue Recognition\r\n-Coordinate and direct the preparation of the budget and financial forecasts and report variances\r\n-Prepare and publish timely monthly financial statements\r\n-Coordinate the preparation of regulatory reporting\r\n-Research technical accounting issues for compliance\r\n-Support month-end and year-end close process\r\n-Ensure quality control over financial transactions and financial reporting\r\n-Manage and comply with local, state, and federal government reporting requirements and tax filings\r\n-Develop and document business processes and accounting policies to maintain and strengthen internal controls\r\n-Salaries and approvals\r\n-Additional financial tasks when necessary\r\n\r\n\r\nYou \r\n\r\nIf you are an enthusiastic, positive, energetic, precise, responsible and a genuinely good person, we might have the job for you.\r\n\r\nRequirements:\r\nProven working experience as a Financial Office Associate\r\n5+ years of overall combined accounting and finance experience\r\nAdvanced degree in Accounting\r\nThorough knowledge of accounting principles and procedures\r\nExperience with creating financial statements\r\nExperience with general ledger functions and the month- / yearend closingprocess\r\nExcellent accounting software user and administration skills\r\n\r\nYou should be fluent in Finnish, English and Swedish, other languages seen as an advantage, have a good written language and have a interest of learning new skills. Organizational skills and prioritizing your tasks and keeping many projects running at the same time.\r\n\r\nNot be afraid to take the lead and finding new solutions to ease the workload. If you think you got what it takes and just happen to be searching for new and exiting opportunity at the frontline of FinTech startup scene, drop us an email.\r\n\r\n\r\nWhat we can offer:\r\n\r\n-Startup environment\r\n-Cool team\r\n-Being a part of building a unique service \r\n-Variety in work\r\n-Education\r\n\r\nInfo\r\nThe position is full-time, located in Vaasa or Helsinki.\r\nThe vacancy will be filled as soon as the perfect candidate is found. So don't waste time and submit your CV with a cover letter to: christina@kleverapp.com\r\n\r\nAppreciated attachments to your application: \r\n-CV\r\n-Recommendations\r\n-Video presentation\r\n-References",
