				"kuvausteksti" : "Enersense International Oy provides its customers with resourcing solutions which appreciate the fluctuations in their projects. Our company is an ISO 9001:2008/14001:2004-certified actor with more than ten years of experience in operating in close cooperation with large-scale nuclear and construction sites, the Olkiluoto 3 nuclear power plant site being the largest of them. \r\n\r\nWe are currently looking for Open Point Engineers as part of an Open Point Team for our client in Olkiluoto, Finland. We are offering challenging work in an international project environment.\r\n\r\nAs part of the Open Point team, the main responsibility will be to close and support the closure of the Open Point in line with the Commissioning priorities and Project target. An Open Point is a reserve on an activity which has already been transferred. The work will require high autonomy and adaption to the different technical topics and deliverables expected (Definition of Solution, Documentation production, coordination).\r\n\r\nThe Team will be composed of 20 persons and will be organized in three groups with complementary missions:\r\n\r\nDaily Open Point Management\r\n\r\n- Review and assessment of all the newly created Open Point, sorting according to severity (no topic can be overlooked)\r\n- Analysis of the stakeholders required for closure (Procurement, Retest)\r\n- Definition of action plan if needed\r\n\r\nBacklog OP Closure\r\n\r\n- Closure of OP in the backlog (Document update, confirmation that OP not relevant)\r\n- Definition of solution / action plan with specialist\r\n\r\nCommissioning Interface\r\n\r\n- Manage the OP impacting systems under commissioning\r\n- Identify and plan the remaining work to be performed (2-3 months look ahead) on system under commissioning\r\n- Coordinate and Interface with all stakeholders on a weekly basis (Construction, Procurement and Engineering) to ensure that the pre-requisites are met and that execution will be performed as planned (identification and resolution of blocking point)\r\n\r\nThe staffing in each group will be subject to adaptation over the duration of the mission in line with the project expectations.\r\n\r\nRequirements:\r\n\r\n- Degree in Engineering (for 19 people) or Management (for 1 person)\r\n- Some experience in Design, Construction or Commissioning of Industrial facilities\r\n- 0-1 years of experience: 7 people\r\n- 2-3 years of experience: 10 people\r\n- 4+ years of experience: 1-2 people\r\n- Diverse technical profile (General, Process, Electrical, Mechanical)\r\n\r\nLanguage Skills:\r\n\r\n- Fluent in English\r\n\r\nThe post will be filled as soon as a suitable applicant is found.",
