				"kuvausteksti" : "We are currently looking for an NI Mechanical PTW Officer for our client in Olkiluoto Nuclear Power Plant, Finland.  We are offering challenging work in an international project environment.\r\n\r\nWe are currently looking for PTW Officers for our client in Olkiluoto Nuclear Power Plant, Finland. We are offering challenging work in an international project environment.\r\n\r\nMain Tasks and Responsibilities\r\n\r\n- Permit to Work Officer in the OIO/PTW team\r\n- Technical clarification of work orders / Permits to test and creation and validation of blockings / simulations\r\n- Execution of blockings and simulations\r\n- Oversee in-field operator teams for establishing safe work conditions (equipment alignment, depressurizing, de-energising, locking and tagging)\r\n- Coordinate activities with Operating, Construction, Installation and Commissioning units\r\n- Prepare Permit to Work documentation and ensure strict compliance\r\n\r\nExpected Deliverables:\r\n\r\n- Validated work orders and blockings\r\n- Carried out blockings\r\n- Work programs\r\n\r\nInterfaces with:\r\n\r\n- OIO Manager\r\n- PTW Office Manager\r\n- Other PTW Officers\r\n- Commissioning Engineers\r\n- Client\r\n\r\nRequirements:\r\n\r\n- Mechanical engineering degree or Electrical or I&C Engineering degree, or an experienced technician \r\n- 5 years of experience in nuclear power plants\r\n- 5 years of experience with mechanical work orders and blockings\r\n- Detailed knowledge about the mechanical process documentation\r\n- Ability to work on the different process diagram, isometrics, preparation of solution and support for inventories in the field\r\n- General understanding of mechanics, thermodynamics, fluid mechanics and measurement/instrumentation technology\r\n- General understanding of electrical technology\r\n- Computer literacy in MSOffice\r\n- Knowledge about EPR technology\r\n- Working experience in Permit to Work offices\r\n- Ability to use the different project databases, software etc. desirable\r\n\r\nLanguage Skills:\r\n\r\n- Fluent in English\r\n\r\nDrug test and concise security clearance will be done for the selected person in order to get the permanent access to OL3 site.\r\n\r\nThe post will be filled as soon as a suitable applicant is found.",
