				"kuvausteksti" : "Enersense International Oy provides its customers with resourcing solutions which appreciate the fluctuations in their projects. Our company is an ISO 9001:2008/14001:2004-certified actor with more than ten years of experience in operating in close cooperation with large-scale nuclear and construction sites, the Olkiluoto 3 nuclear power plant site being the largest of them.\r\n\r\nWe are currently looking for Quantity Surveyors for our client in Olkiluoto Nuclear Power Plant, Finland. We are offering challenging work in an international project environment.\r\n\r\nMain Tasks and Responsibilities\r\n\r\n- The main mission of the Quantity Surveyor is to work with the Contract Responsible and to have full autonomy over the following missions, on various scopes such as but not limited to - Electrical, Painting, Piping, Mechanical, Scaffolding, etc.\r\n\r\nTo check and verify the subcontractor's monthly progress statements / invoices (physical quantities to be measured at Site, contractual entitlement to be assessed)\r\n- To keep track and update files / database for all measurement periods\r\n- To analyze outcome and value in detail all subcontractor progress reports\r\n- To value the works completed and arrange payment\r\n\r\nTo check the subcontractor organization at site for:\r\n- Labor and management of time\r\n- Costs of equipment\r\n- Totality of the materials\r\n- Stock of materials and equipment\r\n- Quantities of all items\r\n\r\nTo undertake costs analysis for preparing additional work order and contract amendments, including bills of quantities:\r\n- To examine all quantum justification\r\n- To evaluate prices and unit rates proposed\r\n\r\nBack charging and claims: to assist in preparing any quantum section for back charging and claim\r\n- To provide advice on contractual claims\r\n\r\nTo be aware of the different contractual scheme (fixed price, Bill of Quantity, Time and Material, etc.)\r\n- The Quantity Surveyor works in a team with the Contract Responsible on site\r\n- He/she has the complete knowledge of the contractual obligations of the Parties\r\n\r\nRequirements:\r\n\r\n- Ability to understand construction plans (civil or mechanical or electrical)\r\n- Ability to work on the field (construction site, inside NI building)\r\n- Strong IT skills (Excel and Word as minimun, Access as an advantage)\r\n- Previous experience from similar work\r\n\r\nLanguages:\r\n\r\n- Fluent in English\r\n- Other language skills (Finnish, French, German) are an advantage\r\n\r\nDrug test and concise security clearance will be done for the selected person in order to get the permanent access to OL3 site.\r\n\r\nPlease note that due to clients urgent need only applicants with a valid working permit / EU-citizenship can be considered.\r\n\r\nThe post will be filled as soon as a suitable applicant is found.",
