				"kuvausteksti" : "Enersense International Oy provides its customers with resourcing solutions which appreciate the fluctuations in their projects. Our company is an ISO 9001:2008/14001:2004-certified actor with more than ten years of experience in operating in close cooperation with large-scale nuclear and construction sites, the Olkiluoto 3 nuclear power plant site being the largest of them. \r\n\r\nWe are currently looking for a Field Instrumentation Commissioning Technician/ Engineer for our client in Olkiluoto Nuclear Power Plant, Finland. We are offering challenging work in an international project environment.\r\n\r\nMain tasks and responsibilities: \r\n\r\n- Performing on-site baseline measurements on different kind of valves (valves with electrical or hydraulic actuator, solenoid valves, safety valves, check valves) and vibration measurements on safety related and operational pumps\r\n- Execution of field tests/ loop checks on different type of sensors/ measurement chains according to commissioning instructions of diagnostic systems\r\n\r\n1. Prepare the field task:\r\n\r\n- Check availability and accessibility of components to be measured/ commissioned on site and request establish the blockings and test permits as needed\r\n- Request any special permits needed for test execution (confined space, scaffold...)\r\n- Identify the components for which technical clarifications (OPs, CR, FCR, DCRs...) are on-going. Exchange with component engineering/ system commissioning responsible to get precise input concerning open points or outstanding issues which might impact the test result\r\n- Make sure the equipment needed for test execution is available, calibrated and functional. -\r\n Support equipment like cranes for the actuators to be tested shall be organized well in advance\r\n- Make sure the HSE aspects of the task are covered by appropriate analysis (MSRA)\r\n\r\n2. Perform the field task:\r\n\r\n- Perform the field task by applying the dedicated procedures applicable for the valve kind or the dedicated commissioning instructions\r\n- Make a quick review of the results before removing the measurement equipment and exchange with the valve engineering / system commissioning responsible if necessary\r\n\r\n3. Test evaluation and result documentation:\r\n\r\n- For valve baseline measurements:\r\n- Ensure the evaluation criteria are available on the evaluation software\r\n- Make an evaluation of the measurement using the dedicated measurement software\r\n- Print-out, sign and archive the evaluation protocols properly\r\n- Periodically, a backup of the databases shall be done\r\n- At the end of the measurement campaign, make sure the databases are secured and archived in a proper way\r\n\r\nFor test execution according to commissioning instruction:\r\n\r\n- Fit the result record sheets of the tests executed in-line with the instructions\r\n- Troubleshoot deviations from acceptance criteria under supervision of system commissioning responsible\r\n\r\n4. Reporting:\r\n\r\n- Daily Progress reporting on progress to system commissioning responsible and/ or section lead\r\n- Weekly reporting to commissioning management/ customer on progress and issues\r\n\r\nRequirements:\r\n\r\n- Engineer degree in electrical or mechanical engineering\r\n- Valve/ actuator diagnostic knowledge and advanced knowledge on vibration measurements is a must \r\n- Advanced knowledge in measurement and instrumentation\r\n- Experience in preparation of measurement setups on valves, actuators and sensors\r\n- Experience in loop checks and measurement chain calibration\r\n- Experience in analysis of signals resulting from measurements on valves, actuators and vibration sensors\r\n- Capacity of troubleshooting\r\n- Good relational and communication skills\r\n- Analysis and synthesis skills\r\n- Ability to work in an international team\r\n- Aware of HSE and IT security aspects\r\n\r\nTools: \r\n\r\n- Proficient in MS Excel Reporting (Pivot Tables, Statistics...)\r\n- Experience with OL3 Engineering Tools (COEDM 1.4, OPMS, AIMS, CMS.) considered as a benefit\r\n\r\nLanguages: \r\n\r\n- Fluent English required\r\n- Ability with French, German or Finnish considered as a benefit\r\n\r\nDrug test and concise security clearance will be done for the selected person in order to get the permanent access to OL3 site.\r\n\r\nPlease note that due to clients urgent need only applicants with a valid working permit / EU-citizenship can be considered.\r\n\r\nThe post will be filled as soon as a suitable applicant is found.",
