				"kuvausteksti" : "Enersense International Oy provides its customers with resourcing solutions which appreciate the fluctuations in their projects. Our company is an ISO 9001:2008/14001:2004-certified actor with more than ten years of experience in operating in close cooperation with large-scale nuclear and construction sites, the Olkiluoto 3 nuclear power plant site being the largest of them. \r\n\r\nWe are currently looking for a Fire Officer for our client in Olkiluoto Nuclear Power Plant. We are offering challenging work in an international project environment.\r\n\r\nMain Tasks and Responsibilities:\r\n\r\nUnder the authority of the HSE department Manager and Fire Protection team leader:\r\n\r\n- Strict follow up of application and the compliance with site rules, national standards and legislation\r\n- Reporting and recording of actions and deviations\r\n- Active communication with contractors personnel, their guidance and instructing\r\n- Rescue trainings and test with site personnel\r\n- Follow up and updating daily fire protection tasks (exit ways, signalization)\r\n- Reporting daily to Team Leader\r\n- Manage the fire safety inspection on site with the contractors. Follow up corrective actions defined during the inspection\r\n- Closely work with supervisors and team (construction / commissioning to have the knowledge of the coming activities (anticipation) and involve them with the daily safety\r\n- Animate the safety in the team (construction / commissioning), through visit on spot, training, lesson learned\r\n\r\nRequirements:\r\n\r\n- Good knowledge of Finnish Rescue and Chemical and Occupational Health and Safety Regulation, applicable standards\r\n- Good knowledge of Finnish Rescue Service and related operations (HAKE) structure\r\n- Holder of blue and black card - asset if trainer\r\n- Experienced on industrial, ship yard, construction site - fire protection\r\n- Skilled to write reports, records and instruction; procedure\r\n- Comfortable speaking in public (especially when giving training and eventually leading meetings)\r\n- Knowledge of Microsoft office (excel, word, power point and outlook)\r\n- Knowledge of automatic systems (extinguishing, alarm) or experience in electrical, Mechanical risks linked to industrial activities or commissioning activities will be the best.\r\n\r\nLanguage Skills:\r\n\r\n- Fluent in Finnish and English\r\n\r\nDrug test and concise security clearance will be done for the selected person in order to get the permanent access to OL3 site.\r\n\r\nPlease note that due to client's urgent need only applicants with a valid working permit / EU-citizenship can be considered.\r\n\r\nThe post will be filled as soon as a suitable applicant is found.",
