				"kuvausteksti" : "We are looking for a Technical manager to join our growing team in Vaasa and lead the technical aspects of our projects. You'd be involved with our customers, project managers and of course developers to make sure we finish our projects on time and according to specification.\r\n\r\nTogether with our CTO you'd make decisions of what technologies we use for our tailor-made projects. The industry we're in is ever-changing, so you'll be evaluating and choosing which technologies and solutions we use moving forward. This position will also give you the opportunity to actively keep coding yourself, so you can keep your skills up to par. Still interested? Well let's get in to the nitty gritty of what we're after:\r\n - At least 3 years of professional coding experience in some, all (or perhaps more than) the following languages: Java, Objective-C, C#, PHP, C and C++\r\n - Familiarity with Agile development/Scrum \r\n - Great social and communication skills\r\n - A couple of human languages (preferably both Finnish and Swedish)\r\n\r\nA little bit about us\r\nAt Gambit, we digitize to make things easier. Our business-oriented IoT solutions, apps and third party integrations make every work day better than the previous one. \r\n\r\nOur growing team currently consists of sixteen developers, designers and project managers, as well as a bunch of cute doges. Although they do lack work morale. The dogs that is, not the humans.\r\n\r\nWorking at Gambit\r\nWe like to balance hard work with good times. Creating a positive work environment is one of our driving factors. That's why we always meet up every now and then outside of work to barbeque, watch a movie or play Dungeons & Dragons.\r\n\r\nOur office is in Runsoria Business Park in Vaasa. We have the best lunch in town, video games, a ping pong table and there's also a gym in the building (or so we've been told).\r\n\r\nGolly gee that sounds fantastic, where do I sign up?\r\nIf you want to be a part of our proud, nerdy bunch - send your applications or get in touch with us for more information. Start date for this full-time position is flexible but preferably as soon as possible.",
