				"etatyo" : false,
				"kuvausteksti" : "WITRON has been developing and designing logistics and material handling solutions for leading companies all over the world for more than 45 years. With our mechanized systems, our customers are able to place products in storage and remove them from storage in a fast and economic way, to pick and deliver them to their branches or customers. Whether in Europe, America or Canada, with our system solutions we provide technical advancement for our customers! With an annual turnover of 485 million Euros, the WITRON group has more than 2.820 employees worldwide. Own education is the cornerstone for our success. Since the foundation, we have successfully trained more than 1.000 young people in our different professions.\r\n\r\nAs an industrial electronics engineer at WITRON, you will be an important specialist for installations, start-ups, and maintenance of our systems across the globe. However, this practical education will offer you more than just professional knowledge. You will be exposed to new cultures and different languages while you study and work with your colleagues.Your apprenticeship with WITRON starts with a six-week German course. You will then learn the basic skills for your work within the manufacturing of control cabinets and different other production areas at WITRON. In the course of your apprenticeship, you will alternately spend some weeks at the vocational school or at the WITRON plant in Parkstein, or at one of our international project sites. After two years, you will take your exam at the Chamber of Industry and Commerce. The transnational apprenticeship starts annually in mid-July.\r\n\r\nTheoretical training:\r\n\r\nVocational school in German language in regular time periods (12 weeks per year)\r\nGerman lessons in courses at WITRON\r\nTwo examinations: intermediate and final examination (both written in German language)\r\n\r\nPractical training:\r\n\r\nWiring and equipping switch cabinets\r\nMeasuring, analyzing and testing electrical systems\r\nImplementation of functional and safety tests\r\nInstallation and commissioning of electrical systems\r\nMaintenance of systems\r\n\r\nPrerequisites:\r\n\r\nCompleted school education\r\nMinimum age: 18 years\r\nTechnical interest, skills and understanding\r\nGood english skills (ideally also German skills)\r\nHigh motivation\r\nHigh degree of fl exibility and willingness to travel\r\nInterest in other cultures\r\nOur contributions:\r\n\r\nApprenticeship pay\r\nProviding accommodation during the entire apprentice ship (at the beginning host family, later apartment)\r\n2 paid flights home per year\r\nHelp with all formalities an visa requirements\r\nTaking over apprenticeship costs (tools, language course)\r\n\r\nYour personal benefits:\r\n\r\nQualified, practical and extensive apprenticeship\r\nObtaining linguistic and intercultural competence\r\nVersatile field of occupation after the apprenticeship at our worldwide project sites / service locations\r\nBest development possibilities in an internationally operating, successful and future-oriented enterprise\r\n\r\nIf you \r\n are interested in a qualified technical apprenticeship,\r\n are curious about other cultures and open to everyone,\r\n would like to extend your foreign linguistic skills,\r\n then you are right in our enterprise!\r\n and take your chance and start your professional career with a transnational apprenticeship\r\nin our successful and internationally operating company!\r\nConvince us with your comprehensive application:\r\ne. g. motivation letter / CV / school certificate / copy of your passport / photo / certificates of traineeships\r\n\r\nHave an inside look: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Z5FPji3XHbQ \r\n\r\nLocation: 92711 Parkstein, Bavaria, Germany.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nPlease send your application in German or English to:\r\nZAV-IPS-Bayern@arbeitsagentur.de by referring to BT-301.\r\n\r\nFor further assistance, please contact us. We'll be happy to provide further assistance.\r\n\r\n\r\nThe International Placement Services Bavaria supports your job-seeking in Germany. We are a department of the German Federal Employment Agency. Our services are free of charge. Citizens of EU Member states may have the possibility to receive financial support (for example travel expenses, language course).",
