				"kuvausteksti" : "Kaiku HR is specialized in personnel leasing, outsourcing and recruitment. It is very important for us to find an inspiring and motivating job for the candidate or otherwise well-fitting task for his/ her current life situation. We believe that a motivated and inspired employee grants the success for our customer.\r\n\r\nWe are looking for Field Engineer to our customer company at Olkiluoto 3.\r\n\r\n\r\nWe are looking for Field Engineer with extended experience in the field of I&C and electrical design.\r\n\r\nTASKS:\r\n- Responsible for preparing and finalizing the dedicated working package for his scope.\r\n- Contributes to the scope of Special and Self-Standing Systems which includes different systems of different technologies:  electrical, I&C, mechanical parts and process parts. \r\n- Prepares all required inputs to secure installation completion and handover towards commissioning.\r\n- Serves as strong support for commissioning troubleshooting.\r\n- Works as a team member of Special and Self-Standing System Team on site.\r\n- Responsible of closing issues connected to general Special System topics.\r\n- Responsible for the management of technical changes via CRs/FCRs/DCRs/NCRs/ICCRs new orders/open points. Closing of the issues independently.\r\n- Redlines and updates documentation.\r\n- Performs Site walk-downs with together with construction and commissioning.\r\n- Supports open point closure in the respective scope.\r\n- Supports the technical clarifications for all the other technical issues related to Special Systems.\r\n- Support Construction and Commissioning in all technical issues with the defined working package such as commissioning tests preparation.\r\n- Provides input to the different weekly/monthly reports.\r\n- Support scheduling in close relationship with construction and commissioning.\r\n- Reports to on-site Field Engineering Special System EDL.\r\n\r\nREQUIREMENTS:\r\n- Engineering expertise in Process or Petro-Chemical Systems.\r\n- Fluent in English (verbally and in writing).\r\n- Adapts successfully to changing situations and environments.\r\n- Gathers information systematically to establish facts & principles.\r\n- Problem-solving attitude.\r\n- Manages time effectively, prioritizes tasks and is able to work according to deadlines.\r\n- Highly motivated to solve problems/issues, target oriented.\r\n- Strong experience in Electrical and Automation System Design.\r\n- Commissioning experience is required.\r\n\r\n- General technical knowledge of I&C and/or Automation based systems.\r\n- Expert in area of electrical and/or automation engineering; at least 5 years. \r\n- Deep knowledge in PLC Software tools (e.g SIMATIC S7, SIMATIC WIN CC) and office tools.\r\n- SIMATIC STEP7 experience\r\n- French and German languages would be a plus\r\n\r\n\r\nStarting as soon as possible and for duration of 6 months.\r\n\r\nWe appreciate your contact as soon as possible. Please send us your CV in English plus your salary request.",
