				"etatyo" : false,
				"kuvausteksti" : "Enersense International Oy provides its customers with resourcing solutions which appreciate the fluctuations in their projects. Our company is an ISO 9001:2008/14001:2004-certified actor with more than ten years of experience in operating in close cooperation with large-scale nuclear and construction sites, the Olkiluoto 3 nuclear power plant site being the largest of them. \r\n\r\nWe are currently looking for an NSSS Commissioning engineer - CPE for our client in Olkiluoto Nuclear Power Plant, Finland. We are offering challenging work in an international project environment.\r\n\r\nMain tasks and responsibilities: \r\n\r\n- Support CE in the KOT2/ TOTO preparation \r\n- Manage the closure of OP \r\n- Lead meeting with engineering, construction and procurement to ensure the closure of the OP on due time \r\n- Coordinate interfaces (which other disciplines/ systems, electrical, I&C, vendors, etc.) for assigned tasks \r\n- Ensure a clear reporting \r\n- Support various project planning and transverse coordination topics as requested\r\n\r\nRequirements:\r\n\r\n- Technical degree required in one of the following disciplines: mechanical equipment or nuclear technician / engineer\r\n- At least 1 - 2 experience years on construction site \r\n- Proficiency with Microsoft Office Suite, Documentum and AIMS\r\n- Good knowledge of transfer process that allows him/ her to be operational quickly\r\n- Knowledge of Pressurized Water Reactor (PWR) systems\r\n- Experience in EPR considered as a benefit\r\n\r\nLanguages:\r\n\r\n- Fluent English required\r\n- Ability with French, German, and/or Finnish considered as a benefit\r\n\r\nDrug test and concise security clearance will be done for the selected person in order to get the permanent access to OL3 site.\r\n\r\nPlease note that due to clients urgent need only applicants with a valid working permit / EU-citizenship can be considered.\r\n\r\nThe post will be filled as soon as a suitable applicant is found.",
