				"kuvausteksti" : "Enersense International Oy provides its customers with resourcing solutions which appreciate the fluctuations in their projects. Our company is an ISO 9001:2008/14001:2004-certified actor with more than ten years of experience in operating in close cooperation with large-scale nuclear and construction sites, the Olkiluoto 3 nuclear power plant site being the largest of them. \r\n\r\nWe are currently looking for a Fire Safety Expert for our client in Helsinki, Finland. We are offering challenging work in an international project environment. As a Fire Safety Expert you will be working with the development of working documentation for fire detection system, fire alarm system and fire automatics.\r\n\r\nMain Tasks and Responsibilities\r\n\r\n-Developing working documentation in the area of fire safety (fire detection system, fire alarm system and fire automatics)\r\n-Designing systems with relevant equipment in the area of fire safety\r\n-Advising the design engineers of client on the specifics of local regulations\r\n-Giving advice on all fire safety related activities\r\n\r\nRequirements:\r\n\r\n-Degree or Certificate in Fire Safety and experience in the field\r\n-Experience of at least 10 years and at least two projects implemented at large industrial / power plants in Europe\r\n-Experience with Schneider Electric equipment (Invensys) - industrial controllers of the Trident series, Tri-GP, Triconex\r\n-Preferred participation in Siemens AG in the project Oilkiluoto-3 in the part of fire detection system, fire alarm system and fire protection automation\r\n-Preferred experience of design using Schneider Electric equipment (Invensys) - industrial controllers of the Trident, Tri-GP, Triconex series\r\n\r\nLanguage Skills\r\n\r\n-Fluent English required\r\n-Russian language skills is an advantage\r\n\r\nThe post will be filled as soon as a suitable applicant is found.",
