				"kuvausteksti" : "Enersense International Oy provides its customers with resourcing solutions which appreciate the fluctuations in their projects. Our company is an ISO 9001:2008/14001:2004-certified actor with more than ten years of experience in operating in close cooperation with large-scale nuclear and construction sites, the Olkiluoto 3 nuclear power plant site being the largest of them. \r\n\r\nWe are looking for Steel Structure Supervisor for our client in Syktyvkar, Russia\r\n\r\nMain tasks and Responsibilities:\r\n\r\n- Planning and performance of the preparation work for the specific contractor under consideration of the engineering input, availability of stored materials in Client scope.\r\n- Caretaking for removal of any obstructions by other disciplines or intervention group in advance to the start of execution Works\r\n- Supervision and follow up of the contractor's execution works\r\n- Involvement of other parties like inspection organizations, HSE organizations of the different stakeholders\r\n- Review and closure of execution documentation in coordination with the method team and final documentation team\r\n- Support for contractual negotiation\r\n- Weekly / Monthly internal reporting.\r\n- Ensure that the activities of the team as well as those of the subcontractors are performed according to the highest HSE standards\r\n- Ensure that the works on site and are performed according to the contractual standards of quality, time schedule and budget, and according to Project Procedures including but not limited to Work follow up documentation requirements.\r\n- Check that human resources and equipment are mobilized by the subcontractors according to plans\r\n- Check that the subcontractors are using the right technical documentation\r\n- Tracking and cleaning up the list of open points related to these works\r\n- During take over operations, check that works have been completed according to schedule and quality requirements\r\n- Attending Weekly meetings with the relevant subcontractors\r\n- Report directly to the Finishing and Room Completion Group Supervision manager\r\n- Report weekly progress to the team leader supervision manager\r\n- Supervise the erection and installation work of Client employees and subcontractors. \r\n- Assure that the subcontractors comply with agreed contracts. \r\n- Assure that the subcontractors comply with the End Clients and Client's HSE (Health, Safety and Environmental) rules, as well as with local requirements in the country of the site.\r\n- Approve technical and commercial change orders requested by the subcontractors, within the limits set by the Site Manager. \r\n- Stop the work in his/her responsibility area if there is a risk of serious accident. \r\n- Work in a safe manner without risk to him/herselves, others or the environment \r\n- Obey HSE policy and related instructions \r\n- Comply with site rules \r\n- Report all incidents, near miss cases or HSE risks as instructed \r\n- Correctly use all required personal protective equipment (PPE) \r\n- Make suggestions on how to improve HSE practices \r\n- Ensuring effectiveness and quality of erection and installation work \r\n- Preparation of erection and installation work, defining and reserving needed manpower and resources \r\n- Ensuring the safety of erection and installation work in own responsibility area \r\n- Supervision of right timing of erection and installation work \r\n- Coordinating material sending and receiving together with the shipping department and Construction Planning Engineer\r\n- Daily, weekly and monthly reporting of erection and installation work progress to the Site Manager \r\n- Compile quality documentation \r\n- Compile acceptance certificates contractor/ Client and Client/ The End Client (lifts, elevators, HVAC etc.)\r\n- COR/NCR settlement with contractors and Customer \r\n- Hand-over punch-list and finishing works to Site Manager\r\n\r\nRequirements:\r\n\r\n- Good technical knowledge of metal Works, specific knowledge in the supervision of steel structures installation and corrosion protection works are favoured.\r\n- Experience about supervising the similar steel structure works\r\n- Organisational and planning ability to prepare for the execution works of the subcontractors \r\n- Good communication skills in order to interface with the supervisors of other disciplines \r\n- Good human relationship and team spirit \r\n- Ability to communicate with people of different professional background and culture \r\n- Result oriented in particular with respect to Safety, Quality, Cost and Schedule (On Time Delivery-OTD)\r\n- Needs to be experienced about similar steel structure supervising\r\n- Good knowledge of site erection and installation work and/or suitable education/experience\r\n- Minimum 2 years of experience as Site Supervisor on boiler, evaporation or similar process plant \r\n- Has good understanding of contractual issues \r\n- Has proved to have capabilities to adopt skills outside his/her discipline\r\n- Has good knowledge of Site Reporting Tools\r\n\r\nLanguages:\r\n\r\n- Good knowledge of English\r\n\r\nPlease register as a jobseeker and apply for the position through our website. \r\n\r\nThe post will be filled as soon as a suitable applicant is found.",
