				"kuvausteksti" : "Enersense International Oy provides its customers with resourcing solutions which appreciate the fluctuations in their projects. Our company is an ISO 9001:2008/14001:2004-certified actor with more than ten years of experience in operating in close cooperation with large-scale nuclear and construction sites, the Olkiluoto 3 nuclear power plant site being the largest of them. \r\n\r\nWe are currently looking for QA/QC Supervisor for our client in Syktyvkar, Russia. \r\n\r\nMain responsibilities:\r\n\r\n- Examine project quality requirements.\r\n- For example, review Site Quality Plan (if any), main assembly documents, availability of latest revisions of drawings and participate in kick-off meetings with contractors\r\n- Review qualifications\r\n- Checking of welder, heat treatment and NDE qualifications (personal and company licenses)\r\n- Advise in document system\r\n- Review QA/QC documentation as work proceeds (e.g. welding, material certificates, heat treatment, NDT, NCR's, as-built records, partial erection inspection reports)\r\n- Getting the approval from Third Party/Authority when required\r\n- Advise in production/work and qualification tests (e.g. welding, bending, NDE)\r\n- Advise in ITP's and checklists\r\n- Advise in installation work at site\r\n- Inspect execution, quality and progress of welding, heat treatments, NDE and proof/pressure testing works\r\n- Witness pressure and leak tests\r\n- Carry out visual examination of installed constructions and perform VT (Visual Testing) on all pressure bearing welds.\r\n- Ensure proper handling of non-conformities and coordinate the handling of nonconforming products\r\n- Participate in receiving inspections (when applicable)\r\n- Visual examination for agreed components (pressure contained components, mechanical equipment, ducts, tanks, steel structures)\r\n- Review of components CE marks/name plates (when required)\r\n- Participate in Hold point inspections\r\n- Participate in final inspections\r\n- Review Site Quality documentation\r\n- Give continuous feedback to e.g. engineering, production, supplier management and quality assurance\r\n\r\nRequirements:\r\n\r\n- Degree in Mechanical Engineering or other relevant\r\n- Minimum of 5 years of experience\r\n- Experienced in compliance to ISO 9001, 14001 and 18001\r\n- Experience and knowldge abut welding\r\n- Relevant QA qualification\r\n- Good report writing and communication skills\r\n- Advanced user of MS Office\r\n- Strong interpersonal and communication skills\r\n- Responsible and proactive\r\n- Good planning and organizing skills\r\n\r\nLanguages:\r\n\r\n- Fluent English\r\n- Russian language skills considered as beneficial\r\n\r\nThe post will be filled as soon as a suitable applicant is found",
