				"kuvausteksti" : "We are seeking for a Reservations Manager In Kakslauttanen Arctic Resort, Tallinn office, who will take full responsibility of operations and effectively Manage Agents and Guest inquiries and maximize revenue.\r\n\r\nKey responsibilities: \r\n-To ensure all reservation enquires are promptly handled and maximise revenue with added sales.\r\n-Handle and resolve all Guest reservation issues in a positive manner, ensure Guest satisfaction with no loss of revenue. \r\n-Develop and maintain staff schedule to handle reservation calls, emails and ensuring a high level customer service standards with all enquiries in conversion into bookings and sales revenue. \r\n-Performance reports on daily, weekly and monthly basis. \r\n-Implementing selling strategies and effectively handling online reservations system. \r\n-Hiring reservations team and effective training. \r\n-Responsible for all administration and accounting of Tallinn office. \r\n-Effectively assisting with sales and marketing jobs. \r\n \r\nDesired qualifications, experience and skills:\r\n- 2-3 years of experience as manager in reputed organizations.\r\n- Relevant certified education and training.\r\n- Fluent in written and spoken English and Finnish, other languages are considered as an advantage.\r\n- Ability to work under pressure. \r\n\r\nKakslauttanen Arctic Resort is one of Finland's best-known and most talked about travel destinations. This family business, founded in 1974, is located in Saariselkä, Lapland. Kakslauttanen hosts around 30,000 visitors each year, the majority of them from abroad. The guests include several high-profile visitors, media and international filming crews. Among others, Kakslauttanen has served as the location for Ralph Lauren and Vogue fashion shoots, the new TV show from Top Gear creators, The Grand Tour, Sports Illustrated as well as hundreds of travel programmes. During the winter season, the hotel employs 100 people from 25 different countries.",
