				"kuvausteksti" : "4finance is seeking Risk IT Analyst to join their highly skilled international team in the heart of Helsinki. Risk IT Analyst will be responsible for technical specifications of the loan product.\r\nCandidate will report to the Country Manager in Finland and Regional Head of Risk and will work as member of Nordic Risk Team. Approximately 10 to 20 travel days per year are expected.\r\n\r\n\r\nEmployee's Job Responsibilities\r\n\r\nPerform data querying and data quality assessment of risk management policy related data\r\nDeploy and amend the risk management policy rules, credit risk assessment scorecard, fraud prevention and other risk management and debt collection models in Risk Management System (RMS)\r\nFollow and strengthen quality assurance and track changes procedures for risk policy rules and models implemented in RMS\r\nPerform and contribute to improvement of User acceptance testing policies and risk management software support in production environment\r\nMake proposals for work process improvement and effective achievement of work tasks\r\nInform the immediate supervisor of the challenges preventing timely implementation of assigned tasks\r\nPerform Acceptance Rate simulation before implementation of new changes\r\nDevelop and maintain KPI monitoring tool \r\nAssist Head of Risk in risk strategy and modelling management \r\n\r\nSkills, Required for Performance of Basic Tasks in Professional Activity\r\n\r\nMasters degree in Mathematics, Statistics, IT, Finance, Economics or similar area\r\nAbility to use theoretical knowledge into practice\r\nFluent written and spoken Finnish and English\r\nExcellent computer skills\r\nAbility to independent work and decision making\r\nAbility to present the findings and recommendations to the management\r\nAbility persuade others and argue their views\r\nConsulting skills are advantage \r\nGood problem-solving skills and creativity\r\nAbility to carry out risk analyses\r\nLoan lifecycle knowledge and management\r\nUse of information acquisition, processing, and categorization technologies\r\nCommunicate and interact with various departments to employees, partners and direct control\r\nEvaluate the work and labor intensive task execution time and draw up a schedule\r\nParticipate in project management\r\nUse information search and selection tools\r\nStrong professional ethics\r\nHigh energy level and positive attitude \r\nProven record of leadership in a work setting and/or through extracurricular activities\r\n\r\n\r\nAbout us \r\n\r\n4finance is a market-leading short-term loan provider throughout the world. To date, 4finance has provided more than ten million loans to over five million customers.  \r\n\r\nAt 4finance, we believe that our achievements are based on our ability to attract and retain the right kind of people. That is why we focus on making 4finance a great company to work for. \r\n\r\n- We invest in skills and knowledge of our people \r\n- With 16 offices across the globe, we enjoy working in a multicultural environment \r\n- We are a fast-growing company in an exciting industry\r\n\r\nIf you believe that you are the right person, please apply for this position by sending your CV and salary request to HR@4finance.fi no later than November 30, 2017. \r\n\r\nFor more information, please contact us from same email address. We will start interviews already now and fulfill position as soon as we find suitable person.",
