				"etatyo" : false,
				"kuvausteksti" : "We are looking for an experienced design engineer, who has a strong will to develop own competence in respective technology area and who feels confident in making own decisions and taking initiatives. The design tasks consist of preparing and making electrical calculations and system studies for MV and LV distributions networks. The work includes direct customer contacts, problem solving, and participation in development projects. You will be joining our electrical team providing design solutions and technical services in operative and development projects. Your location is preferably Vaasa, but other locations (Tampere, Vantaa or Pietarsaari) can also be considered.\r\n\r\nYour main tasks will be:\r\n\r\n- Short circuit calculations of MV and LV switchgears\r\n- MV and LV cable dimensioning and selection according to load current, short circuit current, voltage drop and project specifications\r\n- Protective relay co-ordination calculations and selectivity studies with reporting\r\n- Grounding calculations for power plants and reporting\r\n- Load flow studies and reporting\r\n- Concept and basic design of electrical distribution networks in sales projects\r\n- Providing support and communicating with internal and customer project teams\r\n\r\nQualifications:\r\n\r\n- B.Sc. or M.Sc. in electrical engineering\r\n- Working experience of power system engineering in power plant or industrial projects, preferably 5 years or more\r\n- Good knowledge of electrical MV and LV distribution networks and power generation technology and equipments\r\n- Comprehensive experience of electrical system calculations in MV and LV switchgears including power generating\r\n- Advanced knowledge and experience of calculation software ETAP, FebDok and AutoGrid Pro\r\n- Good knowledge and experience of design tools Autocad or CADS Planner Pro\r\n- Co-operative team-worker with business orientated and proactive attitude\r\n- Fluent verbal and written knowledge in English and Finnish or Swedish\r\n- Flexibility and customer-orientation\r\n\r\nWe offer you:\r\n\r\n- Exciting and challenging work within domestic and international engineering projects\r\n- International and flexible work environment\r\n- Skilled colleagues and friendly working environment\r\n\r\nFor more information, please contact Rickard Nygård +358(0)50 4283 862 or Timo Wolff +358(0)50 4320 321.\r\n\r\nPlease submit you application by 29th September, 2017 via our career pages, www.citec.com/careers.",
