				"kuvausteksti" : "You will be part of a dynamic and exciting Delivery and Support Team and your work as Technical Project Engineer can bring you to any location of the world where our international customers are located. Your main task is to collaborate with the customer and develop customer specific programming and configuration to our leading edge Industry 4.0: Smart Production powered by NESTIX production control solution. \r\n\r\n\r\nResponsibilities \r\n\r\nYou are of course well versed in SQL and Windows operating systems, knowledge of ActiveReports 11 and C# language programming is definitely an advantage. \r\n\r\nBesides being a supportive team member you are also capable of handling smaller projects from design, programming and delivery by yourself. You are willing to work with customers and give them support and guidance in English and Finnish. You like to continuously learn and develop as a member of our team as well as share your skills and knowledge with your team members. \r\n\r\n \r\nWe expect that you have finished a Bachelor's or Master's Degree study and have zero to five years of working experience.\r\n\r\n \r\nWe offer interesting projects in an international company, while your office will be Oulu. We provide you with the full support of our staff, the appropriate methods, tools and benefits. We expect you to travel to our customers on occasion. \r\n\r\n \r\nTo apply, please submit your application including CV (Curriculum Vitae) and salary request via our online application system. \r\n\r\nApplication and CV must be uploaded as one document. \r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nFor additional information, please contact Juha Marjomaa on +358 40 3100 572 or Marko Ukkola (Director, Delivery and Support) via marko.ukkola@hexagon.com.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nNestix is part pf Hexagon PPM (formerly Intergraph Process, Power & Marine) a leading global provider of engineering software and project control solutions. We transform unstructured information into a smart digital asset, empowering our clients to visualize, create, and manage the life cycle of facilities and structures of all complexities. For more information visit HexagonPPM.com\r\n\r\nHexagon PPM is part of Hexagon (Nasdaq Stockholm: HEXA B; Hexagon.com), a leading global provider of information technology solutions that drive productivity and quality across geospatial and industrial landscapes.",
