				"kuvausteksti" : "Linux Kernel Specialist\r\nWe are currently looking for a Linux Kernel specialist to join our Jolla boat. This position is primarily based in our office in Finland in Tampere, but other locations can be considered based on the applicant.\r\n\r\nIn this role you will participate in porting Sailfish OS to new devices and maintaining kernel for existing devices. Your tasks will include planning, designing, implementing and testing software modules.\r\nThis is a permanent, full-time position and starts immediately once we have found the ideal candidate.\r\n\r\nYou are the person we are looking for, if you\r\n- have experience in working with Linux Kernel and kernel module development\r\n- have working experience with ARM based devices\r\n- have strong C language programming skills\r\n- have excellent debugging, profiling and performance optimizing skills\r\n- have thorough understanding of Linux OS architecture\r\n- have good command of English language, other languages seen as an advantage\r\n- have good team working skills and 'can do' attitude\r\n\r\nWe offer you\r\n- a unique opportunity to work in an international and dynamic company\r\n- a chance to be part of Jolla's growth\r\n- a multicultural, passionate and professional crew to work with\r\n\r\nPlease send your CV and application to careers@jolla.com and mark \"Linux Kernel specialist\" to the email subject field. We will call suitable candidates to interviews and fill the position when we have the right match.",
