				"kuvausteksti" : "Whether you're just entering the workforce or have decided on a career change, it's your time to win in the world of work - and Manpower can help. We've been a world leader in employment services for nearly 70 years. We work to give you choices that suit your work style and fit your lifestyle. We arm you with everything you need to get a great job - and to succeed. It's time to explore the possibilities with Manpower.\r\nYour main role is to develop, execute and maintain test plans for the HireRight's product releases. You will create defects, analyse testing results, identify and report root causes for test failures. You will cooperate with the development team, product managers and make recommendations to improve product reliability, performance, quality and processes.\r\nYou are perfect candidate if you have 2 years' experience as a QA Engineer and have fluent English. You must have tested and shipped at least one commercially successful product through multiple releases. You have experience with QA processes and methodologies (automated and manual test processes, black box, white box and gray-box testing, test case design and execution), experience in SQL queries and working with databases. A Bachelor's degree in computer engineering, computer science or related engineering field would be a benefit.\r\nThe company offers challenging job in one of the biggest and developing companies in the world,  friendly working environment, opportunity to develop HireRight's own product, attractive salary and annual bonuses, office in the city centre, free parking and other bonuses.\r\nThis employment complies with the legislation of Estonia.",
