				"kuvausteksti" : "Primary Purpose of the Position:\r\nOperate equipment following standard work procedures.Support the senior Innovation technician in maintaining up-to-date documentation.\r\nVerify machines are maintained properly, operate reliably, and provide consistent 'spec' cycle times.   Drive to zero equipment breakdown.\r\nIdentify and help resolve issues quicly by working with your co-workers. Participate in cross-functional teams to implement operational improvements and roll out best practices.\r\nPrinciple Duties and Responsibilities\r\nDaily Equipment Care & Preventative Maintenance. \r\nVerify and maintain machine reliability to insure proper operation. Adhere to Total Preventive Maintenance (TPM) and calibration standards. Recognize abnormal situations and work with team members to identify and resolve equipment or process related issues.  \r\nProcess Control & Equipment Support:\r\nUse Statistical Process Control (SPC) run charts to recognize abnormal conditions, determine root cause(s), and work as a team to resolve problems. Provide operational assistance on equipment installation/upgrades. Implement improvements to improve Overall Equipment Effectiveness (OEE)\r\nSafety & Environment. \r\n You are accountable for your safety and the safety of your team members.  Take proper precautions to insure no one gets hurt. Follow environment, health, and safety standards/procedures and promote positive, proactive safety practices with your team.\r\nTraining: \r\nTrain / Develop others on machine/equipment setup and operations. Share best practices with your team and perform updates to safety, quality, and standard work procedures.\r\nExpectation:\r\nKnow your strengths and apply them to help build a collaborative innovation culture at our facility.  \r\nSeek and implement new ideas to drive safety, quality, and reliability.  Share in our committment to produced consistent, high quality tires just in time for our customer.\r\nEducation:\r\nRequired: min 2-year associate degree in mechanical, electrical, chemical or manufacturing technology or equivalent apprenticeship plus 3 years experience\r\nDesired: Bachelor in mechanical or electrical Engineering or in Automation\r\n\r\nExperience:\r\nPreferably a minimum of 3-5 years industrial facility experience. \r\nNetworking and Information Technology experience desired.\r\nKnowledge & Skills:\r\nAbility to operate both manual and automated industrial machinery - Knowledge of PLCs \r\nAbility to troubleshoot / improve mechanical and electrical systems.\r\nAbility to follow documented procedures.  \r\nAbility to perform multiple tasks or operate multiple equipment within any work day. \r\nWorking knowledge of data acquisition, production planning, run charting systems.\r\nStrong teamwork and collaboration skills.\r\nSense of urgency to resolve issues. \r\nGood problem solving skills.\r\nSelf initiative and self discipline.\r\nPosition requires shift, evening, night and weekend work assignments\r\n\r\nApplications have to be sent to: jeff.hurt@adem.etat.lu \r\n\r\nThis employment complies with the legislation of Luxembourg",
