				"kuvausteksti" : "Ridgewood house is in County Meath in Ireland c 20 kms from Dublin city near the University town of Maynooth (8,000 students) in County Kildare.\r\n\r\nThis family have 10- 12 horses and ponies and they need a permanent/temporary person to work with these animals including  some pleaseure horses/ show jumping horses in various stages of development and some hunters.  Accommodation in a loft apartment and food in the family home - needed someone to start as soon as possible and to stay at least 6 months - with breaks to go home for Summer holidays or other short visits.\r\n\r\nGroom- rider needed  for Sport Horses in Ireland to start as soon as possible.  Must have reasonable riding and horse care skills. Live in with no expenses for electricity, heating etc.  Possible help with travel costs to and from Ireland.\r\nApplicants needs to be able to do all the normal stable jobs, cleaning stables, feed and watering and cleaning the horses, taking care of the equipment and being able to ride.Riding skills must be at least intermediate and  should be able to take a horse from the stable, put on the tack (saddle and bridle etc) and get up and ride the horse without supervision and not fall off. It is important that the applicant is truthful about their experience with horses as safety is most important.\r\n\r\nEssential requirements:  Must be able to ride to a reasonalbe level in the  English Style - must have knowledge of horses and be able to clean and care for the horse and their equipment. Must have sufficient English to be understood and understand for safety reasons. Must be able to work without supervision.\r\n\r\nDesirable requirements:  Must be able to ride.\r\nDrivers license an advantage.\r\n\r\nAccommodation offered in loft apartment - own bedroom and all facilities, cooking, laundry, Wifi - cable t.v. \r\nSkype interview or contact by email/text/facebok etc.",
