				"kuvausteksti" : "G.Adair ,Springfield stables is a family run business situated in West Cork on the south coast of Ireland and is a commercial sport horse farm where  young horses are brought in for training. These horses range in age from 2 year olds upwards. Family members work with these horses and more staff is needed as the foaling season is starting in February and there are several mares who are in foal and due this Spring.\r\n\r\nNeed a person who can work with all sorts of riding horses  as well as breeding horses and who is willing to learn.  Some experience essential.  Able to care for horses and do all normal stable duties, cleaning stables and horse equipment. Feeding and bring to and from the fields and helping with mares and foals.  Good riding skills would be an advantage but not essential but a willingness to learn is most important.\r\n\r\nEssential requirements:\r\nDriver not essential.\r\nReasonable horse care skills but mainly someone who is willing to learn more about sport horses as well as mares and foals and who has some actual hands on experience with horses.  All applicants considered and replied to.\r\n\r\nDesirable requirements:\r\nsome horse care and riding skills no matter how little.\r\n\r\nFull accommodation in the family home with one grandmother and son - plenty of room - bedroom with t.v. Wifi etc - laundry facilities and absolutely no living expenses.  Skype or email/facebook interview",
