				"kuvausteksti" : "Enersense International Oy provides its customers with resourcing solutions which appreciate the fluctuations in their projects. Our company is an ISO 9001:2008/14001:2004-certified actor with more than ten years of experience in operating in close cooperation with large-scale nuclear and construction sites, the Olkiluoto 3 nuclear power plant site being the largest of them. \r\n\r\nWe are currently looking for Database Development Services to Support I&C Field Tests for our client in Olkiluoto Nuclear Power Plant, Finland. We are offering challenging work in international project environment. \r\n\r\nTasks and responsibilities:\r\n\r\n1. Function\r\n\r\n- The database development engineer will be in charge of following activities:\r\n- Acknowledge development already drafted\r\n- Review needs with users of the data base\r\n- Complete users requirement analysis accordingly\r\n- Develop database in accordance with\r\n- Existing draft (objective is to continue what has been developed and not to restart from scratch)\r\n- Revised users requirement\r\n- Client IT department recommendations\r\n- Support start-up phase with users\r\n\r\n2. Organization\r\n\r\n- The supplier will interface with various representatives of users groups\r\n- The supplier will be supervised by Client IT department\r\n\r\nRequirements:\r\n\r\n- Performance of above described scope of work requires following expertise:\r\n- Experience in data base management systems, particularly using Access software\r\n- Experience on projects with multiple users\r\n- Good interpersonal and communicative skills\r\n\r\nLanguages:\r\n\r\n- Fluent English (spoken and written)\r\n\r\nDrug test and concise security clearance will be done for the selected person in order to get the permanent access to OL3 site.\r\n\r\nPlease note that due to client's urgent need only applicants with a valid working permit / EU-citizenship can be considered.\r\n\r\nThe post will be filled as soon as a suitable applicant is found.",
