				"kuvausteksti" : "Call for Lähde! international pilot project artist \r\n \r\nLähde! Art and Culture as part of social and health services in Oulu arc -project is looking for international artists to test and develop a social art residency program in Northern Ostrobothnia region.\r\n \r\nWe are looking for artists with experience of artistic work within the social services. The artist will work and live at a group home or other social service location such as a group home for the disabeled in Ii. The artist is expected to bring art to the everyday life of the community of residents/customers and workers. The artist may plan the stay and the contents of the work, the pilot project, rather freely. However, main emphasis should be in the community: the sense of community, empowerment and participation. \r\n \r\nWe are offering recidensy periods during December 2017 - May 2018. The salary is 2350 euros per month. Travelling and food will be at own cost. There is some budget for materials for work that involves the customers (like a collaborative artwork etc.). The length of the stay is not fixed - you may suggest the timetable you think would work best. Please apply by sending us (taija.sailio(at)oulunkaari.com) an open application with your previous experience highlighted, a short project plan with the desired timetable and your CV (all in PFD-format). The call is open until 10.11.2017 but we reserve the right to hire artists as we find suitable applicants. \r\n \r\nLähde! Art and Culture as part of social and health services in Oulu arc -project:\r\n \r\nLähde! (2017-2020) aims to promote wellbeing through methods of art and the prevention of social exclusion especially among youngsters, immigrants, disabeled and mental health rehabilitators. New models and platforms will be created to add level of wellbeing and social participation, and to support daily life.\r\n \r\nThere are three work packages in the project:\r\nWP1. Promoting performance in work life and career planning by methods of art\r\nWP2. Public spaces as promoters of wellbeing through methods of art\r\nWP3. Connecting mobility of arts field professionals to welfare services\r\n \r\nThe project offers new perspectives to the use of art as a tool of wellbeing and adds utilization and accessibility of arts. By using art-based methods, the sense of community, empowerment and participation of youngsters, immigrants and other special groups as well as citizens can be added. Key value of the project is social, economical, cultural and ecological sustainability.\r\n \r\nThe project is administrated by Oulu Arc. The main collaborator of the project is KulttuuriKauppila Art Centre/KulttuuriKauppila Association. The ESR funded project is initiated in Northern Ostrobothnia in Finland 02/2017-02/2020. (Oulu Arc produces the health and social services in the municipalities of Ii, Pudasjärvi, Simo, Utajärvi and Vaala)\r\n \r\nwww.facebook.com/lahdetaide",
