				"kuvausteksti" : "Enersense International Oy provides its customers with resourcing solutions which appreciate the fluctuations in their projects. Our company is an ISO 9001:2008/14001:2004-certified actor with more than ten years of experience in operating in close cooperation with large-scale nuclear and construction sites, the Olkiluoto 3 nuclear power plant site being the largest of them. \r\n\r\nWe are currently looking for a I&C Radioprotection Commissioning Engineer for our client in Olkiluoto Nuclear Power Plant, Finland. We are offering challenging work in an international project environment.\r\n\r\nMain tasks and responsibilities:\r\n\r\n1. Planning (preparation):\r\n\r\n- Support in the building of the commissioning time schedule related to RMS \r\n- Review and comment follow-up of the RMS System Commissioning Programs (SCP) and Commissioning Instructions (CI)\r\n- Management of the reviews and inspections associated to the ECC (Erection Completion Certificate) process\r\n- Participation in the review of the testing equipment and peripheral testing devices required during commissioning\r\n- Collect of the l&C system related testing documentation at the applicable reference configuration (e.g. logic diagrams, Result Record Sheets and attachments, engineering master documents)\r\n- Participation in the definition and building of RMS training programs\r\n- Coordination with IT Security team for meeting plant requirements on that topic\r\n- Participation in the update of the spare parts list for commissioning purposes\r\n\r\n2. Execution:\r\n\r\n- Management of the RFCC (Ready for Commissioning Certificate) process\r\n- Initiation of I&C system isolation process (blocking process) if applicable as well as request for  temporary means (e.g. power supply)\r\n- Preparation of the commissioning document adaptation according to the actual system status on site\r\n- Performance of the commissioning activities within the entrusted scope under Permit-to-Test (PTT) conditions including the issuance of test reports\r\n- Supervision of the commissioning activities performed by other personnel in accordance with approved commissioning documents and in compliance with safety and quality rules\r\n- Check and evaluation of test reports belonging to RMS\r\n- Review of Work Order (WO) requests associated to RMS as well as the implementation of blockings - if any\r\n- Troubleshooting and analysis activities\r\n- Assessment of change requests and implementation of approved changes and requalification tests - if any\r\n- Management of temporary changes on site and outstanding issues (open points) for RMS\r\n- On-the-job training of operation and maintenance personnel\r\n- Enforcement of the IT-Security and HSE rules including applicable PTT / PTW processes\r\n- Management of the interface with the maintenance team\r\n\r\n3. Control and monitoring:\r\n\r\n- Provide inputs to progress measurement according to performance indicators\r\n- Initiate corrective actions in case of deviations\r\n- Issue progress reports\r\n\r\n4. Closure:\r\n\r\n- Issue Customer's approved System Commissioning Reports (SCR) for phase A and participate in the elaboration of PCR (Phase Commissioning Report) for subsequent phases\r\n- Close all open points directly assigned to I&C Commissioning organization for RMS\r\n- Support the overall project effort in demonstrating that contractual requirements are met\r\n\r\nRequirements:\r\n\r\n- Engineering educational background (nuclear or radioprotection preferable field)\r\n- At least one significant experience in Test Bay or commissioning activities related to radioprotection systems\r\n- Capacity of organization and managing daily activities involving several disciplines\r\n- Good relational and communication skills\r\n- Analysis and synthesis skills\r\n- Rigorous especially for adherene to procedures in force on site including configuration management\r\n- Good oral expression & writing skills\r\n- Ability to work in an international team (French, German, US...)\r\n- Aware of HSE and IT security aspects\r\n- EPR knowledge would be a plus\r\n\r\nTechnical skills required:\r\n\r\n- Sound knowledge in radioprotection technology - both hardware and software products\r\n- Use of Engineering and Maintenance equipment as well as peripheral testing tools either at Test Bay or during Commissioning\r\n- Knowledge of MIRION products would be a plus\r\n- Establishment and / or review of system test procedures\r\n\r\nLanguages:\r\n\r\n- Fluent spoken and written English required.\r\n- Knowledge of French, German or Finnish would be a plus\r\n\r\nDrug test and concise security clearance will be done for the selected person in order to get the permanent access to OL3 site.\r\n\r\nOnly applicants with a valid working permit / EU-citizenship can be considered.\r\n\r\nThe post will be filled as soon as a suitable applicant is found.",
