				"kuvausteksti" : "In keeping with our brand promise \"Engineering with a difference\", Etteplan takes a different attitude to embedded system and IoT solutions - something our customers confirm time and time again. We are proud of our expertise and our ability to impact our customers' success. \r\n\r\nYour expertise matters to us - come join our success story!\r\n\r\nWe are looking for EMBEDDED SOFTWARE DESIGNERS to join our Embedded Systems and IoT team in Jyväskylä. \r\n\r\nWe expect the candidate to have a good understanding of embedded software design using C/C++/Java language, DSP coding skills, understanding of Wireless Communications like air interface timings as well as knowledge in real-time operations. We value Bachelor's, Master's or PhD degree in information technology, computer science or similar. In an international company fluent Finnish and English skills are required, too. \r\n\r\nMatlab or other simulation tool skills,  RF hardware development skills and experience in one or more other programming languages like Qt or Python are beneficial competences in carrying out the tasks. We also value familiarity with Agile methodologies and Linux environment, Linux kernel and driver programming skills.   \r\n\r\nIf you are a real team player with customer-oriented approach and fluent communications skills, send your application along with your CV already today! \r\n\r\nEtteplan offers diverse and interesting projects in many different fields of technology. We provide good working atmosphere among highly experienced professionals, and a great chance to develop your professional skills. Above all, you get a chance to feel professional pride in job well done.\r\n\r\nEtteplan is Finland's biggest employer in industrial engineering, technical product information, embedded systems and IoT solutions. We offer a vantage point to international industry, serving top players in their specific fields of expertise. With Etteplan you will gain a deeper insight into their products.\r\n\r\nWe are a genuine engineering house: our Group employs around 2,800 experts mainly in Finland, Sweden, the Netherlands, Germany, Poland and China - most of them engineers. Our success is based on our competence and our knowledgeable staff, both of which we take good care of. \r\n\r\nEtteplan offers interesting and challenging tasks in a growing working community in 30 locations around Finland. The work involved in customers' varied and demanding projects means constant learning and development.",
