				"etatyo" : false,
				"kuvausteksti" : "We are looking for a Documentation Engineer to implement our client's new Product Data Management system. Do you have a technical background and want to work in an international start-up minded company? You should have some previous working experience from product documentation and have a relevant education or be about to finish your studies within engineering. In this position you will be working a fixed six-month project, where after there might be a possibility of development and new opportunities within the company.\r\n\r\nABOUT THE ROLE\r\n\r\nAcademic Work is looking for a Documentation Engineer to work in Espoo. Our client Innohome is exporting more than 90% of their Stove Guard products and they are strengthening their capabilities by hiring an Electrical Engineer to implement their new PDM system. This is a 6-month fixed-term position, and you will be directly hired to our client Innohome Oy.\r\n\r\nJOB DUTIES\r\n\r\nThe job is a project based position, where your main responsibility will be to implement the client's new PDM system. You will be going through the product data and together with the R&D team, develop the company's product documentation procedure.\r\n\r\nWE ARE LOOKING FOR\r\n\r\nOur ideal candidate has a Bachelor's degree in Electronics Engineering or in an equivalent field of study. You should have some previous experience PDM implementation, this experience might be from a summer job or part time job, as long as you can routinely work with technical documentation.\r\n\r\nYou are fluent both in spoken and written English. You have good team working skills, but you also have the ability to work independently with minimal supervision, as you will not have someone to guide you through this project.\r\n\r\nOur ideal candidate has:\r\n\r\n-Bachelor's degree in Electronics Engineering, or equivalent\r\n-Some previous experience and understanding in PDM systems\r\n-Good team working skills\r\n-Independent working and problem solving skills\r\n-Fluent both written and spoken English\r\n-Ability to concentrate on details\r\n-Technical knowledge\r\n\r\nPlease send your application as soon as possible, because we will begin the interviews with suitable candidates immediately.\r\n\r\nApply for the position here:\r\n\r\nRemember to attach your CV into your application!\r\n\r\nINFORMATION ON THE APPLICATION PROCESS\r\n\r\nTo apply for the job click on \"Apply here\" below. Remember to attach your CV into your application! We only handle applications through our website but if you have questions about the position you can reach us via email esp01@academicwork.fi. Please write the advert ID in the subject and paste the advert link in the mail. We are continuously screening and contacting candidates so make sure to send your application as soon as possible. Please notice that the advert can be removed before eventual last dates on our external advertising pages. When the advert is being removed it's either due to that the processes is finished or because we have many qualified applications and are continuing in the selection/interview phase. We are the Home of the Young Professionals. We are experts in recruitment and staffing university students, recently graduated and professionals in the beginning of their career. You can be employed by us as a consultant in one of our client companies or be recruited directly to our client via our recruitment co-operation. You can read more about us at www.academicwork.fi. When employed at Academic Work you will have your own dedicated Consultant Manager, whose role is to answer your questions, support your career development and ensure you enjoy your place of work.\r\n\r\nINFORMATION ABOUT THE COMPANY\r\n\r\nOur client Innohome Oy is a Finnish company headquartered in Espoo. They develop intelligent, leading edge safety devices for home. Innohome is the international market leader of cooker safety products and they are also in the forefront of preventing other household appliances fires and water damages.",
