				"kuvausteksti" : "Do you have a passion for software development and a desire to grow into a professional within the field? We are looking for a Junior Ruby on Rails Developer to work in a successful company with pioneers of web analytics technology development in Northern Europe. Our client's mission is to implement web intelligence into business.\r\n\r\nABOUT THE ROLE\r\n\r\nAcademic Work is looking for a Junior Ruby on Rails Developer for our client Leadfeeder.\r\n\r\nYou will be recruited to our client company. Academic Work will take care of the recruitment process, therefore candidates are kindly asked to direct all questions to Academic Work at hel03@academicwork.fi.\r\n\r\nJOB DUTIES\r\n\r\nIn this position, you will work closely with an experienced team to make the software better every day by developing the Leadfeeder product and the backend systems. Leadfeeder has a solid international business and their customers love what they have to offer!\r\n\r\nKeywords: Ruby on Rails, JavaScript, Unix, web analytics\r\n\r\nThis position suits an eager Ruby on Rails Developer who wants to work hard and be a part of a success story!\r\n\r\nWE ARE LOOKING FOR\r\n\r\nOur ideal candidate is interested in web development and has a continuous desire for growth and is familiar with Ruby on Rails. In order to succeed in this job you have to have knowledge in databases and hopefully you are familiar with Unix operating system. The person we are looking for has a suitable academic background (e.g. IT, computer science).\r\n\r\nGood social skills and the ease of communicating with people are also seen as vital factors. Knowledge of English language is a requirement for this position.\r\n\r\nApply for this position if you have:\r\n\r\n- Suitable academic background (e.g. IT, computer science)\r\n- Knowledge in Ruby on Rails\r\n- Knowledge of database technologies\r\n- Good communication skills and fluency in English\r\n- A desire for growth and improvement!\r\n\r\nIt is also seen as an advantage if you have experience with JavaScript and some knowledge or experience in web analytics. If you have your own free time projects or school projects (e.g. on Github) that would be relevant in this position, please make sure you include those in your application.\r\n\r\nGo ahead and apply already today, since we fill the positions as soon as we find a suitable candidate!\r\n\r\n\r\nTo apply for the job you need to register on our website and then click on \"Apply here\". Remember to attach your CV into your application! We only process applications through our website but if you have questions about the position you can reach us via email in hel03@academicwork.fi. Please write the advert ID in the subject field and paste the advert link in the mail.\r\n\r\nWe are continuously screening and contacting candidates so make sure to send your application as soon as possible. Please note that the advert can be removed prior to the last application dates on our external advertising pages. In the event the advert has been removed, it is due to either the process being completed or because we have a sufficient number of qualified applications and are proceeding to the selection/interview phase in the process.\r\n\r\nINFORMATION ABOUT THE COMPANY\r\n\r\nLeadfeeder is a fast-growing startup based in Helsinki, Finland. Our roots are deep in web analytics and we have been the successful pioneers of web analytics technology development in Northern Europe. Our mission is to bring web intelligence into business and we are doing that with a team of incredible talents in five countries.",
