				"kuvausteksti" : "ALTEN, the European leader in engineering and technology consulting, provides support for its clients' development strategies in the fields of innovation, R&D and it systems. ALTEN is active in 21 countries, covers the whole development cycle and offers a choice of service levels, from technology consulting to full-blown project outsourcing. It is the technology partner of choice for Europe's leading companies. \r\n\r\nALTEN Finland employs 400 people in 8 different locations in Espoo, Hyvinkää, Hämeenlinna, Lahti, Paimio, Tampere, Raahe and Oulu. \r\n\r\n \r\nWe are now looking for a driven\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nEXPERIENCED SITE SUPERVISOR\r\n\r\n\r\nYou will work as a site supervisor in our customer's projects which are located different locations in Finland and abroad. Projects consist from the different fields of Automation, Electrical, Mechanical, QA/QC, Piping etc.\r\n\r\nYour Responsibilities in this position will be:\r\n\r\n- Responsibility of supervising works at project site\r\n- Knowledge of mechanical and/or electrical design\r\n- Successful leadership of the construction / assembly / commissioning team\r\n- Monitor, control and report quality, delivery time, cost and scope of the works in the projects\r\n- Maintaining and improving the customer relationship\r\n\r\n\r\nRequirements for this position are:\r\n\r\n- An appropriate technical degree in relevant area\r\n- Good written and spoken Finnish and English\r\n- Excellent communication and cooperation skills\r\n- Problem solving skills and systematic ways of working\r\n- Ability to work under pressure\r\n- Being forward thinking and goal focused\r\n- Readiness to travel as required\r\n- Experience in large energy, mining, oil&gas or other industrial construction projects (+5 years)\r\n\r\n \r\nTo be right candidate for this position you are willingness to travel long periods. You are also flexible, active and get along with different kind of people. We offer you a challenging position where you will have the ability to work in an inspiring working environment as well as find opportunities for personal development. The contract type of the employment and the place of the recruitment may be discussed. \r\n\r\n \r\nFor additional information, please contact Business Manager Juuso Tikka, tel. 040 156 4171.\r\n\r\nIf you are interested in this position, please send your application and salary expectation by November 13th, 2017 via link below. We are looking forward to receive your application.",
