				"kuvausteksti" : "Do you have the curiosity to explore what problems need to be solved? Are you familiar with the basics of machine learning and data mining? We are now looking for aspiring, ambitious Data Scientist for Sergel. If you are self-motivated and desire new opportunities, please read further and send your application!\r\n\r\nABOUT THE ROLE\r\n\r\nAcademic Work is looking for Data Scientist to our client Sergel Oy.\r\n\r\nThis job is a staffing position, which means that you will be employed by Academic Work and work as a consultant at Sergel Oy.\r\n\r\nJOB DUTIES\r\n\r\nIn this position, your role is to provide accurate, timely, relevant and quality analysis while driving data insights for a dynamic business. You will be working in a team that delivers end-to-end BI and analytics solutions as actionable recommendations to business. You will get to engage in critical problem solving through data modeling, mining, predictive analytics, pattern recognition, machine learning, and statistics. In this position, you will be supported by a senior professional and will have the opportunity to grow and learn by doing.\r\n\r\nIf you are motivated and looking for an opportunity in BI and data science field, apply today! This is a great opportunity to kick-start your professional career and advance your skills as a part of thriving international company.\r\n\r\nWE ARE LOOKING FOR\r\n\r\nOur ideal candidate has an applicable education and enthusiastic attitude towards all things related to BI, machine learning and data analysis. You might be already graduated or just finishing your studies. Succeeding in this position requires strong problem-solving skills and analytical thinking. Furthermore, you are also eager to develop yourself and willing to play for the team.\r\n\r\nApply for this position if you have:\r\n\r\n-Degree in Computer Science, Math or Statistics or in related field\r\n-Strong listening, verbal, written and presentation skills in English\r\n-Demonstrated skill in the use of one or more analytic software tools or languages (e.g., R, \r\n Python, or other analytical tools)\r\n-Good mathematical knowledge; basic understanding of machine learning and statistics\r\n-Strong data-driven thinking and ambition to develop your skills\r\n\r\nIt is also seen as an advantage if you have earlier experience in databases (SQL), Power BI and other BI softwares.\r\n\r\nEmployment period: 12 montsh fixed term, with a possibility to discuss further employment\r\n\r\nIn this position you will be employed by Academic Work and we take care of all the legal responsibilities of an employer such as salary payments, insurances and health care. It is important for us that you feel well and perform in your job. Your consultant manager will be in regular contact with you during the assignment and guides you on your career. Academic Work is an authorized staffing and recruitment agency and our employees are extremely satisfied, something that we are very proud of. We are here to help you succeed!\r\n\r\nINFORMATION ON THE APPLICATION PROCESS\r\n\r\nTo apply for the job click on \"Apply here\" below. Remember to attach your CV into your application! We only handle applications through our website but if you have questions about the position you can reach us via email in esp01@academicwork.fi. Please write the advert ID in the subject and paste the advert link in the mail. We are continuously screening and contacting candidates so make sure to send your application as soon as possible. Please notice that the advert can be removed before eventual last dates on our external advertising pages. When the advert is being removed it's either due to that the processes is finished or because we have many qualified applications and are continuing in the selection/interview phase.\r\n\r\nWe are the Home of the Young Professionals. We are experts in recruitment and staffing university students, recently graduated and professionals in the beginning of their career. You can be employed by us as a consultant in one of our client companies or be recruited directly to our client via our recruitment co-operation. You can read more about us at www.academicwork.fi.\r\n\r\nWhen employed at Academic Work you will have your own dedicated Consultant Manager, whose role is to answer your questions, support your career development and ensure you enjoy your place of work.\r\n\r\nINFORMATION ABOUT THE COMPANY\r\n\r\nSergel is one of the leading providers of credit management services in Norway, Finland, Denmark, Latvia and Lithuania with approximately 360 employees. Sergel is owned by Marginalen Group.",
