				"kuvausteksti" : "As our Device Developer, you will be a member of our Product Development Team and be part of implementing our next generation Smiley products, as well as maintaining the existing ones. You will be evaluating and trying out new emerging technologies to support the development of even more versatile solutions for our customers.\r\n\r\nYou will be responsible for implementing both embedded coded and server side code for handling data transfer between the Smiley products and our backend on a global scale. As part of our global team in Tampere, Finland, you will be working with technologies such as 2G, 3G, CDMA, NB-IOT and Cat-M and global mobile operators.\r\n\r\nYour responsibilities will include:\r\n\r\n- Implementing embedded code for our Smiley products\r\n- Implementing server side code to handle data transfer between the Smiley products and our backend\r\n- Improving our support and diagnostics tools for the Smiley products\r\n- Exploring new technologies and creating working demos for evaluation\r\n- Collaborating with engineers from different fields to make turnkey solutions for our customers\r\n- Collaborating with external and internal stakeholders regarding the Smiley products' life cycle\r\n\r\nOur ideal candidate will have:\r\n\r\n- Experience on embedded code development, preferably with C/C++\r\n- Experience on server side code development\r\n- Passion for delivering high quality and working code\r\n- Curiosity towards new technologies\r\n\r\nWhat we offer\r\n\r\nOur work environment is open, energetic, multicultural, flexible, and positive. We have a significant international client base and a large reseller network all over the world. Joining our happy team means becoming part of the company behind the globally recognized 4 Smileys whose mission is to make people happier - one Smiley at a time.",
