				"kuvausteksti" : "We are looking for a Software Development Tool Engineer to work with development and support of software engineering environments. If you already have good skills in Python or Linux shell scripting and you like to work with various projects with different complexity this might be the opportunity you are looking for. Read further to learn more about this position and send in your application today!\r\n\r\nKUVAUS\r\n\r\nAcademic Work is looking for Software Development Tool Engineer for our client Airbus Defence and Space Oy.\r\n\r\nThis job is a staffing position, which means that you will be employed by Academic Work and work as a consultant at Airbus Defence and Space Oy.\r\n\r\nTYÖTEHTÄVÄT\r\n\r\nAs a Software Development Tool Engineer, you will take part in development and support of software engineering environments. In this position, your tasks also include solving internal support requests.\r\n\r\nThis is a great opportunity to get to work in interesting projects with good tools and flexible working conditions with experienced software developers. The opportunity to be recruited by the company during or after the consultancy is continuous.\r\n\r\nETSIMÄMME HENKILÖ ON\r\n\r\nOur ideal candidate has relevant academic background and at least 1-2 years previous working experience. You have experience in working in Windows and Linux environments and good skills in Python or Linux shell scripting. You have customer and service oriented mindset and you are recognized for your ability to work in a team, especially in cross cultural teams. As an employee you are creative and self-confident, enthusiastic to work on various activities with a different level of complexity. Fluent verbal and written skills in English are required to succeed in this position, and Finnish skills are seen as an advantage.\r\n\r\nApply for this position if you have:\r\n\r\n- Relevant academic background (for example Master of Science in Technology)\r\n- At least 1-2 years previous working experience\r\n- Experience of working in Windows and Linux environments\r\n- Good working skills in Python or Linux shell scripting\r\n- You've worked with some of the following tools: Jenkins, JIRA, VisualStudio, GIT, Eclipse, Linux toolchain\r\n- Fluent verbal and written skills in English\r\n- Customer and service oriented mindset.\r\n\r\nStart: As soon as possible\r\nWorking hours: Fulltime, 37,5 hours/week\r\nEmployment period: 12 months\r\nLocation: Helsinki\r\nSalary: According to agreement\r\nPublished: 12.10.2017\r\n\r\nTo apply for the job you need to register to our website and then click on \"Apply here\" below. Remember to attach your CV into your application! We only handle applications through our website but if you have questions about the position you can reach us via email in hel03@academicwork.fi. Please write the advert ID in the subject and paste the advert link in the mail. We are ongoing screening and contacting candidates so make sure to send your application as soon as possible. Please notice that the advert can be removed before eventual last dates on our external advertising pages. When the advert is being removed it's either due to that the processes is finished or because we have many qualified applications and are continuing in the selection/interview phase.\r\n\r\nWe are the Home of the Young Professionals. We are experts in recruitment and staffing university students, recently graduated and professionals in the beginning of their career. You can be employed by us as a consultant in one of our client companies or be recruited directly to our client via our recruitment co-operation. You can read more about us at www.academicwork.fi.\r\n\r\nWhen employed at Academic Work you will have your own dedicated Consultant Manager, who's role is to answer your questions, support your career development and ensure you enjoy your place of work.\r\n\r\nINFOA ASIAKKAASTA\r\n\r\nAirbus Defence and Space is a division of Airbus responsible for defence and aerospace products and services. It is the world's second largest space company and one of the top ten defence companies in the world. In Finland, Airbus Defence and Space Oy employs around 300 people in Helsinki and Jyväskylä.",
