				"kuvausteksti" : "We are looking for Swedish-speaking project assistants for transcription. The work is part-time transcription of research interviews. This work is suitable for students because the employee can decide on the amount of work to take on.  \r\n \r\nRequirements\r\n\r\nWe are looking for people with native Swedish language skills. You should have excellent knowledge of Swedish grammar as well as perseverance. We appreciate the ability to transcribe also English.\r\n\r\nWe expect you to have some level of prior experience with transcription. A fast typing speed is essential. You can test your typing speed at https://10fastfingers.com/typing-test/swedish. The work will be done remotely using your own computer, where you must have access to Microsoft Word. \r\n\r\nAs projects may be assigned on short notice, ability to commit to deadlines is required.\r\n\r\nCompensation\r\n\r\nCompensation is based on the length of the recording, number of speakers on the recording and the transcription type. The time spent to transcribe one recording hour depends on the person's typing speed (usually around 3-4 hours per recording hour).\r\n\r\n\r\nHow to apply and more information\r\n\r\nApply for this position by sending your application and CV in English or Finnish by email to rekry@spoken.fi. Attach your results from the typing test (words per minute). Questions about the position can be sent to the same email address. \r\n\r\n-----------------------\r\n\r\nSpoken is a Finnish communications company serving customers in the Nordic countries. We employ around 60 language professionals and serve our customers in 5 different languages. Our services include transcription and proofreading. \r\n\r\nRead more: www.spoken.fi",
