				"kuvausteksti" : "Do you have a passion for software development and a desire to grow into a professional within the field? We are looking for a Junior Embedded Software Designer to work for our client Digitalist Group. This is an amazing opportunity for you to be part of a fantastic team and learn from the best!\r\n\r\nABOUT THE ROLE\r\n\r\nAcademic Work is looking for a Junior Embedded Software Designer C/C++ for our client Digitalist Group.\r\n\r\nThis job is a staffing position, which means that you will be employed by Academic Work and work as a consultant at the client company. All candidates are kindly asked to direct all questions to Academic Work hel03@academicwork.fi.\r\n\r\nJOB DUTIES\r\n\r\nIn this position, you will work closely with an experienced team to make sure the solutions Digitalist delivers match and exceed their customer's expectations. You will be designing and developing embedded software systems and devices mostly for clients in the industrial field. You will mainly be working with C/C++ and embedded Linux.\r\n\r\nDigitalist is working in the industrial domain to utilize modern connectivity, embedded hardware and software technologies together with modern UX design principles. They are working with well-known companies such as Cargotec, Kone and Savox.\r\n\r\nWE ARE LOOKING FOR\r\n\r\nOur ideal candidate is interested in embedded software design and has a continuous desire for growth. In order to succeed in this job you have to have some knowledge in C/C++ and you are familiar with Linux operating system. The person we are looking for has a suitable academic background (e.g. IT, computer science) or you are finishing your studies. Good social skills and the ease of communicating with people are also seen as vital factors. This position requires fluent written and oral English language skills, knowledge of Finnish language is seen as an advantage.\r\n\r\nApply for this position if you have:\r\n\r\n- Suitable academic background (e.g. IT, computer science)\r\n- C/C++ development knowledge from embedded SW environments (e.g. school projects)\r\n- Knowledge in embedded Linux\r\n- Fluent in written and spoken English, Finnish\r\n- Desire for growth and improvement\r\n\r\nIf you have your own free time projects or school projects (e.g. on Github) that would be relevant in this position, please make sure you include those in your application.\r\n\r\nGo ahead and apply already today, since we fill the position as soon as we find a suitable candidate!\r\n\r\nEmployment period: Fixed-term contract for 12 months, with potential for extension\r\n\r\nLocation: Tampere, Helsinki or Jyväskylä\r\n\r\nApply here:: https://academicwork.fi/avoimet-tyopaikat/junior-embedded-software-designer-c-c-tampere-helsinki-or-jyvaskyla/14995228\r\n\r\nTo apply for the job you need to register on our website and then click on \"Apply here\". Remember to attach your CV into your application! We only process applications through our website but if you have questions about the position you can reach us via email in hel03@academicwork.fi. Please write the advert ID in the subject field and paste the advert link in the mail.\r\n\r\nWe are continuously screening and contacting candidates so make sure to send your application as soon as possible. Please note that the advert can be removed prior to the last application dates on our external advertising pages. In the event the advert has been removed, it is due to either the process being completed or because we have a sufficient number of qualified applications and are proceeding to the selection/interview phase in the process.\r\n\r\nINFORMATION ABOUT THE COMPANY\r\n\r\nDigitalist Group Digitalist Group is a creative technology company that provides creative digital solutions and services for customer companies in selected target industries. We help our customer companies embrace digitalisation, Internet and mobility for productivity and unique user experiences for competitive advantage. We realise innovative dreams with unparalleled design and impeccable technical delivery.",
