				"kuvausteksti" : "Do you like to combine physical and digital worlds together? Would you like to use and expand your current knowledge to create great and useful software for real-life use cases?\r\n\r\nIf yes, you could be one to join our team.\r\n\r\nWe are looking for an experienced and motivated Front End Developer to build usable & modern web experiences, while taking full advantage of the system backend services. In this position you would work closely with our Safea access control core team in Abloy Oy Espoo office.\r\n\r\nWe can offer you an interesting environment and challenging tasks, as well as competitive benefits and the possibility to grow together with the solution and advance in your career.\r\n\r\nCome join and work with us in the interesting field of access control!\r\n\r\nFE Developer Responsibilities:\r\n\r\n- Analyze the needs of Safea end-users\r\n- Create an optimized user experience\r\n- Identify design problems and devise solutions \r\n- Make strategic designs and user experience decisions related to existing and new functionality\r\n- Take a user-centered design approach and rapidly test and iterate your designs\r\n- Proactively manage escalations in a smooth, timely and professional manner in addition to providing recommendations and rationale\r\n- Champion new ideas and drive user-centered process and outcomes\r\n\r\nEducation, work experience and Personal Qualities:\r\n\r\n- At least Bachelor's degree in Computer Science or Software Engineering or related field, or equivalent work experience\r\n- Minimum 3 years of experience in implementing web user interfaces and utilizing APIs\r\n- An overall understanding of web production and the capabilities within digital channels is essential\r\n- Proven ability to work creatively and analytically in a problem-solving environment\r\n- Ability to explain rationale behind decision\r\n- Expertise in multiple of the following: Javascript, Angular, CSS/Less, Webpack, websockets, UI/UX design, software security\r\n- Bonus expertise: Graphical skills, Back End knowledge (Java, Rails, MySQL), AWS, Atlassian tools, Jenkins, Scrum/agile development\r\n- Fluency in English, fluency in Finnish a plus\r\n\r\nFor more information, please contact Teemu Thorström, R&D Manager, tel. +358 50 3293059, best times to contact: October 19 at 14:00 - 16:00 or October 20 at 13:00 - 15:00. You may also contact Kirsi Parviainen, HRD Manager, tel. +358 40 5304754.\r\n\r\nPlease complete your application no later than 12th November 2017 at www.abloy.fi.",
