				"kuvausteksti" : "Job description:\r\nDesigner & Support Technician in the Engineering Department (EN), the Alignment Coordination and Engineering Group (ACE), the Integration Section (INT).\r\n You will join:\r\nThe Engineering Department (EN) that provides engineering competences, infrastructure systems and technical coordination for the world's largest particle accelerator complex and its experimental facilities.\r\nThe Alignment Coordination and Engineering Group (ACE), which provides project coordination for the accelerator complex, including layout management, integration, scheduling, work and safety coordination as well as metrology and alignment services. The Group further provides development and support for the Organization's engineering data, maintenance management tools and CAD systems.\r\nThe Integration Section (INT), responsible for the 3D integration studies of all the installations necessary for the operation of a particle accelerator.\r\nFunctions \r\nAs a Designer and Support Technician in the Integration Office, you will:\r\nStudy the integration of mechanical systems, components and services for CERN accelerator complex, using CATIA V5 as a main Computer-aided design tool.\r\nPrepare drawings for technical documentation, in compliance with relevant drafting standards and current quality assurance plan, and provide, comparison and evaluation of different options for technical-system layouts.\r\nAssist CAD and PLM/PDM users by providing support, disseminating best practices and resolving problems around the CAD and PLM/PDM tools. Typical application areas include; CAD Data Management and CAD methodologies.\r\nParticipate in tests, user-documentation creation and maintenance of applications in collaboration with the team in charge of CAD support at CERN.\r\nQualification required :   Higher technical diploma in the field of mechanics, or equivalent.\r\n  \r\nThe experience required for this post is:\r\nDemonstrated experience of mechanical integration in a mechanical, aeronautical, or civil engineering design office.\r\nDemonstrated experience with providing user support, as well as technical support and troubleshooting of applications.\r\nDemonstrated experience with PLM/PDM systems; knowledge of SmarTeam is an asset.\r\nThe technical competencies required for this post are:\r\nMechanical systems integration.\r\n3D & 2D technical drawing: using CATIA V5 and relevant standards.\r\nMechanical analysis & modelling: solving of basic mechanical engineering problems using strength of materials and materials selection principles.\r\nThe behavioural competencies required for this post are:\r\nWorking in teams: building and maintaining constructive and effective work relationships.\r\nCommunicating effectively: ensuring that information, procedures and decisions are appropriately documented; expressing opinions, ideas and suggestions with conviction and in a logical/structured manner; keeping to the point.\r\nSolving problems: identifying, defining and assessing problems, taking action to address them.\r\nThe language competencies required are:\r\nSpoken and written English or French: ability to understand and speak the other language in routine situations. Willingness to acquire the knowledge of the other language rapidly.\r\nEligibility conditions \r\nDiversity has been an integral part of CERN's mission since its foundation and is an established value of the Organization. Employing a diverse workforce is central to our success.\r\nWe welcome applications from all Member States and Associate Member States.\r\nThis vacancy will be filled as soon as possible, and applications should normally reach us no later than 12.11.2017.\r\nBy applying here, you allow CERN to consider your application for any position it considers relevant with respect to your profile. Please ensure you update your profile regularly with any relevant information and that you inform the recruitment service if you wish your file to be removed from the database.\r\n \r\nNote on Employment Conditions \r\nWe offer a limited-duration contract for a period of 5 years. Limited-duration contracts shall terminate by default on their date of expiry. \r\nSubject to certain conditions, holders of limited-duration contracts may apply for an indefinite position.\r\nThese functions require:\r\nWork during nights, Sundays and official holidays, when required by the needs of the Organization.\r\n\r\nTravel costs will be compensated.\r\n\r\nWe use an online recruitment website. We do not engage in direct contact.\r\n\r\nAPPLICATION PROCESS\r\nDeadline for applications:12/11/2017\r\nSend applications to:http://jobs.web.cern.ch/job/12823#utm_source=palvelut",
