				"kuvausteksti" : "Enersense International Oy provides its customers with resourcing solutions which appreciate the fluctuations in their projects. Our company is an ISO 9001:2008/14001:2004-certified actor with more than ten years of experience in operating in close cooperation with large-scale nuclear and construction sites, the Olkiluoto 3 nuclear power plant site being the largest of them. \r\n\r\nWe are currently looking for Licensing Specialist (Non-nuclear) for our Client in Helsinki, Finland. We are offering challenging work in an international project environment.\r\n \r\nMain tasks and responsibilities: \r\n \r\n-Developing programs and schedules for receiving construction permits (non-nuclear)\r\n-Defining the requirements and contents of different documents to be developed\r\n-Providing project licensing direction for assigned regulatory projects\r\n-Providing licensing services to engineering, test, safety analysis internal resources on regulatory and licensing activities\r\n-Supporting the Client for defense of construction documentation and receiving necessary non-nuclear construction permits in Finland\r\n \r\nRequirements:\r\n \r\n-Experience of completing similar tasks - minimum 5 years\r\n-Knowledge of construction documentation requirements\r\n-Experience of submitting construction documentation to regional and national regulatory authorities of Finland\r\n-Experience of working in Oulu region is considered as a benefit\r\n-University degree in the area of Civil Construction or another engineering area\r\n \r\nLanguage skills: \r\n \r\n-Fluent Finnish and English are required\r\n-Russian language skills are considered as a benefit\r\n\r\nThe post will be filled as soon as a suitable applicant is found.",
