				"kuvausteksti" : "Nipromec Oy Ltd is a global consulting and engineering company operating in energy-, industry- and offshore fields. \r\n\r\nWe are now looking for Preparation and Method Engineers for a project in Olkiluoto. Work starts as soon as possible and estimated duration is 6 (six) months.\r\n\r\nTasks:\r\n-Plan and prepare field activities for maintenance (especially spare parts identification for remaining open points to close).\r\n-To respect the requirements of Technical specifications.\r\n-Review maintenance work reports.\r\n-Ensuring the application of safety, security and environmental standards, guidelines and rules.\r\n\r\nGeneral and technical background expected:\r\n-Engineering degree/diploma with an emphasis on Mechanical Engineering or experienced technician with a mechanical or electromechanical background.\r\n-At least 3 years of experience as maintenance planner for mechanical works, mechanical engineering, or experience as field supervisor/technician.\r\n-Understanding of technical documentation for power plant components.\r\n-Understanding of technical drawings / part lists/ manuals/specifications.\r\n-Maintenance mechanical works.\r\n-Procedure/instruction compliance.\r\n-Good communicator and coordinator.\r\n-Exposure to facets of plant operation, maintenance outages, preparation, coordination and field supervision of planned work and permit to work implementation.\r\n-Experience in procedure and instructions writing (required for creating maintenance instruc-tions).\r\n-Fluent English both written and spoken required. Ability with French, German or Finnish is a plus.\r\n\r\nSkills required:\r\n-Several years of specialist work experience.\r\n-In-depth knowledge of nuclear plant operations, maintenance and/or procedural planning.\r\n-Knowledge of power plant, system and process engineering.\r\n-Knowledge of commissioning procedures and organization.\r\n-Good relational and communication skills.\r\n\r\nPosition is filled as soon as suitable candidate is found. To apply please send application and CV with salary request to info@n-pro.fi . For any further information, you might require please go to www.nipromec.com",
