				"kuvausteksti" : "ABB is a pioneering technology leader in electrification products, robotics and motion, industrial automation and power grids, serving customers in utilities, industry and transport & infrastructure globally. Continuing more than a 125-year history of innovation, ABB today is writing the future of industrial digitalization and driving the Energy and Fourth Industrial Revolutions. ABB operates in more than 100 countries with about 136,000 employees and of them around 5,100 in Finland. www.abb.com\r\n\r\nWe are looking for a Design Engineer at ABB Oy, Motors and Generators in Helsinki. In this position, you will be responsible for the electrical design of large AC motors and generators, including electromagnetic and thermal calculations and dimensioning.\r\n\r\nYour responsibilities\r\n- Producing electrical design documentation for customers, production, procurement and the test field\r\n- Analyzing test results\r\n- Supporting sales, procurement and after sales in technical matters\r\n- Order engineering\r\n- Generating development proposals using calculation programs\r\n\r\nWe offer \r\n- Challenging and exciting work in the growth markets of the power generation and motor businesses\r\n- Insight into the latest developments in electrical machines, drives, power generation products and systems\r\n- An excellent opportunity to develop professionally by completing more challenging tasks as an electrical designer and participating in ABB's training programs\r\n- The opportunity to further your career in ABB Motors and Generators' locations around the globe\r\n\r\nRequirements\r\n- B.Sc. or M.Sc. in electrical engineering\r\n- Theoretical knowledge of electrical machines\r\n- Capability to apply theoretical knowledge to practical work\r\n- Ability to work in teams, also with people from different cultural backgrounds\r\n- Analytical approach to problem solving\r\n- Commitment to completing tasks, keeping schedules and communicating results\r\n- Excellent written and spoken communication skills in English and Finnish\r\n\r\nIdeally, you have\r\n- Knowledge of dimensioning of electrical machines and calculation \r\n- Knowledge of measuring technology, power electronics, thermodynamics and insulation technology \r\n- A few years' experience in electrical design or engineering\r\n- Experience in production, product management, and project management\r\n- Other language skills in addition to English and Finnish\r\n- Analytical and numerical tools, ADEPT, numerical program (Matlab, Simulink etc.), electrical FEM (Flux, FCSME etc.)",
