				"kuvausteksti" : "Enersense International Oy provides its customers with resourcing solutions which appreciate the fluctuations in their projects. Our company is an ISO 9001:2008/14001:2004-certified actor with more than ten years of experience in operating in close cooperation with large-scale nuclear and construction sites, the Olkiluoto 3 nuclear power plant site being the largest of them. \r\n\r\nWe are currently looking for a Safety Analysis Engineer for our client in Helsinki, Finland. We are offering challenging work in an international project environment. \r\n\r\nMain Tasks and Responsibilities\r\n\r\n- Safety Analysis Engineer has two main activities:\r\n- First main activity is the coordination and contribution to the tasks related to deterministic safety and safety for operation which comprises assessment of systems to ensure the contractual commitment for Plant safety and availability and validation of the results and requirements from safety analyses by means of site walkdowns and preparation of corresponding documentation.\r\n- Second main activity is the contribution to the commissioning, comprising a direct communication with the Commissioning team and the counterpart at Customer side for clarification of technical questions in regard to nuclear safety. \r\n- General support to the Process & Safety team for clarification of open points, DCR investigation, etc. \r\n\r\nOther tasks:\r\n\r\n- Development of documents and safety reports (PSAR/FSAR; PSA-1,2)\r\n- Solution of technical issues for submission of SAReports, Topical Reports, etc.\r\n- Submission of documents / sections to the Customer\r\n- Acceptance of documentation for various reports developed by subcontractors (for including to SAR)\r\n\r\nRequirements:\r\n\r\n- At least 5 years of experience in similar position\r\n- Experience of working in nuclear industry of Finland\r\n- Knowledge of IAEA/EUR requirements and procedures of their implementation\r\n- General knowledge of radiation safety\r\n- General knowledge of the field of severe accidents\r\n- General engineering knowledge of justifying calculations of safety and ecological impact\r\n\r\nLanguage Skills:\r\n\r\n- Fluent English required\r\n- Russian language skills is an advantage\r\n\r\nThe post will be filled as soon as a suitable applicant is found.",
