				"kuvausteksti" : "The early morning newspaper delivery has 2700 professional workers who ensure that the newspapers are delivered from the printing press to the customers breakfast tables in just a few hours. We work in 1600 delivery routes and the newspapers are delivered on 353 days in a year. \r\n\r\nOur walking and cycling distance in a year is around the same as going around the world six times.\r\n\r\nWe drive over 10 million kilometers in a year, which equals the distance of going 13 times back and forth to the moon. All the driving is carbon neutral. The early morning delivery distributes around 131 million newspapers in a year.\r\n\r\nNIGHT TIME EXERCISERS TO NEWSPAPER DELIVERY\r\n\r\nWe are looking for workers to a part time job  for  permanent working contracts to metropolitan area (Helsinki, Vantaa, Espoo, Kauniainen) . \r\n\r\nNewspaper deliverer works when others are asleep. In the break of day, you have already done your work shift.\r\n\r\nAs a newspaper deliverer, you work in small hours between 01:00-7:30Am. The newspaper delivery is done in every night of the week and off days change every week. The working schedule is 6+2 which means that six nights of work is followed by two days off.\r\n\r\nThe delivery routes are done either by walking, cycling or with a car. For car areas, a valid driving license is mandatory.\r\n\r\nA paid training for the work is 2-3 working shifts before you start your independent work. \r\n\r\nPlease leave your application for the job to Posti recruitement system by 19.11.2017 at www.posti.com/careers \r\n\r\nHave a look at career stories at Posti. \r\n\r\nPosti is a service provider that delivers the smartest and most customer-focused postal and logistics services in the market. Posti is expanding into new service areas and playing an increasingly significant role in the daily life of its customers. We operate in eleven countries, our net sales in 2016 amounted to EUR 1.6 billion and the number of our personnel is approximately 20,500. Our businesses also include the logistics service provider Itella Russia and the electronic business specialist OpusCapita. www.posti.com",
