				"kuvausteksti" : "The University of Eastern Finland, UEF, is one of the largest multidisciplinary universities in Finland. We offer education in nearly one hundred major subjects, and are home to approximately 15,000 students and 2,500 members of staff. We operate on three campuses in Joensuu, Kuopio and Savonlinna. In international rankings, we are ranked among the leading universities in the world.\r\nThe Faculty of Science and Forestry operates on the Kuopio and Joensuu campuses of the University of Eastern Finland. The mission of the faculty is to carry out internationally recognised scientific research and to offer research-education in the fields of natural sciences and forest sciences. The faculty invests in all of the strategic research areas of the university. The faculty's environments for research and learning are international, modern and multidisciplinary.  The faculty has approximately 3,800 Bachelor's and Master's degree students and some 490 postgraduate students. The number of staff amounts to 560. http://www.uef.fi/en/lumet/etusivu\r\nWe are now inviting applications for \r\ntwo Postdoctoral Researcher/Project Researcher positions in mid-infrared spectroscopy and biophotonics, Department of Applied Physics, Kuopio Campus  \r\nWe are seeking two highly motivated and talented postdoctoral researchers to work full-time on an EU-funded project focused on the development of an innovative mid-infrared arthroscopic imaging system for real-time clinical diagnostics of degenerative joint diseases. The primary tasks of the postdoctoral researchers will involve designing and testing of the fiber optic probe that is developed in the project for diagnostics of articular cartilage, meniscus, and ligament pathologies.\r\nThe ideal candidate will possess the following: \r\n- A PhD in optics, spectroscopy, biophotonics or a related field.\r\n- Expertise in at least one programming language, e.g. MATLAB, Python, etc.\r\n- Working knowledge of advanced multivariate techniques for analysis of spectroscopic data, e.g. partial least squares (PLS) regression. \r\n- Good publication track record in high impact journals.\r\n- Background in laboratory experiments (not essential but highly desirable).\r\n- Proficiency in the English language.\r\nThe project will be conducted in the Biophysics of Bone and Cartilage (BBC) research group, at the Department of Applied Physics, University of Eastern Finland, Kuopio, Finland, under the supervision of Professor Juha Töyräs and in collaboration with the other project partners across Finland and Europe. The BBC group is one of the global leaders in the biophysics of bone and cartilage, and consists of more than40 researchers applying experimental, theoretical and clinical approaches for understanding and development of innovative techniques for diagnostics of joint diseases. \r\nTo be considered for the position of a postdoctoral researcher, applicants must hold a suitable doctoral degree (in optics, spectroscopy, biophotonics or a related field).\r\nIf the applicant has been awarded his or her doctoral degree less than five years ago, the post will be one of a Postdoctoral Researcher. If the doctoral degree has been awarded more than five years ago, the post will be one of a Project Researcher.\r\nThe positions will be filled from January 1, 2018 to June 30, 2021.\r\nThe positions will be filled for a fixed term due to them pertaining to a Horizon 2020 project (Mid-infrared arthroscopy innovative imaging system for real-time clinical in depth examination and diagnosis of degenerative joint diseases). Postdoctoral researcher positions shall always be filled for a fixed term, UEF University Regulations 31 §.\r\nThe salary of the position is determined in accordance with the salary system of Finnish universities and is based on level 5 of the job requirement level chart for teaching and research staff (€2,865.30/ month). In addition to the job requirement component, the salary includes a personal performance component, which may be a maximum of 46.3% of the job requirement component.\r\nApplicants finishing their PhD in the near future are also encouraged to apply.  However, they are expected to hold a PhD degree by the starting date of the position.\r\n\r\nThe names and contact information of at least two referees are requested in the application form.\r\nFor further information on the positions, please contact: Professor Juha Töyräs, email: juha.toyras@uef.fi, tel. +358 40 355 2026. For further information on the application procedure, please contact: Executive Head of Administration Arja Hirvonen, email: arja.hirvonen@uef.fi, tel. +358 44 716 3422.\r\nA probationary period is applied to all new members of staff.\r\nThe electronic application should contain the following appendices:\r\n- a résumé or CV\r\n- a list of publications\r\n- copies of the applicant's academic degree certificates/diplomas, and copies of certificates/diplomas relating to the applicant's language proficiency, if not indicated in the academic degree certificates/diplomas\r\nThe application needs to be submitted no later than 15 November, 2017 (by 24:00 EET) by using the electronic application form. \r\nPlease click on the \"apply for the job\" link to submit your application.",
