				"kuvausteksti" : "Nipromec Oy Ltd is a global consulting and engineering company operating in energy-, industry- and offshore fields. \r\n\r\nWe are now looking for a Civil steel structure engineer for a project in Olkiluoto. Work starts on asap.\r\n\r\nTasks:\r\n-Planning and performance of the preparation work for the specific contractor under consideration of the engineering input, availability of stored materials in customers scope.\r\n-Handling of all relevant permit processes for start of works (permit to work, hot work permit, confined space permit, etc.).\r\n-Care taking for removal of any obstructions by other disciplines or intervention group in advance to the start of execution works.\r\n-Supervision and follow up of the contractor's execution works.\r\n-lnvolvement of other parties like inspection organizations, HSE organizations of the different stakeholders (contractor, customer, client).\r\n-Review and closure of execution documentation in coordination with the method team and final documentation team.\r\n-Support for contractual negotiation Weekly / Monthly internal reporting.\r\n-Ensure that the activities of the team as well as those of the subcontractors are performed according to the highest HSE standards.\r\n-Ensure that the works on site and are performed according to the contractual standards of quality, time schedule and budget, and according to Project Procedures including but not limited to work follow up documentation requirements.\r\n-Check that human resources and equipment are mobilized by the subcontractors according to plans. Check that the subcontractors are using the right technical documentation.\r\n-Tracking and cleaning up the list of open points related to these works.\r\n-During take over operations, check that works have been completed according to schedule and quality requirements.\r\n-Attending weekly meetings with the relevant subcontractors.\r\n-Report directly to the Finishing and Room Completion Group Supervision Manager Report weekly progress to the team leader supervision manager.\r\n-Undertake any other duties from time to time as instructed by the Finishing and Room Completion Group Supervision Manager.\r\n\r\nGeneral and technical background expected:\r\n-Civil engineer or equivalent with substantial experience of civil finishing works and coating works supervision on large construction projects.\r\n-Civil engineer or architect at least 3 years.\r\n-Civil technician at least 5 years.\r\n-As an alternative it might be acceptable to provide staff with experience in civil design in-stead of supervision civil engineer or architect at least 5 years.\r\n-One-year professional experience on the OL3 project in the scope of supervision of civil or mechanical scope.\r\n-Good technical knowledge of civil finishing works, specific knowledge in the supervision of door installation works are favored.\r\n-Good technical knowledge of metal works, specific knowledge in the supervision of steel structures installation and corrosion protection works are favored.\r\n-Fluent English both written and spoken required. Ability with French, German or Finnish is a plus.\r\n\r\n\r\nSkills required:\r\n-Organizational and planning ability to prepare for the execution works of the subcontractors.\r\n-Good communication skills in order to interface with the supervisors of other disciplines.\r\n-Good human relationship and team spirit.\r\n-Ability to communicate with people of different professional background and culture.\r\n-Result oriented in particular with respect to safety, quality, cost and schedule (on time delivery - OTD).\r\n\r\nPosition is filled as soon as suitable candidate is found. To apply please send application and CV with salary request to info@n-pro.fi . For any further information, you might require please go to www.nipromec.com",
