				"kuvausteksti" : "Would you like to work for the global market leader in oil spill response solutions and environmental services? Are you a well-organized team player who's not afraid of challenging tasks and likes to take initiative? Do you have a suitable education and preferably some relevant work experience within e.g. project or sales support? Then you might be the one for us. Academic Work is now looking for a Project & Sales Support person, to perform versatile tasks in the field of project management and sales support for our client Lamor Corporation Ab. Don't pass on this opportunity and apply now!\r\n\r\nABOUT THE ROLE\r\n\r\nAcademic Work is looking for a Project & Sales Support person to our client Lamor Corporation.\r\n\r\nThis position will start as a staffing position for the first 12 months, with the possibility of continuing as a full-time permanent employee employed directly by Lamor Corporation Ab. This means that for the first 12 months you will be employed by Academic Work and work as a consultant at Lamor Corporation Ab.\r\n\r\nJOB DUTIES\r\n\r\nIn this position you will work closely with the Project Managers and the Global Service Sales Team. Your main responsibilities include assisting the company's Project Managers with preparing documentation, arranging and following up project schedules and other day-to-day tasks related to the projects. You will also prepare documentation and assist with proposals, tenders and other tasks for the Service Sales Team.\r\n\r\nThis is a great opportunity to become a part of an international organization and take on a responsible role in an innovative and fast-paced environment. This position includes the possibility to advance within the company both in Finland and abroad.\r\n\r\nWE ARE LOOKING FOR\r\n\r\nOur ideal candidate has a suitable education and preferably already some work experience from similar tasks, during e.g. summer jobs or internships. You can either be graduated or at the very end of your studies. You are well organized and adaptive. You seek to actively participate in the development of processes and you are not afraid of taking on challenging tasks. Lastly, you feel at home in a fast working environment and work effectively under pressure. This position requires fluent written and oral English language skills, and good IT skills (Excel, Word etc.). Fluency in Finnish, Swedish or other languages is seen as an advantage as the company has operations globally.\r\n\r\nA technical background or an interest in technology is also considered a benefit in this position.\r\n\r\nIn this position you will be employed by Academic Work and we take care of all the legal responsibilities of an employer such as salary payments, insurances and health care. It is important for us that you feel well and perform in your job. Your consultant manager will be in regular contact with you during the assignment and guides you on your career. Academic Work is an authorized staffing and recruitment agency and our employees are extremely satisfied, something that we are very proud of. We are here to help you succeed!\r\n\r\nApply for the position here: \r\nhttps://www.academicwork.fi/avoimet-tyopaikat/project-sales-support/14995435\r\n\r\n\r\nINFORMATION ON THE APPLICATION PROCESS\r\n\r\nTo apply for the job click on \"Apply here\" below. Remember to attach your CV into your application! We only handle applications through our website but if you have questions about the position you can reach us via email in esp02@academicwork.fi. Please write the advert ID in the subject and paste the advert link in the mail. We are continuously screening and contacting candidates so make sure to send your application as soon as possible. Please note that the advert can be removed before eventual due dates on our external advertising pages. When the advert has been removed it's either due to that the process is finished or because we have received many qualified applications and are continuing to the selection/interview phase.\r\n\r\nWe are the Home of the Young Professionals. We are experts in recruitment and staffing university students, recently graduated and professionals in the beginning of their career. You can be employed by us as a consultant in one of our client companies or be recruited directly to our client via our recruitment co-operation. You can read more about us at www.academicwork.fi.\r\n\r\nWhen employed at Academic Work you will have your own dedicated Consultant Manager, whose role is to answer your questions, support your career development and ensure you enjoy your place of work.\r\n\r\nINFORMATION ABOUT THE COMPANY\r\n\r\nLamor Corporation is a growing environmental company and the world's leading supplier of oil spill clean-up solutions. Our operations are global and our head office is located in Porvoo, close to the old town and with good public transit connections. We have offices in the U.K., Spain, China, Peru, Colombia, Ecuador, Brazil, Turkey, Oman and the United States. There are about 40 employees in Finland, and around 200 employees in the entire Group.",
