				"kuvausteksti" : "Become a Kunstportal blogger - writers wanted!\r\n\r\nWe are looking for two creative writers to be part of the Kunstportal. We want bloggers to share their experiences in art trends, art happenings and art life in the Nordic Countries.\r\nRather than critical reviews, we hope that the blog will be alive with content, which opens up discussion and interest in art. We want bloggers to report on their experience of happenings, phenomenon and trends within art, especially in the Nordic Countries.\r\n\r\nWe offer you:\r\n\r\n- Chance to be a part of something new and exciting\r\n- Creative freedom in writing\r\n- Full support with new ideas and approaches\r\n- Work from home possibility\r\n- Excited and encouraging team\r\n\r\nWe need you to be:\r\n\r\n- Effective and creative, we will give you the full support in implementing new ideas\r\n- Work independently\r\n- Familiarity with content management systems like Wordpress\r\n- Write at weekly entries for the blog\r\n- Take photos and/or video documenting art events\r\n- Respond promptly to blog comments and email\r\n- Start asap\r\n\r\nThis is a part time, work-from-home position. Salary as agreed.\r\n\r\nJoin us\r\n\r\nKunstportal is a growing start up company with digital platform for selling and buying art. We offer a place, where people inside and outside the art world, can meet to exchange ideas, products and services. We want to make it simple for art interested people and art buyers to get closer to the art.  Our aim is to be the biggest social media portal with focus in art, we want to bring art to people. We are a launching our service in October 2017.",
