				"kuvausteksti" : "Enersense International Oy provides its customers with resourcing solutions which appreciate the fluctuations in their projects. Our company is an ISO 9001:2008/14001:2004-certified actor with more than ten years of experience in operating in close cooperation with large-scale nuclear and construction sites, the Olkiluoto 3 nuclear power plant site being the largest of them. \r\n\r\nWe are looking for an experienced Site Engineer for our client in Denmark.\r\n\r\nMain responsibilities and tasks:\r\n\r\n- Assure compliance with contracts at site (customer and contractors)\r\n- Assist Site Manager in contractual correspondence\r\n- Site cost control and erection cost forecast\r\n- Site change management, internal and external\r\n- Erection document management at site\r\n- Progress and schedule reporting\r\n- Quantity management\r\n- Supervise the erection and installation work at site\r\n- Coordinate material receiving together with the shipping department \r\n- Assure that the subcontractors comply with the Client's HSE (Health, Safety and Environmental) rules, as well as with local requirements in the country of the site\r\n- Approve technical and commercial change orders requested by the subcontractors, within the limits set by the Site Manager\r\n- Carrying out system tasks within agreed timescales and budgets and reporting system\r\n- Organisation and day to day management of the project engineering issues\r\n- Client liaison on all technical and commercial aspects\r\n- Commercial and contractual awareness to identify variations to order\r\n- Define technical responsibilities within the project - interfaces, system and work packages\r\n- Monitor project progress and deliverables through regular review meetings\r\n- Monitor timelines of system reviews throughout the project\r\n- Read the contracts and understand the contractual responsibilities of the Client, the End Client and Contractors\r\n- Proactively assure compliance with the contracts\r\n- Notify customer and contractors formally in writing in case there is deviation in their performance (e.g. delay of providing areas/services by the Customer, delay, quality or HSE shortage in contractors' performance) \r\n- Review contractor progress payment requests\r\n- Maintain site cost report (with site assistant)\r\n- Prepare monthly updated cost forecasts to ERP\r\n- Maintain document, equipment and other lists (together with engineering manager) \r\n- Reporting to project team as instructed by Site manager\r\n\r\nRequirements:\r\n\r\n- M.Sc. or B. Sc. in Industrial Economics, Mechanical/Electrical Engineering or Construction. \r\n- At least 2 years of experience from construction site works or from project management. \r\n- Working independently on targets and providing practical solutions\r\n- Exceptional interpersonal skills, including teamwork, facilitation and negotiation\r\n- Ability to handle multiple tasks\r\n- Handling of local subcontractors\r\n- Proven leadership skills in a dynamic project environment\r\n- Excellent problem solving, decision analysis and interpersonal skills\r\n- Proven to be thorough and show meticulous attention to detail\r\n- Able to meet deadlines in a fast paced environment with a positive attitude\r\n- Candidates with territory experience will be preferred.\r\n- Expert project management skills\r\n- Good understanding of contractual issues and claims management. \r\n- Good knowledge of modern office IT and scheduling software (MS Project and/or Primavera)\r\n\r\nLanguages:\r\n\r\n- Good knowledge of English\r\n- Danish language skills considered as a benefit\r\n\r\nThe post will be filled as soon as the suitable candidate is found.",
