				"kuvausteksti" : "INTRODUCTION\r\n\r\nWe help create better buildings. Progman Oy is a Finnish software company behind MagiCAD for Revit MEP and AutoCAD. We have over three decades of experience in developing solutions for the building services industry, specialising in products and services for the design of heating, piping, ventilation, sprinkler, and electrical systems. With nearly 20,000 licenses in use across over 70 countries globally, MagiCAD has a solid track record from thousands of successful MEP design projects used by leading mechanical and electrical design companies. For over two decades we have been also helping manufacturers in the industry to bring their products closer to their customers. Our solutions include digital catalogues, tailored software online tools. Today, we cooperate with over 200 manufacturers and our MagiCloud online service is the biggest MEP catalogue in Europe. Our business is steadily growing and profitable. Progman is a Glodon Group company and our team consists of over 140 passionate software professionals located in Finland and across the Europe. \r\n\r\nWe are now looking for highly motivated Product Development Engineer / MEP to join our growing team of high professionals. \r\n\r\n\r\nJOB DESCRIPTION\r\n\r\nIn this position you will be working together with other members of the Product Management Team and the Product Manager for MagiCloud. The team is responsible for all functionalities concerning the development of MagiCAD for Revit and MagiCAD for AutoCAD and MagiCloud. Your responsibility will be to develop cloud based services on MagiCloud for our MagiCAD users as well as for pure Revit users.\r\n\r\nAs a Product Development Engineer your work will consist of a number of versatile tasks, including:\r\n\r\n- Collecting and handling demands and wishes related to the cloud services. Demands coming directly from End users, Sales, After Sales and Product Management teams as well as from Manufacturers.  \r\n- Evaluating, Prioritizing, Specifying and Testing of new functions in cooperation with Product Data Sales, Product Management and Production Teams.  \r\n- Supporting Marketing Team by creating technical marketing material for Sales Teams \r\n- Supporting After Sales team to create training material for End Users\r\n- Taking part in MagiCloud and MagiCAD Steering Groups\r\n\r\nIn Finland, we have offices in Turku, Rauma, Espoo and Hämeenkyrö. In the position you can be located in any of our offices. Also other locations are possible. Position is permanent\r\n\r\n\r\nREQUIREMENTS\r\n\r\nTo develop the future cloud solutions we are looking for a technical-minded MEP Engineer with fluent English skills. Today you are probably working as consultant making design & engineering solutions for MEP in buildings, but feel that you could make a difference by developing cloud solutions for engineers like you. Good ability in English writing and communication is a strong benefit. Any experience of MagiCAD, Revit and AutoCAD are very beneficial. Occasional travelling will also be required. \r\n\r\n\r\nWHAT WE OFFER\r\n\r\n- Job at rapidly growing international software house\r\n- Modern and comfortable working environment in centrally located offices\r\n- Secured job in a financially stable company\r\n- Relaxed, professional and productive work community \r\n- Good possibilities for professional growth and development\r\n- Flexible working conditions including possibility for remote working, flexible working hours and usage of flexitime \r\n- Good benefits e.g. sport allowance and extensive health care.\r\n\r\nOur personnel survey results and the feedback from new employees shows that new employees are well received and feel at home when they onboard to the Progman team. \r\n\r\n\r\nADDITIONAL INFORMATION\r\n\r\nMore information about this position and Progman can be found at http://www.magicad.com/careers \r\n\r\nGot more questions? Please contact Pauli Keinonen on pauli.keinonen@magicad.com or +358405477633\r\n\r\n\r\nHOW TO APPLY\r\n\r\nIf this sounds like you, please send your application with salary request by 12th November 2017 via our recruitment portal at https://www.sympahr.net/public/pq.aspx?9d276166 \r\n\r\nApply fast! We are going through applications as they arrive and will fulfill the position immediately when the right person is found!",
