				"kuvausteksti" : "Do you have experience in web development? Do you value freedom in your daily work and possibility to try new things to expand your knowledge? Futurice is now looking for new talents to join their international team of skilled developers. If you answered 'yes' to these questions send your application today!\r\n\r\nKUVAUS\r\n\r\nAcademic Work is looking for web developers for our client company, Futurice.\r\n\r\nYou will be recruited to our client company. Academic Work will take care of the recruitment process, therefore candidates are kindly asked to direct all questions to Academic Work hel03@academicwork.fi.\r\n\r\nTYÖTEHTÄVÄT\r\n\r\nIn this position, you will work with Futurice's web development projects as a front-end, back-end or full stack developer depending on the set of skills you have. The projects you will participate in also depends on your personal interests and your previous experience. You will work side-by-side with world-class experts of different fields and get the possibility to try new things and expand your expertise to the direction you prefer. At Futurice, you will be treated like an adult and work as a part of a tribe, a smaller group of people where your voice will be heard.\r\n\r\nKeywords for Futurice:\r\n\r\nReact, Node, Scala and Java\r\nReact Native, iOS and Android\r\n\"Personally, I want to work in a company with high ambition levels and attractive goals. I want to be part of something which I believe can achieve great things - and that is how I feel about Futurice. Doing great things requires great people. In Futurice, people are thought to be the most important part of doing good business, and it shows: people are assigned to projects which give them value, resources are not spared when making working (and having fun) convenient, and recruitment is focusing on finding the best people to work with.\" Ville Sillanpää, Software Developer\r\n\r\nThis position suits you who appreciate freedom and taking responsibility of your work. You will have the possibility to pursue your personal interests by developing your expertise to the direction you like. Futurice offers great career opportunities in an international environment surrounded by experts of different fields.\r\n\r\nETSIMÄMME HENKILÖ ON\r\n\r\nOur ideal candidate has an educational background in IT or related field. You have experience in software development but it doesn't matter which technologies you have used as long as building usable digital services is your thing! You are the one we are looking for if you are enthusiastic about software development and eager to develop your skills by trying new things.\r\n\r\nApply for this position if you have:\r\n\r\n- Educational background in IT or related field\r\n- Experience as a front-end, back-end or full-stack developer\r\n- Strong interest towards developing your skills\r\n- Fluent skills in English\r\n\r\nStart: As soon as possible \r\nWorking hours: Fulltime \r\nEmployment period: Permanent \r\nLocation: Helsinki \r\nSalary: According to agreement \r\nPublished: 18.10.2017\r\n\r\nTo apply for the job you need to register on our website and then click on \"Apply here\". Remember to attach your CV into your application! We only process applications through our website but if you have questions about the position you can reach us via email in hel03@academicwork.fi. Please write the advert ID in the subject field and paste the advert link in the mail. We are continuously screening and contacting candidates so make sure to send your application as soon as possible. Please note that the advert can be removed prior to the last application dates on our external advertising pages. In the event the advert has been removed it is either due to the process being completed or because we have a sufficient number of qualified applications and are proceeding to the selection/interview phase in the process.\r\n\r\nWe are the Home of the Young Professionals. We are experts in recruitment and staffing university students, recently graduated and professionals in the beginning of their career. You can be employed by us as a consultant in one of our client companies or be recruited directly to our client via our recruitment co-operation. You can read more about us at www.academicwork.fi.\r\n\r\nINFOA ASIAKKAASTA\r\n\r\n\"We hire smart people and trust that they are still smart after signing on the dotted line. We work to give all these smart people a voice in the organization and create an environment that people feel vested enough in to be open and honest about how they feel. At Futurice people can have a real impact on the world, too - not just the company. The Spice Program sponsors open source contributions our people make on their own time and we have an employee-driven social impact program called the Chilicorn Fund. Join us and work for a real change.\"",
