				"kuvausteksti" : "Firesteel Resources is a junior mining company focused on the acquisition and development of mining properties with near term production potential.  The company has recently signed a Joint Venture Agreement with Nordic Mines AB to operate the past producing Laiva gold mine near Raahe Finland.   \r\nUnder the agreement, Firesteel will be the operator of the JV and will be responsible for restarting production at the mine.   The Laiva mine includes two open-pits and a recently constructed 6,000 tpd, state-of-the-art process plant designed by Metso and constructed by Outotec.\r\n\r\nIn preparation for restarting production at the Laiva mine, Firesteel Resources is looking to hire a \r\n\r\nHuman Resources Manager (Henkilöstöjohtaja).\r\n\r\nJob Description\r\nReporting to the General Manager and as a member of the Laiva Management Team, the Human Resources Manager will lead all HR related activities with the objective to optimize employee capability and performance.  \r\n\r\nJob Responsibilities\r\nManage all aspects of Employee and Industrial Relations, as well as Health and Safety.\r\nProvide generalist Human Resources support to the Laiva Management Team.\r\nProvide advice, support and coaching to Supervisors in the areas of Employee and Industrial Relations. \r\nAdminister the Collective and Local Agreements.\r\nAssist in the development and delivery of training program for the operating workforce.\r\nManage the recruitment, hiring and onboarding of all salaried employees.\r\nDevelop Human Resources procedures and system with the objective to create consistency within the Human Resources function.\r\nDevelopment Human Resources related KPIs, ensure key objectives are met.\r\n\r\nQualifications\r\nBSc/MSc in Human Resources Management or other relevant degree.\r\nMinimum of 7 years of Human Resources experience including position a mining operation.\r\nExtensive knowledge of Finnish employment laws, regulations and practices.\r\nExperience in working with Collective Agreements negotiated by the Federation of Finnish Technology Industries.\r\nExperience in expatriate contracts and support is an advantage.\r\nFluent in English and Finnish.\r\nQualified candidates should send their applications to employment@firesteelresources.com by November 3, 2017.",
