				"kuvausteksti" : "Firesteel Resources is a junior mining company focused on the acquisition and development of mining properties with near term production potential.  The company has recently signed a Joint Venture Agreement with Nordic Mines AB to operate the past producing Laiva gold mine near Raahe Finland.   \r\nUnder the agreement, Firesteel will be the operator of the JV and will be responsible for restarting production at the mine.   The Laiva mine includes two open-pits and a recently constructed 6,000 tpd, state-of-the-art process plant designed by Metso and constructed by Outotec.\r\n\r\nIn preparation for restarting production at the Laiva mine, Firesteel Resources is looking to hire a \r\n\r\nMine Manager (Kaivosinsinööri).\r\n\r\nJob Description\r\nReporting to the General Manager and as a member of the Laiva Management Team, the Mine Manager will lead all mining related activities with the objective to optimize operating performance. \r\n\r\nJob Responsibilities\r\nManage all aspects of Mine Operations and Maintenance including the activities of the Mining Contractor.\r\nEnsure that all activities of Mine Operations and Maintenance are carried out in a safe, environmentally sound, cost effective and productive manner.\r\nDevelop Mine Operations and Maintenance budget plan in the context of the Life-of Mine plan. Ensure that budget plan is adhered to.\r\nOversee the development of mining plans that allow selective mining of ore with the objective to minimize dilution and optimize fragmentation.\r\nDevelop training program for the Mine Operations and Maintenance workforce; ensure that said training program is followed.\r\nDevelop Mine Operations and Maintenance related procedures; ensure that safe work practices are reflected in said procedures.\r\nDevelop Mine Operations and Maintenance related KPIs; ensure key objectives are met.\r\nQualifications\r\nBSc/MSc in Mining Engineering.\r\nMinimum of 10 years of experience in open-pit, hard-rock precious metal mining.\r\nPrior leadership experience in a mining environment.\r\nPrior experience in managing a mining contractor.\r\nExtensive knowledge of blasting techniques utilized in selective mining.\r\nFluent in English.  The ability to communicate in Finnish is an advantage.\r\nQualified candidates should send their applications to employment@firesteelresources.com",
