				"kuvausteksti" : "Firesteel Resources is a junior mining company focused on the acquisition and development of mining properties with near term production potential.  The company has recently signed a Joint Venture Agreement with Nordic Mines AB to operate the past producing Laiva gold mine near Raahe Finland.  \r\nUnder the agreement, Firesteel will be the operator of the JV and will be responsible for restarting production at the mine.   The Laiva mine includes two open-pits and a recently constructed 6,000 tpd, state-of-the-art process plant designed by Metso and constructed by Outotec.\r\n\r\nIn preparation for restarting production at the Laiva mine, Firesteel Resources is looking to hire a \r\n\r\nSenior/Chief Metallurgist (Kemian insinööri).\r\n\r\nJob Description\r\nThe Senior/Chief Metallurgist will provide leadership and specialized technical expertise to optimize the metallurgical performance of the Laiva process plant.\r\n\r\nJob Responsibilities\r\nMonitor and manage all aspects of metallurgical performance of process operations.\r\nDevelop and execute procedures to track mill operation metrics.\r\nDirect and manage process optimization and cost savings evaluations.\r\nDevelop and execute all metallurgical test programs required for proper mill operations.\r\nManage metallurgical testing facilities.\r\nManage mill operations and process staff in absence of Mill Superintendent.\r\nEnsure that all required safety procedures are utilized by all process staff at all times.\r\nQualifications\r\nBSc/MSc in Metallurgical or Chemical Engineering \r\nMinimum of 5 years experience including position of metallurgical responsibility in precious metal milling operation.\r\nMinimum of 2 years experience in the operation of an agitated tank cyanide leach operation, preferable carbon in leach.\r\nExperience in developing and managing all aspects of a detailed metallurgical balance for a precious metal milling operation.\r\nExperienced in the implementation and management of a mill sampling program.\r\nExperienced in the proper utilization and maintenance of mill instrumentation and process automation systems.\r\nExperience in the implementation and execution of a metallurgical testing laboratory facility.\r\nAbility to evaluate metallurgical test results and implement appropriate process modifications based on test results.\r\nExperience in the supervision of metallurgical testing laboratory staff.\r\n\r\nQualified candidates should send their applications to employment@firesteelresources.com  by November 3, 2017.",
