				"kuvausteksti" : "Are you passionate about mobile games? Do you drive for excellence and top-notch quality in whatever you do? Are you longing to be part of a world-class international game development team with true professionals in a fun atmosphere? RedLynx offers you this and much more!\r\n\r\nRedLynx, a Ubisoft studio is a multiplatform game development studio located in Helsinki. Along with the hugely popular Trials series, we have developed and published more than 100 games. We are a passionate team of over 140 people of 21 different nationalities. Founded in 2000, we are one of the oldest and biggest game studios in Finland.\r\n\r\nSince 2011 RedLynx has been part of Ubisoft, the 3rd biggest independent publisher in the world with over 13,000 team members, who work hand-in-hand to deliver rich and innovative gaming experiences. At RedLynx we cherish the spirit of innovation and experimentation, and we are proud to have the support and trust from Ubisoft to push for new practices and solutions that may be used by other studios worldwide.\r\n\r\nWe are now looking for a\r\n\r\nUI Programmer\r\n\r\nTo complete our mobile team working on our latest mobile release South Park: Phone Destroyer™\r\n\r\nAs a UI Programmer your responsibility is to bring the UI of our latest mobile game to the next level and make sure South Park: Phone Destroyer™ is going to be the greatest success on the market! You will play a key role in ensuring that the feeling of the game is perfectly smooth and that our players will just LOVE IT. Your job is to implement practical and efficient solutions and features related to in-game menus, Heads-Up-Display and user experience that meet the UI, design and technical requirements. As a UI Programmer you'll have an independent role and ownership of the UI Programming in a project where there are lots of opportunities to create cool stuff and let your know-how shine. You will be working inside the talented programmer team and closely with our amazing artists and designers.\r\n\r\nWe are looking for a passionate programmer with an interest in interface design and motivation not to do things just well, but pixel perfect! You are comfortable collaborating with stakeholders from different disciplines and you are not afraid to communicate your ideas in the team. We will offer you a unique opportunity to work with a successful mobile game with a huge IP. You will have a friendly and welcoming team supporting you and making sure you'll have fun while doing what you love!\r\n\r\n\r\nCORE RESPONSIBILITIES\r\n- Writing modular and reusable UI code\r\n- Optimization of UI performance on mobile\r\n- Work hand in hand with UI artists and UX designers to prototype and deliver the best experience for players\r\n- Support programming team in other than UI related tasks when needed\r\n\r\nOUR DREAM CANDIDATE \r\n- Has strong interest in interface design, especially mobile and games\r\n- Is willing to work closely with the UI and UX crew\r\n- Has proficiency in C#\r\n- Is experienced in using source control systems such as Git, Perforce \r\n- Has professional experience in the video game industry\r\n- Has solid knowledge of Unity engine, specially UI and animation best practices and optimization\r\n- Has knowledge of rapid wire frame prototyping\r\n- Is detail oriented\r\n- Works independently and is well organized\r\n- Speaks fluent English\r\n- Has good communication and team work skills\r\n\r\nWE APPRECIATE\r\n- Education in relevant field\r\n- Experience in app/web development \r\n- Experience supporting live games\r\n\r\nWE OFFER\r\n- Awesome projects with a lot of variety\r\n- An open, international and massively friendly work environment full of ambitious and skilled people \r\n- Lots of challenges and opportunities to develop yourself\r\n- Competitive compensation and benefits such as wide healthcare and insurances, phone benefit, lunch vouchers, free gym, free breakfast, free games, parties, events you name it :)\r\n- Good work/life balance: We take our work very seriously but we also respect and value our employees' personal lives, also during high-intensity periods, that's why we have flexible work hours\r\n- Relocation help",
