				"kuvausteksti" : "Operations division's task is to execute Finnair's flight operations safely, economically and in a reliable manner. Finnair Technical Operations is responsible for the airworthiness of Finnair fleet. The key objectives of Technical Operations are safety, reliable flight operations and cost-efficient maintenance processes. Finnair Technical Operations consists of Finnair Technical Services and Operational Maintenance.\r\n\r\nWe are now looking for enthusiastic and skilled\r\n\r\nAIRCRAFT MECHANICS\r\n\r\nto be a part of our new A350 fleet phase and support Finnair's growth. As an Aircraft Mechanic you will perform maintenance work in accordance with instructions provided by your supervisor. We are looking for employees who have completed Part-66 basic training including B1 or B2 modules, but also for some Sheet Metal Aircraft Mechanics, who have not necessarily completed B1/B2 modules but are capable of working also as aircraft mechanics. In both positions work is done in shifts so willingness to shift work is essential.\r\n\r\nMain responsibilities:\r\n- Perform the maintenance work provided by Supervisor\r\n- Ensure high quality and good turn-around time performance on maintenance work packages and tasks provided\r\n- Perform other tasks ordered by the management\r\n\r\nKey competencies:\r\n- Completed Aircraft mechanic Part-66 basic training including B1/B2 EASA modules\r\n- Good English and Finnish skills\r\n- Punctuality and accuracy\r\n- Ability and willingness to learn and develop\r\n\r\nWe encourage you to leave your application as soon as possible at www.finnair.com/jobs, as first selections will begin immediately. We plan on continuing the selections during fall 2017 and the upcoming years, on a need basis. We recommend you to follow your email frequently after submitting the application (please also check spam/clutter folder as sometimes emails are filtered there). By leaving your application, you will automatically be considered in the future selections, as your application stays valid until you yourself wish to withdraw your open application.\r\n\r\nWe are primarily looking to hire for permanent employment, but we might also have a need for fixed-term employment, e.g. for seasonal work. \r\n\r\nSelection process will consist of several steps, including online assignments and face-to-face interviews. \r\n\r\nUnfortunately, we are not able to answer inquiries by phone but we are happy to answer any questions about this job via jobs@finnair.com.",
