				"kuvausteksti" : "Enersense International Oy provides its customers with resourcing solutions which appreciate the fluctuations in their projects. Our company is an ISO 9001:2008/14001:2004-certified actor with more than ten years of experience in operating in close cooperation with large-scale nuclear and construction sites, the Olkiluoto 3 nuclear power plant site being the largest of them. \r\n\r\nWe are looking for Piping Supervisor for our client in Novodvinsk, Russia.\r\n\r\nTasks and responsibilities:\r\n\r\n- Responsible for piping installation schedule and ensuring completion of scheduled work on time and within budget\r\n- Assisting installation team when required\r\n- Planning and performing of the preparation work for the specific contractor under consideration of the engineering input, availability of stored materials in our client's scope\r\n- Supervision and follow up of the contractor's execution of piping works\r\n- Review and closure of execution documentation in coordination with the method team and final documentation team\r\n- Ensure that the piping works on site are performed according to the contractual standards \r\n- Check that human resources and equipment are mobilized by the subcontractors according to plans\r\n- Check that the subcontractors are using the right technical documentation\r\n- During take-over operations, check that piping works have been completed according to schedule and quality requirements\r\n- Supervise the erection and installation work of clients employees and subcontractors. \r\n- Assure that the subcontractors comply with agreed contracts. \r\n- Assure that the subcontractors comply with the End Client's and Client's HSE (Health, Safety and Environmental) rules, as well as with local requirements in the country of the site.\r\n- Approve technical and commercial change orders requested by the subcontractors, within the limits set by the Site Manager. \r\n- Ensuring effectiveness and quality of erection and installation work \r\n- Preparation of erection and installation work, defining and reserving needed manpower and resources \r\n- Ensuring the safety of erection and installation work in own responsibility area \r\n- Supervision of right timing of erection and installation work \r\n- Coordinating material sending and receiving together with the shipping department and Construction Planning Engineer\r\n- Daily, weekly and monthly reporting of erection and installation work progress to the Site Manager \r\n- Compile quality documentation \r\n- Compile acceptance certificates contractor/client and client/the End Client (lifts, elevators, HVAC etc.)\r\n- COR/NCR settlement with contractors and Customer\r\n\r\nRequirements:\r\n\r\n- Civil Engineer, Mechanical Engineer or Architect with at least a year of professional work experience\r\n- Must have leadership skills to direct labor resources including installers and subcontractors\r\n- Must have organizational skills to take a project from the design stage and see it through to completion\r\n- Excellent communication, listening and presentation skills\r\n- Good knowledge of piping, equipment insulation and mechanical works\r\n\r\nSkills required:\r\n\r\n- Result oriented in particular with respect to Safety, Quality, Cost and Schedule (On Time Delivery - OTD)\r\n- Organizational and planning ability to prepare the execution works of the contractors\r\n- Assertiveness in front of the contractors\r\n- Ability to analyse, optimize and improve the performance of works\r\n- Ability to work in a team with good human relationship and team spirit\r\n- Good knowledge of site erection and installation work and/or suitable education/experience\r\n- Minimum 2 years of experience as Site Supervisor on boiler, evaporation or similar process plant \r\n- Has good understanding of contractual issues \r\n- Has proved to have capabilities to adopt skills outside his/her discipline\r\n- Has good knowledge of Site Reporting Tools\r\n\r\nLanguages:\r\n\r\n- Good knowledge of English\r\n- Russian language skills are beneficial\r\n\r\nThe post will be filled as soon as a suitable applicant is found.",
