				"kuvausteksti" : "We are looking for a \r\n\r\nLaboratory  Manager; Porvoo\r\n\r\nAs Laboratory Manager you lead our Laboratory Services department. In your team you have approximately 60 employees (laboratorians, chemists, engineers).\r\n\r\nIn this role you are responsible for ensuring laboratory services for all Borealis production units  (polyolefin plants, petrochemicals plants) in Porvoo and also supporting research and product development activities in line with the KPIs (Key performance Indicators) and high HSE (Health, Safety and Environment) standards. \r\n\r\nYou are responsible for the planning and follow up of the projects and investments of your department in close co-operation with the laboratory team.\r\n\r\nKnowledge, skills and experience required:\r\n\r\nMaster's degree or equivalent through experience from laboratory work.\r\nAt least 10 years' experience in a similar role or other relevant experience\r\nMastery of Finnish language and of English at business level.\r\nUnderstanding of the petrochemical industry, suppliers and customers\r\nRecognised for having excellent people skills, coaching and feedback, adjusting when necessary and creating a winning team culture.\r\nRecognised for being dialogue engaging, inspiring, motivating and setting direction for others within a multicultural environment\r\nDriver/Challenger\r\n\r\n \r\nWe offer you an international working environment with emphasis on competence, innovation and working together. \r\n\r\nStartdate: November/December 2017\r\nThis is a permanent position.\r\n \r\n\r\nFor more detailed information please contact Porvoo Location leader Salla Roni-Poranen, +358503794080.\r\n\r\nIf you are interested in this role and meet most of the above criteria, please send your application and CV latest 12.11.2017\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nBorealis is a leading provider of innovative solutions in the fields of polyolefins, base chemicals and fertilisers. The company is headquartered in Vienna, Austria, and operates in over 120 countries with around 6,600 employees worldwide, generating EUR 7.2 billion in sales revenue in 2016",
