				"kuvausteksti" : "In keeping with our brand promise \"Engineering with a difference\", Etteplan takes a different attitude to embedded system and IoT solutions - something our customers confirm time and time again. We are proud of our expertise and our ability to impact our customers' success. \r\n\r\n\r\nYour expertise matters to us - come join our success story!\r\n\r\n\r\nWe are looking for talents with experience in C# and embedded systems to join our team in Espoo. Working in other Etteplan offices in the capital area is also possible. In this position you will be responsible for the full understanding of the technical architecture and working as an interface between local and international software maintenance teams.\r\n \r\nWe appreciate experience or knowledge in the following:\r\n\r\n- Technical architecture design  \r\n- Visual Studio  \r\n- .NET libraries  \r\n- Script programming skills\r\n\r\n\r\nWe wish you to have a degree in electrical engineering, information technology, computer science or similar applicable area. In an international company fluent written and spoken English skills are required as well as excellent communication skills. Written and spoken Finnish skills are valued, too.\r\n \r\n\r\nEtteplan offers variety of interesting Embedded and IoT projects to work with. This is a great chance to evolve and develop your skills to the direction that supports you in your future career path. Wide range of experts and highly experienced professionals help you in learning and support your daily tasks. Above all, you get a chance to feel professional pride in job well done.\r\n \r\n\r\nIf you are a real team player with customer-oriented approach, send your application and CV soon. We will go through the candidates already during the application period.\r\n\r\n\r\nEtteplan is Finland's biggest employer in industrial engineering, technical product information, embedded systems and IoT solutions. We offer a vantage point to international industry, serving top players in their specific fields of expertise. With Etteplan you will gain a deeper insight into their products.\r\n\r\n\r\nWe are a genuine engineering house: our Group employs around 2,800 experts mainly in Finland, Sweden, the Netherlands, Germany, Poland and China - most of them engineers. Our success is based on our competence and our knowledgeable staff, both of which we take good care of. \r\n\r\n\r\nEtteplan offers interesting and challenging tasks in a growing working community in 30 locations around Finland. The work involved in customers' varied and demanding projects means constant learning and development.",
