				"etatyo" : false,
				"kuvausteksti" : "Are you a newly graduated mechanical engineer and you have experience of 3D-modelling or mechanical design? We are looking for a person, who has the ability to run multiple tasks simultaneously and take care of various stakeholders. This is a great chance for person who is curious and enthusiastic learner. You will work in a big, international company at Hyvinkää.\r\n\r\nABOUT THE ROLE\r\n\r\nAcademic Work is looking for a fulltime Mechanical Engineer for our client in Hyvinkää.\r\n\r\nThis job is a staffing position, which means that you will be employed by Academic Work and work as a consultant at our client company.\r\n\r\nJOB DUTIES\r\n\r\nOur client is a leading company in their field. They offer production, maintenance and development for their products and solutions. In this position you will be part of a team, which manages mechanical component changes before they are taken into the production.\r\n\r\nThe job will be project-based, you will have multiple project going forward simultaneously and one project can take a year or two. When new mechanical part or component is decided to take in to the production you will manage the process.\r\n\r\nYour tasks include:\r\n\r\n3D-modelling and mechanical design for component\r\nTest new component and set needed quality standards together with quality control\r\nFind suppliers together with sourcing\r\nManage how components are ordered, when and where from and how they are delivered\r\nCheck quality and project results on site if needed\r\nIn the job you will be communicating daily in English in the company as well as internationally with the other teams. Many of the skills needed in the positions will be learned by doing the job as the work tasks are highly versatile. This job offers a great opportunity for a newly graduated Young Professional who already has some relevant work experience: You get to work with experts who are best at what they do.\r\n\r\nWE ARE LOOKING FOR\r\n\r\nWe are looking for a person who has the ability to run multiple tasks simultaneously and take care of various stakeholders. You are not afraid to ask lot of questions. You need to be able to tolerate uncertainty in a challenging international environment, since you learn by doing. Our ideal candidate is a newly-graduated mechanical engineer. To succeed in the job, you need to have some earlier experience with 3D-modeling or mechanical designing. In this position you need to be able to work great in a team as well as independently. The job requires fluent written and spoken English skills.\r\n\r\nApply for this position if you have:\r\n\r\n- Relevant educational background (eg. Bachelor of Mechanical Engineering or Mechanics Design)\r\n- 3D modeling or mechanical design experience\r\n- Social and daring personality\r\n- Fluent written and spoken English skills\r\n\r\nIt is also seen as an advantage if you have skills in PTC Creo.\r\n\r\nStart: January 2018\r\n\r\nWorking hours: Fulltime\r\n\r\nEmployment period: at least 12 months, great potential for extension\r\n\r\nLocation: Hyvinkää\r\n\r\nSalary: According to agreement\r\n\r\nPublished: 17.10.2017\r\n\r\nIn this position you will be employed by Academic Work and we take care of all the legal responsibilities of an employer such as salary payments, insurances and health care. It is important for us that you feel well and perform in your job. Your consultant manager will be in regular contact with you during the assignment and guides you on your career. Academic Work is an authorized staffing and recruitment agency and our employees are extremely satisfied, something that we are very proud of. We are here to help you succeed!\r\n\r\nINFORMATION ON THE APPLICATION PROCESS\r\n\r\nTo apply for the job click on \"Apply here\" below. Remember to attach your CV into your application! We only handle applications through our website but if you have questions about the position you can reach us via email in hel01@academicwork.fi. Please write the advert ID in the subject and paste the advert link in the mail. We are continuously screening and contacting candidates so make sure to send your application as soon as possible. Please notice that the advert can be removed before eventual last dates on our external advertising pages. When the advert is being removed it's either due to that the processes is finished or because we have many qualified applications and are continuing in the selection/interview phase.\r\n\r\nWe are the Home of the Young Professionals. We are experts in recruitment and staffing university students, recently graduated and professionals in the beginning of their career. You can be employed by us as a consultant in one of our client companies or be recruited directly to our client via our recruitment co-operation. You can read more about us at www.academicwork.fi.\r\n\r\nWhen employed at Academic Work you will have your own dedicated Consultant Manager, whose role is to answer your questions, support your career development and ensure you enjoy your place of work.\r\n\r\nINFORMATION ABOUT THE COMPANY\r\n\r\nOur Hyvinkää based client is one of the leading companies in their industry. They offer whole solutions from production to maintenance and modernization services.",
