				"kuvausteksti" : "Pöyry is an international consulting and engineering company.  We deliver smart solutions across power generation, transmission & distribution, forest industry, chemicals & biorefining, mining & metals, transportation, environment and water. Pöyry's net sales in 2016 were EUR 530 million. The company's shares are quoted on Nasdaq Helsinki (POY1V). Approximately 5500 experts. 40 countries. 130 offices.\r\n\r\nFor more than 50 years, Pöyry has been successfully executing projects for a large industrial customer base all over the world. We are a world leader in forest industry consulting and engineering and have been a trusted partner for many clients for decades. We provide local presence with global competences. This helps us optimise our operations for our clients' benefit and enables quick support at the plant whenever needed.\r\n\r\nPöyry Industry Business Group is now looking for a\r\n\r\nTECHNOLOGY MANAGER, FOOD INDUSTRY\r\n\r\nto enforce our team in Vantaa, Finland. \r\n\r\nThe role of the Technology Manager is to participate in Client's investment projects as a project manager in early project phases as well as senior adviser in following project phases. The position will have a vital role in coordinating the other engineering disciplines in an investment project as well as in supporting sales.\r\n\r\nWe are looking to find the following characteristics in our Technology Manager\r\n\r\n- Master's degree in relevant field, such as bioprocess engineering \r\n- +10 years of relevant work experience in food industry, either in design or operation\r\n- Deep understanding of the technical requirements in food applications\r\n- Fluent in Finnish and good communication skills in English, other language skills are considered as a merit\r\n- Excellent interpersonal and communication skills\r\n- Readiness to travel\r\n- As a person you are safety focused, persistent, goal and client oriented, as well as a dynamic team player.\r\n\r\nWe offer you a variety of interesting tasks and good opportunities for professional growth in a stimulating global environment with pleasant co-workers and team's full support. \r\n\r\nTo learn more about this position please contact Ilkka Rantanen, tel. 040 528 7762.\r\n \r\nInterested? Please submit your CV and cover letter with salary request by November 15, 2017 on our website: http://www.poyry.fi/ura-poyrylla",
