				"kuvausteksti" : "Stora Enso is a leading provider of renewable solutions in packaging, biomaterials, wooden constructions and paper on global markets. Our aim is to replace fossil based materials by innovating and developing new products and services based on wood and other renewable materials. We employ some 25 000 employees in more than 35 countries, and our sales in 2016 were EUR 9.8 billion. Stora Enso shares are listed on the Helsinki and Stockholm stock exchanges. \r\n\r\nPaper division provides best-in-class paper solutions for print media and office use. The wide selection covers papers made from recycled and fresh wood fibre. Our main customer groups include publishers, retailers, printing houses, merchants, converters and office suppliers. Our mills are located predominantly in Europe, and in China. Three of the mills produce paper based on 100%-recycled fibre.\r\n\r\nDescription \r\n\r\nStora Enso Paper is now looking for a Digital Marketing Manager.\r\n\r\nMain responsibilities include: \r\n\r\nMaintenance, development and analytics of Paper online channels \r\nPlanning and execution of digital marketing campaigns using marketing automation tools\r\nCreating graphic designs & presentations  \r\nPreparing and assisting in the production of artwork for ads\r\nManaging content in digital sales tools\r\nProviding sample service support\r\nAssisting in day-to-day marketing tasks\r\n\r\nRequirements \r\n\r\nWe would expect you to have:\r\n\r\nBA or Masters degree in Business Administration, marketing, economics, engineering, or other relevant areas\r\nExcellent knowledge of design software: InDesign, PhotoShop and MS Office systems\r\nExperience in working with marketing automation tools \r\nProven track record from working in the field of b to b/c marketing \r\nExperience of working with advertising agencies and other sub-contractors\r\nFluent in spoken and written English, additional language skills are considered a merit\r\nEnergetic, proactive, responsible, open, flexible and hands on attitude, team worker\r\n\r\nPosition is reporting to Katariina Tanner, VP, Marketing.\r\n\r\nLocation to be agreed, one where Stora Enso Paper has presence.",
