				"kuvausteksti" : "Studentwork is looking for an English-speaking Software Developer for Financial Trading IT team to work for our client company. \r\n\r\nYour work space is located in Financial Trading department where traders analyze derivative markets of energy and fuels and make trades in various exchanges. This is an extremely rare environment to work in and an extraordinary possibility for a recent graduate to show his/her talent. If you are excited as you should be, keep on reading!\r\n\r\nThis role is a combination of software development and data science, focusing more on software development. You will have a wide range of tasks and use different sources of information to visualize and analyse the information to help the financial traders. The role provides you with experience in multiple technologies. \r\n\r\nYou are not expected to be a developer-guru already, but you must have proven track record with hands-on skills in software development. We are looking for a person with right profile to fit in the team and of course you will get full support from your Manager and colleagues. You are fluent in English - Finnish/Swedish are seen as a plus.\r\n\r\nWe hope that you have experience in some of the following technologies: R, Matlab, .NET, C++, Qlik Sense and/or Visual Basic. You are also familiar with SQL.\r\n\r\nWe don't expect you to be familiar with all the technologies above - we value attitude over experience! By attitude we mean learning-orientation and self-leadership - curiosity over the new technologies and drive to learn. Hence, you can be in the beginning of your career but, however, we hope that you have some experience working in IT.\r\n\r\nThe position is full-time for 12 months via Studentwork. For a person who shows their talent there are good chances for a permanent position. Companies office is located in Espoo.\r\n\r\nGot interested? Please send us your CV and an application (with a salary request) via the link below which describes why you are the best candidate for the position. The position will be filled as soon as a suitable candidate is found.\r\n\r\nFor further information you can contact Consultant Manager Marjukka Laakso ( +358 50 573 2425).\r\n\r\nOur story\r\n\r\nStudentwork is a leading Nordic recruitment and staffing company specialised in rising and experienced graduates. Our view of the business is revolutionary, putting online assessments in the center of every assignment. This is so we can spot the best, minimise on-boarding and recruitment time, and secure cultural and motivational fit between graduates and companies. In fact, our goal is to have the most satisfied customers - one candidate, one employee and one recruitment at a time.",
