				"kuvausteksti" : "Cloud Value Tree Oy\r\nWe are young start-up company, established at spring this year, working on IT and business process development, cloud technologies, data warehousing, reporting & planning and related services providing content expertise and development. We have both global and small / medium size companies as customers. We are having strong growth on our services, and we more skilled people working on our innovative environment.\r\n\r\nPosition\r\nCloud Architect\r\nWe are looking for full time, 37,5 hours per week, permanent role for existing customer. Work is going to be at Finland capital area Helsinki, Espoo, Vantaa primary at customer premises.\r\nJob Description\r\nWe are looking for a passionate Cloud Solution Architect to be based in Espoo/Helsinki, Finland.   Cloud Solution Architects are pre-sales engineering professionals that are responsible for driving end-to-end IoT solution creation and deployment, powered by both Microsoft/Amazon and 3rd-party / open-source technologies.   Cloud Solution Architects are trusted technology advisors that build deep relationships with our partners and that significantly influence partner innovation, strategy and adoption of Microsoft technologies.   They are responsible for all aspects of the solutions engagement, including architectural design sessions, driving proof of value / proof of concept and the driving final project engagements.\r\n \r\nResponsibilities\r\nSelecting features, building, delivering, and managing Cloud IaaS environments using IaaS platforms, including AWS, Azure and google\r\nConducting proof-of-concept, developing prototyping, and building reference models\r\nProvide directions to data integration, relational databases, and SQL cloud choices\r\nEnhancing data collection procedures to include information that is relevant for building analytic systems\r\nKnowledge of development methodologies and more than one of the following languages: Java, .NET Csharp, PHP, and JavaScript\r\nAbility to display a demonstrated track record in building and setting architecture strategies\r\nStreamline and focus on full automation and build secure systems.\r\n\r\nSkills and Qualifications\r\nBA or BS degree in Computer Science, Computer Engineering, Information Systems, or Systems Engineering preferred; MA or MS degree a plus \r\nExperience with building and delivering Single Sign On (SSO) solutions using SAML, LDAP, and related technologies\r\nAmazon/Azure/Google Certified Solutions Architect, Associate, or MCSD Azure Solutions Architect Certification\r\nExperience with implementing Web services, including SOAP and RESTful\r\nExperience with common data science toolkits, such as R, google analytics and cloud based tools\r\nGreat communication skills\r\nExperience with data visualization and all data services in one of Azure/Amazon/Google Offerings\r\nProficiency in using query languages such as machine learning, SQL, Hive, Pig \r\nExperience with NoSQL databases, such as MongoDB, Cassandra, HBase will be added advantage\r\nData-oriented personality\r\nAll our solutions will be on cloud, so understanding and working experience in cloud is must have skill.\r\n\r\nApplications\r\nPlease, send your application, CV and possible salary wish to mika.pehkonenatcloudvaluetree.com no later than 15.11.2017. On the same e-mail address, you may ask more information of the position.",
