				"kuvausteksti" : "Ponsse is a pioneering developer of mechanical timber harvesting based on the cut-to-length method. At Ponsse we put customers always first and we aim to be the preferred partner in our industry. At Ponsse fairness, responsibility and freedom go hand in hand. Are you interested in working in one of the world s premier companies?\r\n\r\nFounded in 1970 by forestry machinery entrepreneur Einari Vidgrén, Ponsse continues to be a forerunner of timber harvesting solutions based on the cut-to-length method. With experience of designing and building over 12,000 forest machines, this family company is one of the world s leading forest machine manufacturers. The Ponsse group has 12 subsidiaries and 32 dealers around the world, and employs around 1,500 people.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nWe are looking for an\r\nApplication Engineer, Matlab/Simulink\r\nto join our new R&amp;D unit in Tampere\r\n\r\nIn your work, you will develop and test the control systems of forest machines using modern tools. The central content of your work will be the design of forest machine control applications as a member of a model-based SCRUM development team in a Matlab/Simulink environment, as well as the integration of the implemented models to an existing machine control system. You can test the results of your work in a modern test environment for forest machines and in an authentic work environment in cooperation with testing professionals. You will become a member of a model-based design team and work in close cooperation with different R&amp;D departments.\r\n\r\nYour required profile:\r\n\r\n     a degree of Master of Science (Technology) or Bachelor of Engineering\r\n\r\n     knowledge of control and measurement technology\r\n\r\n     knowledge of the Matlab/Simulink tools\r\n\r\n     an independent and enthusiastic attitude to work and willingness to develop your skills\r\n\r\n     good cooperation and interaction skills\r\n\r\n     fluent spoken and written English\r\n\r\n                      The following are considered an advantage:\r\n\r\n     C/C++ programming skills\r\n\r\n     knowledge of embedded microcontrollers\r\n\r\n     knowledge of agile development methods (SCRUM)\r\n\r\n     knowledge of electronics\r\n\r\nWe offer an interesting and challenging position in R&amp;D for forest machines, as well as the support of a highly skilled organisation, in a development-friendly and comfortable working environment in the joint R&amp;D unit of Ponsse and Epec at Tampere University of Technology s Kampusareena.\r\nFurther information: For further information on the position, please contact Team Leader Antti Mikkonen, antti.mikkonen@ponsse.com or tel. +358 40 8230 250.",
