				"kuvausteksti" : "As the world's leader in serving science, Thermo Fisher Scientific is a driving force in the research, healthcare, industrial and applied markets, generating more than USD 20 billion in annual revenue. No other company can match our range of customer touch points - technologically, geographically or commercially. We help our customers in finding cures for cancer, protecting the environment, making sure our food is safe and moving forward with thousands of important projects that improve millions of lives. At Thermo Fisher Scientific, each one of our 65,000 extraordinary minds has a unique story to tell. Join us and contribute to our singular mission - enabling our customers to make the world healthier, cleaner and safer.\r\n\r\nIn Finland we have over 800 employees in Vantaa and Joensuu. We employ experts in several different functions such as production, instrument and reagent manufacturing, R&D, marketing, sales, quality, support functions and supply chain. We hire experts in different engineering fields, chemistry, microbiology and bioinformatics. Vantaa site is located close to the Vantaankoski railway station. Our extensive range of products developed and manufactured in Finland includes pipettes, microplate instruments, magnetic particle processing systems as well as clinical chemistry and industrial chemistry analyzers, laboratory automation solutions and food safety kits.\r\n\r\nPlease find more information on www.thermofisher.com\r\n\r\n\r\nSenior Software Architect\r\nVantaa, Finland\r\n\r\n\r\nWhat story will YOU tell? Yes, YOU.\r\nWe are always looking for great people and we can't do our new Senior Software Architect opening justice on one page so please visit jobs.thermofisher.com or www.thermofisher.com to find out about Our Mission, Our Stories and discover where We are going.\r\n\r\nWe are currently recruiting a Senior Software Architect to join our R&D Software team in Vantaa to work with world renowned Clinical and Industrial Analyzers and Automation Systems to enable our customers to make the world healthier, cleaner and safer. The team consists of around 20 software engineers and you will also be working with different cross-functional stakeholders like project managers, product managers, scientists as well as hardware, usability, verification and validation engineers.\r\n\r\n\r\nWhat you will be responsible for:\r\nDefine a common technical and architectural vision for the System(s)/Solution(s) under development\r\nDrive alignment of the development teams on common technological and architectural vision\r\nCollaborate with other professionals to define the higher-level Functional and Nonfunctional Requirements\r\nValidate technology assumptions, identify and evaluate technical alternatives and make technical trade-offs\r\nLead definition of the system, subsystems as well as the interfaces and collaboration between them\r\nSupervise and foster Built-in Quality through adoption of practices like Continuous Integration, Test Driven Development (TDD), Refactoring, Pair work, Automated acceptance testing\r\nProvide technical mentoring and advice to other engineers/colleagues\r\nTrain team members in design related disciplines like Object Oriented Design Principles and Patterns\r\n\r\n\r\nWhat we are looking for:\r\n\r\nTechnical:\r\nMinimum 5 years proven track record of designing and building highly scalable, maintainable, secure and robust software\r\nUnderstanding of Object Oriented Design Principles and Patterns\r\nWorking experience with both Application and Embedded Software development\r\nExcellent knowledge of UML and other modeling methods\r\nWorking experience with Agile development practices (Scrum, Kanban)\r\nExperience with software development lifecycle (SDLC) processes\r\n\r\nCommunication and drive:\r\nFluent in English, both verbal and written\r\nExcellent inter-personal and communication skills with all global stakeholders\r\nAbility to convey very complex information in both written and oral form to both non-technical and deeply technical audiences\r\nPassion towards continuous improvement, high quality and willingness to own and be accountable for design decisions\r\nAnalytical thinker and problem solver. Able to resolve complex problems independently\r\nAbility to drive results and make necessary trade-offs effectively for multiple projects and tasks simultaneously\r\n\r\nQualifications:\r\nM.Sc. Degree in software engineering, computer science or information technology.\r\n\r\n\r\nThese will impress us even more:\r\nExperience with IVD regulations\r\nStrong knowledge and experience of C#/.NET, C++, C, cloud technologies and platforms like AWS and/or Azure as well as both Windows and Linux software development experience\r\nExperience with scaling Agile practices across all levels of the organization\r\nWorking knowledge of Test Automation frameworks like Robot Framework\r\nKnowledge of Behavioral Driven Development and tools (BDD)\r\nWide understanding on generic verification/validation processes and procedures\r\n\r\n\r\nWe look forward to receiving your application, including a cover letter, CV and a salary request in English. Please apply via http://jobs.thermofisher.com/. Candidates will be reviewed during the process. Please apply by 12th of November 2017. Ref: 55710BR.\r\n\r\nShould you have questions about Thermo Fisher Scientific and/or the position, feel free to contact Horia Biro, Senior Manager - SW Engineering, by calling +358 408516993 on Monday, 30th of October, between 3pm and 4pm as well as Thursday, 2nd of November, between 1pm and 2pm.\r\n\r\n\r\nAt Thermo Fisher Scientific, each one of our 50,000 extraordinary minds has a unique story to tell. Join us and contribute to our singular mission - enabling our customers to make the world healthier, cleaner and safer.\r\n\r\nThermo Fisher Scientific is an EEO/Affirmative Action Employer and does not discriminate on the basis of race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, protected veteran status, disability or any other legally protected status.",
