				"kuvausteksti" : "Ponsse is a pioneering developer of mechanical timber harvesting based on the cut-to-length method. At Ponsse we put customers always first and we aim to be the preferred partner in our industry. At Ponsse fairness, responsibility and freedom go hand in hand. Are you interested in working in one of the world s premier companies?\r\n\r\nFounded in 1970 by forestry machinery entrepreneur Einari Vidgrén, Ponsse continues to be a forerunner of timber harvesting solutions based on the cut-to-length method. With experience of designing and building over 12,000 forest machines, this family company is one of the world s leading forest machine manufacturers. The Ponsse group has 12 subsidiaries and 32 dealers around the world, and employs around 1,500 people.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nWe are looking for a committed\r\n\r\nCompliance Engineer\r\n\r\nto join our R&amp;D in Vieremä, Kajaani or Tampere office\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nYou will work as a member of R&amp;D team and participate in ensuring the safety and compliance of PONSSE products delivered to the global market. Your job description will include following of the relevant standards, directives and market-specific requirements and interpreting them into technical specifications. In cooperation with different R&amp;D units and network of partners you will support R&amp;D projects in ensuring that new products and services comply with applicable requirements. Your role covers tasks from the definition phase and preliminary planning to the verification of finished complete product and its approval by the authorities. You will be in contact with authorities responsible for the technical requirements in the industry worldwide and be responsible for the development of definition, approval and certification processes. You are also participating in the international standardization work.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nYour required profile:\r\n\r\n     applicable education in the technical field, e.g. Master of Science or Bachelor of Engineering\r\n\r\n     strong skills in spoken and written English\r\n\r\n     self-reliant and diligent approach to work and willingness to develop your skills\r\n\r\n     good cooperation and interaction skills\r\n\r\n     consistent project work skills\r\n\r\n     some willingness to travel\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nThe following are considered as an advantage:\r\n\r\n     previous experience in specialist tasks in R&amp;D\r\n\r\n     knowledge of the power generation, transmission, automation, control and adjustment systems of modern mobile work machines\r\n\r\n     knowledge of the general safety of machinery and the functional safety of embedded control systems\r\n\r\n     experience in the interpretation of standards and directives and participation in their development\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nWe offer an interesting, challenging and responsible position in the field of machine safety and compliance, as well as the support of a highly skilled organisation, in a development-friendly and comfortable working environment at the Ponsse factory in Vieremä, our office in Kajaani or the joint R&amp;D unit of Ponsse and Epec at Tampere University of Technology s Kampusareena in Tampere, upon your choosing.\r\n\r\nFurther information:             \r\n\r\nFor more information on the position, please contact R&amp;D Manager Kalle Einola, kalle.einola@ponsse.com or tel. +358 40 514 3994. \r\n\r\nApplications:  \r\n\r\nPlease apply for the position by 31 December 2017 at www.ponsse.com/tyopaikat. We will fill in the position as soon as the right candidate is found.",
