				"kuvausteksti" : "ALTEN, the European leader in engineering and technology consulting, provides support for its clients' development strategies in the fields of innovation, R&D and it systems. ALTEN is active in 21 countries, covers the whole development cycle and offers a choice of service levels, from technology consulting to full-blown project outsourcing. It is the technology partner of choice for Europe's leading companies. \r\n\r\nALTEN Finland employs 400 people in 8 different locations in Espoo, Hyvinkää, Hämeenlinna, Lahti, Paimio, Tampere, Raahe and Oulu. \r\n\r\n\r\nWe are now looking for a driven\r\n \r\n\r\nTECHNICAL WRITER\r\n\r\n\r\nto join our team in our Lahti office. \r\n \r\n\r\n\r\nYou will work with several projects with our partners and create content to the technical documents for different target groups. You will also have the opportunity to participate in our customers' documentation development projects. \r\n\r\nWe offer you a challenging position where you will have the ability to work in an inspiring and friendly working environment as well as find opportunities for personal development. We are looking for a highly motivated person with a can-do attitude. \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nIn order to succeed in this position you will benefit of having:\r\n\r\n- A suitable educational background (M.A., M.Sc. or B.Sc. degree)\r\n- Experience in technical writing\r\n- Excellent communication skills in Finnish and English, both verbally and in writing\r\n- Good co-operational skills and willingness to work with clients\r\n- A structured and independent approach to completing your assignments and ability to understand and control large technical entities\r\n\r\n\r\nWe also value:\r\n\r\n- Experience in structural XML based documentation\r\n- Experience in Simplified Technical English (STE) content creation\r\n- Additional spoken and written languages\r\n\r\n\r\nFor additional information, please contact Experienced Business Manager Hanna-Riitta Vesa, tel. +358 50 385 1792. \r\n\r\nIf you are interested in this position, please send your application and salary expectation by November 13th, 2017 via the link below.  \r\n\r\nWe are looking forward to receive your application!",
