				"kuvausteksti" : "Nipromec Oy Ltd is a global consulting and engineering company operating in energy-, industry- and offshore fields. \r\n\r\nWe are now looking for a CTT Planner for a project in Olkiluoto. Work starts on 01.11.2017 and es-timated duration 11 months.\r\n\r\nTasks:\r\n-Plan and prepare field activities for temporary modifications (electromechanical) and their restoration after use (specifically related to the containment tightness test-CTT).\r\n-Check and prepare dismantling, transport routes, and temporary storage locations and requirements.\r\n-Issue procedures, drawings and instructions including required spare parts related to temporary modifications / final installation.\r\n-Identify, coordinate and other external resources to perform the CTT.\r\n-To respect the requirements of TS (technical specifications).\r\n-Review maintenance work reports.\r\n-Ensuring the application safety, security and environmental standards, guidelines and rules.\r\n\r\nGeneral and technical background expected:\r\n-At least 3 years of experience as maintenance planner for mechanical works, mechanical engineering, or experience as field supervisor/technician. Exposure to facets of plant operation, maintenance outages, preparation coordination and field supervision of planned work and permit to work implementation.\r\n-Experience in procedure and instructions writing (required for creating maintenance instructions).\r\n-Fluent English both written and spoken required. Ability with French, German or Finnish is a plus.\r\n\r\nSkills required:\r\n-Engineering degree/diploma with an emphasis on mechanical engineering (or similar) or experienced technician with and mechanical or elechtromechanical background.\r\n-Understanding of technical documentation for power plant components.\r\n-Maintenance/mechanical works.\r\n-procedure/instruction compliance.\r\n-Good communicator and coordinator.\r\n\r\nSkills favorable:\r\n-Several years of specialist work experience.\r\n-In-depth knowledge of nuclear plant operations, maintenance, and/or procedural planning.\r\n-Knowledge of power plant, system and process engineering.\r\n-Knowledge of commissioning procedures and organization.\r\n\r\nPosition is filled as soon as suitable candidate is found. To apply please send application and CV with salary request to info@n-pro.fi . For any further information, you might require please go to www.nipromec.com",
