				"kuvausteksti" : "Our client NPAC, owner of the world's leading producer of high-performance cores and board (Corenso), and packaging-solutions (Powerflute) is looking for an experienced IT system administrator to ensure the smooth IT operations of their Finnish region. Would you like to work in an international team with cutting edge tools in a company where IT is an investment, not a cost center? If you have experience in IT system administration, will to develop processes, and motivation to grow your expertise further in an international environment this might be the job for you.\r\n\r\nABOUT THE ROLE\r\n\r\nAcademic Work is looking for a Regional IT System Administrator for our client NPAC (Nordic Packaging and Container). NPAC is the owner of Corenso and Powerflute and in this position you will work with the IT infrastructure for both Corenso and Powerflute.\r\n\r\nYou will be recruited to our client company. Academic Work will take care of the recruitment process, therefore candidates are kindly asked to direct all questions to Academic Work hel03@academicwork.fi.\r\n\r\nJOB DUTIES\r\n\r\nIn this role you are coordinating the work of 2 system administrators located in Finland. Your job is to ensure the smooth running of the regions IT systems and together with your team you will make sure the system hardware, operating systems, software systems, and related procedures adhere to organizational standards across the region. You will also design solutions for various project and operational needs regionally and globally, and research and recommend new innovative automative system administration processes. Occasionally you will also support users on their local site in the absence of a permanent local system administrator.\r\n\r\nThe job includes:\r\n\r\nCoordinating the work of 2 local IT Administrators in Finland\r\nEnsuring smooth running of the regions IT systems (Linux, Windows, ESX hypervisor and other)\r\nDesigning solutions for various project and operational needs regionally and globally\r\nSupporting users on their local site in the absence of a permanent local system administrator, mostly in Finland but occasionally abroad as well\r\nResearch and recommend new innovative system administration processes.\r\nCorenso offers a great opportunity to join their international, relaxed and fun team of IT professionals. This is a new role in Finland and you will report directly to the Group IT Infrastructure Manager based in UK.\r\n\r\nWE ARE LOOKING FOR\r\n\r\nOur ideal candidate has a bachelor (or master's) degree in engineering or computer science and experience in general system administration including Windows server 2008+, Windows 7, DHCP, DNS and Exchange. You have also worked with VMWare ESX before and you have experience in network support and troubleshooting. You are good with customers, able to manage your time efficiently and you speak fluently both English and Finnish.\r\n\r\nApply for this position if you have:\r\n\r\n-A bachelor or master's degree in engineering or computer science\r\n-Experience in general system administration including Windows, Linux DHCP, DNS, -Terminal Services and Exchange\r\n-Experience in VMWare ESX (4 or onwards)\r\n-Good customer service and time management skills\r\n-Fluent English and Finnish language skills\r\n-Ability/willingness to travel approximately once a month (in Finland and abroad occasionally)\r\n\r\nIt is also seen as an advantage if you have previous experience of leading a small team of IT administrators or support staff. Technical skills are important but what Corenso is really looking for is the right personality: self-starter, good with people and someone who fits well with their team. So, please send your CV the soonest so we can discuss this opportunity further with you.\r\n\r\nTo apply for the job you need to register on our website and then click on \"Apply here\". Remember to attach your CV into your application! We only process applications through our website but if you have questions about the position you can reach us via email in helo03@academicwork.fi. Please write the advert ID in the subject field and paste the advert link in the mail. We are continuously screening and contacting candidates so make sure to send your application as soon as possible. Please note that the advert can be removed prior to the last application dates on our external advertising pages. In the event the advert has been removed it is either due to the process being completed or because we have a sufficient number of qualified applications and are proceeding to the selection/interview phase in the process.\r\n\r\nWe are the Home of the Young Professionals. We are experts in recruitment and staffing university students, recently graduated and professionals in the beginning of their career. You can be employed by us as a consultant in one of our client companies or be recruited directly to our client via our recruitment co-operation. You can read more about us at www.academicwork.fi.\r\n\r\nINFORMATION ABOUT THE COMPANY\r\n\r\nNPAC (Nordic Packaging and Container) is the owner of Corenso and Powerflute. Corenso offers high-performance cores and board to customers worldwide. They have board mills and core plants in multiple locations across Europe, China, and the USA, out of which three are located in Finland. Powerflute creates packaging solutions to clients in several markets globally and has its production in Kuopio, Finland. NPAC works with cutting edge tools in IT and invests a lot on their IT infrastructure. They are always looking for ways to improve in their IT systems in order to help their business grow.",
