				"kuvausteksti" : "University of Vaasa is taking bold steps forward to become a future-proof university with strong societal impact. Excellence in research and education are our corner stones, combined with close interaction with business ecosystems. \r\n\r\nWe are making major investments in renewal of the academic units and new platforms for innovative interdisciplinary research.\r\n\r\nAs of January 2018, University of Vaasa will launch Digital Economy, an open multi-disciplinary research platform. We are hiring new talent to join our close-knit community to build a future university with us. \r\n\r\nDigital Economy platform capitalizes on the University's expertize in all of its focus areas. As an open research platform, Digital Economy will benefit from the partnerships with businesses, other research performers and government agencies. Its research will focus on analysing digitalisation driven innovations and their impacts that are cutting across on individual, organisational and society levels. Digitalisation driven innovations are being realised in the contexts of products, services, processes, marketing, organisations, actors' roles, relations and values.\r\n\r\nPosition\r\nWe are seeking an innovative and experienced leader to head the new Digital economy research platform. You will play a key role in initiating the platform's operations and developing an interactive research platform with strong connections not only within the organization but also to local and international industrial and research partners. \r\n\r\nAs the Director, you will be responsible for organizing, coordinating and developing the activities and resources of the research platform in accordance with the University of Vaasa's strategy. You will lead and coordinate a team of experts assigned to the platform. There will be particular emphasis on developing the University of Vaasa's Digital economy research in a multidisciplinary way and promoting the international profile of the research. As the Director, you will further advance existing and new collaborative networks and work in close co-operation with internal and external partners. The director will also be responsible for the platform's financial management and acquiring external funding.\r\n\r\nWe offer you an attractive position in a dynamic research environment. As a leader of the new platform you will organise research that analyses digital technologies based innovations and their impacts on individual, organisational and society levels. The position offers you an opportunity to establish a research group in close collaboration with established business networks and research partners. \r\n\r\nRequirements\r\nBesides research management capabilities, the director should have the mindset of a digital entrepreneur. A person with experience in research as well as organising digital business is an ideal combination. This role will develop the strategic plan on how to grow the research as well as be out in the marketplace identifying potential partner opportunities for research and development projects. Substantial experience in managing groups of experts and good interactive skills are required from the candidate. To succeed in the position a doctoral degree in a relevant discipline, academic track record and fluency in spoken and written English are essential.\r\n\r\nHow to apply\r\nSubmit your application by using the University of Vaasa's electronic recruitment system. Please attach a cover letter incl. salary expectation as well as a CV and publication record to your application.  The deadline for applications is 17th November 2017.\r\n\r\nThe University of Vaasa reserves the right to not fill the position if there is good reason for this, to postpone the deadline for applications and to consider candidates who apply after the deadline. \r\n\r\nUniversity of Vaasa\r\nThe University of Vaasa educates responsible leaders and experts for the needs of the future. Our fields of research and education are organized into four schools: Marketing and Communications, Technology and Innovations, Management, Accounting and Financing. Creative, innovative research is channeled to three multidisciplinary research platforms: Vaasa Energy Business Innovation Centre - VEBIC, Digital Economy as well as Open and User Innovation Lab. The strength of our university is the community spirit, which promotes multidisciplinary studies and research. Our 5400 students and 500 employees thrive in the most beautiful campus in Finland. \r\n\r\nCity of Vaasa\r\nVaasa is a coastal city with almost 70,000 inhabitants and enjoys a position at the forefront of flourishing urban regions. Vaasa has the leading energy technology cluster in the Nordic countries with several global market leaders, total business turnover of EUR four billion, 30 percent of Finland's total export in energy technology and  11 000 employees.\r\n\r\nRead more about University of Vaasa, city of Vaasa and Finland: http://www.uva.fi/en/rekry/  and http://vaasaregion.fi",
