				"kuvausteksti" : "Finnish Schools International is a K12 school network based on best practices of Finnish Education system and the Finnish National Core Curriculum, with the first three campuses in Prishtina, Kosovo, Tirana, Albania and Zagreb, Croatia to open in September 2018. We are on the road to revolutionizing global education system, one country at a time. More info on www.finnish.school\r\nWe are recruiting for the Principal, Deputy Principal, Special Education Teachers, ICT Coordinator, Classroom teachers for grades 0-6 and subject teachers in all areas for grades 7-12 for Prishtina, Tirana and Zagreb schools.\r\nPlease fill in the application form at https://goo.gl/JqXQPz and send a CV to jobs@finnish.school before Janury 20, 2018. Informal interviews will take place via Skype and on-site in Helsinki during November 26-30, 2017. All positions start in August 2018.\r\nPay and Benefits\r\nWe provide a solid package of pay and benefits, including assistance in finding a suitable housing and the chance to grow professionally and experience the beautiful and historical region of the Balkans.\r\nThis employment complies with the legislation of Republic of Kosovo.\r\n\"The Employment Services will not take the responsibility for the above mentioned information nor will it assist in labour permit issues.\"",
