				"kuvausteksti" : "We are looking for an Embedded Software Engineer for our client Gryphon Secure, international company offering unique, ultra-secure mobile and fixed line telecommunications solutions for government, enterprise and military organizations world-wide. If you have at least some hands-on experience with C and C++ programming on embedded Linux on ARM platforms, enthusiasm to learn and ambition to grow in your career, keep reading because you might be the one we are looking for.\r\n\r\nABOUT THE ROLE\r\n\r\nAcademic Work is looking for an Embedded Software Engineer for our client Gryphon Secure, Canadian-based company offering ultra-secure mobile and fixed line telecommunications solutions for government, enterprise and military organizations world-wide. They are growing and want to strengthen their product development in Finland. This is a new position in Finland.\r\n\r\nYou will be recruited to our client company. Academic Work will take care of the recruitment process, therefore candidates are kindly asked to direct all questions to Academic Work hel03@academicwork.fi.\r\n\r\nJOB DUTIES\r\n\r\nIn this position, your main job is to build and develop SW for Gryphon Secure's newest product that is running Linux, and has several connectivity features. You will work tightly with cross-functional teams to innovate, define, design, build and deliver new features for embedded Linux platform. This is a new position in Finland but you will be supported with your colleagues who are world-class experts in product development, software development, quality assurance and information security.\r\n\r\nThe job includes:\r\n\r\n-Software development, debug, release and maintenance for Linux based, Gryphon Secure computing and connectivity product.\r\n-Ensuring and maintaining software code/applications usability, reliability, robustness, performance and quality\r\n-Working tightly with cross-functional teams to innovate, define, design, build and deliver new features for embedded Linux platform\r\n\r\nGryphon Secure offers a change for you to develop a new, unique product in an international company. You will focus on embedded Linux platform programming but you will have a change to widen your expertise to, for example, Android OS and iOS application development or in a server programming and set-ups according to your own ambitions. Team leader path is also an option for your career growth in the future.\r\n\r\nWE ARE LOOKING FOR\r\n\r\nOur ideal candidate has a bachelor's or master's degree in IT, engineering or economics and hands-on experience (from work or your own projects) with C, C++ and scripting languages on embedded Linux platforms. You are also familiar with Wi-Fi Kernel module. You are energetic and enthusiastic to develop and you have excellent English communication skills. Finnish is considered as a plus but is not necessary.\r\n\r\nApply for this position if you have:\r\n\r\n-Bachelor's or master's degree in IT, engineering or economics\r\n-1-2 years of hands-on experience (from work or your own projects) with C and C++ on ARM based Linux platforms.\r\n-Experience with Communication module Linux drivers like Wi-Fi, Bluetooth and Ethernet.\r\n-Excellent written and oral communication skills in English\r\n-Experience in network programming, Yocto projects, ARM architecture or secure communication protocols and standards (for example VPN, IPsec, SIP, XMPP) are considered as a big plus, but not necessary.\r\n\r\nTechnical skills are important but what counts is your enthusiasm, activity and high ambition to learn and develop in your career. If we got you interested, send your application the soonest. We would be happy to discuss this opportunity further with You.\r\n\r\n\r\nTo apply for the job you need to register on our website and then click on \"Apply here\". Remember to attach your CV into your application! We only process applications through our website but if you have questions about the position you can reach us via email in hel03@academicwork.fi. Please write the advert ID in the subject field and paste the advert link in the mail. We are continuously screening and contacting candidates so make sure to send your application as soon as possible. Please note that the advert can be removed prior to the last application dates on our external advertising pages. In the event the advert has been removed it is either due to the process being completed or because we have a sufficient number of qualified applications and are proceeding to the selection/interview phase in the process.\r\n\r\nWe are the Home of the Young Professionals. We are experts in recruitment and staffing university students, recently graduated and professionals in the beginning of their career. You can be employed by us as a consultant in one of our client companies or be recruited directly to our client via our recruitment co-operation. You can read more about us at www.academicwork.fi.\r\n\r\nINFORMATION ABOUT THE COMPANY\r\n\r\nGryphon Secure delivers ultra-secure mobile and fixed line telecommunications solutions for government, enterprise and military organizations. They provide end-to-end and real time encryption of all voice, chat, SMS, email and data file transmissions utilizing trusted elliptical curve cryptography, on top of hardened OS software, and a securely manufactured and rugged hardware platform. Gryphon Secure is the only company in the ultra-secure telecommunications industry to offer interoperability between its encrypted mobile and fixed line solutions.",
