				"kuvausteksti" : "Robot offline programming software expert \r\n\r\nDelfoi is one of the leading developers of robot offline programming and simulation systems (OLP, Offline Programming). We have delivered solutions to the automotive and aviation industry as well as to machine and equipment manufacturers around the world through our partners. Today, Delfoi Robotics software has nearly 400 business customers such as ABB, Boeing, Caterpillar, Daimler, John Deere and Ponsse among others. Our customers are mainly located in Europe, but we also have an increasing number of customers in North America, Asia and South America.\r\nAs our business is growing, we are looking for an expert in robot offline programming and simulations to join our Robotics Ream in Tampere, Finland.\r\n\r\nRequirements:\r\n\r\nWe expect you to have a basic knowledge of robotics. Knowledge of industrial robots is considered an advantage. \r\nYour work will be to implement and commission the software with robot stations, supporting our sales partners as well as customer training and support. Also, software demonstrations and marketing videos for software promotion is part of your work.  \r\nWe use the Visual Components software platform, so previous experience with the software or other robotic simulation applications such as Delmia and overall experience in 3D modeling and robotic simulation is considered a major advantage as well.\r\nYou should be able to work independently and have a fast learning ability. We are looking for an open, social person that enjoys working in a team. Implementation projects involve working with our customers around the world, so traveling is part of the job.\r\nGood English language skills both written and spoken are essential, other languages such as German are an advantage.\r\n\r\nWhat we offer\r\n\r\nWe offer competitive benefits and wages as well as a permanent position. The work is highly interesting as you, for example, get to work with leading experts in the field as well as with international projects in the automotive, aviation and mechanical engineering industries.\r\n\r\nStart of employment\r\n\r\nWe would like our new team member to start in January 2018 or at an agreed upon time.\r\nSend your informal application and CV to rekry@delfoi.com. Deadline: November 28, 2017.\r\nFor inquiries contact Heikki Aalto, heikki.aalto@delfoi.com,  +358 500 506816 \r\nwww.delfoi.com",
