				"etatyo" : false,
				"kuvausteksti" : "Do you want to be a part of digital marketing transformation? Join Nokia's Digital Transformation initiative in Espoo, Finland! We are taking Nokia digital marketing technology solutions to the next level! You will be working with highly skilled individuals across the globe.\r\n\r\nWe are looking for YOU, Dashboard Developer, to implement and maintain a server-based MCA performance dashboard. You are responsible for dashboard production and building the foundation for analytics insights as well as data-driven learning. This shall include a data warehouse that holds staged campaign and marketing performance information. The Dashboards will provide highly responsive data in a multi-user environment. This is an opportunity to a hands-on developer that loves to be on the pulse of the latest trends and technologies.\r\n\r\nYour key responsibilities include:\r\n\r\n- Dashboard portal development\r\n- Dashboard, UI Design, and multi-dimensional reporting design\r\n- Data mining, unstructured data analysis, cluster analysis\r\n- Dashboard performance tuning design and optimization\r\n- Engaging with Reporting Analysts, Data Science and Marketing Technologies functions to implement reports\r\n- Contribute to the continuing evolution of analytics and reporting capabilities\r\n- Design and implementation of ETL processes including data quality and insurance for reporting feeds\r\n- Data sciences, predictive intelligence, advanced modeling techniques will be an advantage\r\n\r\nYour technical skills and abilities include:\r\n\r\n- Apply frameworks like Responsive Web Design, Web-Services, Web-Standards or AngularJS to develop modern front ends for mobile devices and desktops alike\r\n- 3+ years' experience using frontend-web technologies such as: JSON, Ajax, PHP, HTML5, CSS3, JavaScript and ready to use tools as, Bootstrap, Grunt, jQuery\r\n- 3+ years' experience in maintenance and set up of relational DBMSS, SQL\r\n- Proven experience in PowerBI or TABLEAU, or other business intelligence tools\r\n- SAS/R/Python would be an advantage\r\n\r\nWe expect you to have:\r\n\r\n- Great team work skills, with a willingness to learn and the ability to solve problems\r\n- Meticulous attention to detail driven to produce high quality code\r\n- Strong analytical and reporting skills, someone who enjoys digging data, KPI's and metrics\r\n- Using best practice and methodologies\r\n- Good communication skills, both written and verbal\r\n- Ability to work under pressure with tight timelines and at short notice\r\n- Master of computer science or associate field, strong Data Science background\r\n- Alternatively, Master in Mathematics, Data Science or Operations Research\r\n- Or a minimum of 5+ years' proven experience in a related field\r\n\r\nWe offer you an exciting opportunity to join a team working on digital marketing transformation and the opportunity to grow as a professional - every day. This position gives you a chance to influence how Nokia communicates with our customers and markets our products. Come and join us to give your own input for Nokia's future success!\r\n\r\nDoes this make you tick?\r\n\r\nIf you say yes, please submit your application online no later than 12th of November 2017. For more information about the position, please contact our recruitment partner Arja Martikainen Mon-Fri between 2 and 3 pm +2 CET. Tel +358407621564 or arja.martikainen(at)barona.fi.\r\n\r\nFind out more about Nokia's digital marketing & marketing technology opportunities:\r\nhttps://www.nokia.com/en_int/about-us/careers/currently-seeking/opportunities-in-finland#",
