				"etatyo" : false,
				"kuvausteksti" : "Do you want to be a part of digital marketing transformation? Join Nokia's Digital Transformation initiative in Espoo, Finland! We are taking Nokia digital marketing technology solutions to the next level! You will be working with highly skilled individuals across the globe.\r\n\r\nWe are looking for YOU, modern GTM & Strategic Planner, known for your data-driven, analytical and at the same time creative mindset. You are a visionary but still hands-on, keeping yourself on the pulse of the latest trends and technologies.\r\n\r\nYou will be part of the Campaign Planning & Strategy team which is tasked with developing and executing customer centric campaigns. The person in this role will be a part of a team that will develop a unified go to market plan for marketing and overarching business strategy to help drive demand generation goals.\r\n\r\nYour Responsibilities\r\n\r\n- Working with other key marketing functions, this role will be integral to defining and communication overall marketing strategy, setting targets and goals, prioritization (segments, solutions, markets, routes to market, etc) and providing investment recommendations.\r\n- Identify customer/audience segments to deferentially serve with our Business Group (BG) and cross-BG offerings driven business needs, market context and customer insights\r\n- Facilitate the creation of Marketing program's overarching strategy that all other campaign strategies stem from by aligning with Nokia use-cases, defining customer cohorts, and focusing on business outcomes\r\n- Determine how to go-to market with our offerings by developing a business plan and aligning sales plays with Marketing motions\r\n- Design overarching value propositions to meet needs of target customers in a differentiated way by positioning offerings from across the BG portfolio in a compelling and differentiated way\r\n- Determine the role of marketing in driving demand and increasing awareness through existing and new channels and determine best route to market\r\n- Develop a unified GTM strategy by working across functional silos to arrive at a cohesive plan and budget.\r\n\r\nYour Qualifications and Skills\r\n\r\n- 8+ years of relevant experience in strategic planning for marketing programs or campaigns; experience in telecom, high-tech, or software are a plus\r\n- Financial planning background is strongly desired\r\n- Prior experience in coordinating a global GTM marketing plan\r\n- Bachelor's Degree in related fields of study\r\n- Strong attention to detail and project management skills\r\n- Excellent written and verbal communication skills\r\n- Organized with strong analytical skills\r\n- Able to work in a fast-paced environment\r\n- Excellent with both MS Excel and PowerPoint\r\n\r\nWe offer you an exciting opportunity to join a team working on digital marketing transformation and the opportunity to grow as a professional - every day. This position gives you a chance to influence how Nokia communicates with our customers and markets our products. Come and join us to give your own input for Nokia's future success!\r\n\r\nDoes this make you tick?\r\n\r\nIf you say yes, please submit your application online no later than 12th of November 2017. For more information about the position, please contact our recruitment partner Sonja Otranen Wednesday between 9 and 11 am +2 CET. Tel +358469221228 or sonja.otranen(at)barona.fi.\r\n\r\nFind out more about Nokia's digital marketing & marketing technology opportunities:\r\nhttps://www.nokia.com/en_int/about-us/careers/currently-seeking/opportunities-in-finland#",
