				"kuvausteksti" : "CALL FOR NMR LABORATORY MANAGER/ENGINEER POSITION\r\n\r\nThe University of Oulu in Northern Finland, with approximately 14 000 students and 3000 employees, is an international, multidisciplinary research university. The strengths of the University are broad multidisciplinary research interests, modern research and study environment and wide cooperation with international research and educational institutes (http://www.oulu.fi/english/). \r\n\r\nThe NMR laboratory at the University of Oulu belongs to the Center for Microscopy and Nanotechnogy (CMNT), which is part of the strategic, multidisciplinary research infrastructure of the University. The laboratory has currently six Bruker NMR instruments (AVIII300, DSX300, AVIII400, AVIII500, AV500 and AVIII600) with solution and solid-state probes as well as micro imaging, diffusion and hyperpolarization (SEOP, PHIP, SABRE) utilities. \r\n\r\nCMNT is now announcing a five-year position for the NMR Laboratory Manager post. \r\n\r\nThe NMR laboratory manager is responsible for supervising the daily operation of the laboratory, maintaining the spectrometers and workstations as well as taking part in planning and applying funding for new instrumentation. She/he should also keep up with the newest developments in the field and be capable of implementing these for the instruments as well as educating and helping the users to utilize them. She/he will also be carrying out experiments for the clients (university researchers, local companies and research institutions) and actively designing and marketing service packages for the existing and potential external users. \r\n\r\nJob Responsibilities and Required Qualifications\r\n\r\n\r\nThe applicant should have at least an MSc degree in physics, chemistry or other related field as well as experience on NMR methodology, instrumentation and research, optimally on wide variety of methods and equipment (solution, solid state, micro imaging, diffusion, hyperpolarization). Previous experience on Bruker NMR spectrometers, electronics and software as well as Linux operating system will be considered as an asset. The candidate must have excellent command in English language and the capability to communicate in Finnish language is considered as a plus.\r\n\r\nThe position will be filled from 1 January 2018 until 28 February 2023 with four months trial period. There may also be a possibility to hire the candidate permanently after the five-year period. \r\n\r\nSalary \r\n\r\nThe salary of the NMR laboratory manager will be based on the General Collective Agreement for universities in Finland and more precisely on job requirement level 10-11 within salary scale.\r\n\r\nIn addition to the basic salary, the appointee will be paid a salary component based on personal performance level with a maximum of 46.3 % of the basic salary. In the beginning of the employment the full salary is approximately 3800-4300 euros per month. The salary level will be reviewed during the first six months of the employment. \r\n\r\nThe successful candidate will receive full benefits provided by the University of Oulu to university employees, including holidays and occupational healthcare services. An international appointee will also receive benefits provided by the Finnish government to residents, for example possibility to obtain access to the national healthcare system, tax benefits for employees with children and high-quality affordable childcare services. \r\n\r\nReviewer Assessment\r\n\r\nA recruitment committee will take care of the evaluation process. The top candidates will be interviewed. \r\n\r\nApplication \r\n\r\nApplications, together with all relevant enclosures, should be submitted using electronic application form by 17th of November, 2017. \r\n\r\nThe application should be written in English and the following information needs to be included:\r\n1.Curriculum vitae\r\n2.List of publications\r\n3.Brief description of research merits and experience with NMR instrumentation, software and methodology (max 2 pages)\r\n4.Contact information for  two referees willing to give a statement of the candidate.\r\n5.Separate freeform application/motivation letter.\r\n\r\nContact information \r\n\r\nJanne Remes, Director of CMNT, tel. +358 29 448 2727, email: janne.remes(at)oulu.fi\r\n\r\nVille Telkki, Academy Research Fellow, tel. +358 29 448 1309, email: ville-veikko.telkki(at)oulu.fi",
