				"kuvausteksti" : "Are you an eager factoring professional and are you interested in a key role at a growing fintech company within the factoring industry? Nordfin Capital Oy is searching for a finance professional to strengthen their team in Helsinki. Please apply without delay, since the position will be filled as soon as we find the right person.\r\n\r\nAs a Controller you would be in a key role for building Nordfin Capital's coming success story. Your main responsibilities would be to ensure day to day efficiency throughout the factoring process. Tasks entail daily account management duties, invoicing, and debt monitoring. Also including internal and external reporting, solving errors, and communication with different stakeholders. Your accounting expertise and solid understanding of accounting principles should be one of your strengths in order to succeed in this position. Additional tasks such as system and process development should also be expected   \r\n\r\nThe job includes:\r\nAccount control and monitoring\r\nInvoice handling and debt monitoring\r\nConducting internal and external reporting\r\nHandling of error situations\r\nDaily communications with customers\r\nDeveloping processes and systems for more streamlined operations\r\n\r\nThis position suits you if you have a genuine interest in factoring with a strong understanding of accounting processes.\r\n\r\nREQUIREMENTS\r\nOur ideal candidate has experience in the invoice finance industry and a strong understanding of accounting. A background in a commercial finance environment and knowledge in interpreting financial accounts and its practical applications is an advantage. \r\n\r\nYou are the one we are looking for if you fill the mentioned requirements, have good collaboration skills, and a self-driven attitude towards work.  Furthermore, you communicate fluently in English and Finnish. \r\n\r\nApply for this position if you have:\r\n\r\nSuitable education in economics\r\nExperience within the invoice finance industry\r\nStrong accounting expertise  \r\nSelf-starting and systematic way of conduct\r\nA sense of numerical precision\r\nGood MS Office skills, especially in Excel\r\nFluent communication skills in Finnish and English\r\n\r\nIt is also seen as an advantage if you have experience in larger account ledger systems. Furthermore, good communication skills in Swedish is seen as an advantage.\r\n\r\nAs a person, you are eager to take responsibility for daily administrative operations in combination with an enthusiastic and entrepreneurial attitude. Problem-solving skills and good social skills are also valued.\r\n\r\n\r\nStart: As soon as possible (or according to agreement)\r\nWorking hours: Full-time\r\nEmployment period: Permanent\r\nLocation: Helsinki\r\nSalary: According to agreement\r\nTo apply for the job you need to send us your CV and a short resume to info@nordfincapital.com \r\n\r\nNordfin Capital is a new player on the invoice finance market. The team is experienced and have a great track record within the industry. Now it is time to write Nordfin Capital's success story in Finland. Join us in our journey towards success. Head office is located in Stockholm. \r\n\r\nwww.nordfincapital.com",
