				"kuvausteksti" : "Oulun yliopisto on kansainvälinen tiedeyhteisö, jossa työskentelee 16 000 opiskelijaa ja noin 3000 työntekijää. Yliopiston vahvuuksia ovat laaja monitieteisyys ja nykyaikainen tutkimus- ja oppimisympäristö sekä tiiviit yhteistyösuhteet kansainvälisiin koulutus- ja tutkimuslaitoksiin.\r\n\r\nOulun yliopistossa on haettavana seuraava tehtävä:\r\n\r\nDoctoral student, biology, 4 years\r\n\r\nDoctoral student position in a project  Ecology and evolution in trophic interactions in changing boreal forest habitats'\r\n\r\nEcology and Genetics Research Unit, Faculty of Science, announces a doctoral student position in a project  Ecology and evolution in trophic interactions in changing boreal forest habitats'. We offer a unique opportunity to join in the exciting international project led by Professor Markku Orell. The project focuses on climate change induced phenological shifts within a tri-trophic boreal system: deciduous trees, folivorous insects and insectivorous foliage-gleaning passerines (willow tit, crested tit, Siberian tit, great tit, blue tit and pied flycatcher).We elucidate how selection acts on phenotypes and gives proxies for the evolutionary potential in life-history traits. This is essential for understanding ecosystem functioning under changing conditions, rapidly warming climate. A mismatch in timing caused by climate change is critical for fitness at different trophic levels, jeopardizing ecosystem functioning. Our study design offers an opportunity to study evolutionary potential in the context of species interaction.\r\n\r\nThe research of the PhD student is centered on determining the available food abundance and architecture (variation in species composition in time), quantified by sampling the droppings (frass) of insect larvae, and food selection of folivorous birds, quantified by the droppings of bird nestlings. The student will be involved in sampling the droppings in the field and determining the available and selected prey species composition by applying metabarcoding methodology in the lab. The student will work with competent ecologists, entomologists, lab technicians and a bioinformatician.\r\n\r\nQualification requirements. The applicants should hold MSc degree in a relevant field of bioscience; ideally strong background in ecology and/or molecular biology, and above all a passion for biology. Interest in ornithology and entomology are advantageous. We are looking for an enthusiastic and highly motivated person with problem solving skills expected to be capable of both teamwork and independent work in the lab and field. During the doctoral training, she/he would learn advanced statistical methods, generalized linear mixed models, and methods of bioinformatics applicable to metabarcoding. An applicant should be highly motivated, ready to commit her/himself to the project, and have English communication skills. A moderate amount of teaching in courses may be required. The recruited PhD student is expected to visit Dr. Anne Charmantier's lab in Montpellier, France. Other collaborators of the project are Dr. Cameron Ghalambor (Colorado State University, USA) and Dr. Juan Carlos Senar (Natural History Museum of Barcelona, Catalonia, Spain). The doctoral student will be supervised by Seppo Rytkönen, Marko Mutanen, Panu Välimäki and Markku Orell.\r\n\r\nSalary The salary will be based on the levels 1 - 4 of the demand level chart for teaching and research staff of Finnish universities. In addition, a salary component based on personal work performance will be paid (maximum of 46.3 % of the job-specific component). The salary is thus being in practice roughly 1,900 - 2,500 € per month, depending on the appointee's qualification and experience.\r\n\r\nApplications, together with all relevant enclosures, should be submitted electronically by November 15th, 2017.\r\n\r\nThe project is expected to start in the early 2018, exact date to be decided with the successful candidate. A trial period of 4 months is applied in the position.\r\n\r\nThe following documents must be attached to the application:\r\n1) A curriculum vitae in English\r\n2) A list of possible scientific contributions (publications, talks, posters etc.) including possible teaching merits\r\n3) A brief (1 page) description of motivation and suitability to the post\r\n4) Documentation of English language skills\r\n5) Recommendation letters (2) or contact information of two persons whom may be asked to give a statement of the candidate\r\n6) Master's degree certificate (if completed by time of application). The degree must be completed before the start of the employment.\r\n\r\nContact persons for further information. Professor Markku Orell, email: markku.orell(at)oulu.fi, tel.: +358 29 448 1216, Dr. Seppo Rytkönen, email: seppo.rytkonen(at)oulu.fi, tel.:+358 29 448 1257",
