				"kuvausteksti" : "Kaiku HR is specialized in personnel leasing, outsourcing and recruitment. It is very important for us to find an inspiring and motivating job for the candidate or otherwise well-fitting task for his/her current life situation. We believe that a motivated and inspired employee grants the success for our customer. \r\n\r\nWe are looking for TRANSVERSE TEST ANALYSIS ENGINEER to our customer company at Olkiluoto3.\r\n\r\nMain duties are to support Commissioning Branches for the following activities:\r\n- Participate and support commissioning in meetings.\r\n- Support commissioning branches in analysing and freezing design changes, which are required before phase B Cold and Hot Functional Tests and phase C & D commissioning sub phases.\r\n- Preserve the Plant reference configuration in the commissioning documentation (system commissioning programs and commissioning instructions).\r\n- Technical control of Commissioning Master Files: maintaining, ensuring their consistency, preparation of Client and Finnish Nuclear Regulator?s audit of the master files, participation in their audit.\r\n- Creation of the following reports: Check-list after the review of the test report, list of comments on the commissioning documentation before the RFA meeting with the client (TVO), technical event analysis report.\r\n\r\nYou may also be assigned these tasks:\r\n- Supporting technical commissioning SCI 52 NI / SCI 53 NI team for the analysis of critical open points before/during/after commissioning tests of motors, actuators and control valves and measuring binary and analog circuits.\r\n- Validating commissioning documentation through the RFA (Ready For Application) process.\r\n- Analysing and validating test reports\r\n- Technical event analysis\r\n\r\nSCI 52 NI = Commissioning tests of switchgear feeders, motors, actuators and control valves.\r\nSCI 53 NI = Commissioning tests of measuring binary and analog circuits.\r\n\r\nNOTE: There may be a need to adapt to weekend work /shift work/on duty work, if the project activity requires it. \r\n\r\nRequirements:\r\n- Degree in general, process or mechanical engineering\r\n- At least 10 years? field experience in nuclear power plant\r\n- PWR and EPR technology knowledge would be a plus\r\n- System design or commissioning experience\r\n- MS Office knowledge\r\n- Document writing capacity\r\n- Versatile and adaptable, rigorous and attentive to details\r\n- Good interpersonal skills\r\n- Client and result oriented\r\n- Fluent English: ability with French, German or Finnish would be a plus.\r\n\r\nThe position will be filled as soon as a suitable candidate is found, so be quick to send us your application with CV in English and a salary request!\r\n\r\nThe contract is for 10 months.",
