				"kuvausteksti" : "ABB (ABBN: SIX Swiss Ex) is a pioneering technology leader in electrification products, robotics and motion, industrial automation and power grids, serving customers in utilities, industry and transport & infrastructure globally. Continuing more than a 125-year history of innovation, ABB today is writing the future of industrial digitalization and driving the Energy and Fourth Industrial Revolutions. ABB operates in more than 100 countries with about 132,000 employees www.abb.com\r\n\r\nWe are looking for a Senior R&D Engineer at ABB Oy, Drives unit in Helsinki. You will be leading technology concept development in demanding product development projects in the Low Power Drives product group. In this position, you will solve technical challenges by using your own solid competence in AC Drive technologies.\r\n\r\nYour responsibilities\r\n- Creating ground-breaking technical solutions and platforms for high performance and energy-efficient next generation AC drives \r\n- Coordinating and planning daily design and testing activities according to the project scope and schedule\r\n- Working in close collaboration with Project and Product Managers giving your valuable feedback to the project management\r\n- Mentoring and leading younger designers by your own example and experience\r\n- Actively seeking innovative technical concepts to differentiate our products from competitors and increase customer value\r\n\r\nWe offer\r\n- A challenging position in an international working environment, maintaining the brand of world's best variable speed drive manufacturer\r\n- The opportunity for personal development \r\n- A broad selection of future projects and the opportunity to further your career in a global company\r\n\r\nRequirements\r\n- M.Sc. or higher degree in a relevant field \r\n- Several years' experience of developing AC drives, or corresponding experience\r\n- Architecture- and concept-level understanding of drives and modern power electronics and devices \r\n- A deep understanding of cutting-edge technology and trends in drives technology\r\n- Good skills in and understanding of at least three of the following areas: electronics, mechanics, FPGA design, embedded software, design for manufacturing, quality\r\n- A deep understanding of different converter topologies and concept-level design work\r\n- Excellent written and spoken communication skills in English and Finnish\r\n- Familiarity with Microsoft Excel, PowerPoint and Word\r\n\r\nIdeally, you have\r\n- Familiarity with modern simulation tools\r\n- Knowledge of drive standards\r\n- Experience of the compatibility requirements of both the grid and motor sides of drives",
