				"kuvausteksti" : "Kaiku HR is specialized in personnel leasing, outsourcing and recruitment. It is very important for us to find an inspiring and motivating job for the candidate or otherwise well-fitting task for his/her current life situation. We believe that a motivated and inspired employee grants the success for our customer. \r\n\r\nWe are looking for RADIATION PROTECTION ENGINEER to our customer company at Olkiluoto 3.\r\n\r\nJob description:\r\n\r\nAssessment of the N-16 source term from the measured gamma close rates. Preparing of methodology, performing of calculations for the installation of the detectors, procuring of the detectors, participating to the installation of the detectors, monitoring the results (extrapolation) and performing the reporting to the project and TVO. Evaluating potential changes in zoning and predicted service lifetimes to be implemented only after commissioning feedback comes available. \r\n\r\n- Confirmation of the zoning, including assessment of potential hot spots close to buildings openings (SCP RAD)\r\n- Support the overall project in demonstrating that contractual requirements are met\r\n- Initiate corrective actions in case of deviations, the candidate will coordinate the handling of CR/DCR if any related to radiation shielding\r\n- Participate in review and testing of equipment required during commissioning\r\n- Troubleshoot and perform analysis activities during commissioning\r\n\r\nGeneral and technical background expected:\r\n\r\n- Knowledge in radiation protection technology\r\n- Experience in nuclear safety and/or system engineering\r\n- EPR design basic knowledge\r\n- Adherence to access requirements in Controlled Area and Sign Posting \r\n- Use of radiation protecting software\r\n- Knowledge of radiation production products such as MIRION would be a plus\r\n- Establishment and/or review of system test procedures \r\n\r\nSkills required:\r\n\r\n- Engineering level degree in nuclear or radiological engineering\r\n- Experience in nuclear power plant operations\r\n- At least one significant experience in testing or commissioning activities related to radiation protection\r\n- Knowledge of source term characteristics\r\n- Knowledge of the applicable licensing requirements\r\n- Excellent relational and communication skills\r\n- Rigorous especially for adherence to procedures in force on site including configuration management\r\n- Aware of safety and security aspects\r\n\r\nStarting ASAP, and for a duration of 12 months.",
