				"kuvausteksti" : "Kaiku HR is specialized in personnel leasing, outsourcing and recruitment. It is very important for us to find an inspiring and motivating job for the candidate or otherwise well-fitting task for his/ her current life situation. We believe that a motivated and inspired employee grants the success for our customer. \r\n\r\nWe are looking for FIRE OFFICER to our customer company at Olkiluoto 3.\r\n\r\nYou should have technical experience from fire protection and prevention on industrial environment or on construction site (hot works: welding, lifting?). Also, you are prepared to work on the radiation protection area and in shift/rotation.\r\n\r\nOther requirements:\r\n- Knowledge of MS Office (Word, Powerpoint, Outlook)\r\n- Fluent Finnish and English\r\n- Knowledge of automatic systems (extinguishing, alarm) OR experience in electrical and/or mechanical risks linked to industrial activities or commissioning activities.\r\n\r\nYou would be working under the authority of HSE department Manager and Fire Protection team leader. The tasks include:\r\n- Follow-up of application and compliance with site rules, national standards and legislation. Follow-up and update of daily fire protection tasks (exit ways, signalisation), reporting and recording actions and deviations. Reporting daily to the team leader.\r\n- Actively communicating with contractor personnel, guiding and instructing them. Performing rescue trainings and tests with site personnel, and managing the fire safety inspection on site with the contractors. Follow-up on corrective actions defined during the inspections.\r\n- Animating the safety in construction/commissioning teams through visits on spot, trainings, lessons-learned etc. \r\n- Closely working with supervisors and construction/commissioning teams to have the knowledge of the coming activities (anticipation) and in the daily safety.\r\n\r\nThe contract length is 8 months and the position will be filled as soon as a suitable candidate is found. Send us your CV already today!",
