				"kuvausteksti" : "Enersense International Oy provides its customers with resourcing solutions which appreciate the fluctuations in their projects. Our company is an ISO 9001:2008/14001:2004-certified actor with more than ten years of experience in operating in close cooperation with large-scale nuclear and construction sites, the Olkiluoto 3 nuclear power plant site being the largest of them. \r\n\r\nWe are currently looking for a Chemistry Technician for our client in Olkiluoto Nuclear Power Plant, Finland. We are offering challenging work in an international project environment.\r\n\r\nMain tasks and responsibilities:\r\n\r\n-Chemical surveillance of the nuclear and conventional circuits of the nuclear power plant\r\n-Taking of samples from the different fluid and gas circuits\r\n-Analysis of the samples in the laboratory\r\n-Following of the chemistry handbook\r\n-Secure the chemical parameters in the technical specification\r\n-Documentation of the chemical surveillance\r\n-Preservation of fluid systems\r\n-Supervision of the nuclear waste handling\r\n--The work will include working in radiological controlled zone.\r\n\r\nRequirements\r\n\r\n-Chemical Technician Degree\r\n-5 years' experience in radiological chemistry of a running nuclear power plant with -pressurized water reactor\r\n-Experience in laboratory work in a running nuclear power plant\r\n-Knowledge of all chemical laboratory methods needed in a nuclear power plant\r\n-MS Office Programs\r\n-Knowledge of all chemical and radiological laws and guidelines (Finnish/National and European)\r\n-Basic knowledge of the EPR technology\r\n-Knowledge of pressurized water reactor technology and chemistry\r\n\r\nLanguage Skills:\r\n\r\n-Fluent in English\r\n\r\nDrug test and concise security clearance will be done for the selected person in order to get the permanent access to OL3 site.\r\n\r\nOnly applicants with a valid working permit / EU-citizenship can be considered.\r\n\r\nThe post will be filled as soon as a suitable applicant is found.",
