				"kuvausteksti" : "Adecco Group is the world's leading provider of workforce solutions. Adecco Finland Oy has been in operation since 1997. Our company is authorized by the Private Employment Agencies' Association of Finland. Hundreds of professionals in various fields are employed through us each day in jobs ranging in duration from a few days to several years. We also recruit professionals for our client companies.\r\n\r\nWe're currently looking for Chemistry Technician for our international client in the OL3 Site in Eurajoki. The job starts as soon as the suitable candidate is found and last approximately 12 months, possibly longer depending on our client's need.\r\n\r\nExpected background:\r\n\r\nChemical Technician Degree\r\n5 years' experience in radiological chemistry of a running nuclear power plant with pressurized water reactor\r\nExperience in laboratory work in a running nuclear power plant\r\nKnowledge of all chemical laboratory methods needed in a nuclear power plant\r\n\r\nSkills required:\r\n\r\nIT-skills: MS Office Programs\r\nKnowledge of all chemical and radiological laws, guidelines (Finnish national and European)\r\nTechnical: Basic knowledge of the ERP technology and knowledge in pressurized water reactor technology and chemistry\r\nLanguage skills: Fluent in English\r\n\r\nJob description:\r\n\r\nChemical surveillance of the nuclear and conventional circuits of the nuclear power plant.\r\nTaking of samples from the different fluid and gas circuits.\r\nAnalysis of the samples in the laboratory.\r\nFollowing the chemistry handbook.\r\nSecure the chemical parameters in the technical specification.\r\nDocumentation of the chemical surveillance.\r\nPreservation of fluid systems.\r\nSupervision of the nuclear waste handling.\r\n\r\nThis is a rewarding and challenging opportunity for a professional to gain valuable work experience in her/his scope and work in an international team. We are offering a competitive salary. \r\n\r\nPlease apply for the Chemistry Technician position by registering at www.adecco.fi. Attach your English CV to the application. For more information please contact HR \r\nConsultant Eerika Jantunen +35846 875 0111.",
