				"kuvausteksti" : "Adecco Group is the world's leading provider of workforce solutions. Adecco Finland Oy has been in operation since 1997. Our company is authorized by the Private Employment Agencies' Association of Finland. Hundreds of professionals in various fields are employed through us each day in jobs ranging in duration from a few days to several years. We also recruit professionals for our client companies.\r\n\r\nWe are currently searching for Shift Assistant for our international client in the OL3 Site. The job starts in November and lasts approximately 12 months with the possibility for extension. Please apply for the position quickly or contact me for further information today!\r\n\r\nCriterions:\r\n\r\nFormation in all secretarial works\r\nExperience with technical documentation\r\nIT-skills: MS Office, CMS if possible\r\nTechnical skills: Basic knowledge of the EPR technology is a plus but not mandatory\r\nLanguage skills: English (fluent), Finnish (fluent)\r\n\r\nResponsibilities:\r\n\r\nPerform all administrative work in the Main Control Room and in the PTW office.\r\nPerform administrative activities in CMS.\r\n-Work order, permit to test and blocking printout and distribution.\r\n-Storage of work order, permit to tests and blocking lists printouts.\r\n-Receiving back work orders and permits to test from supervisors and commissioning engineers.\r\n-Preparation of tags for blockings.\r\n-Transfer of blocking results to CMS.\r\nGive out and receive back of room and cabinet keys.\r\n\r\nWe're offering you the possibility to work with an interesting International project where you can adapt your skills and gain valuable work experience. The person chosen for the position will be drug tested prior to start.\r\n\r\nPlease apply for the \"Shift Assistant OL3 Site\" position by registering at www.adecco.fi. Attach your English CV to the application. For more information contact HR Consultant Eerika Jantunen at +358 (0)46 875 0111.",
