				"kuvausteksti" : "Are you looking to join a dynamic, innovation-driven, international company building a better future for us all? UPM leads the integration of bio and forest industries into a new, sustainable and innovation-driven future. We live by our values - trust and be trusted, achieve together, renew with courage.\r\n\r\nWe are now looking for an Financial Controller for a Record to report team in Tampere.\r\n\r\nUPM Financial Services is a customer service oriented global organization providing financial expertise for all UPM businesses and functions. We as a team drive to be operationally efficient, performing on a high level to give our very best to our both internal and external customers and stakeholders. In order to succeed in our work we are now looking for new talents to make our organization even more professional, versatile, collaborative and dynamic - ready to take in new challenges!\r\n\r\nGreetings from your future colleague\r\n\"Traditional accounting tasks are not anymore part of our daily work in UPM. We have outsourced all our routine transactional type of work to our outsourcing partners and our work is to ensure on-time quality reporting and develop everything we do towards world class levels. This makes every day as an interesting journey in answering to the needs of fast changing global environment. Our vision is to be world class finance in year 2020. We are on a good path achieving this, but we still need great people to join our journey. If you got excited about these words, we are looking forward to meet you!\" -Anne Hänninen\r\n\r\nWhat you'll do\r\n- Perform complex accounting and reporting tasks \r\n- Participate in the development of reporting\r\n\r\nWho you are\r\n- You have a bachelor's degree in finance, preferably in accounting or equal qualification and at least 3 years' work experience in similar field of responsibility area\r\n- You have a proven track record in accounting\r\n- You have expertise in asset accounting\r\n- You have excellent prioritization capabilities and solution oriented, proactive and problem solving mind-set\r\n- You have good co-operation, coordination and communications skills as you will be having daily contact with key stakeholders\r\n- You can communicate fluently in English\r\n- Understanding internal controls, financial and management accounting and SAP are considered an asset\r\n\r\nThis is what we offer for you\r\n- Meaningful job: We are proud of what we do. Our work highlights the expertise of our personnel, the high quality of our products and the company's values.\r\n- Inspired and motivated teams: We have highly skilled workforce. We are a multifaceted, international organisation that works as a team to achieve our shared objectives.\r\n- Development opportunities: With us you can build up your expertise. We provide opportunities to support your development throughout every stage of your career.\r\n- Responsibility for people and environment: Our ethical principles embrace people as well as the environment. We are always striving to build a more sustainable future.",
