				"kuvausteksti" : "Are you experienced Software Engineer seeking to expand your experience in a high-tech environment? We are now looking for Software Engineer for our client Biolin Scientific. This is an excellent opportunity to work with customers and colleagues around the world in a relaxed, informal and friendly atmosphere! You will be working on products used by top universities and major companies globally. If you match the requirements, please apply as soon as possible!\r\n\r\nABOUT THE ROLE\r\n\r\nAcademic Work is looking for a Software Engineer for our client Biolin Scientific.\r\n\r\nYou will be recruited to our client company. Academic Work will take care of the recruitment process, therefore candidates are kindly asked to direct all questions to Academic Work hel01@academicwork.fi.\r\n\r\nJOB DUTIES\r\n\r\nIn this position, your task will be develop Windows desktop application software included in all instruments in the portfolio. This includes developing software managing the instruments, presenting data from measurements and developing software tools to analyze data in a Windows environment.\r\n\r\nIt will help to have an understanding of the physics behind the measurement principles, mathematical modeling, etc, but also an awareness of the needs of users and how they want to be able to interact with the instruments. This understanding should be the basis on which a user-friendly software suite is built.\r\n\r\nKeywords: Hardware oriented software development, C/C++, Java, Tech lead ambitions, Windows API\r\n\r\nWHAT WE OFFER\r\n\r\nBiolin Scientific offer high scientific value to their clients, such as top universities and major companies globally. You will be offered an opportunity to work alongside experienced professionals, smart & fun colleagues in an international team. You will be working within instruments that help develop better solutions for energy and materials, as well as perform research at the frontiers of science and technology.\r\n\r\nBiolin Scientific's working environment supports the employees to explore new possibilities, test new ideas and take measured risks - in science, product development and developing new business! At Biolin Scientific they offer you flexible working hours, a good work-life balance and development opportunities (e.g. tech lead).\r\n\r\nWE ARE LOOKING FOR\r\n\r\nWe are looking for a person with a genuine interest in using software as a tool making our technology easily accessible and attractive to customers. Our ideal candidate has a relevant academic background, work experience as a programmer in a high-tech company for some years, and is used to work both independently and in a Scrum team. You have also ambitions on developing yourself into tech lead position. Foremost, you are passionate about making a good product where good is defined from the perspective of the customer.\r\n\r\nApply for this position if you have:\r\n\r\n-MSc in Physics, Electrical engineering, Computer science or equivalent with a strong mathematical interest\r\n-Preferably a few years of work experience as a software developer in a high-tech environment\r\n-Skills in hardware oriented software development\r\n-Implementation skills in C, C++, Java and Windows API.\r\n-Willingness to learn new programming languages and tools as needed\r\n-Tech lead ambitions\r\n-Ability and willingness to work both independently as well as part of a team\r\n-Ability and willingness to learn and work on old code bases, as well as create new ones\r\n-Good command of written and spoken English\r\n\r\nDesirable qualities:\r\n\r\n-High skills in developing SW in Windows OS and experience in different programming languages and tools, e.g. Delphi.\r\n-Experience in Scrum process and continuous integration\r\n-Experience and a genuine interest in signal processing, image processing, scientific computing & numerical analysis\r\n-Experience from electronics and embedded software development\r\n-You have knowledge about modular design and integration into overall system architecture\r\n\r\nTo apply for the job you need to register on our website and then click on \"Apply here\". Remember to attach your CV into your application! We only process applications through our website but if you have questions about the position you can reach us via email in hel01@academicwork.fi. Please write the advert ID in the subject field and paste the advert link in the mail. We are continuously screening and contacting candidates so make sure to send your application as soon as possible. Please note that the advert can be removed prior to the last application dates on our external advertising pages. In the event the advert has been removed it is either due to the process being completed or because we have a sufficient number of qualified applications and are proceeding to the selection/interview phase in the process.\r\n\r\nWe are the Home of the Young Professionals. We are experts in recruitment and staffing university students, recently graduated and professionals in the beginning of their career. You can be employed by us as a consultant in one of our client companies or be recruited directly to our client via our recruitment co-operation. You can read more about us at www.academicwork.fi.\r\n\r\nINFORMATION ABOUT THE COMPANY\r\n\r\nBiolin Scientific is a leading Nordic instrumentation company with roots in Sweden and Finland. Their customers include companies working with pharmaceuticals, energy, chemicals, and advanced materials. They also offer products for academic and governmental research institutes. Biolin Scientific is helping customer to perform research at the frontiers of surface science technology. The company offers world-class know-how, committed to scientific excellence and continuous solution development. They are focusing on working together with the customers and building long-standing relations with a commitment to customer service and application support.\r\n\r\nBiolin Scientific currently has 72 employees globally and distributors in more than 70 countries. Their office in Pohjois-Tapiola is located within a good reach of public transport.",
