				"kuvausteksti" : "ABB is a pioneering technology leader in electrification products, robotics and motion, industrial automation and power grids, serving customers in utilities, industry and transport & infrastructure globally. Continuing more than a 125-year history of innovation, ABB today is writing the future of industrial digitalization and driving the Energy and Fourth Industrial Revolutions. ABB operates in more than 100 countries with about 136,000 employees and of them around 5,100 in Finland. www.abb.com\r\n\r\nWe are looking for a Project Controller at ABB Oy, Process Industries unit in Helsinki or Vaasa. You will be assigned to multiple projects, support project managers in all financial and commercial matters and actively driving the projects' performance. In this position, you will ensure that projects follow sound methodology and execution practices, in accordance with internal standard procedures.\r\n\r\nYour responsibilities\r\n- Supporting project managers in all financial and commercial matters and actively driving project performance\r\n- Leading planning, scheduling and cost control efforts for all project phases\r\n- Maintaining and analyzing actual and forecast schedules, cost and risk\r\n- Monitoring, reporting and managing deviations.\r\n- Participating in project reviews and composing reports.\r\n\r\nWe offer\r\n- A challenging position in an international working environment\r\n- The opportunity for personal development\r\n- The opportunity to further your career in a global company.\r\n\r\nRequirements\r\n- A B.Sc. or M.Sc.in accounting, finance or equivalent\r\n- A few years' experience in project controlling\r\n- Deep knowledge of finance and control processes and tools\r\n- A good understanding of relevant GAAP (local, US, ABB GAAP)\r\n- Advanced computer software knowledge, including of SAP, Microsoft Office tools\r\n Excellent written and spoken communication skills in English and Finnish.\r\n\r\nIdeally, you have\r\n- A proactive attitude and the ability to operate individually and as part of a team",
