				"kuvausteksti" : "Do you want to be a part of digital marketing transformation? Join Nokia's Digital Transformation initiative in Espoo, Finland! We are taking Nokia digital marketing technology solutions to the next level! You will be working with highly skilled individuals across the globe.\r\n\r\nWe are looking for YOU, modern Campaign Strategist, known for your data-driven, analytical and at the same time creative mindset. You are a visionary but still somewhat hands-on, keeping yourself on the pulse of the latest trends and technologies.\r\n\r\nYou will be part of the Campaign Planning & Strategy team which is tasked with developing and executing customer centric campaigns. The person in this role will be responsible for driving increased demand and improved brand awareness of Nokia offerings through best in class campaigns.\r\n\r\nYour Responsibilities\r\n\r\n- Developing an audience based marketing architecture or framework for strategic campaigns\r\n- Building campaign-level strategy, hierarchies/themes, value propositions and messaging architecture, integrated campaign flow, and a customer journey strategy that drive results\r\n- Working with Business Groups (BG) and Regions to define the target personas and its preferences, needs, and challenges\r\n- Translating campaign concepts into succinct and effective strategies and content needs across all stages of the journey\r\n- Working with BG content experts and content strategists to develop a campaign map that aligns to the target audience and buyer journey\r\n- Identifying and adjusting appropriate mix of assets and tactics to engage the audience and generate Marketing Qualified Leads\r\n- Developing cross-channel digital media and communications plans to engage customers across their journey\r\n- Managing the overall campaign budget and delivering measurement/reporting to key stakeholders.\r\n\r\nYour Qualifications and Skills\r\n\r\n- 10+ years' experience in B2B marketing and multifaceted campaigns\r\n- Master's Degree in related fields of study\r\n- Previous experience with digital direct response marketing, search engine marketing, programmatic media buying, and paid social media strongly desired\r\n- Ability to evaluate, negotiate, purchase and plan Internet media on various pricing models\r\n- Working knowledge of media plan development, media negotiations, and buying is essential\r\n- General knowledge of campaign strategy and execution\r\n- Strong communication and analytical skills\r\n- Experience in working across matrix environments and delivering to internal customers\r\n- Excellent command of English, both written and spoken\r\n- Flexibility to travel as needed.\r\n\r\nWe offer you an exciting opportunity to join a team working on digital marketing transformation and the opportunity to grow as a professional - every day. This position gives you a chance to influence how Nokia communicates with our customers and markets our products. Come and join us to give your own input for Nokia's future success!\r\n\r\nDoes this make you tick?\r\n\r\nIf you say yes, please submit your application online no later than 12th of November 2017. For more information about the position, please contact our recruitment partner Sonja Otranen Wednesday between 9 and 11 am +2 CET. Tel +358469221228 or sonja.otranen(at)barona.fi.\r\n\r\nFind out more about Nokia's digital marketing & marketing technology opportunities:\r\nhttps://www.nokia.com/en_int/about-us/careers/currently-seeking/opportunities-in-finland#",
