				"kuvausteksti" : "Do you want to be a part of digital marketing transformation? Join Nokia's Digital Transformation initiative in Espoo, Finland! We are taking Nokia digital marketing technology solutions to the next level! You will be working with highly skilled individuals across the globe.\r\n\r\nWe are looking for YOU, modern Customer Insights Manager, known for your data-driven, analytical and at the same time creative mindset. You are a visionary but still hands-on, keeping yourself on the pulse of the latest trends and technologies.\r\n\r\nYou will be part of the Campaign Planning & Strategy team which is tasked with developing and executing customer centric campaigns. The person in this role will develop insights to inform marketing and overarching business strategy to help drive demand generation goals.\r\n\r\nYour responsibilities\r\n\r\n- Collaborate closely with GTM & Strategic Planner and Campaign Strategist to analyze and identify opportunities to transform quantitative and qualitative insights into customer-centric campaign strategies\r\n- Collaborate with researchers, reporting leads and data sciences to deliver a holistic view of customers through primary and secondary research - integrating behavioral and attitudinal data\r\n- Understand key business priorities, drivers and hypotheses, in order to deliver actionable insights and recommendations on channel mix and investments (and/or propose new areas for investigation)\r\n- Partner with Strategy leads, Business Group (BG) Marketing and Campaign teams to develop comprehensive insight agendas and to translate into relevant research / analytics roadmaps\r\n- Help tell the customer story in a consistent and digestible way, so that business partners have a clear understanding of customer behaviors, attitudes and needs\r\n- Impact persona building and Learning & Measurement plans with an informed perspective based on facts\r\n- Play a significant role in unifying Nokia's market research capabilities to deliver high quality analysis and insights\r\n- Understand industry and key competitor best practices and our overall competitive position and Develop improvement action plans with the business.\r\n\r\nYour Qualifications and Skills\r\n\r\n- 8+ years of relevant experience in marketing research & analysis; experience in telecom, high-tech or software are a plus\r\n- Bachelor's Degree in related fields of study\r\n- Experience in running multiple complex projects, numerous internal teams and a myriad of external vendors\r\n- Strong analytical and interpretive skills with the ability to distill copious amounts of data (qualitative, quantitative, secondary etc.) into an insightful story with actionable recommendations\r\n- Passionate about moving from data and insight to action and impact with a sense of urgency\r\n- Executive presence when presenting to key partners across the organization\r\n- Highly collaborative and demonstrated ability to work closely across both marketing and cross-functional teams.\r\n\r\nWe offer you an exciting opportunity to join a team working on digital marketing transformation and the opportunity to grow as a professional - every day. This position gives you a chance to influence how Nokia communicates with our customers and markets our products. Come and join us to give your own input for Nokia's future success!\r\n\r\nDoes this make you tick?\r\n\r\nIf you say yes, please submit your application online no later than 12th of November 2017. For more information about the position, please contact our recruitment partner Sonja Otranen Wednesday between 9 and 11 am +2 CET. Tel +358469221228 or sonja.otranen(at)barona.fi.\r\n\r\nFind out more about Nokia's digital marketing & marketing technology opportunities:\r\nhttps://www.nokia.com/en_int/about-us/careers/currently-seeking/opportunities-in-finland#",
