				"kuvausteksti" : "Do you want to work for creating better and happier workplaces? Want to join our journey to conquer the world with, well, phone booths?\r\n\r\n\r\nAbout us:\r\n\r\nFramery makes soundproof phone booths and meeting pods for open-plan offices. Our award-winning design products solve the noise problem in the open office, making work more efficient and the employees more satisfied. The hi-tech solution is proven right by dozens of world's leading brands who are our repeat customers. Framery is one of the fastest-growing companies in Finland with a revenue rising to about 18 million euros in 2016 from 5.1 million in 2015.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nAbout the job:\r\n\r\nFramery is now looking for an eager and organized Buyer to join our troops in Tampere, Finland. Working closely with the Sourcing team, Buyer works to ensure the material stock for our production is always on an ideal level and the materials find their way from the supplier to the right place in Framery smoothly.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nTasks include:\r\n- Material planning\r\n- Purchases of production components\r\n- Coordinating logistics \r\n- Co-operating closely with suppliers and other subsidiaries\r\n- Developing sourcing processes\r\n\r\n\r\nAbout you:\r\n- Applicable degree of education (for example in business or technical)\r\n- Previous experience of similar tasks\r\n- Fluency in both Finnish and English. Other language skills are seen as a plus.\r\n- Proactive \"self-starter\" attitude with \"get it done\" mentality\r\n- Organized working style and strong communications skills\r\n- Readiness to jump, every now and then, into the company swimming pool with colleagues\r\n\r\n\r\nWe offer a once-in-a-lifetime chance to join an amazing growth story in an ambitious but joyful working culture. As experts in happy workplaces, we take the well-being of our employees very seriously. This means, among other things, high-class benefits and amenities. We aim to be no less than the best workplace in Finland. Join the phone booth revolution now - you won't regret it!\r\n\r\nPlease send your application through the link below as soon as possible, latest on Sunday 12.11.2017 as we will proceed with most potential candidates quickly. Applications sent through the link will be added to our recruitment system, which is our primary channel when recruiting new co-workers so please do not email the application.\r\n\r\nThe job is fulltime and we hope to get you as our colleague as soon as possible! Regarding any questions or additional information about the task please contact Sourcing Director Jaakko Luhtasela by phone +358 505 024 626 on Tuesdays 31.10. and 7.11. or Thursdays 2.11. and 9.11. or by email jaakko.luhtasela@frameryacoustics.com. If you have questions about the hiring process please contact HR Manager Anni Lamminen by phone +358 407 054 335 on Wednesday 8.11. at 15-16 or by email anni.lamminen@frameryacoustics.com.\r\n\r\n\r\nKeywords:\r\nTampere, sourcing, purchasing, recruitment, phonebooth",
