				"kuvausteksti" : "Do you want to work actively with cutting Carbon emissions where it really counts? Does using Big Data & IoT to optimize industrial multi Mega Watt systems using as much electricity as a smaller city sound interesting? Do you have the technical background and analytical edge that is required to master this ? Then this is your chance. Academic Work is now looking for a System Data Analyst to our client Enersize Oyj, a fast growing, compressed air efficiency software developer. Send your application today!\r\n\r\nABOUT THE ROLE\r\n\r\nAcademic Work is looking for a fulltime System Data Analyst to our client Enersize Oyj.\r\n\r\nThis position will start as a staffing position for the first 12 months, with the possibility of continuing as a full-time permanent employee employed directly by Enersize Oyj. This means that for the first 12 months you will be employed by Academic Work and work as a consultant at Enersize Oyj.\r\n\r\nJOB DUTIES\r\n\r\nIn this position, you will work with several compressed air efficiency projects as a System Data Analyst for our client Enersize Oyj. Your work duties include Big Data and technical system analysis as well as planning and support for our on-site optimization teams . You will also participate in analysis tool development and give input from the user perspective to the R&D team. You will be offered a sound introduction into your role and you will have your colleagues support throughout.\r\n\r\nThis position suits you who have an interested in complex technical systems as well as the latest in computer driven analysis. You will be a part of a small, relaxed team in an interesting and dynamic work environment. You have the possibility to work partially remotely once your expertise develops.\r\n\r\nWE ARE LOOKING FOR\r\n\r\nOur ideal candidate has a suitable education within automation, process or machinery engineering. You have preferably already some practical work experience in e.g. automation engineering or process industries, and a good understanding of computer driven data analysis. In this position, you can be a seasoned veteran of data analytics or someone who has the right technical background and attitude. Succeeding in this position requires creativity, analytical thinking, strong technical understanding as well as structured work methods and good communication skills. Furthermore, you are also ambitious, eager to learn more and a good team player.\r\n\r\nApply for this position if you have:\r\n\r\n- Suitable academic and/or practical background\r\n- Some work experience related to automation engineering or process industries\r\n- Interest in Big Data analytics and eagerness to learn more and develop yourself\r\n- Strong technical understanding and analytical thinking\r\n- Skilled in written communication and structured work methods,\r\n- Fluent skills in English\r\n\r\nIn this role, proficiency in Finnish, Swedish and/or Chinese is an asset. It is also seen as an advantage if you have already some work experience related to compressed air systems or similar.\r\n\r\nIn this position you will be employed by Academic Work and we take care of all the legal responsibilities of an employer such as salary payments, insurances and health care. It is important for us that you feel well and perform in your job. Your consultant manager will be in regular contact with you during the assignment and guides you on your career. Academic Work is an authorized staffing and recruitment agency and our employees are extremely satisfied, something that we are very proud of. We are here to help you succeed!\r\n\r\nINFORMATION ON THE APPLICATION PROCESS\r\n\r\nTo apply for the job click on \"Apply here\" below. Remember to attach your CV into your application! We only handle applications through our website but if you have questions about the position you can reach us via email in esp02@academicwork.fi. Please write the advert ID in the subject and paste the advert link in the mail. We are continuously screening and contacting candidates so make sure to send your application as soon as possible. Please notice that the advert can be removed before eventual last dates on our external advertising pages. When the advert is being removed it's either due to that the processes is finished or because we have many qualified applications and are continuing in the selection/interview phase.\r\n\r\nWe are the Home of the Young Professionals. We are experts in recruitment and staffing university students, recently graduated and professionals in the beginning of their career. You can be employed by us as a consultant in one of our client companies or be recruited directly to our client via our recruitment co-operation. You can read more about us at www.academicwork.fi.\r\n\r\nWhen employed at Academic Work you will have your own dedicated Consultant Manager, whose role is to answer your questions, support your career development and ensure you enjoy your place of work.\r\n\r\nINFORMATION ABOUT THE COMPANY\r\n\r\nEnersize is a fast-growing, publicly listed software provider in the compressed air efficiency market, and currently focused on more advanced automated analytics and monitoring using artificial intelligence and machine learning. Enersize achieves up to 30% energy savings in industrial compressed air systems. 90% of all manufacturing plants utilize compressed air and it consumes 5% of global electricity. Enerize is a global leader in developing and using advanced Big Data analysis to optimize these systems.\r\n\r\nEnersize head office is located in Helsinki and the company has an advanced research department in Lund, Sweden. Enersize has extensive sales representation in China.\r\n\r\nEnersize mission is to become the global leader in compressed air efficiency software. Join us and be part of our dynamic crew in the journey.\r\n\r\n Apply here: https://www.academicwork.fi/avoimet-tyopaikat/system-data-analyst-to-work-with-compressed-air-efficiency-software/14995959",
