				"kuvausteksti" : "Finago is a part of Accountor Group's software division. Overall, we employ almost 200 experts in for example financial management, software development and sales. Over 1.300 accounting offices in Finland, Sweden, Norway and Denmark uses our products, Procountor and Tikon. We are market leaders in the field of financial management. \r\n\r\n  \r\nWe are hiring new team members to our team of Test Engineers to develop our web-based financial management software Procountor in Keilaniemi, Espoo \r\n\r\nJob description\r\n\r\nYou will be working with the designing and testing of the changes made on Procountor. As we utilize test automation in our work, your role will also include coding and scripting. You will also work with manually testing our software.\r\n\r\nOur core codebase is mostly written in Java, and we use the open-source Vaadin framework for providing a beautiful front-end to the end-user. For UI test automation, we are using Selenium and JBehave Framework. Other key technologies include MySQL, JUnit, Jenkins, Docker, Ansible and Git. You can also have a look at our current public APIs by visiting dev.procountor.com\r\n\r\nWe embrace Scrum We realize that a process is never perfect and always strive to make improvements wherever possible. Our development team consist of over 50 people - family of developers, testers, UX designers and domain experts all tightly working together for a common goal. \r\n\r\nQualifications\r\n\r\nKeys to success\r\nA good candidate has solid background in software testing and is always yearning to learn more. \r\n\r\nYou also\r\n- have a proven track record of software testing\r\n- are familiar with relational databases, SQL and web-based software\r\n- communicate fluently with Finnish and/or English both orally and in writing\r\n\r\nWe also value\r\n- experience is test automation\r\n- knowledge of financial management, ERP and/or CRM systems\r\n- knowledge of Scrum methodologies\r\n- prior knowledge of tools/technologies that we are currently utilizing \r\n\r\nYou are self-imposed and have a solution-focused attitude. To succeed in this position, you need to be able to work as part of a team and take responsibility as a team member. In autonomous teams every team member is responsible for getting work done. You do not hesitate to ask for help or to help others. As a colleague you are friendly and fun to work with. \r\n\r\nBenefits\r\n\r\nOur aim is to be the best employer in our industry\r\nWe believe that motivated and happy people are the main ingredient in our success story. We have built ourselves an environment that supports wellbeing at work, professional development and work-life balance. We offer for example flexible working hours, good working ergonomics and benefits of sport and recreation. Additionally, we hold numerous events every year, including sports, culture and other bigger or smaller occasions for celebration. Fast growing company with international endeavors provides good opportunities for professional learning and career development. Our recently renovated office is very pleasant environment to spend your days working.\r\n\r\n\r\nMore information\r\n\r\nWould you like to hear more?\r\nPlease don't hesitate to contact Jarmo Krohns, he is happy tell you more about us. You can contact Jarmo via email jarmo.krohns@finago.com or by phone +358 50 569 6043. \r\n\r\nIf you are ready to apply, please submit your cover letter and resume with a salary request via email to finago@poolia.fi. The application process is handled by our recruitment partner Poolia Suomi Oy. \r\n\r\nThe start date of new contracts can be agreed separately. The contract of employment will be made between the chosen candidate(s) and Finago.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nContact\r\n\r\nJarmo Krohns\r\n\r\njarmo.krohns@finago.com\r\n+358 50 569 6043\r\n\r\nYou can submit your cover letter and resume with a salary request via email to finago@poolia.fi",
