				"kuvausteksti" : "With offices in 80 countries, Manpower is one of the largest contingent and permanent staffing firms globally, and the market leader in the Nordic and Baltic countries. In Finland we are one of the largest companies specializing in recruitment, temporary staffing and assessments. We help employers find competent and motivated professionals for interim and permanent positions at all organizational levels. We serve our clients and candidates across the nation. Manpower is an authorized private employment agency.\r\n\r\n\r\nWe are looking for a CHEMISTRY ENGINEER for our client in Olkiluoto. Work starts as soon as possible and the duration is 12 months.\r\n\r\nJob description:\r\n\r\n- Chemcical surveillance of the nuclear and conventional circuits of the nuclear power plant\r\n- Following of the chemistry handbook\r\n- Guarantee the chemical parameters in the technical specification\r\n- Documentation of the chemical surveillance\r\n- Optimization of the resin use\r\n- Optimization of the lithium use\r\n- Preservation of fluid systems\r\n- Planning and supervision of the nuclear waste handling\r\n- Leading and training of the chemical and laboratory teams\r\n- The work will include working in radiological controlled zone and shift work.\r\n\r\nRequirements:\r\n\r\n- Chemical Engineering Degree\r\n- 5 years experience in radiological chemistry of a running nuclear power plant with pressurized water reactor\r\n- Experience in laboratory work in a running nuclear power plant\r\n- Knowledge of all chemical laboratory methods needede in a nuclear power plant\r\n- Leadership skills and experience\r\n\r\nSkills required:\r\n\r\n- MS Officer programs\r\n- Knowledge of all chemical and radiological laws, guidelines (finnish national and European)\r\n- Basic knowledge of the EPR technology\r\n- Deep knowledge in pressurizer water reactor technology and chemistry\r\n- English (fluent)\r\n\r\nWe are offering you a challenging position with a competitive salary!\r\n\r\nInterested? Apply for this job with your registered CV by clicking \"Hae\".\r\n\r\nFor more information (Mon-Fri 9-10) contact Recruitment Consultant Merja Nevalainen, p. 050 501 0031",
