				"kuvausteksti" : "With offices in 80 countries, Manpower is one of the largest contingent and permanent staffing firms globally, and the market leader in the Nordic and Baltic countries. In Finland we are one of the largest companies specializing in recruitment, temporary staffing and assessments. We help employers find competent and motivated professionals for interim and permanent positions at all organizational levels. We serve our clients and candidates across the nation. Manpower is an authorized private employment agency.\r\n\r\n\r\nWe are looking for a Design Handover Engineer - Team Leader for our client in Olkiluoto. Work starts as soon as possible and the duration is 12 months.\r\n\r\nThis position is to check that all the technical documents expected from the Suppliers for engineering and manufacturing  contracts are received before the Supplier's contract is closed.\r\n\r\nThis check is to be performed against a list of documents provided by the Suppliers or technical specifications and requisition files.\r\n\r\nThe resource is also to check that\r\n\r\n-    There is no open point remaining on those documents and that they are in an as-built status\r\n-    And that those documents were provided in native format\r\n-    Metadata of those documents also need to be checked\r\n-    The resource is to fill in check lists to indicate that the check was performed as requested\r\n\r\nSkills required:\r\n\r\n-    Engineer/Technician able to handle several activities, understanding of technical and quality documents\r\n-    Previous experience at OL3 project (prefer)\r\n-    Multi-tasks, autonomous, rigorous, good communication skills\r\n-    Proficient with Excel\r\n-    Electrical or mechanical engineering experience\r\n-    Good level of English is required, other language skills (Finnish, German, French) are beneficial.\r\n\r\nWe are offering you a challenging position with a competitive salary!\r\n\r\nInterested? Apply for this job with your registered CV by clicking \"Hae\".\r\n\r\nFor more information (Mon-Fri 9-10) contact Recruitment Consultant Merja Nevalainen, p. 050 501 0031",
