				"kuvausteksti" : "Technical Manager in Event Production (Tallinn)\r\n\r\nNJ Production designs and implements unique business events in the Nordic-Baltic region and around the world. We focus on building strong relationships with both our clients and our partners. We have more than 15 years of experience in organising conferences and meetings. We are now looking for a TECHNICAL MANAGER.\r\n\r\nThis is a lead role in the technical production across a wide range of events from brief to on-site delivery.\r\n\r\nKEY RESPONSIBILITIES:\r\n Putting together technical solutions\r\n Estimating technical budgets\r\n Drawing preliminary 2D and 3D floorplans\r\n\r\nWE EXPECT\r\n Good understanding of technical requirements and restrictions of complex AV-systems\r\n Good knowledge of planning and using complex AV-setups \r\n Comfortable around computers and cloud services \r\n System design and 3D-drawing software: Sketchup or similar\r\n Basic video editing skills\r\n Fluency in English\r\n\r\nWHY NJ?\r\n International clients and global events\r\n Passionate and highly motivated team \r\n High quality productions \r\n Motivating salary\r\n Possibilities to adjust the work description depending on your competencies\r\n\r\nSounds interesting? Send us CV and motivation letter no later than 15th of November.\r\nContact person: Kadri Eller (+372 56921901, kadri.eller@atalent.ee)",
