				"kuvausteksti" : "In keeping with our brand promise \"Engineering with a difference\", Etteplan takes a different attitude to embedded system and IoT solutions - something our customers confirm time and time again. We are proud of our expertise and our ability to impact our customers' success. \r\n\r\nYour expertise matters to us - come join our success story!\r\n\r\n\r\nAre you interested in test system development? Do you enjoy working in product development and want continuously develop yourself in a global environment?\r\n\r\n \r\nWe are searching for a Software Developer to strengthen our team in our Hyvinkää, Vantaa or Espoo office. Your role is to develop software by using LabVIEW and TestStand and you also need to be ready to play with instruments and various customer products. Assembly of test systems is familiar to you, as well.\r\n\r\n \r\nTo succeed in this role we wish you to have\r\n- B.Sc. in Electronics or equivalent education\r\n- Experience in LabVIEW and TestStand\r\n- Understanding of instrument controls  \r\n- Understanding of electronics  \r\n- Hands-on attitude  \r\n- Open-minded service attitude  \r\n- Willingness to learn new things  \r\n- Possibility to travel\r\n\r\nWe appreciate\r\n- Experience in PLC programming  \r\n- Experience in other programming languages  \r\n- Finnish language skills  \r\n\r\nEtteplan offers interesting scale of products from medical to industrial and anything between to work with. We serve local and global companies worldwide and the results of Etteplan's innovative engineering can be seen in numerous industrial solutions and everyday products. Wide range of experts and highly experienced professionals help you in learning and support your daily tasks. Above all, you get a chance to feel professional pride in job well done.\r\n\r\nEtteplan is Finland's biggest employer in industrial engineering, technical product information, embedded systems and IoT solutions. We offer a vantage point to international industry, serving top players in their specific fields of expertise. With Etteplan you will gain a deeper insight into their products.\r\n\r\nWe are a genuine engineering house: our Group employs around 2,800 experts mainly in Finland, Sweden, the Netherlands, Germany, Poland and China - most of them engineers. Our success is based on our competence and our knowledgeable staff, both of which we take good care of. \r\n\r\nEtteplan offers interesting and challenging tasks in a growing working community in 30 locations around Finland. The work involved in customers' varied and demanding projects means constant learning and development.",
