				"kuvausteksti" : "Nets is one of northern Europe's leading companies for payment solutions, information services and digital security solutions, with one of the most extensive and innovative product portfolios in Europe. Our ambition is to become an even stronger partner to our customers by supporting their business nationally as well as internationally. We want to make the handling of both financial and information assets easier and more secure. Nets employs over 2,700 people and has its registered office in Copenhagen, as well as competence and commercial centres in Oslo, Stockholm, Helsinki and Tallinn. Find out more about us at www.nets.eu.\r\n\r\n\r\nAre you passionate professional of customer service?\r\n\r\nYou can now be part of Nets Contact Centre Finland team and work with 15 customer service professionals. Customer Service is one of the Nets' key strengths.\r\n- we provide expert and quality service for merchants.\r\n\r\nWe are looking for one employee, who is able to work at different working hours, both on weekdays and on weekends. Employment is permanent and the work will begin in February 2018.\r\n\r\nWant to be our new colleague and fill in an important role?\r\n\r\nYour main responsibility will be to handle and answer our customers' (merchants) inquiries and to provide excellent and expert customer service to our customers. Service language is Finnish, but also Swedish and English skills are required.\r\n\r\nYour key responsibility areas are:\r\n- Customer service: phone, emails and later on chat etc.\r\n- Daily and weekly Lean Performance board meetings (and giving suggestions how to improve the customer service work)\r\n- Work task development\r\n- Other tasks given by manager\r\n\r\nWe are looking for talents with ambitions - and passion for what they are doing!\r\nWork in a challenging customer service requires the ability to advise and guide customers. Performing a task requires active work, continuous development of your own competence and the ability to understand and take into account large entities.\r\n\r\nTo succeed in this position we expect you to be:\r\n- Organised way of working\r\n- Service minded and customer focused and understand of customer needs\r\n- Goal oriented\r\n- Flexibility, ability to adapt and react to change\r\n- We also appreciate the following features:  You are a positive, genuinely interested in customer service and want to develop in your job.\r\n\r\nYour competences & experiences are:\r\n- Relevant working experience in customer service\r\n- Customer oriented and a strong ability to combine operational understanding of processes with the subsequent impact on end customers\r\n- Great communicator in both written and spoken\r\n- Strong Finnish, Swedish and English language skills required\r\n- Knowledge of the business area is a benefit\r\n- Ability to work under pressure\r\n- Ability to work in shifts during the weekdays and weekends.\r\n\r\nYour career driven by curiosity and customer insights\r\n\r\nAt Nets, we are working towards realizing a one-company approach to development, innovation and doing business, where you'll be encouraged to think across borders and business areas to find new ways of merging our products, new technologies and market trends into innovative new solutions.\r\n\r\nWe want to attract, develop and engage the best talent, which means that at Nets, you will be working with colleagues across the Nordics. Whether it is innovation or operation that makes you tick, our company structure allows you to build your own career and grow in a business that encompasses all aspects of the digital payment value chain. We work in a thriving environment characterized by team play and informality and with plenty of social activities within sports, culture and social network.\r\n\r\nApply with registered CV as soon as possible by clicking \"Hae/Apply\". Interviews will begin immediately and the position will be filled as soon as the right candidate is found.\r\n\r\nWith offices in 80 countries, Manpower is one of the largest contingent and permanent staffing firms globally, and the market leader in the Nordic and Baltic countries. In Finland we are one of the largest companies specializing in recruitment, temporary staffing and assessments. We help employers find competent and motivated professionals for interim and permanent positions at all organizational levels. We serve our clients and candidates across the nation. Manpower is an authorized private employment agency.",
