				"kuvausteksti" : "Does working with the best game studios in the world sound good? Can you handle project management and sales of software products? If that's the case then definitely get in touch! EasyAntiCheat is looking for a Project Manager!\r\n\r\nWorking time: Fulltime, Flexible\r\nLength: Permanent \r\nLocation: Helsinki \r\nRequested starting date: As soon as possible, negotiable\r\nDL for applications: 13.11.2017\r\n\r\nEasyAntiCheat was established by entrepreneurial gamers in 2013 and exists around a shared love of gaming, excellence, and technology. As a fast-growing startup, EasyAntiCheat today provides game security services to over 50 PC games in collaboration with over 35 game studios. We are currently looking to grow the team significantly as we are branching out with new services beyond anti-cheat. These services build upon the existing infrastructure that already serves over 40 million users and gives us unmatched ability to provide state of the art tools for the PC gaming industry. If all of this gives you the good kind of goosebumps and you'd love to be involved with scaling our integration efforts to AAA and indie game studios alike, reach out and apply!\r\n\r\nAt EasyAntiCheat you will join a great team full of self-driven people with strong work ethic who also know how to have serious fun. We're expecting fast and exciting growth in the years ahead of us and offer an opportunity to work in a true tech startup culture where you'll have the ability to affect what processes and tools are used in your work.\r\n\r\nNow we are looking for a Project Manager for game integration projects. In this role you will get to organize and coordinate all the moving parts of development to ensure the process is running smoothly. You'll bridge our highly agile Kanban-based product development teams with game studios, publishers, and sales. \r\n\r\nSupporting the technical execution and sales of our projects, you'll work with the team to make sure they can get their work done efficiently and in alignment with customer schedules. Your approach is collaborative and team-focused, in line with EAC's flat and organic company structure. You have a healthy attitude towards feedback and continuous learning.\r\n\r\nTasks: \r\n\r\nPlan and oversee integration projects in collaboration with game studios\r\nTechnical support in sales meetings, both in calls and on-site with customers\r\nManage relationships with the network of global agents and partners\r\nIdentify, evaluate, and communicate project risks as they appear in the development cycle\r\nDrive delivery by both our internal and the customer engineering teams\r\nMaintain relationships with key customers on ongoing basis\r\n\r\nQualifications:\r\n\r\nPassionate multiplayer PC gamer\r\nHighly organized, always planning ahead\r\nKnowledge & understanding of software and game development processes\r\nExperience in scoping, managing & executing multiple projects simultaneously\r\nCultural awareness to serve the global customer base\r\nStellar communication, both written and verbal\r\nEnglish\r\n\r\nWhat we offer: \r\n\r\nChallenging work with great opportunities to learn and apply your skills\r\nInternational work with trips to customers and conferences\r\nAn opportunity to become part of industry groups and collaborate with the great minds at many of our varying partner organizations in the gaming industry\r\nFreedom to do your work when and how you like, as long as it is done well\r\nExcellent insurance coverage, with private health and dental care\r\nRelaxed and flexible working environment at our awesome office space in Ruoholahti\r\n\r\n\r\nRead more about what it's like to work at EasyAntiCheat from our blog in here: https://atalent.fi/blog/talent-of-august-richard-deist-easyanticheat/ \r\n\r\nAnd be sure to also check EasyAntiCheat's presentation on their anti-cheat from Steam DevDays here: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hI7V60r7Jco \r\n\r\nSounds good? If you're the person we're looking for, send by latest 13th of November your CV, application in a PDF format and relevant samples of your projects here: https://apply.atalent.fi/easyanticheat-project-manager-game-integration-10-2017.\r\n\r\nYou can read more about EasyAntiCheat at https://www.easyanticheat.net/ If you have questions about the application process, please contact Recruitment Manager Mia Paatsalo (mia.paatsalo(at)atalent.fi +358 50 468 0610",
