				"kuvausteksti" : "Is retail business the thing for you? Are you ready to roll up your sleeves and work in good company? We are constantly building new and adapting to changing environment.  Our present Service Manager transfers to new position in our group and now we are looking for an experienced RtoR Finance Service Manager to our Shared Service Center (SSC) in Tampere.\r\n\r\nYour job:\r\n\r\nYou will work for K common services in Kesko Shared Service Center. Your main duties as a RtoR Finance Service Manager and as a member of SSC's operational management team are:\r\n\r\n- effective organizing and leading of RtoR services in SSC \r\n- controls, quality and timetables of RtoR process  \r\n- managing closing process and financial reporting in group company level\r\n- participation in group level development initiatives and co-operation with group accounting and customer companies' financial organizations\r\n\r\n\r\nEdellytämme sinulta\r\n\r\nWe are looking for a person who has \r\n\r\n- degree in Economics: Finance / Accounting and minimum 5 years of relevant experience / auditing background is an advantage \r\n- strong proof of abilities to perform successfully in similar positions\r\n- excellent knowledge on accounting relevant legislation and requirements (FAS, IFRS, VAT, Tax, etc)\r\n- strong leadership experience - co-operation ability with different personalities and ability to work in the matrix organization\r\n- previous experience in SAP and its functionalities including FICO, IHC, ERP - solutions\r\n- hard work and challenges - that's what you like!\r\n\r\n\r\nTarjoamme sinulle\r\n\r\nWhat we offer: \r\n\r\n- modern accounting environment and top modern tools and all the time developing technical environment (incl. robotics)\r\n- professional RtoR teams with good team spirit \r\n- supportive and co-operative colleagues \r\n- very interesting and challenging work in renewed K-Group\r\n\r\nWorking for K Group \r\nThe about 45,000 exceptionally nice people of K Group work daily to make shopping fun for customers in our stores in the Nordic countries, the Baltic countries, Poland and Russia. We help our more than 1,500 stores serve their customers in the grocery trade, the building and technical trade, and the car trade. We do our work with big heart while paying attention to society and the environment. We are already the most responsible food retailer in the world and are constantly trying out something new. We are doing this to provide good choices both on the shelves of the local stores and online.\r\n\r\n\r\nKiinnostuitko?\r\n\r\nVoit hakea tehtävää rekisteröimällä hakemuksesi ja CV:si palkkatoiveineen osoitteessa www.staffpoint.fi/executive. \r\n\r\nLisätietoja tehtävästä antaa StaffPoint Executiven konsultti Heidi Tuomikorpi p. 043-8243261\r\n31.10. klo 9-11, 2.11. klo 15-16, 7.11. 9-11, 9.11. klo 15-16.\r\n\r\n\r\nLisätietoja\r\n\r\nHeidi Tuomikorpi\r\nSenior Consultant\r\nStaffPoint Oy    Ruoholahdenkatu 14    00180 Helsinki\r\np. 043-824 3261\r\nheidi.tuomikorpi@staffpoint.fi    www.staffpoint.fi",
