				"kuvausteksti" : "Now we are looking for a\n\nQA Manager, Test Automation\n\nYou will have a key role in our product development team and you are responsible for the quality assurance of our products. You tasks includes QA processes, metrics and objectives, test management, test planning and execution of automated tests. You will also be responsible of test suite and test tools. You work closely with the development teams and give guidance on how to utilize the testing framework and existing test code.\n\nResponsibilities:\n\n   -Improve quality assurance processes and documentation\n   -Define test methods and create test plans for new and updated product features to determine if the software will perform appropriately\n   -Review code, develop, and execute various exploratory and automated tests to ensure product quality requirements\n   -Support software developers to implement QA procedures, tools and processes\n\nTo be successful in this role, we expect you to have:\n\n   -Previous experience from test automation, test management and test planning\n   -Experience from team leading or line management\n   -Strong knowledge of Java or Python and good technical understanding of Linux and Windows environments\n   -Good knowledge of test tools and methods ( E.g Robot, Jenkins, Ansible, Selenium,\n   -Amazon AWS, Tomcat, Wildfly)\n   -Good communication skills\n\nInterested?\n\nSubmit your application by 15th of November at the latest. For more information, please contact Ville Saviluoto, Barona IT, 040 869 0180 or ville.saviluoto@barona.fi.",
