				"kuvausteksti" : "Design Engineer, Mechanical\r\n\r\nOur business is growing and we are now looking for a Mechanical Design Engineer in our Power Solutions team in Turku.  \r\n\r\nIn this role, you will be designing cable harness assemblies and mechanical components. Typical customer project consists of harness design for large industrial machinery. \r\n\r\nAn ideal candidate would have some experience in mechanical design engineering by Siemens NX tool from previous work history or through studies. In this position you would have an independent role but you would have the support of the team close-by.\r\n\r\nYour main tasks will be:\r\n- Cable harness and component design in global projects\r\n- Regular project communication with the customer \r\n\r\nRequirements:\r\n- M.Sc. or B.Sc. in Mechanical Engineering \r\n- Siemens NX tools knowledge, modelling and drafting\r\n- Strong organising and problem solving skills\r\n- Good communication skills in English and Finnish or Swedish\r\n\r\nWe appreciate:\r\n- Siemens Teamcenter knowledge  \r\n- Experience in electromechanical and mechanical design work \r\n- Ability to read and understand electrical wiring diagrams\r\n\r\nWe can offer you:\r\n- Interesting work in close connection with the customer\r\n- Chance for professional development through our multi-discipline engineering projects for our industrial customers\r\n- Skilled colleagues and friendly atmosphere\r\n\r\nFor more information, please contact Kenneth Edsvik, Manager, Power Engineering +358 50 345 2399.\r\n\r\nWant to join our team of experts! Apply at www.citec.com/careers by 19th November, 2017.",
