				"kuvausteksti" : "Elektrobit is building car of the future! We are now offering exciting career opportunities in growing automotive business at every career level. EB Automotive Finland is established three years ago, and today we have over one hundred software professionals working with us. We are growing steadily and have openings for various AWESOME CAR AND MOBILITY DEVELOPER roles in our appreciated technology site located in Oulu Technology Village.\r\n\r\n\r\nThis is how our developers describe their work and responsibilities at EB:\r\n\r\nSW EXPERTS AND SENIOR SW DEVELOPERS:\r\n\"Working as a Senior SW Engineer at Elektrobit in AUTOSAR AdaptiveCore project is rewarding because I can develop embedded software with C++ to the next car I'll buy. What makes this job even more rewarding is great colleagues, interesting industry and possibility to work in an international environment. Usual day can consist of architecture designing, programming, integration activities, travelling and of course coffee drinking. Not one day is similar to another! \" - Heikki\r\n\"I'm a Senior Software Developer at EB working in a Linux Distribution team. I'm bringing the latest and greatest Open Source Software to the future vehicles. My toolbox includes Yocto, Python, Bash and a bunch of other languages and OSS tools. I like working for EB, thanks to great colleagues and office atmosphere.\" - Markku A.\r\n\r\nJUNIOR SW DEVELOPERS:\r\n\"I started my work as a summer trainee and have seen that Elektrobit offers great possibilities for young professionals to learn and develop skills that are for sure useful during the whole upcoming career. Supportive and fun colleagues make it both easy to enjoy your job and become more talented. If you are still studying, do not be afraid - job and studies can be combined so it is possible to graduate and change the way we drive our cars at the same time!\" \r\n- Krista V.\r\n\r\nYour profile:\r\n- A solid \"yes WE can\" attitude and strong team player mentality\r\n- Will to learn\r\n- To enjoy variety in your work due to the nature of project work\r\n- Good written and spoken English and courage to use it with your colleagues globally\r\n- Good sense of humor - we love to have fun and laugh with each other\r\n- KEYWORDS FOR TECHNICAL PROFILE: C++, CMake, Linux, Yocto, HTTP, JSON, Continuous Integration, DevOps, Java, Qt, QML, Software integration \r\n\r\nInterested?\r\nPlease send your application in English via our Jobportal  at your earliest convenience.\r\n\r\nFor more information, you may contact our Team Managers:\r\nJukka.Lahti@elektrobit.com  / +358 40 344 5927,\r\nJukka.Schroderus@elektrobit.com / +358 40 344 5901 or \r\nHeikki.Pietila@elektrobit.com / +358 40 344 5971\r\n\r\nWe look forward to receiving your application!",
