				"kuvausteksti" : "We are looking for a PROCUREMENT PLANNER\r\nThe position is temporary covering a sick leave, 1.12.2017 - 13.4.2018.\r\nWe are looking for a good team player, who has a strong understanding of supply chain processes and procurement, to be responsible for procurement planning.\r\nYour main tasks include planning and ensuring timely purchases and a constant inbound flow in co-operation with forwarding companies, managing the material inventory levels, optimizing service levels and minimizing working capital. You will also maintain procurement related master data, solve system related issues and report to different stakeholders.\r\nYou have a technical or economical Bachelor's degree, or minimum of five years' experience of procurement. You are fluent in written and spoken Finnish and English. Good knowledge of MS Office tools and some ERP system are necessary, SAP knowledge is preferred.\r\nYou are a self-driven and result oriented person with capability to complete actions and ability to organize your own work environment and schedule according to different variables from various stakeholders. Flexible and open minded attitude towards new requirements and situations, as well as, an ability to make decisions independently and good interaction with people are essential.\r\nWe offer you a challenging job with good development opportunities in a growing international company. For further information, please contact HR Manager Anna Näri, +358 40 748 6887, Monday 30.10.2017 at 9.30 -10.30 or Tuesday 7.11.2017, at 9.00 -11. 00.  Please send you application latest by November, 10, 2017",
