				"kuvausteksti" : "Come work with us - we are looking for skilled professional to build success with us!\r\n\r\nWe are looking for a dynamic and enthusiastic new member to join our laboratory in the R&D Department at our head office in Nokia, Finland. Position is a temporary until December 2018. Are you a hands-on and analytical minded laboratory professional? Do you want to be part of laboratory team with versatile measurement capabilities and interesting field of analytes.\r\n\r\nWe're looking for you, a Laboratory Analyst, to work in laboratory in our Material Development R&D unit.\r\n\r\nMaterial Development develops new compounds and controls the quality of materials used in production. Laboratory has wide variety of testing equipment for physical and analytical testing of compounds and raw materials. Your role will be an important part of raw material quality control and requires active collaboration with different organizations within the company.\r\n\r\nKey responsibilities:\r\n\r\n-\r\nRaw material quality control measurements\r\n\r\n-\r\nCompile raw material quality reports\r\n\r\n-\r\nInvestigating raw material properties for development of high quality tyres\r\n\r\n-\r\nWorking as a team member in the laboratory team\r\n\r\nQualifications:\r\n\r\n-\r\nMinimum B.Sc. in Chemisty or Laboratory Science\r\n\r\n-\r\n1-2 years professional experience in laboratory work or newly graduated\r\n\r\n-\r\nExperience in operating various laboratory instruments\r\n\r\n-\r\nFast learner and able to manage several duties simultaneously\r\n\r\n-\r\nInnovative and active and your working style is analytical and hands-on\r\n\r\n-\r\nComfortable to work with different software environments\r\n\r\n-\r\nAbility to work as a member of a team and under pressure\r\n\r\n-\r\nAble to use Finnish and English as working languages\r\n\r\nWhy Nokian Tyres?\r\n\r\n-\r\nGrowing and successful company\r\nWe are a globally oriented and growing tyre manufacturer that focuses on customer needs in demanding conditions. The guidelines for our way of working are safety and sustainability.\r\n\r\n-\r\nInspired and target-minded people\r\nWe are skilled and development-minded people that are willing to do their best to achieve the set targets. We believe that by investing in employee experience we reach and even exceed our goals.\r\n\r\n-\r\nMeaningful job\r\nWe make roads safer by developing innovative, premium-quality and environmentally friendly tyres designed for demanding conditions.\r\n\r\n-\r\nDevelopment opportunities\r\nYou will have opportunities to grow and develop in-depth expertise, as long as you are ready to take on new challenges, question existing practices as necessary, and bring new ideas to our business.\r\n\r\nAre you interested in joining our inspiring team?\r\n\r\nPlease fill in the electronic application form with CV and salary request by 12.11.2017.\r\n\r\nFor further information please contact Laboratory Manager, Harri Moisio tel. 010 401 7224 (Wed 1.11.2017 at 12.00-12.00 / Mon 6.11.2017 at 14.00-15.00)\r\n\r\n______________________________________________________________\r\n\r\nDid you know that Nokian Tyres is the world's northernmost tyre manufacturer? We are also the only tyre manufacturer who focus on products for demanding conditions and customer requirements. Our unique expertise creates the safest premium products and services for the everyday life. We care deeply about safety and well-being on the road as well as at work at our company. As a pioneer in the tyre industry, we want to be the best in everything we do. A part of Nokian Tyres group, the tyre chain Vianor has 1,500 outlets in 27 countries. We have over 4,500 employees worldwide and our net sales was approximately 1.4 billion euros in 2016. Further information:  www.nokiantyres.com (http://www.nokiantyres.com/)",
