				"kuvausteksti" : "eSett Oy is a company formed and jointly owned by the three Nordic Transmission System Operators (TSOs): Fingrid Oy, Statnett SF and Svenska kraftnät and is headquartered in Finland. eSett provides imbalance settlement services to the electricity market participants in Finland, Norway and Sweden. The purpose of the imbalance settlement is to establish financial balance in the electricity market after the operation hour. Our customers are energy companies active in the Nordic Energy Market. We are a young team working closely together with great spirit.\r\n\r\nWe are strengthening our team and searching for an\r\n\r\nIT Project Manager\r\n\r\nto a new position, for managing development projects of imbalance settlement and messaging systems, and development and upgrade of the ERP system (Microsoft AX). You will plan and prepare projects and tenders together with our business developers. You will also conduct requirement specifications, act as a project manager in the development of systems and cooperate with our system providers actively.\r\n\r\nAs a person you are service-minded and ready to take on the responsibility for ensuring smooth, agile and cost-effective project management of eSett.\r\n\r\nTo be a successful candidate you will have:\r\n\r\n -A masters degree and more than five years work experience.\r\n -Experience in the development of IT systems and requirement specifications together with \r\n  business management, as well as in IT project management, including management of \r\n  change, stakeholders and service providers.\r\n -Good understanding of enterprise and application architecture and related technologies.\r\n -Knowledge of procurement processes in the public or private sectors.\r\n -Fluency in Finnish and English.\r\n\r\nYou have personal qualities like:\r\n\r\n -An open mindset, business-oriented way of doing things, and interest in energy markets.\r\n -Good skills in collaboration, team work and effectivity in negotiations.\r\n -Ability to independently manage operations in your responsibility area.\r\n -Aptitude to take initiative and motivation to long-term work.\r\n -Willingness to work hands-on as well as to take responsibility of all IT project management.\r\n -Capacity to fill any competence gaps through learning, with eagerness to develop yourself.\r\n\r\neSett Oy offers you a great opportunity to be part of a successful international Nordic company and a possibility to develop yourself as a multi-talent IT Project Manager.\r\n\r\nFor further information, call Ms. Sanna Leppäluoto at S&S Consulting, tel. +358 50 344 6864.\r\n\r\nPlease submit your application and CV in English, with your salary request, through the link http://www.ssconsulting.fi/tyonhakijalle/ by 12th November 2017. Please fill in the application form carefully, especially your personal information and work experience.",
