				"kuvausteksti" : "Lounais-Suomen Tietojakelu Oy takes care of newspaper and addressed mail early morning delivery in 25 municipal areas of south-western Finland, covering a total of 240 000 households. Lounais-Suomen Tietojakelu is the 3rd biggest distribution company in Finland. It is a part of TS-Group.\r\n\r\nThere are about 350 employees working in Turku area delivery operations. We deliver 22 different newspapers and the main product is Turun Sanomat.\r\nWe are seeking for Turku area\r\n\r\nNEWSPAPER DELIVERERS\r\n\r\nfor fixed-term and permanent employment contracts.\r\n\r\nAs a newspaper deliverer, you work during the early morning hours, between 02.00 - 06.00, depending on the length of the route. In your work, you use a bicycle or a car. You can use your own car in bicycle routes if you want to. \r\n\r\nNewspaper delivery is done seven days a week and your day-offs change at each week (as a rule you work for 6 nights and then have 2 nights off). You will be trained to your duties before you start to work. Training time is paid.\r\n\r\nAs a newspaper early morning deliverer you will work as an important part of newspaper production process. Our customers expect to receive their products at the right time and to the right place. The work is very independent and requires initiative, good basic fitness and -health and as the work takes place at night you have to be at least 18 years old. This task is best suited for you if you are responsible, precise and brisk. Some tasks require you to have your own car and driving license.\r\n\r\nPlease fill an application at http://avoinhakemus.ts.fi/jakajaksi. Inside the application please select Lounais-Suomen Tietojakelu Oy as the company and also select any areas you are interested to work in.",
