				"kuvausteksti" : "Healthcare Informatics Consultant (275646)\r\n\r\nJob ID: 279826\r\nCity: Espoo\r\nOrganisation: Siemens Healthineers\r\nMode of Employment: Permanent, full-time\r\n\r\nSiemens Healthcare Oy's Enterprise Services and Solutions (ES) team provides a diverse portfolio of consultancy services to our partner organisations. Due to expansion of our team we are searching for a Healthcare Informatics Consultant. The position will be filled in our Espoo Headquarters.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nWhat are my responsibilities?\r\n\r\nHealthcare Informatics Consultant will support the Diagnostic Imaging, Advanced Therapies, Laboratory Diagnostics and Point of Care sales teams with ES team in complex and large IT projects, developing  our portfolio and to help grow the business in line with agreed targets.\r\n\r\nYour task is to provide the team with advice on all aspects of healthcare informatics with expert level knowledge in healthcare IT with an expectation to expand the understanding to other diagnostic fields such as Diagnostic Imaging, Advanced Therapies, Laboratory Diagnostics and Point of Care.\r\n\r\nThey will also lead on the implementation of Siemens systems and services when delivered through a transformation and advisory project.\r\n\r\nYour main responsibilities will be:\r\n\r\nLeading the IT-portfolio consulting, marketing and sales activities;\r\nPresenting and selling our IT solutions throughout the Hospital;\r\nSupporting the design of our portfolio and assisting with the strategic continuous development.\r\nSupporting the positioning of the portfolio within the market;\r\nWork with sales the teams on the Identification, acquisition and implementation of projects;\r\nProviding mentoring and/or project management function internally and externally;\r\nResponsible for the detailed analysis of customer information and to present this information in a relevant and meaningful way for our customers;\r\nMaintaining an expert knowledge of healthcare informatics and to apply this to the clinical context of a Project.\r\n \r\n\r\nWhat do I need to qualify for this job?\r\n\r\nWe expect you to have:\r\n\r\nBachelors / master's degree in informatics, engineering, biotechnology or an equivalent education, with a genuine interest in data analytics and its application in the healthcare domain,\r\nA few years appropriate working experience,\r\nGood written and verbal communication skills in Finnish and in English;\r\nUnderstanding of healthcare IT with experience of customer workflows and engagements with hospital IT, Departments;\r\nBe a \"self-starter\" with the ability to identify, extract, analyse, interpret and present relevant data;\r\nGood verbal and written communication skills with problem solving capability;\r\nGood presentation skills;\r\nDemonstrable expertise in Healthcare informatics with practical experience of improving services through the implementation of innovative IT systems;\r\nAbility to engage with a wide range of partners in order to give a meaningful context to data held in the relevant systems;\r\nAbility to focus on detail with demonstrable analytical skills;\r\nProficiency in standard business IT office systems and Advanced IT skills;\r\nFlexibility around working hours\r\nPossibility and willingness to travel for work in Finland and abroad;\r\nDriving license (minimum: B).\r\n \r\n\r\nWe hope that you have experience in:\r\n\r\nIHE, HL7, DICOM, web services\r\nConnecting HIS, EMR, RIS, PACS, LIS, Comm-Servers, etc.\r\nDICOM, multi-media, home monitoring devices\r\nElectronic Health Record (Document Repositories, Documents Registries, Access Control Systems, Audit Trail\r\nDesigning and implementing regional and national eHealth Solutions\r\nPatient Portal, Physician Portals, EHR Browsers for documents, Images, and multimedia\r\nSecure and standardized connection for mobile devices HL7 FHIR compliant\r\n \r\n\r\nWhat else do I need to know?\r\n\r\nSiemens Healthineers one of the largest medical device manufacturers and a leading company in providing medical imaging, laboratory diagnostic and healthcare IT solutions. As an innovative company Siemens Healthineers is continuously innovating and providing new solutions and services to the market. Siemens Healthineers is involved in the development of digital health services and services for hospital management, to minimize risks and better utilize the potentials of new innovative technologies. In 2016 our turnover was 13, 5 billion. Globally we have over 46 000 employees. Siemens Healthcare Oy employs 120 people in Finland and the Baltics. Read more at www.healthcare.siemens.fi\r\n\r\nWe offer you a look out position to the diagnostic and healthcare IT market in a motivating environment. You will be working closely with other the other Nordic teams and will have the possibility to grow professionally.\r\n\r\nWe are looking forward to receiving your online application by 30.11.2017 at the latest.\r\n\r\nPlease ensure you complete all areas of the application form to the best of your ability as we will use the data to review your suitability for the role.",
