				"kuvausteksti" : "Job Title: Energy customer behaviour analyst\r\n\r\nProfile: Master level in psychology or other behaviour related subject and ideally a minimum of 2 years' experience from working in the energy sector\r\nHours: Full-time\r\nPlace: Helsinki\r\n\r\nVaasaETT, a Finland-based globally-focussed consulting business in the energy sector is looking to hire a behavioural scientist with expertise in consumer behaviour for its Helsinki office. \r\n\r\nVaasaETT is recognised internationally as a leader in the analysis of customer-centric issues in competitive energy markets globally. VaasaETT's experts have for instance analysed customer churn and loyalty behaviour in more markets for longer than any other consulting business. VaasaETT's work in the field of behavioural energy efficiency and customer engagement is recognised across the industry, and our data base of consumer-focused pilots is arguably the largest in the world.\r\n\r\nVaasaETT now wishes to move its consumer and modelling capabilities to the next level and as part of this would like to recruit a person who will be able to integrate expertise from the field of sociology, psychology and other behaviour related disciplines into VaasaETT's research projects and broader offerings.\r\n\r\n\r\nAbout your responsibilities:\r\n\r\nYou will take part in research and analysis including the modelling of behaviour patterns around energy usage including explaining behavioural patterns around customer churn, loyalty, satisfaction and customer engagement.\r\n\r\nThe successful candidate will be responsible for conducting primary research and synthesizing quantitative and qualitative findings into informative and easy-to-understand deliverables related to market intelligence, new services, behaviour models and approaches in the energy sector. This is a position for a smart, enthusiastic person who wants to learn quickly, conduct leading edge research and provide practical support for major international clients and large EU research projects. \r\n\r\nThe position will consist of:\r\n\r\nSynthesizing quantitative and qualitative findings related to customer behaviour into both complex models and informative and easy-to-understand written and visual deliverables.\r\nStructuring and developing individual and group behavioural models, energy analysis and primary research to uncover insights that drive our knowledge in the field of people changing their energy usage.\r\nProduce high quality reports and other material for external and internal use.\r\nOrally communicate findings to a wide variety of internal and external audiences.\r\nSupport the implementation of VaasaETT's strategy to develop research and commercial offerings around customer behaviour, customer communication, policy creation, best-practice and future scenarios in the energy industry.\r\n\r\n\r\nAbout You:\r\n\r\nPreferably, you have a Master's degree in psychology or another behaviour related-subject\r\nPreferably, you have worked a minimum of 2 years in areas related to energy\r\nPreferably, you have experience in EU-funded R&D projects\r\n\r\nYou easily decipher the big picture and can communicate and describe it in simple models\r\nYou are comfortable with dealing with numbers and technical descriptions \r\nYou work quickly and error-free under tight deadlines\r\nYou have strong organizational, analytical and communication skills\r\nYou are an achiever and consistently exceed individual and team goals\r\nYou are a good team player but also able to work alone and think for yourself\r\nYou are curious, resourceful and show good initiative\r\nYou have excellent written and spoken English. Professional knowledge of other languages may also be an advantage\r\nModelling experience is an advantage\r\n\r\n\r\nAbout Us\r\n\r\nVaasaETT is a research and advisory consultancy guiding future-focused energy markets globally. Our three focus areas are Consumers, Markets and Offerings We monitor and analyse energy markets, companies and consumers around the world to help our clients enter markets, develop offerings, models and policies, as well as identify future visions and take advantage of evolving opportunities and trends applying 20 years of unmatched global experience.\r\nWe help regulators make markets more competitive; retailers become more competitive and develop new models and offerings; network companies utilise the demand side; vendors become more relevant to the market; and large customers to get a better deal from competition.\r\n\r\n\r\nHow to Apply\r\n\r\nIf you are interested in the above position, please send us your CV and cover letter with a salary expectation to thomas.mikkelsen@vaasaett.com. VaasaETT is an equal opportunities employer. \r\n\r\nApplication deadline: 17.11.2017",
