				"kuvausteksti" : "Chef (f/m)\r\n\r\nYou organize and supervise the work process as well as the personnel allocation in the kitchen and ensure the quality of the food. You do food preparation and cook different dishes. You draw up the menu, purchase ingredients and store them professionally. Last but not least, you have basic knowledge of German (not less than A2). \r\nThe employer offers accommodation for employees from abroad. \r\n\r\nYour professional competence:\r\n\r\nBasic knowledge of a-la-carte-service\r\nBasic knowledge of banquet cooking\r\nBasic knowledge of food preparation and cooking\r\n\r\nWorking hours: \r\n\r\nFull-time job, 40 hours per week, 5-day per week from Monday to Sunday\r\nPredominantly working from 14:00 to 22:30 p.m.\r\nWilling to work at weekends \r\n\r\nSalary:\r\nAccording to tariff;\r\nMinimum 8,84 € per hour a week, but it depends on the qualification and work experiences\r\n\r\nLocation: Hohen Neuendorf, Brandenburg, Germany\r\n\r\n\r\nThis employment complies with the legislation of Germany.",
