				"kuvausteksti" : "Wärtsilä Energy Solutions is a leading global energy system integrator offering a broad range of environmentally sound solutions. Our offering includes ultra-flexible internal combustion engine based power plants, utility-scale solar PV power plants, energy storage & integration solutions, as well as LNG terminals and distribution systems. The flexible and efficient Wärtsilä solutions provide customers with superior value and enable a transition to a more sustainable and modern energy system. As of 2017, Wärtsilä has 65 GW of installed power plant capacity in 177 countries around the world.\r\n\r\nProcess Design in Wärtsilä Energy Solutions is now looking for Project Engineers to strengthen their team. The position is located in Vaasa, Finland or in Mumbai, India. \r\n\r\nResponsibilities \r\n- Executing safeguard that mechanical works according to contract specifications and design directives\r\n- Engineering in AutoCAD PID, making main flow diagram (or P&Ds) and device lists \r\n- Making project-specific design and design packages \r\n- Co-ordinating the design between sub-suppliers \r\n- Carrying out sub-supplier quality- and delivery follow-ups \r\n- Supporting our site team during installation and commission phases \r\n- Giving feedback regarding technical solutions and complaints \r\n- Act as stand-in for Chief Project Engineer Mechanical when requested (including travelling globally) \r\n- Participating in development projects.\r\n\r\nRequirements \r\n- BSc. or MSc. in Mechanical or Process Engineering \r\n- AutoCAD P&ID \r\n- Self-initiative, ability to work in teams, motivation to learn and grow professionally and willingness to travel as well as ability to understand and work with diverse cultures \r\n- Working experience with similar task is seen as an advantage\r\n- Fluency in English.",
