				"etatyo" : false,
				"kuvausteksti" : "We are looking for a Sourcing Manager to strengthen our Sourcing Team. Join us to our mission to protect people, property and business continuity!\r\n\r\nYour tasks will include sourcing and negotiating supply agreements to ensure that value for the organization is being achieved. Your main task includes sourcing strategy implementation, material productivity improvement, commercial negotiations, managing and executing sourcing projects, ensuring sufficient supplier capacity and supply chain improvements. Besides working with external suppliers, daily communication with internal stakeholders (Buyers, Supplier Quality, Project Teams and Engineering) is an important part of the job.\r\n\r\nThe ideal candidate has 3+ years' of experience in sourcing and ability in being able to drive projects successfully to completion and preferably previous experience in working in a multinational environment. Excellent communication skills both in English and Finnish are a requirement other languages are an advantage.\r\n\r\nRequirements:\r\n? Experience in Supply Chain Management, Sourcing & Procurement\r\n? Experience in establishing and implementing category strategies\r\n? Commercial or technical degree either at Master's or Bachelor's level\r\n? Experience in international business negotiations\r\n? Strong communication and cross-functional team skills\r\n? Analytical and good problem solving skills\r\n? Your way of working is self-driven, determined and persistent\r\n\r\nSome of the main categories sourced at Marioff are tubes and fittings, metal fabrications, machined components, electrical cabinets, motors and pumps as well as indirect categories. The category responsibilities will be defined based on the experience of the person hired for the job.\r\n\r\nWe offer you a dynamic and international work environment in a company with high technology products, a strong growth strategy and people who are passionate about fire safety. The position is located in our modern and functional office premises in Vantaa. At Marioff we value diversity in all its forms and we believe that it is our excellent, highly skilled people who make success, competitive excellence and innovation happen.\r\n\r\nAny questions? Please contact:\r\nTuomo Tiainen\r\nGlobal Sourcing Manager, Supply Chain\r\nTel. +358 50 5929470\r\nPreferred call times 3.11 at 9-11 and 10.11 at 12-14\r\n\r\nInterested to join our journey? Please send your application and CV right away or by Nov 15th, 2017 at latest via our website http://www.marioff.com/about-marioff/careers. Please include your salary request.\r\n\r\nMarioff is a global leader and innovator of the water mist fire protection technology. We design, develop and maintain HI-FOG® water mist fire protection solutions that enhance safety in buildings, industrial applications and at sea, all over the world. There are over 350 motivated professionals working at Marioff. Our head office and factory are in Finland, we have subsidiaries in Italy and UK, and service customers globally together with our certified partners. Marioff is a part of UTC Climate, Controls & Security, a unit of United Technologies Corp., a leading provider to the aerospace and building systems industries worldwide. For more information, visit www.marioff.com.",
