				"etatyo" : false,
				"kuvausteksti" : "Oil Products Development holds the responsibility for managing strategy development and deployment in Oil Products business area. Oil Product's Asset Development is responsible for continuously improving the performance of our existing refinery, harbour and terminal assets by steering investments projects. The team hosts Steering Manager roles for maintenance investments as well as small and medium-sized productivity improvement projects. The team secures effective use of capital and high quality of project delivery across Oil Products investment portfolio.\r\n\r\nWe are looking for\r\n\r\nTeam Leader\r\n\r\nto join Oil Product's Asset Development team to Porvoo refinery.\r\n \r\nAs a team leader you will be leading a team of Asset Development Managers with nominated focus areas. You will also be responsible for managing the team's project portfolio as a whole and with respect to other portfolios and for developing the ways of working within the team together with your peer(s) and the Head of Asset Development.\r\n \r\nParallel to team leader role you will act as a Steering Manager for nominated investment projects with the delegated authority and responsibility to execute projects with the assigned resources, budget and schedule. Projects are executed in matrix organizations and succeeding in this task requires intense communication and co-operation with multiple stakeholders (e.g. production, supply chain management, manage & maintain assets, engineering).\r\n \r\nKey requirements for the position include:\r\nPeople leadership and team working skills\r\nSkills to motivate highly professional experts\r\nWe highly appreciate:\r\nPrevious experience as a line manager\r\nStrong organizational skills\r\nEarlier experience in process industry/refinery processes\r\n \r\nMain responsibilities as a Steering Manager include:\r\nCorrect scope definition to meet the interests of different stakeholders\r\nResourcing of the project and related steering and support teams\r\nManagement of change\r\nManagement of project HSEQ items and required authority approvals and permits\r\nProject follow-up and decision making\r\n \r\nWe expect you to have:\r\nExcellent team working and communication skills\r\nApplicable education e.g. master's degree in engineering\r\nAt least 5-10 years of relevant work experience in the industry or industrial projects, process industry preferred\r\nFluent written and spoken English\r\n \r\nWhy join Neste? We believe we have much to offer for the right candidate, including:\r\nA stimulating leader position with diverse challenges\r\nOpportunities for personal growth and development\r\nA professionally supportive company culture and encouraging colleagues\r\nTechnologically advanced work with our very high-level portfolio of cutting edge projects\r\n \r\nIn your position you will report to Head of Asset development. For additional information, please contact\r\nEeva-Liisa Lindeman, tel. +358 50 458 7575, 26th October between 10-12 am and 2nd November between 12-2 pm. Or via email eeva-liisa.lindeman@neste.com.\r\n \r\nThe selected candidate must pass a health check including a drug test. A security clearance will be conducted of the candidate with their consent.\r\n \r\nFurther information and more detailed instructions for applying can be found from our website: www.neste.com/joinus. Please submit your application by 15th November 2017.",
