				"kuvausteksti" : "Project Engineer\r\nJämsänkoski, Middle Finland \r\n\r\nJob Description\r\n\r\nDuPont has a rich history of scientific discovery that has enabled countless innovations and today, we're looking for more people, in more places, to collaborate with us to make life the best that it can be.\r\n\r\nWe celebrate diversity of thought and experience and truly believe that our inclusive and collaborative culture strengthens  our organization. Our aim is  to enable  EVERY individual in our company to share their ideas to leverage richer perspectives  and find innovative solutions to solve the world's biggest challenges. Working TOGETHER works!\r\n\r\nJämsänkoski Plant is looking for a\r\n\r\nPROJECT ENGINEER\r\n\r\nwho believes working together is the way to reach common goals. This role represents an opportunity to join the exiting world of Industrial Biosciences at our enzyme production plant in Jämsänkoski. As a Project Engineer you will be responsible for project management and technical direction for new investment projects, and for cost estimates. We offer you challenges where you need to utilize your knowledge and experience, great opportunities to learn more, and to develop yourself in an inspiring work environment. You live your core values matching the core values of DuPont.\r\n\r\n  \r\nYou will be responsible for: \r\nSetting expectations and hold people accountable. You are clear on expectations for adherence to policies, standards and procedures and you ensure operational discipline\r\nMaintain safe and clean working environment and attitude by enforcing procedures, rules, and regulations\r\nProvide technical support or management for new investment projects, including project tracking, inspections, document control, and coordination of activities throughout the investment project collaborating with FSDC (full service design contractor)\r\nCoordinate activities on projects, including the design, scope, schedule, quality, and technical issues with FSDC\r\nMonitor projects budget and status reports and forecasts\r\nEffective communications between engineering, technical, construction and project controls groups\r\nProvide tracking and monitoring tools for process safety management including document control for critical process equipment\r\n\r\nJob Qualifications\r\n\r\nYou need to have:\r\nB.Sc or M.Sc. in related technical field\r\nExperience in project management\r\nDemonstrated leadership skills\r\nDemonstrated communication and collaboration skills\r\nFluency in spoken and written Finnish and English \r\n\r\n\r\nAbout DowDuPont\r\n\r\nDowDuPont (NYSE: DWDP) is a holding company comprised of The Dow Chemical Company and DuPont with the intent to form strong, independent, publicly traded companies in agriculture, materials science and specialty products sectors that will lead their respective industries through productive, science-based innovation to meet the needs of customers and help solve global challenges. For more information, please visit us at www.dow-dupont.com. \r\n\r\n The positions represented by this job posting are aligned to one of the three divisions, Agriculture, Materials Science or Specialty Products, which are expected to separate from DowDuPont into stand-alone public companies in late 2018 or early 2019. Information on the division alignment will be provided during the recruitment process.",
