				"kuvausteksti" : "We are strengthening EMEA (Europe, Middle East and Africa) Life Time Care (LTC) service team. To support the growth we are looking for \r\n\r\nService Engineer\r\n\r\nYour main tasks include service, maintenance, operation training and customer support for Normet machinery and vehicles designed for tunnel-making processes. You will also be responsible for product training for customers in mines and tunnel construction in region. You solve acute problems concerning our equipment usage, function and tunnel construction at customers' location. Additionally, customer support, customer operations development and technical support are a part of your area of responsibility.\r\n\r\nIn order to be successful in your tasks you are technically multi-skilled, service-minded and able to work with different kinds of people. Your social skills are in an important role in training situations. Your independent attitude and good stress tolerance are prerequisites for handling faulty and emergency situations. Adequate technical training (automotive, machinery, automation or civil engineering technology) combined with previous experience or desire develops you to build a solid basis for successful performance. Both willingness to travel and ability to communicate in Finnish and English are required. Other language skills are an asset. \r\n\r\nWe offer a free/liberal working culture and a strong can do attitude in a growing company. You will be trained for our equipment as well as for customer processes. You will and get both challenging tasks and support of our youthful and professional organisation. We also provide you with good professional development possibilities in an international environment. The preferred location of the job is in Iisalmi.\r\n\r\nPlease send your resume and application letter in English with salary request no later than November 24th, 2017 to rekry@normet.com.\r\n \r\nTo the subject field please add \"Service Engineer EMEA\". \r\nFor more information contact Juha Heikkilä tel. +358 40 1823501, on 16. - 17.11. and 20. - 21.11. between 08:00 and 12:00.",
