				"kuvausteksti" : "Firesteel Resources is a junior mining company focused on the acquisition and development of mining properties with near term production potential.  The company has recently signed a Joint Venture Agreement with Nordic Mines AB to operate the past producing Laiva gold mine near Raahe Finland.  \r\nUnder the agreement, Firesteel will be the operator of the JV and will be responsible for restarting production at the mine.   The Laiva mine includes two open-pits and a recently constructed 6,000 tpd, state-of-the-art process plant designed by Metso and constructed by Outotec.\r\n\r\nIn preparation for restarting production at the Laiva mine, Firesteel Resources is looking to hire a Controller.\r\n\r\nJob Description\r\nReporting to the General Manager and with a dotted line to the CFO, the Controller will lead site financial activities with the objective to optimize operating performance and assist with corporate financial reporting.\r\n\r\nJob Responsibilities\r\nOverseeing all site financial activities, including financial reporting and analysis, treasury and cash flow management, annual and monthly budgeting & forecasting.\r\nManage site accounting team, inducing accounts payable and payroll.\r\nEnsure that government reports and remittances are prepared on a timely basis.\r\nWork with other managers to optimize warehouse and other site inventory levels.\r\nOther tasks as required. \r\nQualifications\r\nA recognized designation in Accounting.\r\nMinimum 5 years' experience in managing an accounting department, preferably within the mining industry.\r\nExtensive knowledge of applicable Finnish regulations and reporting requirements.\r\nCommunication skills are essential, as well as strong relationship building and negotiation skills.\r\nExperience presenting & reporting financial information to stakeholders in an accurate and timely manner. \r\nExperience with estimating and purchasing, preferably within the mining industry. \r\nFluent in English, with the ability to communicate in Finnish.\r\n\r\nQualified candidates should send their applications to employment@firesteelresources.com  by November 17, 2017.",
