				"kuvausteksti" : "Citec provides multi-discipline engineering and information management services for the industry. The number of Citec employees amounts to approximately 1300 and the turnover for 2016 to about 77 million EUR. Citec is headquartered in Vaasa, Finland, and has offices in Finland, Sweden, Norway, the UK, France, Germany, Russia, India, Singapore, Kazakhstan and Saudi Arabia.\r\n\r\nWe are looking for Process Engineers to our office in Turku or Vaasa. As a Process Engineer you will be working with challenging power plant engineering in multi-discipline engineering projects. As a Process Engineer your tasks will include various process engineering related task such as preparation of P&ID's, equipment-, instrument- and valve specifications as well as process descriptions and various calculations.\r\n\r\nGrow with us! We offer you the opportunity to develop your skills in multidiscipline project management and other engineering areas. At Citec you will be part of a motivated team of younger and senior designers working in an international and open atmosphere.\r\n\r\nMain responsibilities\r\n- P&ID's\r\n- Equipment and component specifications\r\n- Process descriptions\r\n- Process calculations\r\n- Harmonisation of design with other disciplines whenever necessary\r\n- Inter and cross-discipline co-operation of engineering\r\n- Solving technical process engineering related issues\r\n\r\nQualifications:\r\n. M.Sc. in process, chemical, energy engineering, or similar, or\r\n- B.Sc. in process, chemical, or energy engineering and a few years of working experience in the field of process engineering\r\n- Good understanding of Chemical / Process Engineering principles.\r\n- Basic competence in Process design tools (e.g. design software, calculations)\r\n- Willing and eager to learn\r\n- Ability to work in a team\r\n- Good communication skills in English\r\n\r\nAdditional information:\r\nFor more information, please contact our Manager, Process Engineering Thomas Johansson, thomas.v.johansson@citec.com or +358 40 8242 675.",
