				"kuvausteksti" : "Adecco Group is the world's leading provider of workforce solutions. Adecco Finland Oy has been in operation since 1997. Our company is authorized by the Private Employment Agencies' Association of Finland. Hundreds of professionals in various fields are employed through us each day in jobs ranging in duration from a few days to several years. We also recruit professionals for our client companies.\r\n\r\nWe're currently looking for HSE Officer for our international client in the OL3 Site. The job starts as soon as possible and lasts approximately 12 months depending on our client's need. The position will be fulfilled as soon as the right person is found so please apply quickly.\r\n\r\nCriterions:\r\nHSE background on complex system\r\nPrevious construction activities like team leader or supervisor\r\nExperienced on running nuclear power plant \r\nKnowledge/experience in electrical and/or mechanical risks linked to industrial activities or commissioning activities \r\nGood knowledge of Finnish Occupational Health and Safety Regulations, Occupational Safety Card is a plus\r\nQualified for OHSAS 1800 I referential\r\nComfortable speaking in public (especially when giving training and eventually leading meetings) \r\nLanguage skills: Fluent in English, Finnish skills would be considered a plus \r\n\r\nThe main responsibilities of the HSE Officer are to work under the authority of the HSE Manager. The HSE Officer will be responsible of the following tasks: \r\n \r\nAnticipate difficulties (interfaces) and propose alternative ways to work \r\nPreliminary review of the risk assessment/method statement submitted by the contractors \r\nCheck the implementation on site of safety rules and mitigation measures defined in the risk assessment \r\nManage the safety inspection on site with the contractors and follow up corrective actions defined during the inspection \r\nClosely work with supervisors and construction group to have the knowledge of the coming activities (anticipation) and involve them in the daily safety \r\nAnimate the safety in the construction groups, through visit on spot, training, lesson learned \r\nBe pro-active to propose safety issues to improve the level and attitude on site\r\n\r\nWe're offering you the possibility to work with an international company where you can use and develop your skills and work in a position with varying tasks. \r\n\r\nPlease apply for the position by registering at www.adecco.fi. Attach your English CV to the application. For more information please contact HR Consultant Eerika Jantunen +35846 875 0111.",
