				"kuvausteksti" : "Mechanics Designer, join our R&D and engineering team!\r\n\r\nTeleste Information Solutions is looking for a Mechanics Designer to develop mechanical designs for railway station displays and train passenger information system devices based on customer requirements. \r\n\r\nYou will be making mechanical design and modeling, selecting materials and manufacturing methods. With a focus on quality and reliability, your daily work includes analysis of customer and standard requirements for mechanical design. You will work in close co-operation with our customers, HW team, product and project management, sourcing, and sub-contractors.\r\n\r\nWe offer you a chance to work in international projects related to in the field of delivery ofing passenger information. You will be implementing Teleste's mission of smart, safe and smooth future in the rail environment. You will work as a member of a close-knit professional team, devoted to innovating solutions for rail traffic. You will see the concrete results of your work in trains and trams used by tens of thousands of daily passengers in Europe, Middle East and North America.\r\n\r\nHow to succeed in the position?\r\n\r\nThe position requires good communication and team working skills. We also wish that you have knowledge and experience ion the following areas:\r\n\r\n- BSc or MSc in mechanical engineering or other suited higher education\r\n- Basic knowledge of sheet metal parts design\r\n- Required design tools skills e.g. SolidWorks\r\n- Basic understanding of how electronic devices work and how they are    composed\r\n- Fluency in written and spoken Finnish and English\r\n- Capability to understand complex system architectures\r\n\r\nExperience or knowledge of the following areas will be considered as a bonus:\r\n\r\n- Working experience in mechanical engineering\r\n- Experience in managing requirements and writing technical specifications\r\n- Understanding of the relevant mechanical and coating standards\r\n- Embedded systems and hardware interfaces\r\n\r\nThe position is located in Forssa, Finland. \r\n\r\nFor further details, please contact Tero Tervo, tero.tervo@teleste.com, +358 50 366 1896\r\n\r\nPlease fill in your application latest by 19th of November 2017 on our website www.teleste.com/career-opportunities.\r\n\r\n\r\nTeleste Information Solutions Oy, a subsidiary of Teleste Corporation, has 25 years of experience in delivering reliable passenger information systems and solutions for diverse on-board, railway and display applications. With our technology, tomorrow's passenger can enjoy secure and easy-going travelling with reliable information. For more information, please visit: www.teleste.com.",
