				"kuvausteksti" : "The usage of API is speeding up digitalization. We assist organizations in developing their services and brands as well as creating new business with flexible API management and utilization. We are now looking for enthusiastic future API Developers to join our team of 150 integration and API professionals located in Helsinki.\r\n\r\nYou will implement Application Programming Interface solutions utilizing micro services, IoT data, bots and cognitive services such as text and image recognition. Your team will support you with ideas, knowledge and tools. Existing knowledge on certain technology is not necessary. The most important requirements are your passion to open interfaces and eagerness to constantly develop yourself.\r\n\r\nYour job description will be driven by your ambitions and adjusted accordingly. Basic tools include for instance Node.js, Ruby, Python, Java, Go and SQL as well as cloud environments such as AWS, Azure, Bluemix and Google. Open interfaces, analytics, artificial intelligence and Internet of Things are intertwined in the daily tasks of your team. We follow lean and agile principles. And to make sure that your tasks won't get dull over time, you will also have the possibility to specialize for example in the areas of security, testing automation, integration solutions, consultation or service design.\r\n\r\nYour best qualities include\r\n\r\n- software development background from studies or previous work experience\r\n- innovative touch and enthusiasm to keep up with this continuously developing field\r\n- willingness to work together with customers and colleagues for greater results\r\n- positive attitude\r\n- business knowledge in some industry is also appreciated, especially if you wish to head towards architect or consultation work\r\n\r\nWhy us? API economy speeds up digitalization and working with APIs you will constantly learn something new. Digia has a wide variety of interesting API projects and a vast technology selection to enable different career paths and possibilities to your personal development. API team develops ideas in internal and external hackathons. Our teams have great amount of autonomy and responsibility, but always with the support from experienced superiors. And since life is not just about work, you will have flexible working hours, excellent benefits and colleagues who inspire you and enjoy spending time with each other, on and off working hours.\r\n\r\nApply by Nov 26th! Any questions regarding our positions or working at Digia? Please contact Fred Keus or Liisa Onninen. Liisa can be reached at +358 46 922 0056 and Fred at +358 40 531 2767, or you can e-mail us: firstname.lastname(at)digia.com.",
