				"kuvausteksti" : "Are you eager to develop your mechanical engineering expertise in international company? Our client Bureau Veritas Finland offers a unique career opportunity for a mechanical engineer in France. You will travel to France for a 1-1,5 year training period in nuclear power plant, and after the training period, you will utilize and share your knowledge in a power plant project in Finland. If you have good skills in French and want to get valuable work and educational experience, read more about this position and apply today!\r\n\r\nABOUT\r\n\r\nAcademic Work is looking for a nuclear power plant engineer for our client Bureau Veritas Finland.\r\n\r\nYou will be recruited to our client company. Academic Work will take care of the recruitment process, therefore candidates are kindly asked to direct all questions to Academic Work hel01@academicwork.fi.\r\n\r\nJOB DESCRIPTION\r\n\r\nIn this position, you will travel to France for 1-1,5 year training period in Flamanville nuclear power plant, and after that you'll bring your expertise to Finland. Depending on your background, you will specialize either in equipment inspection or in design review. In inspection position, you will inspect welding work and pressure equipment, and in design review position you will analyze and review the safety standards of the equipments.\r\n\r\nWE ARE LOOKING FOR\r\n\r\nOur ideal candidate has educational background in mechanical engineering or in nuclear mechanical engineering. You speak good French and fluent English. Good communication skills in Finnish is a plus. Succeeding in this position requires understanding of mechanical engineering and precise and systematic work methods. You might have previous experience from nuclear power plant field, but the most important thing is that you have motivation to learn new skills in international environment.\r\n\r\nApply for this position if you have:\r\n\r\n- Degree in mechanical engineering/nuclear engineering\r\n- Strong understanding of mechanical engineering\r\n- Good command of French and Finnish\r\n- Motivation to learn and grow your expertise\r\n\r\nIt is seen as an advantage if you have previous experience in nuclear field.\r\n\r\nStart: As soon as possible, no later than March 2018\r\n\r\nWorking hours: Fulltime\r\n\r\nEmployment period: Permanent\r\n\r\nLocation: Flamanville, France/Helsinki, Finland\r\n\r\nSalary: According to agreement\r\n\r\nPublished: 30.10.2017\r\n\r\nTo apply for the job you need to register on our website and then click on \"Apply here\". Remember to attach your CV into your application! We only process applications through our website but if you have questions about the position you can reach us via email in hel01@academicwork.fi. Please write the advert ID in the subject field and paste the advert link in the mail. We are continuously screening and contacting candidates so make sure to send your application as soon as possible. Please note that the advert can be removed prior to the last application dates on our external advertising pages. In the event the advert has been removed it is either due to the process being completed or because we have a sufficient number of qualified applications and are proceeding to the selection/interview phase in the process.\r\n\r\nWe are the Home of the Young Professionals. We are experts in recruitment and staffing university students, recently graduated and professionals in the beginning of their career. You can be employed by us as a consultant in one of our client companies or be recruited directly to our client via our recruitment co-operation. You can read more about us at www.academicwork.fi.\r\n\r\nABOUT THE CLIENT\r\n\r\nBureau Veritas Finland is a world leader in testing, inspection and certification services. They deliver high quality services to help clients meet the growing challenges of quality, safety, environmental protection and social responsibility.",
