				"kuvausteksti" : "Do you want to work with innovative solutions that make a difference in many people's lives? Are you an engineer with knowledge of IC-design? Now hiring a Junior Electrical Engineer to design 3D touch display solutions in rapidly growing Finnish based company. Read more and apply!\r\n\r\nABOUT THE ROLE\r\n\r\nAcademic Work is looking for Junior electrical engineer to our client company.\r\n\r\nThis job is a staffing position, which means that you will be employed by Academic Work and work as a consultant at our client company.\r\n\r\nJOB DUTIES\r\n\r\nAs a junior electrical engineer, you are an important part of designing innovative 3D touch dislay products. The requirements are given by customer companies but your team's responsibility is to design a prototype of product and run tests to ensure the quality. In addition to that you have the possibility to develop the existing tools and systems. You cooperate with project management, designers and IT-specialists on daily basis and occasionally attend the client meetings as a technical expert.\r\n\r\nThe job includes:\r\n\r\nDesigning 3D touch sensor systems\r\nTesting the prototypes\r\nDeveloping the tools and systems used\r\nCooperation with project management, designers and IT-specialists\r\nAttending client meetings\r\nThe position gives the opportunity to work with the most modern technologies in rapidly growing international company. Our client company designs solutions for example for automotive industry.\r\n\r\nWE ARE LOOKING FOR\r\n\r\nYou have a suitable university degree of electrical or automation engineering, or have studied IC-design or electrical circle design in some other engineering program. You might have already graduated of finishing your studies with some work experience from relevant designing. The new modern technologies used in this position will be taught to you. The most important factor is you drive to solve technical problems, passion to create new and ability to see the big picture with long-term outcomes. Good oral and written communication skills are required to ensure the cooperation with colleagues and clients.\r\n\r\nApply for this position if you have:\r\n\r\nSuitable university degree\r\nWork experience of relevant electrical design\r\nDrive to solve technical problems and create new\r\nGood communication skills (written/oral)\r\nIt is also seen as an advantage if you have experience from PCB-design or touch displays. Interest towards automotive industry is also seen as an advantage.\r\n\r\nStart: Flexible Working hours: Full-time Employment period: 12 months, possibility for extension Location: Helsinki Published: 31.10.\r\n\r\nIn this position you will be employed by Academic Work and we take care of all the legal responsibilities of an employer such as salary payments, insurances and health care. It is important for us that you feel well and perform in your job. Your consultant manager will be in regular contact with you during the assignment and guides you on your career. Academic Work is an authorized staffing and recruitment agency and our employees are extremely satisfied, something that we are very proud of. We are here to help you succeed!\r\n\r\nINFORMATION ON THE APPLICATION PROCESS\r\n\r\nTo apply for the job click on \"Apply here\" below. Remember to attach your CV into your application! We only handle applications through our website but if you have questions about the position you can reach us via email in hel01@academicwork.fi. Please write the advert ID in the subject and paste the advert link in the mail. We are continuously screening and contacting candidates so make sure to send your application as soon as possible. Please notice that the advert can be removed before eventual last dates on our external advertising pages. When the advert is being removed it's either due to that the processes is finished or because we have many qualified applications and are continuing in the selection/interview phase.\r\n\r\nWe are the Home of the Young Professionals. We are experts in recruitment and staffing university students, recently graduated and professionals in the beginning of their career. You can be employed by us as a consultant in one of our client companies or be recruited directly to our client via our recruitment co-operation. You can read more about us at www.academicwork.fi.\r\n\r\nWhen employed at Academic Work you will have your own dedicated Consultant Manager, whose role is to answer your questions, support your career development and ensure you enjoy your place of work.\r\n\r\nINFORMATION ABOUT THE COMPANY\r\n\r\nThis Finnish based international company designs 3D touch displays for various businesses such as automotive industry.",
