				"kuvausteksti" : "Borealis Finland is looking for a\r\n\r\nProcess Development Engineer, Technical Development, Porvoo Finland\r\n\r\n\r\nRole Purpose\r\nDevelop technical solutions to secure continuous and step change improvements of Polyethylene, Polypropylene and compounding production units and processes in Porvoo.\r\n\r\n\r\nContribution\r\nLead or participate project teams, studies and investments. \r\nProvide start-up and commissioning support to local investment projects.\r\nLead problem solving and trial run preparations and reporting. Initiate improvement projects and establish action plans to achieve targeted plant performance. \r\nSupport plant operation.\r\nInvestigate and analyse process and quality incidents.\r\nBuild up technical expertise, provide support and training.\r\nProactively promote and drive the HSE mindset and behaviour. Lead hazard studies in projects.\r\nNetworking with relevant organisations to ensure sharing of Best Practices and updated technical knowledge.\r\n\r\nKnowledge, Skills & Experience\r\nMaster or PhD (chemical engineering or equivalent). \r\nFluent in English and Finnish language.\r\nAbility to prioritise and take decisions.\r\nGood skills in engaging, motivating and involving people.\r\nGood teamwork capability.\r\nGood communication capability.\r\n\r\nBehaviour\r\nAnalytical thinking\r\nCo-operative\r\nInnovative and initiative\r\nHSE Awareness\r\n\r\nFor more detailed information please contact Jussi Laurell, +358 50 379 4133.\r\nIf you are interested in this role and meet most of the above criteria, please send your application latest 23.11.2017.\r\nSelected persons are required to pass a health check including a drug test before start of the employment.\r\n\r\nBorealis is a leading provider of innovative solutions in the fields of polyolefins, base chemicals and fertilisers. The company is headquartered in Vienna, Austria, and operates in over 120 countries with around 6,600 employees worldwide, generating EUR 7.2 billion in sales revenue in 2016\r\n\r\nBorealis provides services and products to customers around the world in collaboration with Borouge, a joint venture with the Abu Dhabi National Oil Company /ADNOC\r\n\r\nBorealis Finland's production site in Kilpilahti, Porvoo is a fully integrated petrochemicals complex employing about 900 persons. Operations in Finland include five production plants, an Innovation Centre and a Customer Service Centre.\r\n\r\nTo learn more about Borealis visit www.borealisgroup.com",
