				"kuvausteksti" : "H&M BUSINESS CONTROLLER\r\n  \r\nFind your place in a fast moving environment where your role is to maximize sales and profitability through bringing your analysis into action. As vital part of your team, you'll be expected to set goals and follow up on sales targets. We are offering a job where every day is an adventure, where only you set the limits to your career possibilities, and where your personal growth and development is just as important as our business. \r\n \r\nYou will be expected to:\r\nFollow up on sales and profit targets. \r\nBe a vital part of the regional team supporting the store management groups. \r\nManage and monitor the financial control systems. \r\nBe responsible for setting, achieving and following up on sales and profit targets, based on financial analyses. \r\nDevelop and implement methods, systems and decision-making models. \r\nOffer consulting advice to your team with concise analyses and financial insights.\r\n  \r\nWe are looking for you with:\r\nStrong analytical skills \r\nStrong experience in working with Excel \r\nA business degree (Bachelor's or Master's Degree) \r\nA deep interest in business \r\nA strong motivation to constantly improve and achieve your goals \r\nAn interest for working in a dynamic team \r\nAbility to travel approx. 2-3 days a week based on the business needs\r\nGood  Finnish and English skills both written and oral\r\n \r\nWe can offer you:\r\nA great opportunity to get an insight into H&Ms fashion business and we can assure you that you will get plenty of responsibility from day one. If you succeed here, we can offer you a career path with endless opportunities.\r\n \r\n \r\nDeadline to apply is Sunday 12th of November 2017. Please complete the online application and attach a copy of your CV at http://www.hm.com/jobs\r\nPlease also include a detailed covering letter with your salary expectations.",
