				"kuvausteksti" : "Wärtsilä Services supports its customers throughout the lifecycle of their installations by optimising efficiency and performance. The company's service network of approximately 11,000 professionals in 160 global locations is unmatched in the industry, delivering services to more than 12,000 customers every year. The portfolio of services - from spare parts to complete operational, maintenance, and optimisation services - is constantly being developed, not only to improve the availability of customers' installations, but to support them in growing their businesses.  Wärtsilä is committed to providing high quality, expert support, and the availability of services in the most environmentally sound way possible, whenever, wherever.\r\n\r\nTraining Centre in Wärtsilä Services is now looking for a Training coordinator. The position is located in Turku, Finland. \r\n\r\nResponsibilities \r\nTraining coordinator will act as a global contact point to maintain the PSM (Professional Skills management) catalogue for different organizations example Field service, Electrical & Automation, Oil & Gas and Land and sea academy. Training coordinator will be part of WLSA (Wärtsilä Land and Sea Academy) training course coordination team and take part of WLSA training course coordination. \r\n\r\nAs a Coordinator you will work within external and internal customer training. \r\n\r\nCoordinator makes sure that the operation and coordination of competence activities are smoothly running by: \r\n-Handling course requests, missing assessments, training history queries \r\n-Maintaining competence catalogue in WeLearn \r\n-Managing Master Starter-cards process (print, mark completions, data maintenance) \r\n-Managing PSM access right requests \r\n-Managing assessment process for Field Service (create, support and follow-up) \r\n-Problem solving (end user support related to PSM activities) \r\n-Training (scheduled regular end user trainings and manuals) \r\n\r\nRequirements \r\n- Project management skills\r\n- Strong understanding of offering and invoicing process \r\n- Customer-friendly way of working\r\n- Strong correspondence and negotiation skills\r\n- Development and problem solving mind-set\r\n- Presentation skills\r\n- Good IM skills, including SAP and Saba\r\n- Cool personality \r\n- Fluency in English, other language skills are seen as an advantage.\r\n\r\nContact person to give further information \r\n\r\nMikko Issakainen, Manager, Training Center\r\n+358 40 3567348\r\nmikko.issakainen@wartsila.com",
