				"kuvausteksti" : "We are looking for embedded Linux developers to work in our development projects for various global customers. As a Linux developer you will be responsible for low-level software development in embedded Linux environment. Most likely you will be working with international partners and in customer interface daily. The positions are located in Oulu, Espoo and Tampere.\r\n\r\nGood interpersonal skills and team player attitude will fit you well into our crew and healthy enthusiasm for the craft will make you feel like a long lost member of our family. Make the first contact by sending your application today and let's start the discussion on what could be your role at Bittium!\r\n\r\nWhat you need for the job:\r\n\r\n-Software development experience in C/C++ and recent development experience in embedded Linux environments \r\n-Experience in development in Linux kernel space, kernel itself and/or kernel modules \r\n-Tools such as GIT, GDB and HW debugging tools (JTAG) are familiar to you\r\n-Fluency in written and spoken English\r\n\r\nIn addition we appreciate:\r\n\r\n-A strong technical background\r\n-Hands-on experience in writing of hardware device drivers for embedded operating systems \r\n-Experience on baseport, bootloaders, board bring-up, and SW optimization for performance (such as power management)\r\n-Understanding of embedded system hardware design and CPU architectures \r\n-Any submissions done to open source community relating to Linux kernel are considered beneficial",
