				"kuvausteksti" : "Type: Part-time, permanent/ fixed-term depending on your situation\r\nSuitable background: Student or graduated with willingness to work part-time\r\nLocation: Vantaa, Finland \r\nBeginning date: As soon as possible, negotiable \r\nApplication DL: ASAP/ Sunday 12th November\r\n\r\nSympa is the company behind the leading HR solution in Finland, and is rapidly expanding on a global scale. Due to our fast growth, we're constantly looking for new colleagues. Now we're aiming to expand globally even further and are looking for a talented Dutch-speaking Marketing Coordinator to join us. \r\n\r\nWe are now looking for a young professional who shares our commitment and passion for great marketing and communications to drive our marketing actions in the Netherlands to the next level. The work is part-time at first (approx. 2-3 days a week), but in the future, as the business in the Netherlands stabilizes, there might be a possibility to work full-time.\r\n\r\nYou will be working closely with our small, close-knitted marketing team in Finland and our sales team in the Netherlands. You will be working from our office in Vantaa, Finland. Your tasks will be mostly related to content marketing, translating marketing texts and organizing local events. \r\n\r\nAs Marketing Coordinator at Sympa your tasks would include:\r\n\r\n Creating content to support our local sales team in the Netherlands\r\n Localising marketing and sales material (English-Dutch) \r\n Coordinating sales-support campaigns and related activity in close cooperation with sales\r\n Event planning and production \r\n Working closely with the local marketing service providers \r\n\r\nWe are looking for a self-starter, someone curious and eager to learn. You make things happen with a self-imposed way. Sympa, in turn, does its very best to take good care of the whole Sympa family. \r\n\r\nWhat do we offer? \r\n\r\n An independent role with the possibility to grow along your tasks \r\n A great opportunity to play your part in an international growth & success story\r\n A valued and important role alongside 70+ colleagues in a relaxed but ambitious working environment \r\n A chance to show what you can do and act independently \r\n A hands-on role in which you can learn about the latest developments in inbound marketing \r\n\r\nWhat do we value in our candidates? \r\n\r\n Relevant educational background, preferably in Marketing/Communications/Business \r\n An entrepreneurial mind-set, independent and solution-focused working style\r\n A love of writing and eye for design \r\n Experience in B2B marketing or/and sales is highly valued but not required\r\n A great sense of humour (not least about yourself) will take you far with Sympa!\r\n\r\nGot interested? Let us know who you are! Send in your CV and application (in PDF-format) letter by latest Sunday 12th November through this link: https://apply.atalent.fi/sympa-marketing-coordinator-dutch-speaking-11-2017. Please, mention your salary request and possible starting date in your cover letter. Notice that we might proceed with the most suitable candidates before the deadline so act fast! \r\n\r\nTo find out more about Sympa, please visit www.sympa.com. If you have questions about the application process or the position, please get in touch with Recruitment Manager Noora Markoff (noora.markoff@atalent.fi, +358 40 5928 993). For more information regarding the position or the company, you may contact Sympa Marketing Director Kati Tammisto on November 7th, at 10-11:00 or November 9th between 15 -16:00. (+358 40 775 7162, or kati.tammisto@sympa.com).",
