				"etatyo" : false,
				"kuvausteksti" : "The Adecco Group, based in Zurich, Switzerland, is the world's leading provider of HR solutions. With over 31,000 FTE employees and more than 5,500 offices, in over 60 countries and territories around the world, Adecco Group offers a wide variety of services, connecting more than 600,000 colleagues with over 100,000 clients every day. The services offered fall into the broad categories of temporary staffing, permanent placement, outsourcing, consulting and outplacement. The Adecco Group is a Fortune Global 500 company.\r\n\r\nWe're currently looking for Fire Safety Officer for our international client in the OL3 Site in Olkiluoto, Eurajoki. The job starts as soon as the right person is found and lasts for 8 months.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nCriterions:\r\n\r\n- Technical experience on fire protection and prevention on industrial environment or on construction site\r\n- Willing to work in shifts\r\n- Knowledge of Microsoft Office (excel, word, powerpoint and outlook)\r\n- Knowledge of automatic systems (extinguishing, alarm) or experience in electrical, mechanical risks linked to industrial activities or commissioning activities\r\n- Finnish and English language skills\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nResponsibilities:\r\n\r\n- Strict follow up of application and compliance with site rules, national standards and legislation\r\n- Reposting and recording of actions and deviations\r\n- Active communication with contractor's personnel, their guidance and instructing\r\n- Rescue trainings and test with site personnel\r\n- Follow up and updating daily fire protection tasks (exit ways, signalization)\r\n- Manage the fire safety inspection on site with the contractors. Follow up corrective actions defined during the inspection\r\n- Closely work with supervisors and teams to have the knowledge of the coming activities and involve them in the daily safety\r\n\r\n\r\nWe're offering you the possibility to work with an international company where you can use and develop your skills. You will be part of a highly professional team and have responsibility of your own scope. Please send your application on our website www.adecco.fi and attach your English CV to the application. For more information, please contact Senior HR Consultant Eerika Jantunen +358 46 875 0111 or eerika.jantunen@adecco.fi.",
