				"kuvausteksti" : "Bittium is currently looking for a Software Engineer to join the engineering team in Espoo. In this particular position you will be a member of a highly skilled software development team working on our enterprise Mobile VPN product line. You will be responsible for prototyping, designing and developing Bittium's products for laptops, tablets and mobile devices mainly on Windows on both user and kernel space. You will have the pioneer attitude and you will not be afraid to explore new areas.\r\n\r\nResponsibilities\r\n\r\n-Prototyping, designing and implementing Bittium's software products\r\n-Participating in product planning\r\n-Contributing to the development of engineering practices\r\n\r\nTo give our customers the best service we pay them occasional visits, so a small amount of both domestic and international travelling may be required.\r\n\r\n \r\nCompetence characteristics\r\n\r\n-Solid knowledge in programming using C/C++, experience in python is a merit\r\n-Experience in developing software using Windows APIs\r\n-Experience or willingness to learn NDIS drivers (miniport, intermediate driver or protocol drivers)\r\n-Experience in working with advanced Windows networking areas, such as Windows Filtering Platform (WFP) is a merit\r\n-Ability to debug driver level networking issues on Windows\r\n-Understanding of mobility management and security protocols, such as Mobile IP, IPsec and TLS or similar\r\n-Good understanding of overall IP networking, including routing, NAT, firewalls and Wi-Fi\r\n-Understanding of mobile device requirements and embedded requirements in software development\r\n-Demonstrated troubleshooting and problem solving skills and attitude\r\n-Excellent verbal and written communication skill in both English and Finnish\r\n-Experience in working with Linux is a merit",
