				"kuvausteksti" : "Two Doctoral Student positions in Deep Learning\r\n\r\nResearch Unit of Medical Imaging, Physics and Technology, Faculty of Medicine, University of Oulu\r\n\r\n Background\r\n\r\nRecently, Deep Learning (DL) has become widely popular and shows an enormous potential in revolutionizing the health care system. As lots of medical data has become publically available, it can also improve disease diagnostics. Furthermore, DL has an increasing foothold in the future trends of medical image reconstruction: DL can be used to augment other reconstruction techniques or even as an independent approach.\r\n\r\n Aims\r\n\r\nDespite the advantages of the DL technology, it is still poorly understood, and has a lack of trust in medical community. Therefore, we are looking for two talented individuals for the following research projects:\r\n1.New DL methods for automatic osteoarthritis (OA) diagnosis using Magnetic Resonance and Plain Radiographic images. The successful candidate will be working in close contact with healthcare experts - radiologists and OA researchers to develop a new generation of automatic interpretable OA diagnostic methods.\r\n2.Development of computed tomography (CT) reconstruction algorithms using DL methods and automatic coronary artery disease (CAD) diagnostic methods from CT images. The successful candidate will work with medical physicists and radiologists to develop these methods.\r\n\r\n Research environment\r\n\r\nThe research will be conducted at Research Unit of Medical Imaging, Physics and Technology (MIPT), Faculty of Medicine, University of Oulu, Finland (http://www.mipt-oulu.fi/saarakkala-group/, http://www.mipt-oulu.fi/nieminen_group/). MIPT is an international environment of best national and international experts in medical research: Neuroscience, Osteoarthritis imaging and diagnosis and health technologies. Our unit is very interdisciplinary and it is a team of hard-working highly motivated medical doctors, physicists, engineers, biologists and computer scientists.\r\n\r\nAfter acceptance, the students will be enrolled to University of Oulu Graduate School (UniOGS) doctoral program. The general requirements for admission to the UniOGS can be found at the following web pages: http://www.oulu.fi/uniogs/requirements_for_admission.\r\n\r\nLength of the position\r\n\r\nThe contract will be made for four (4) years including a trial period of four (4) months.\r\n\r\nRequirements\r\n\r\nWe expect excellent analytical abilities, abilities to achieve the goals, high motivation. The ideal applicant should also hold preferably an M.Sc. degree in Computer Science, Mathematics, Physics or other technical discipline. If you have completed any of the on-line courses (e.g. on Coursera), please include it to your CV as well.\r\n\r\nThe position requires prior experience in machine learning, data analysis and programming. The applicant should have excellent skills in programming as well as the ability to write efficient code. As a proof of your skills, we will account Kaggle competitions medals, industrial and scientific experience. Contributions to open-source packages, e.g. scikit-learn are also highly valued.\r\n\r\nIf necessary, the applicants will also be given a test task to prove their skills in programming and machine learning.\r\n\r\nSalary\r\n\r\nFinland is known as a country with a high quality of life and good health-care system. The salary of the appointed researcher will be based on the demand level 2-4 chart for the teaching and research staff of Finnish universities. In addition to the basic salary, an additional salary component (not more than 46.3% of the basic salary level) will be paid based on personal achievements and performance. The net starting salary for a Ph.D. student is approximately 2300 € per month and it will progressively increase along with the performance of the student. In addition to the salary, the employed person will be insured by the university.\r\n\r\nApplication process:\r\n\r\nThe application documents should include:\r\n\r\n1)    A cover letter describing motivation for this position and earlier machine learning experience\r\n\r\n2)    Curriculum vitae and degree certificates\r\n\r\n3)    Full list of peer-reviewed publications in English\r\n\r\n4)    Full name and e-mail addresses of 2 referees (referees may be contacted separately).\r\n\r\n5)    Links to your GitHub and Kaggle profile if you have those.\r\n\r\nApplications, including attachments, must be submitted by using electronic application system in English by December 15, 2017:\r\n\r\nContact details\r\n\r\nDirect any questions or correspondence to:\r\n\r\nPosition 1 (OA diagnosis):\r\n\r\nSimo Saarakkala, PhD\r\n\r\nAssociate Professor\r\n\r\nResearch Unit of Medical Imaging, Physics and Technology\r\n\r\nFaculty of Medicine\r\n\r\nUniversity of Oulu, Finland\r\n\r\nE-mail: simo.saarakkala@oulu.fi\r\n\r\nPhone: +358 50 5746681\r\n\r\nPosition 2 (CT reconstruction):\r\n\r\nMiika T. Nieminen, PhD\r\n\r\nProfessor, Chief Physicist\r\n\r\nResearch Unit of Medical Imaging, Physics and Technology\r\n\r\nFaculty of Medicine\r\n\r\nUniversity of Oulu, Finland\r\n\r\nE-mail: miika.nieminen@oulu.fi\r\n\r\nPhone +358 40 5518246",
