				"kuvausteksti" : "ABB (ABBN: SIX Swiss Ex) is a pioneering technology leader in electrification products, robotics and motion, industrial automation and power grids, serving customers in utilities, industry and transport & infrastructure globally. Continuing more than a 125-year history of innovation, ABB today is writing the future of industrial digitalization and driving the Energy and Fourth Industrial Revolutions. ABB operates in more than 100 countries with about 136,000 employees www.abb.com\r\n\r\nWe are looking for a Project Engineer at ABB Oy, Power Grids unit in Vaasa. You will actively participate in the development of project engineering. In this position, you will prepare, update and support project execution in high-voltage activities, in collaboration with lead engineers and project managers in international project environment.\r\n\r\nYour responsibilities\r\n- Designing, preparing, and reviewing or overviewing engineering aspects such as substation layout and sections views, earthing grids, steel structures and installation drawings\r\n- Ensuring that the high-voltage systems are designed and executed according to the given specifications and taking local regulations and requirements into account \r\n- Working with the internal team and subcontractors to develop complete substation high-voltage design packages.\r\n- Participating in installation supervision at remote sites or providing support to site teams from the office\r\n\r\nWe offer\r\n- A challenging position in an international working environment\r\n- The opportunity for personal development in the areas of design and engineering, research and development\r\n- The opportunity to test your skills as a designer in various types of projects, both in Finland and abroad\r\n- The opportunity to further your career in a global company\r\n\r\nRequirements\r\n- A B.Sc. or M.Sc. in Electrical or Mechanical Engineering or other suitable studies\r\n- Basic knowledge of applicable standards (IEC, SFS, Eurocode)\r\n- Excellent written and spoken communication skills in Finnish and English.\r\n\r\nIt is a benefit, if you also have\r\n- Knowledge of substation layouts and structures\r\n- Knowledge of CAD, SAP and Microsoft Office\r\n- Language skills in Swedish and/or Russian",
