				"kuvausteksti" : "FULL-TIME JUNIOR JAVASCRIPT/PHP -DEVELOPER TO DRUID OY, HELSINKI\r\n\r\nTulosta    Tallenna suosikiksi\r\nWe're now looking for a Junior JavaScript/PHP - developer for our client company Druid Oy which is one of the leading Drupal-houses in Finland. Passion and interest are more relevant than education or experience, but all previous experience is regarded as a benefit. If you have passion for technical making and you are familiar with JavaScript and PHP, apply now!\r\n\r\nABOUT THE ROLE\r\n\r\nAcademic Work is looking for a Junior JavaScript/PHP-developer for our client Druid Oy in Helsinki.\r\n\r\nThis job is a staffing position, which means that you will be employed by Academic Work and work as a consultant at our client company.\r\n\r\nJOB DUTIES\r\n\r\nYou will work as a part of a team, which will encourage you to grow and become a more independent developer. You will get familiar to different kind of web-based systems that allow you to build and maintain web pages, digital services and digital solutions. In your work you will use for example JavaScript, PHP and React and you learn to choose the technologies and programming languages that best fit to client needs.\r\n\r\nOne example of our references is The Aava Medical Center. To unify Aava's web service experience we designed and built a universal application programming interface (API) for different applications out of Aava's patient information system. As the first application using the API we built the new Terveytesi (Your health) service using React technology.\r\n\r\nCheck here for more about our references.\r\n\r\nThis position suits you who is proactive and motivated. You don't hesitate to express your own opinion and you are capable and willing to learn new things.\r\n\r\nWE ARE LOOKING FOR\r\n\r\nOur ideal candidate has experience either through education and hobbies, or work experience. Knowledge of multiple technologies is seen in your favor, but minimum requirement would be basic knowledge in PHP and stronger capabilities in JavaScript. If you are a fast learner, you can complement your technology know-how with other technologies.\r\n\r\nApply for this position if you have:\r\n\r\n-Some experience of using PHP and JavaScript\r\n-Passion for technical making\r\n-Will to learn\r\n-Open mind and strong motivation to grow as a delevoper\r\n-Fluent in English\r\n\r\nPrevious work experience in IT development is seen as an advantage.\r\n\r\nStart: Upon agreement Working hours: Full-time Employment period: 12 months Location: Helsinki Salary: Upon agreement Published: 1.11.2017 In this position you will be employed by Academic Work and we take care of all the legal responsibilities of an employer such as salary payments, insurances and health care. It is important for us that you feel well and perform in your job. Your consultant manager will be in regular contact with you during the assignment and guides you on your career. Academic Work is an authorized staffing and recruitment agency and our employees are extremely satisfied, something that we are very proud of. We are here to help you succeed!\r\n\r\nINFORMATION ON THE APPLICATION PROCESS\r\n\r\nTo apply for the job click on \"Apply here\" below. Remember to attach your CV into your application! We only handle applications through our website but if you have questions about the position you can reach us via email in esp02@academicwork.fi. Please write the advert ID in the subject and paste the advert link in the mail. We are continuously screening and contacting candidates so make sure to send your application as soon as possible. Please notice that the advert can be removed before eventual last dates on our external advertising pages. When the advert is being removed it's either due to that the processes is finished or because we have many qualified applications and are continuing in the selection/interview phase.\r\n\r\nWe are the Home of the Young Professionals. We are experts in recruitment and staffing university students, recently graduated and professionals in the beginning of their career. You can be employed by us as a consultant in one of our client companies or be recruited directly to our client via our recruitment co-operation. You can read more about us at www.academicwork.fi.\r\n\r\nWhen employed at Academic Work you will have your own dedicated Consultant Manager, whose role is to answer your questions, support your career development and ensure you enjoy your place of work.\r\n\r\nINFORMATION ABOUT THE COMPANY\r\n\r\nDruid Oy is one of the leading Drupal houses in the Nordics and an expert in agile development. Along the years we have developed into a versatile partner in the digital industry. We choose the technologies and programming languages that best fit your needs to ensure an efficient and reliable delivery. Our base of operations is situated in Helsinki, and we also have staff in Amsterdam and Bangkok. We are open and straightforward - it's fun to work with us!",
