				"kuvausteksti" : "We are looking for a part-time IT Support to join our team in Helsinki\r\n\r\nBird & Bird is a truly international law firm with a rare and invaluable grasp of strategic commercial issues. We have over 1200 lawyers in 28 offices across Europe, the Middle East and Asia-Pacific, and a strong footprint in the Nordic region. As an employer, we are proud of our professional, efficient and friendly working environment and our dedication to uphold this atmosphere.\r\n\r\nAs an IT Support you will provide support to our lawyers and other staff who are seeking technical assistance. This is a part-time position, and you will work approximately one day per week. During vacation season (summer and winter vacation) the job is full-time. This job is ideal for a student.\r\n\r\nWe are looking for candidates who are working towards an applicable technical degree in a polytechnic or university. Our ideal candidate has already studied relevant studies for a few years, but we will also consider students at early-stages of their studies.\r\n\r\nWe appreciate the knowledge of company's data systems and basic knowledge of mobile working environment. Prior experience in similar duties is\r\nvalued. Ability to work under pressure, keen eye for details, thorough grasp of work, fluency in Finnish and English and good sense of humour as well\r\nas good social skills are considered as basic prerequisites to succeed in\r\nthis position. Besides Finnish our international working environment also requires fluency in English.\r\n\r\nWe offer you the opportunity to work in a challenging and rewarding environment where everyone is valued and appreciated. We take pride in our\r\nreputation of having a professional, efficient and egalitarian culture and are dedicated to upholding this reputation. For us, our employees are an invaluable asset and we invest in their development e.g. by offering a wide range of Nordic and international training opportunities.\r\n\r\nHave we captured your interest? Please send your application and CV to careers.helsinki@twobirds.com by 12 November 2017 at the latest. Please write \"IT Support\" on the subject field. For more information, please contact IT Manager Timo Taurula at 050 365 3751 on 7 November between 2 and 4 pm. You can also reach Timo by email: timo.taurula@twobirds.com.",
