				"kuvausteksti" : "We design and implement complex test and measurement systems for the needs of our customers. In recent years our growth has been beyond belief. We've done the right things at the right times, and through a lot of hard work we've been selected as the solution provider by the top global players in our industry, such as Google, Atmel and China Mobile. We're continuously aiming higher, and there's more chapters to the story still coming up. We are increasing focus with our key technologies and investing more into developing the competence of our personnel in order to deliver solutions to the most demanding customers in the world.\r\n\r\nWe solve the measurement challenges and needs of our customers with robot assisted test & measurement systems. We don't settle for off-the-shelf solutions, but tailor the systems to optimally fit each customer case. A key factor in customising the solutions is the software managing the complex solution. Your key role will be the design and implementation of high-quality, modular software that is delivered as the heart of our systems to the most demanding customers in the world.\r\n\r\nOur systems are driven by our software that is responsible for motion, image analysis, business logic and calibration. We need SOFTWARE DEVELOPER with SW programming skills in Python, C, C++\r\n\r\n- Interest/experience on control SW for embedded test solutions\r\n- testing and validation competence\r\n- Understanding of SW development and test processes\r\n- Willing to travel\r\n\r\nFollowing experience is much valued\r\n\r\n- Working experience in automated testing\r\n- Project management expertise\r\n\r\nYour tasks will include:\r\n\r\n- Planning and developing software for solutions containing mechanics, machine vision, motion control\r\n\r\nWhat we offer you:\r\n\r\n- Opportunity to get your hands dirty and learn in unique customer projects with optomized, brilliant, international people and true experts - We really do have the best colleagues possible.\r\n- Easy-going, enthusiastic, open and at the same time a growth and results-driven culture where everyone can participate - What would MacGyver do?\r\n- Projects with the most intelligent test robots of the planet earth and truly global playground with fascinating customers - We love technology and playing with it.\r\n\r\nOur daily work is lead by values. Please click a link below and check how your own values meet with our values http://www.optofidelity.com/careers/working-at-optofidelity/\r\n\r\nIf you see yourself matching to above topics, please don't hesitate to apply for this job.\r\n\r\nWe are also happy to tell you more about our company, our culture and the details of the position. For more information please contact Joni Piililä by phone +358 50 3844 109.\r\n\r\nWhen applying, please tell us about your strong points and the things that motivate and drive you forward. Application deadline is 15t of November 2017. As we are reviewing applications already during the application period, it would be great to hear from you as early as possible. Try to avoid waiting until the very last minute.",
