				"kuvausteksti" : "Security Engineer\r\n\r\nAltair Semiconductor has been operating in Oulu since beginning to the year. Up to this point, the core team has been built with great success and now there are few positions left to be fulfilled. We are now looking for the right professional specialized in security to strengthen their team. Interested? For more information, see the job description below!\r\nWe are now looking for our customer Altair Semiconductor Security Engineer to their office in Oulu. \r\n\r\nAltair is an 11-year-old company focusing on developing LTE technology for the Internet of Things (IoT) era. They develop semiconductors (RF, BB), software stacks, reference designs and complete solutions for their customers, the device makers. Their cutting edge technology positions them as world leaders in their space.\r\nAltair operates mainly in advanced markets like US, Japan and Korea. Their company has 250 employees, out of which 200 are engineers.\r\n\r\nIn 2016 Altair was acquired by Sony Corporation and they are now 100% subsidiary of their mother company. The acquisition provides Altair strong back and ability to leverage the technologies that exist within Sony. Nevertheless, they keep their agile culture and keep operating as a young, dynamic and energetic company.\r\n\r\nAltair/Sony has R&D site in Oulu (main R&D center is in Israel) to develop core LTE IoT technology. By 'core technology' they refer mainly to modem part (DSP, L1), but also to protocol stack, system integration, RF integration, IODT etc.\r\n\r\nWhat is this position about?\r\nAs a Security Engineer you are a significant part of a great team engaged with multidisciplinary design, development and integration of mobile 4G devices for the IoT market. Your job would be to develop and integrate embedded software for new type of secure 4G LTE devices. You will be engaged with various security and system aspects of the product and take part in defining and creating it from the very beginning.\r\nYou would be member of a team that designs, implements, tests and maintains the security software within complex System on a Chip (SoC). You will be deeply engaged with real time, bare-metal embedded firmware development, analyzing and debugging the software behavior and making sure it conforms to the specifications and requirements.\r\nThe platform you will be working on is Altair's newest chipset - designed especially for the IoT market, highly integrated and consuming super low power. The embedded code you will develop will drive new and exciting products for the internet of things era!\r\n\r\nRequirements:  \r\n BSC or MSC in computer science, electrical engineering or software engineering.\r\n At least 3 years of proven experience in software development (C language) and debugging. \r\n Excellent engineering skills - problem solving, pragmatic approach and broad system view.\r\n Experience in platform software development, boot sequence, HW interface.\r\n Experience with secure elements and cryptography.\r\n Superior oral and written communications skills required.\r\n Willingness to travel from time to time.\r\n\r\nIf you believe that our customer Altair Semiconductor and the position that they are offering is made for you, please leave your CV and application as soon as possible. We start the interviews straight away when the potential candidates apply. The chosen candidate will be employed by Altair Semiconductor. \r\nIf you have any questions concerning this position, feel free to contact us in Sharper. For more information, contact Consultant Manager Saara Niskanen +358 50 467 5319 (Monday-Friday 8 am to 4 pm). \r\nAlternatively, you may contact Head of Altair Semiconductor Finland, Markku Hiltunen, on Thursdays and Fridays 9 am to 11 am, on +358 40 543 1752.",
