				"kuvausteksti" : "Wärtsilä Marine Solutions enhances the business of its marine and oil & gas industry customers by providing innovative products and integrated solutions that are safe, environmentally sustainable, efficient, flexible, and economically sound. Being a technology leader, and through the experience, know-how and dedication of its personnel, Wärtsilä is able to customise solutions that provide optimal benefits to its customers around the world.\r\n\r\nPosition description\r\nTechnology, Testing & Validation is looking for a Manager, Engine Testing, to lead the W20 engine testing. The position is permanent and will be located in Vaasa, Finland. \r\n\r\nThe appropriate candidate needs to demonstrate a clear attitude to drive the Engine testing team organisation with strong commitment in: \r\n\r\n1. Managing the testing activities and the test team in the assigned responsibility area. \r\n2. Ensuring that test results are reliable and in compliance with industry specific standards and Wärtsilä guidelines. \r\n3. Reporting test results for required stakeholders. \r\n4. Focusing on right problem solving priorities. \r\n5. Working together with the product factories.\r\n\r\nResponsibilities\r\n- Leading and managing the assigned testing teams globally and locally according to the business strategy within assigned responsibility area \r\n- Defining the objectives, creating the action plan and ensuring its accurate implementation for own organisation \r\n- Planning and organizing component and performance tests on the test engines, production engines and on field engines \r\n- Analysing and reporting the test results, as well as developing and improving the test methods and facilities \r\n- Controlling and supporting the production and field engines\r\n- Monitoring and reporting performance in assigned organisation  \r\n- Co-operating with product group and expert organisation.\r\n\r\nRequirements\r\n- Technical education (BSc or MSc or equivalent) \r\n- Relevant technical background with Wärtsilä engines, system and solution knowledge \r\n- Experience in managerial position, also in Superior's role \r\n- Strong internal motivation, passion for execution \r\n- Ability to work globally with a clear customer understanding \r\n- Structured way of working.\r\n\r\nContact person to give further information\r\nPekka Vaahtera \r\nEmail: pekka.vaahtera@wartsila.com \r\nTel: +358 400 808 416 \r\n\r\nA CV attached to the application will be appreciated.",
