				"kuvausteksti" : "Application Engineer, Fastems Oy\r\n\r\nFastems is a leading Finnish supplier of automation solutions to industry. Fastems delivers world-class software and hardware and wants to act as a partner to its customers, leveraging cutting-edge technology and opportunities brought about by digitalization in its business.\r\nFastems' roots are in Finland, but the company's growth comes from extensive overseas operations.\r\nAt Fastems, you can become part of the 380-strong community of adaptable top professionals. When you take your expertise to Fastems, you will be offered a challenging and versatile job in return. No two days are ever the same at Fastems! Fastems is to an engineer what a sweetshop is to a child, and its customers are at the top of their fields. - Seize the opportunity! www.fastems.com\r\n\r\nOn behalf of our client Fastems, we are looking for a\r\n\r\nApplication Engineer for Robotized finishing solutions\r\n\r\nThe main responsibilities of the Application Engineer are to define, design and test robotized finishing solutions for customer needs. You will participate in customer meetings and support sales in cooperation with bid engineers and other specialists in Fastems. You will also train customers in Fastems' factory in Tampere. Development of finishing and deburring methods, robot tooling and testing as well as documentation are in important role in your tasks. \r\n\r\nRequirements\r\nWide experience of robotic solutions, development and programming\r\nExperience in off-line programming and 3D design\r\nDesire to make and develop documentation\r\nWell-organized working methods\r\nWillingness to travel about 40 days a year\r\nFluent English\r\n\r\nExperience in robot finishing application is a clear benefit.\r\n\r\nAt Fastems, you will work with state-of-the-art tools in one of the top companies in a rapidly growing industry. In your job you will be able to create the world's most advanced production environments for Fastems' customers. Fastems is an international organization with offices in a number of countries. Working at Fastems means that you can see and experience the world and enhance your professional skills in a variety of interesting projects. We want to offer people with a development-oriented approach opportunities and space to grow and improve their own professional skills.\r\n\r\nWe invite you to join us in the digitalization and automation revolution!\r\nWe hope you are excited, now we want to hear from you! \r\n\r\nYou can submit your application and CV on our website: www.raukola.fi/jata-hakemus. The deadline for applications is 19 November 2017, but we process applications immediately in order of arrival and we will start the interviews before the deadline.\r\n\r\nIf you require more information, please contact Arja Raukola Oy's Regional Manager Eeva-Maija Hiekkataipale, who will be happy to answer your questions. Eeva-Maija Hiekkataipale eeva-maija.hiekkataipale@raukola.fi or tel. +358 400 710 141.\r\n\r\nAbout Fastems: Fastems supplies flexible manufacturing systems (FMS) and robot applications for the metal cutting industry for automating the manufacturing and finishing processes. We are a privately-owned Finnish company founded in 1901 with an annual turnover of 80 million Euros and 380 employees worldwide. Our headquarters is located in Tampere, Finland, and we have sales offices covering all main market areas. This position is located at Lahdesjärvi, Tampere, Finland. Read more: www.fastems.com",
