				"kuvausteksti" : "Linux/C++ Developer\r\nWe are currently looking for a C++ engineer to join our Jolla boat. This position is primarily based in our office in Finland in Tampere, but other locations can be considered based on the applicant.\r\n\r\nIn this role you will participate in software development and maintenance of UI and middleware in Sailfish OS. Your tasks will include planning, designing, implementing and testing software modules. Depending on your experience and interests you may be contributing to areas such as accounts, service integration, connectivity, and location frameworks.\r\nThis is a permanent, full-time position and starts immediately once we have found the ideal candidate.\r\n\r\nYou are the person we are looking for, if you\r\n- have multiple years of experience in C++, Qt experience seen as advantage\r\n- have thorough understanding of Linux OS architecture\r\n- have good command of English language, other languages seen as an advantage\r\n- have good team working skills and 'can do' attitude\r\n\r\nWe offer you\r\n- a unique opportunity to work in an international and dynamic company\r\n- a chance to be part of Jolla's growth\r\n- a multicultural, passionate and professional crew to work with\r\n\r\nPlease send your CV and application to careers@jolla.com and mark \"Linux/C++ Developer\" to the email subject field. We will call suitable candidates to interviews and fill the position when we have the right match.",
