				"kuvausteksti" : "DO YOU WANT TO SHAPE THE FUTURE OF ROCK DRILLING?\r\nWE WANT TO HEAR MORE ABOUT YOU\r\n\r\nRock Knowledge Expert\r\n \r\nSandvik Mining and Rock Technology is the leading provider of equipment and tools as well as maintenance and technical services for the mining industry. Its products include drill rigs, mechanical mining equipment, crushers, loading and hauling equipment and material processing equipment. The Tampere plant is a global technology and manufacturing center for drill rigs. Our Product Area Rock Drills & Technologies is now looking for an active and innovative Rock Knowledge Expert for the Rock Drills Business Unit to provide a competitive advantage through deep knowledge of rock and ore extraction process. This is a permanent position and based in Tampere, Finland.\r\n \r\nKey Performance Areas\r\nYour key performance area is based on a deep understanding of distinct rock qualities and their impact on rock and ore extraction performance. You are accountable for developing rock knowledge with our technology development team as new strategic capability resulting in novel, information intensive services which improve customers' excavation processes. You are a networker who will be working closely with rock drills product development as well as our equipment, parts and service businesses.\r\n\r\nYour responsibilities also include the establishment of a rock knowledge related network and a rock knowledge database including links to global geological knowledge hubs. The role is an expert position that requires good communication skills and ability to coordinate work of internal and external parties effectively. You will report to the Head of Technology, Rock Drills Technology Development.\r\n\r\nYour Profile\r\nYou have a degree (M.Sc. or PhD) in geology or geophysics and more than five years' professional work experience, with at least five years in the mining industry. Your passion is in turning data about geology and rock characteristics into valuable information to further improve productivity in rock excavation. \r\n\r\nYou have an independent, proactive and service-oriented can-do attitude, together with a systematic approach and the ability to stay on schedule. You communicate fluently both in Finnish and English. Your technical skill portfolio on the top of your geological rock knowledge consist of skills to utilize mine planning systems, information management and interaction with global key stakeholders of rock data.\r\n\r\nWe offer you the challenge to participate in building a world-class Innovation Center of a global company and to influence the future of mining solutions. Our unique test mine gives you an exceptional opportunity to participate in reshaping of markets through high-end products and services. Furthermore, we offer you the support of our enthusiastic work community, passionate about rock drilling technology.\r\n\r\nSandvik is a high-tech and global engineering group offering advanced products and services that enhance customer productivity, profitability and safety. We hold world-leading positions in selected areas - tools for metal cutting, equipment and tools for the mining and construction industries, stainless materials, special alloys, metallic and ceramic resistance materials, and process systems. In 2016, the Group had approximately 43,000 employees and sales of around SEK 82 billion in more than 150 countries.",
