				"kuvausteksti" : "Enersense International Oy provides its customers with resourcing solutions which appreciate the fluctuations in their projects. Our company is an ISO 9001:2008/14001:2004-certified actor with more than ten years of experience in operating in close cooperation with large-scale nuclear and construction sites, the Olkiluoto 3 nuclear power plant site being the largest of them. \r\n\r\nWe are currently looking for TXS Commissioning Technicians for our client in Olkiluoto Nuclear Power Plant, Finland. We are offering challenging work in an international project environment.\r\n\r\nMain tasks and responsibilities:\r\n\r\n1. Preparation:\r\n\r\n- Request and check at reception TXS testing equipment and peripheral testing devices required during commissioning activities\r\n- Collect I&C system related testing documentation at the applicable reference configuration prior to test execution\r\n- Attend pre-job briefing prior to test execution\r\n\r\n2. Execution:\r\n\r\n- Prepare, implement and trace temporary modifications and simulations on TXS systems with strict respect to applicable procedures under the supervision of the TXS commissioning section lead\r\n- Implement modifications following the change management process in place under the supervision of the TXS commissioning section lead\r\n- Activities linked to I&C systems:\r\n\r\n- Support the commissioning document adaptation according to the actual I&C system status on site (e.g. RFA process)\r\n- Perform the commissioning activities under Permit-To-Test (PTT) conditions including the issuance of test reports and with strict respect of the test procedures\r\n- Troubleshooting and analysis activities\r\n- Activities linked to the support of process (mechanical, HVAC, etc.):\r\n\r\n- Execute the test under the supervision of the system Commissioning Engineer and the Loop Testing Coordinator\r\n- Assist the preparation of the test reports including the assessment of the I&C test outcomes\r\n- Support troubleshooting activities\r\n\r\n3. Control and monitoring:\r\n\r\n- Provide inputs to progress measurement and reporting to the test coordinator she / he is attached to\r\n\r\n4. Closure:\r\n\r\nThe completion of the commissioning activities related to the entrusted I&C system is sanctioned by following events:\r\n\r\n- Provide test results as inputs to the elaboration of Customer's approved System Commissioning Reports (SCR) which closes out the Phase A pre-operational tests associated to this I&C system\r\n- Participate in the elaboration of the documents supporting the TOTO (Temporary Operation Take Over) certificate which finalizes the transfer of the I&C system to OIO (Operation Integrated Organization)\r\n- Support the closure of all I&C system open points assigned to I&C Commissioning branch\r\n- As part of support provided to the commissioning of process systems, following activities need to be completed:\r\n\r\n- Support the closure of all open points assigned to other commissioning branches as involving TXP I&C system \r\n\r\nRequirements:\r\n\r\n- Technician degree in automation field\r\n- Experience in commissioning activities as well as EPR knowledge would be a plus\r\n- Aware of and strict adherence to HSE and IT security aspects\r\n- Knowledge of TXS technology both hardware and software products including maintenance and diagnostic tools\r\n- Familiar with standard testing tools (e.g. multimeter)\r\n- Familiar with TXS system test procedures\r\n- Capacity of organizing the day-to-day activities\r\n- Rigorous especially for adherence to procedures in force on site including configuration management\r\n- Ability to work in an international team \r\n- Good writing skills\r\n\r\nLanguages:\r\n\r\n- Intermediate knowledge of written and oral English\r\n- Ability with French, German or Finnish would be a plus\r\n\r\nPlease register as a jobseeker and apply for the position through our website. \r\n\r\nDrug test and concise security clearance will be done for the selected person in order to get the permanent access to OL3 site.\r\n\r\nThe post will be filled as soon as a suitable applicant is found.",
