				"kuvausteksti" : "We not only have ambitious goals but also a clear agreement on how to achieve them: For us, the means are as important as the ends. Whatever your role at ABB, you can be sure you are helping to create a better world. From building sustainable power plants in remote corners of the world, or improving safety for workers in automotive factories, to developing new technologies to combat pollution, the work we do touches the lives of millions.\r\n\r\nWe are looking for a R&D Engineer at ABB Oy, Motors and Generators unit in Helsinki. As a mechanical R&D Engineer, you will be working in the Performance Design Team with responsibilities related to structural dimensioning, strength and dynamic analysis of electric motors and generators. At ABB, you will have a good opportunity for professional growth and career advancement around the world. \r\n\r\nWe require a M.Sc. in mechanical engineering, and experience in design or product development related to the mechanical engineering of metal structures. We appreciate knowledge in the field of material strength, analytical assessment skills, and know-how related to structural analysis (FEM). Knowledge of different materials and phenomenas related to vibration and component fatigue are an advantage. You are strongly focused on design and development and have a spontaneous and determined attitude. The ability to execute long-term projects and the capability to work in a team as well as on your own are valued qualities. A good command of English and Finnish is required in this position; familiarity with MS Office and skills related to FEM programs, such as NX or ANSYS, are appreciated.",
