				"kuvausteksti" : "In 1987, Red Bull not only launched a completely new product, it created and has led ever since a whole new product category, Energy Drinks. Nowadays Red Bull employs more than 10400 people in over 170 countries, selling over 6 billion cans a year. The World of Red Bull provides the forum for you to use your talent and passion, to develop yourself and make an impact. Find out why we're different.\r\n\r\n\"Musketeers\" have always been main volume contributors as well as trial generators and spark for creating kindred spirits in the On Premise environment, such as bars, restaurants, events, clubs and hospitality. As the face of the brand and the indispensable consultant to your On Premise territory, you are responsible for driving both the current and future sales of our product portfolio and leveraging brand image in the On Premise.\r\n\r\nRESPONSIBILITIES\r\n\r\nTHE RED BULL AMBASSADOR\r\n\r\nAs A Red Bull Musketeer your main responsibility includes establishing and nurturing relationships with key influencers, industry players and business partners (including, but not limited to, outlet owners/managers, bar staff, distribution partners, promoters, agencies, etc.). This contains:\r\n\r\nBuilding affinity and understanding of the Red Bull brand and products within your network.\r\nBeing credible, reliable and knowledgeable face of Red Bull in the On Premise and deliver excellence with Red Bull's premium brand image in all activities and execution.\r\n\r\nTHE ENTREPRENEUR OF THE TERRITORY\r\n\r\nAs an Entrepreneur of the Territory you know your territory like the back of your hand. This includes:\r\nFollowing the company's strategy and creating innovative measures to achieve your goals\r\nMastering the On Premise universe by staying on the cutting edge of industry knowledge, trends and new opportunities (accounts, occasions, consumers)\r\nManaging internal and external resources (materials, tools, budget) to drive efficiency and effectiveness\r\n\r\nTHE INDISPENSABLE CONSULTANT\r\n\r\nAs an Indispensable Consultant you build and maintain long-lasting collaborations with key stakeholders. This requires you to:\r\nNegotiate win/win partnership agreements which add value to both Red Bull and customer's business\r\nLeverage your impressive communication, sales and marketing ability to keep Red Bull number one in the On Premise\r\nDrive and expand the business by identifying the right sales and marketing occasions at which Red Bull should be present (brand, product)\r\nTurn insights into impactful programs to drive sales and leverage Red Bull brand image and measure success diligently\r\n\r\n&#8195;\r\nWHAT WE EXPECT FROM YOU\r\n\r\nWe hope you to be well connected with key figures within the bar and nightclub scene either through previous work experience or personal connections. Also experience in the hospitality and/or FMCG industry is considered an advantage. Sales and marketing experience is highly valued. We also expect you to have:\r\n\r\nEnthusiastic, energetic and positive attitude\r\nAbility to think and act like an entrepreneur\r\nAbility to work independently in a high energy and fast-paced environment\r\nStrategic & innovative commercial awareness and acumen (understanding of sales and finance processes)\r\nStrong planning, prioritization and organizational skills\r\nStrong analytical skills (sales and customer data analysis)\r\nExcellent communication and active listening skills and the ability to negotiate\r\nStreet smart. Know what's going on in the streets - understand all groups of people, what every type of person must deal with daily and know how to act around them. Self-aware and able to adapt communication, presentation and professional appearance according to audience and scene.\r\nAbility to work flexible hours (including nights and weekends)\r\nWillingness to travel weekly within own territory\r\nBasic working knowledge of IOS and MS Office\r\nAt least 5 years of working experience\r\nFluent Finnish and English\r\nCollege degree preferred\r\n\r\nIn your cover letter, please include an explanation why your experience is specifically relevant to this role at Red Bull. We want to see your personal style - what makes you tick and why you think your next opportunity is here with us.\r\n\r\nMore info from Recruitment Consultant Tuija Autio +35840 569 000 or National On Premise Manager Henri Peltomäki 2 to 3. November +358 40 1889950. Send us your cover letter and CV, latest on the 12th of November 2017.",
