				"kuvausteksti" : "Our customer is fast growing international ICT Company. We are now searching Talent Manager to our customers premises located in Helsinki central area. HR team consists of Head of HR and 5 team members with overall Finnish headcount of about 300.\r\n\r\n\r\nAs a Talent Manager in our customers HR team you'll be reporting to Head of HR. Your main role is to support line managers in leadership and talent management. Your responsibilities include wide range of talent management:  on-boarding, training, succession planning, mentoring programs, low performance management and development discussion processes. Your responsibility is to proactively and independently suggest and develop ideas in the area of your responsibility. You are hands-on worker who also enjoys collecting detailed data and analyzing it.\r\n\r\nDesired experience:\r\n\r\n  - 4+ years talent management / coaching experience in an international company and/or at HR services company\r\n  - Fluent Finnish and English language skills\r\n  - Excellent communication skills across multiple stake holders and different nationalities\r\n  - Excellent skills on MS Excel\r\n  - Accuracy and ability to concentrate on details\r\n\r\nWe offer you an opportunity to grow as a talent professional in an international ICT company. Planned start date is January 2nd 2018. Contract is one year fixed term via ManpowerGroup with possibility to extend.\r\n\r\nIf you are interested, please apply at www.experis.fi with your CV and salary request. Interviews of potential candidates will begin during week 45.\r\n\r\nFor more information, please contact Senior Consultant Petteri Paassola, 040 17 55 818 or petteri.paassola@fi.experis.com\r\n\r\nExperis™ is the global leader in professional resourcing and project based workforce solutions. We attract, assess and place specialist professional talent, connecting the passion of individuals with the ambition of business. We specialize in providing professional opportunities across IT and Engineering, Finance and Accounting, Sales, Marketing, Communications and HR. We deliver high-demand talent for mission-critical positions to clients in over 50 countries. Experis is part of ManpowerGroup, the world leader in innovative workforce solutions.",
