				"kuvausteksti" : "Type: Full-time, permanent\r\nSuitable background: End of Studies-Graduated\r\nWorking hours: Fulltime, (Part-time can be negotiable if you still have some studies left)\r\nBeginning day: Negotiable\r\nLocation: Helsinki\r\nApplication DL: ASAP, but at the latest on November 19th 2017\r\n\r\nViking Theories is a startup company with secured funding that is developing a mobile game for an untapped global B2B market. Our team combines business, design and technology skills and has in total over 100 years of experience.\r\n\r\nViking Theories, a fresh start-up, is now looking for a Web Developer to build their core product with modern web technologies! As a Web Developer, you will take part in the daily development work of the product with a Senior Developer. The main technology of the product is JavaScript so you should have good skills to use it on daily basis.\r\n\r\nAs a person, you should be an enthusiastic and motivated developer who wants to develop their skills in a flexible start-up environment. In this role, your attitude matters and we also appreciate knowledge and skills gained from your own projects!\r\n\r\nWe look for:\r\n- Good skills with JavaScript, HTML & CSS\r\n- Relevant educational background and work experience within IT\r\n- Interest in the start-up world\r\n- Fluency in English\r\n\r\nWe consider as an advantage:\r\n- Any experience with React/Redux/other JavaScript frameworks\r\n- Knowledge in back-end development\r\n\r\nViking Theories offers:\r\n- A low hierarchy, transparent and flexible company culture where you are given responsibility yet freedom to carry out your work\r\n- A chance to work with modern technology stack and a possibility to impact future technology selection\r\n- An opportunity to be a part of creating something from the beginning with a highly skilled team\r\n- Tools to your liking and an office at an easily accessible location\r\n\r\nFor more information about Viking Theories visit: www.vikingtheories.com. For more information on the recruitment process and the position contact aTalent's Recruitment Manager Noora Markoff (noora.markoff@atalent.fi, +358 40 592 8993).",
