				"kuvausteksti" : "Viking Theories: Senior Developer\r\n\r\nType: Full-time, permanent\r\nSuitable background: End of studies - graduated with a few years of relevant experience\r\nWorking hours: Fulltime \r\nBeginning day: Negotiable\r\nLocation: Helsinki\r\nApplication DL: ASAP, but the latest on Sunday November 19th\r\n\r\nViking Theories is a startup company with secured funding that is developing a mobile game for an untapped global B2B market. Our team combines business, design and technology skills and has in total over 100 years of experience.\r\n\r\nViking theories, a fresh start-up, is now looking for a Senior Developer to build their core product with modern web technologies! As a Senior Developer you will take responsibility of the daily software development work of the product. You will be working in a small team together with an UI/graphics designer and a software developer. You'll be responsible of the technical part of our products from development all the way to hosting them in production.\r\n\r\nThe main technology of the product is JavaScript but in the future, you have a great chance to impact the technology selection! This is a great opportunity for a passionate developer to influence the success of the company. \r\n\r\nAs a person, you should be an enthusiastic and motivated developer who wants to develop their skills in a flexible start-up environment. To succeed in this role, you should have relevant prior software development experience. However, your attitude matters, and we especially appreciate knowledge and skills gained from your own projects.\r\n\r\nWe look for:\r\n\r\nStrong skills with developing modern web applications with JavaScript, HTML & CSS\r\nRelevant educational background and work experience within IT\r\nInterest in the start-up world\r\nFluency in English\r\n\r\nWe consider as an advantage:\r\n\r\nExperience with React/Redux/other JavaScript frameworks\r\nKnowledge in back-end development\r\nExperience in AWS or other Cloud Platforms\r\n\r\nViking Theories offers: \r\n\r\nA low hierarchy, transparent and flexible company culture where you are given responsibility yet freedom to carry out your work\r\nA chance to work with modern technology stack and a possibility to impact future technology selection\r\nAn opportunity to be a part of creating something from the beginning with a highly skilled team\r\nTools to your liking and an office at an easily accessible location\r\n\r\nFor more information about Viking Theories visit: www.vikingtheories.com. For more information on the recruitment process and the position contact aTalent's Recruitment Manager Noora Markoff (noora.markoff@atalent.fi, +358 40 592 8993).",
