				"kuvausteksti" : "We are a private small animal clinic located in Malmö. We provide basic prophylaxis as well as advanced medical, surgical and diagnostic services to pet owners. Our clinic is equipped with x-ray, ultrasound and our own laboratory.\r\n\r\nDUTIES:\r\nWe are looking for a small animal veterinarian who has some experience in the field. You will be able to work with a team as well as independently.\r\n\r\nQUALIFICATIONS:\r\nYou have a Doctor of Veterinary Medicine (D.V.M. or V.M.D.) degree from an accredited college of veterinary medicine.  You have some experience of working in the veterinary field, manual dexterity and problem solving skills are preferred. Professional comportment and appearance, with excellent interpersonal skills and a positive, friendly attitude are valid and needed. We assume that you have commitment and dedication to improving the lives of animals. You as a person have good communication skills and are able to handle a busy patient load while maintaining a positive attitude.\r\n\r\nMAIN RESPONSIBILITIES\r\nExamine animals to diagnose their health problems\r\nTreat and dress wounds\r\nPerform surgery on animals\r\nTest for and vaccinate against diseases\r\nOperate medical equipment, such as x-ray machines, ultrasound\r\nAdvise animal owners about general care, medical conditions, and treatments\r\nPrescribe medication\r\nEuthanize animals\r\n\r\nKEY SKILLS AND QUALIFICATIONS\r\nRequired\r\n2-3 years practice as veterinarian \r\nPreferred\r\nGood skills in one of Scandinavian language (Swedish, Danish, Norwegian)\r\n\r\n HOW TO APPLY:\r\nApplications including CV and Cover letter by mail to info@alfaveta.se with copy to miguel.salvador@arbetsformedlingen.se\r\n\r\nSalary:  2500 -3000 euro gross /month (Depending on Experience).  \r\n\r\nThis employment complies with the legislation of Sweden.",
