				"kuvausteksti" : "ALTEN Finland offers engineering and technology consulting for the leading companies of their industry. With our global network and strong local market position we are able to provide exact solutions for our clients' needs. ALTEN Finland is a part of ALTEN Group, which is active in 21 countries and employ over 26 000 employees. In Finland we employ over 400 specialists in 8 different locations in Espoo, Hyvinkää, Hämeenlinna, Lahti, Paimio, Tampere, Raahe and Oulu. Our target is to hire nearly 130 new designers and specialist this year.\r\n\r\nOur biggest clients operate in fields of process and energy industry, heavy industry, ICT and automation and electrical technology. In return we meet our clients' needs by offering wide range services in those fields. In addition we have strong expertise in the fields of documentation and technical writing. From our reference portfolio you can find multiple long term partnerships with the large Nordic corporates. \r\n\r\nWe are now looking for a driven\r\n\r\n\r\nTECHNICAL WRITER\r\n \r\n\r\nto join our documentation team in our Espoo office. \r\n\r\nYou will work with several projects with our partners and create content to the technical documents for different target groups. You will also have the opportunity to participate in our customers' documentation development projects. \r\n\r\nWe offer you a challenging position where you will have the ability to work in an inspiring and friendly working environment as well as find opportunities for personal development. \r\n\r\nDesired Skills and Experiences\r\n\r\nWe are looking for a highly motivated person with a can-do attitude. \r\n\r\nIn order to succeed in this position you will benefit of having:\r\n-A suitable educational background (M.A., M.Sc. or B.Sc. degree)\r\n-Experience in technical writing\r\n-Excellent communication skills in Finnish and English, both verbally and in writing\r\n-Good co-operational skills and willingness to work with clients\r\n-A structured and independent approach to completing your assignments and ability to understand and control large technical entities\r\n\r\nWe also value:\r\n-Experience in structural XML based documentation\r\n-Experience in Simplified Technical English (STE) content creation \r\n-Additional spoken and written languages\r\n\r\nWe offer you a challenging and diverse job description in interesting and international work environment. In addition we offer modern tools, nice coworkers and competitive benefits. You have a change to improve your skills and choose your career path according to your own abilities and interests our innovative work environment. \r\n\r\nTake a chance if you are interested in this position, please send your application and salary expectation by November 27th, 2017 via our website http://bit.ly/2lLVxoU. Please notice that we are interviewing candidates during the application period.\r\n\r\nFor additional information, please contact Coaching Business Manager Tomi Hugg, tel +358 504340918. \r\n\r\nWe are looking forward to receive your application.",
