				"kuvausteksti" : "We are now looking for a Chemistry Technician to our client company Areva NP. \r\n\r\nJob description: \r\n\r\n- Chemical surveillance of the nuclear and conventional circuits of the nuclear power plant\r\n- Taking samples from different fluid and gas circuits \r\n- Analysis of the samples in the laboratory\r\n- Following the chemistry handbook\r\n- Secure the chemical parameters in the technical specification\r\n- Documentation of the chemical surveillance\r\n- Preservation of fluid systems\r\n- Supervision of the nuclear waste handling \r\n\r\nCandidate profile: \r\n\r\n- Chemical technical degree\r\n- 5 years of experience in radiological chemistry of a running nuclear power plant with pressurized water reactor \r\n- Experience in laboratory work in a running nuclear power plant\r\n- Knowledge of all chemical laboratory methods needed in a nuclear power plant\r\n- Basic knowledge of the EPR technology\r\n- Deep knowledge in pressurizer water reactor technology and chemistry \r\n\r\nOther:\r\n \r\n- Knowledge of all chemical and radiological laws, guidelines (Finnish national and European)\r\n- MS Office Programs \r\n- Fluent English required \r\n\r\nWork in controlled zone: \r\n\r\n- Work in radiological controlled zone is mandatory\r\n- Radiological category a working capability \r\n\r\n\r\nWe are offering you a challenging position with a competitive salary!",
