				"kuvausteksti" : "Everon is a privately owned Finnish company specializing in cloud-based mobile and healthcare solutions. Its headquarters and product development center is in Lieto, near Turku, Finland. The company also has offices in the UK and Sweden. Today, Everon's solutions are being used in many countries and the company has at a group level doubled its sales during H1 2017. More information you will find from our website www.everon.fi.\r\n\r\nWe are now looking for a (junior) SW Engineer to join our development team in Lieto, Finland. \r\n\r\nAs a younger sw engineer your responsibilities include working tightly with R&D teams to innovate, define, design, build and deliver new features for client-server platform. You are able to take ownership of software features and drive the efforts of full cycle of software engineering delivery.\r\nYou will also be building and developing a server architecture and solutions from pre-existing components. You can ensure and maintain SW code/applications usability, reliability, robustness, performance and quality. And finally, you continuously discover, evaluate, and implement new technologies to maximize our development efficiency.\r\n\r\nQualifications:\r\n-Little experience with C#, .NET, Linux and MS systems, SQL databases,, Azure and Node.js\r\n-Knowledge and experience for SW development tools, methods (like scrum) and Git version control system\r\n-Good communication skills in English\r\n\r\nWhat we offer: \r\n-Position in a strong international growth company's development team\r\n-Versatile job description in fast growing Healthcare -section\r\n-Good and modern working tools\r\n-A creative and friendly work environment with minimal bureaucracy \r\n\r\nPosition will be filled as soon as the suitable candidate is found and work will begin upon agreement. Send your application and CV to Joonas Leiro, Recruitment Consultant, Click Personnel Services by 17.11.2017 at the latest. E-mail addresses are of the form firstname.lastname@click-hp.fi. For more information about the position call Joonas Leiro, tel. 050 411 0348",
