				"kuvausteksti" : "With offices in 80 countries, Manpower is one of the largest contingent and permanent staffing firms globally, and the market leader in the Nordic and Baltic countries. In Finland we are one of the largest companies specializing in recruitment, temporary staffing and assessments. We help employers find competent and motivated professionals for interim and permanent positions at all organizational levels. We serve our clients and candidates across the nation. Manpower is an authorized private employment agency.\r\n\r\n\r\nWe are currently looking for Spare Part Team Support for our client in Olkiluoto. Work starts as soon as possible and the duration is 2 months.\r\n\r\nMain tasks and responsibilities:\r\n\r\n-Assess maintenance and commissioning data to initiate spare parts and consumable orders in due time\r\n-Review and search for items in warehouse inventories\r\n-Search for technical/ quality documentation in databases/ folders\r\n-Follow-up of the purchase requests and purchase orders\r\n-Provide the documentation of the spare parts for the maintenance reports and other work orders\r\n\r\nRequirements:\r\n-Understanding of technical documentation\r\n-General understanding of mechanical, electrical and instrumentation technology\r\n-Computer literacy in MS-office\r\n-Perfect management of usual software (Excel, Work, Powerpoint, Outlook,..)\r\n-Fluent English (spoken and written)\r\n-German and French considered as a benefit\r\n\r\nWe are offering you a challenging position with a competitive salary!\r\n\r\nInterested? Apply for this job with your registered CV by clicking \"Hae\".\r\n\r\nFor more information (Mon-Fri 9-10) contact Recruitment Consultant Merja Nevalainen, p. 050 501 0031",
