				"kuvausteksti" : "Kakslauttanen Arctic Resort is one of Finland's best-known and most talked about travel destinations. This family business, founded in 1974, is located in Saariselkä, Lapland. Kakslauttanen hosts around 30,000 visitors each year, the majority of them from abroad. The guests include several high-profile visitors, media and international filming crews. Among others, Kakslauttanen has served as the location for Ralph Lauren and Vogue fashion shoots, the new TV show from Top Gear creators, The Grand Tour, Sports Illustrated as well as hundreds of travel programmes. During the winter season, the hotel employs 100 people from 25 different countries. The working language at the hotel is English.\r\n\r\nWe are looking for a Housekeeping supervisor to work with us during the next winter season. Employment will commence in November 2017. The supervisor is responsible for all the cleaners at the resort, providing instructions and monitoring the cleaning work, as well as ordering linen. The supervisor works closely with receptions and hotel manager. The role involves demanding manual labor as all our accommodation units are located separately outdoors. The role also involves routine cleaning work.\r\n\r\nDesired qualifications, skills, and experience:\r\nFluent in spoken and written English and Finnish; other languages are considered an advantage\r\nExperience of cleaning work in hotels\r\nA proactive attitude and a desire to do your best at all times\r\nAbility to work independently\r\nA driving license is considered an advantage",
