				"kuvausteksti" : "Logistics organization plans, optimizes and executes logistics services corporate wide both short and long term based on business needs. Tasks include transportation management with all transportation modes, global terminal network management, cross business area optimization and synergy sharing, and logistics development and asset management. Logistics organization focuses on safety, quality and cost-efficiency.  Collaboration and benchmarking also outside Neste are important elements, and teams act as a corporate level interface to the transportation and storage markets.\r\n\r\nWe are now seeking for an energetic and cooperative\r\n\r\nChartering Manager\r\n\r\nwhose task is to take care of chartering cargoes for Neste's account and/or cargoes for outside accounts to be carried on vessels operated by Neste. This includes negotiations with shipowners, tonnage operators and brokers to conclude Charter Parties for the vessels covering Neste's transportation requirements and optimizing on cargoes to obtain the most cost effective transportations for Neste's various business units. The chartering manager will liase closely with our own shipping operations team, internal traders, supply chain management, outside customers and other stakeholders.\r\n \r\nIt's important that you are a strong negotiator, selfconfident and able to form your own market view on basis of market reports, other relevant information, and day to day trading. You must be able to work independently, but you also need to be a team player with good cooperative and interaction skills to actively create and maintain stakeholder contacts, both internally and externally.\r\n \r\nWe prefer\r\n Applicable education (e.g. maritime, commercial)\r\n Experience of commercial shipping\r\n Experience of tankers and tanker trade, either at sea or ashore is advantage\r\n Knowledge of oil product logistics\r\n Customer service experience\r\n \r\nIn addition, we expect from you to be\r\n Fluent in written and spoken English, other languages being a benefit\r\n Flexible and have the right attitude to work at inconvenient hours\r\n Able to handle pressure and work efficiently also when extremely busy\r\n Able to work and make decisions independently\r\n Precise, analytical and careful, yet able to make quick decisions\r\n \r\nWe offer you interesting and challenging tasks in an international business environment with ample learning opportunities. The Chartering Manager reports to Head of Chartering.\r\n\r\nThe person selected for the position must pass a health examination that includes a drug test.\r\nSecurity clearance is obtained for the person with their consent.\r\n \r\nFurther information and more detailed instructions for applying can be found from our website: www.neste.com/joinus. Please submit your application by 14 November 2017 and include your CV and cover letter.",
