				"etatyo" : false,
				"kuvausteksti" : "BRAZILIAN EMBASSY IN HELSINKI\r\n\r\nOPEN POSITION:\r\n\r\nHOUSEKEEPER FOR THE AMBASSADOR'S OFFICIAL RESIDENCE\r\n\r\nApplicants are invited to participate in the selection process for the position of Housekeeper at the Ambassador's Residence. The agreement starts in the second half of November. It will be probationary for a period of six months, unless notice of termination is given prior to the end of that period.\r\n\r\nThe monthly salary is EUR 1.750.00, the working hours are 40 hours per week. The working time may vary. Currently it is 8 hours/day, Monday to Friday and weekends when needed. The position requires flexibility and availability to work occasionally longer shifts.\r\n\r\nJOB DESCRIPTION\r\n\r\nThe main activities of the job for the housekeeping are:\r\n- Take good care of daily household tasks paying attention to details.\r\n- Prepare and serve breakfast and meals.\r\n- Help in the kitchen before and during official events and also serve the table.\r\n- Wash, iron and arrange clothes in closets.\r\n- Clean the premises.\r\nMore detailed list of the chores will be provided in the interview.\r\n\r\nSELECTION CRITERIA\r\n\r\nThe applicant must have legal status in Finland, i.e. have a regular situation of residence and legal permission to exercise remunerated activities in Finland, and hold a Kela card.\r\n\r\nThe candidate must be:\r\n- Proactive and have initiative to solve daily problems.\r\n- A good team worker and work well under pressure.\r\n- Able to keep up with the daily chores even in special situations.\r\n- Able to work without close supervision and prepared to ask for instructions if needed.\r\n- Able to speak perfectly at least one of the following languages: English, French, Spanish or Portuguese.\r\n- Have flexibility to eventually change working shift.\r\n\r\nPlease send your application, CV and reference letters to recruitmentebh@gmail.com, no later than Friday 10 November. Please note that only the persons who send the application and CV in one of the abovementioned languages will be eligible for consideration. Interviews for the short-listed applicants will be held afterwards.\r\n\r\nWe are looking forward to your application.\r\n\r\nHelsinki, 6/11/2017\r\n\r\nThe Selection Committee",
