				"kuvausteksti" : "Wärtsilä is a global leader in complete lifecycle power solutions for the marine and energy markets. By emphasizing technological innovation and total efficiency, Wärtsilä maximizes the environmental and economic performance of the vessels and power plants of its customers. In 2016, Wärtsilä's net sales totalled EUR 4.8 billion with approximately 18,300 employees. The company has 170 locations in 70 countries spread around the world. \r\n\r\nOperations, Project Management is a part of Services 4-Stroke Engines organization. We provide Wärtsilä's Marine and Power Plant customers with life-cycle support services related to fuel conversions, modernizations, upgrades and new equipment. The Project Management teams operate in an environment which requires collaboration with a wide range of internal and external stakeholders, in order to serve a global variety of customers. Lean organization and direct responsibility towards the end customer requires the individuals to have a high level of commitment to the team and to take ownership of their own work. \r\n\r\nProject Management is now looking for a Project Engineer to strengthen their team. The position is located in Turku, Finland. \r\n\r\nResponsibilities\r\nProject Engineer works with customer delivery projects together with Project Manager and is accountable for technical solutions, supervision of ordered services, purchasing, quality, contract / requirement compliance, customer satisfaction, schedules and budget. \r\n\r\nThe project work is performed in compliance with Company Project Management Methodology and Business Directives. \r\n\r\nProject Engineer reports periodically status to the Project Manager or to the superior. \r\n\r\nThe product portfolio consists of Engines, Auxiliaries, Controls and E&A. The projects are single- or multi-portfolio products related to modifications, conversions, repairs and maintenance on both Wärtsilä and other OEM equipment. \r\n\r\nRequirements\r\n- B.Sc. or M.Sc. in Engineering, Naval Architect or Marine Engineer is an advantage\r\n- Autocad, MS Office, competence in some 3D engineering software seen as an advantage \r\n- SAP, Clarity and MS Project working experience is an advantage \r\n- General technical and functional knowledge of marine engines, propulsion and electrical\r\n- Good communication and team work skills \r\n- Passion and enthusiasm to work with customer delivery projects\r\n- Willingness to travel\r\n- Fluency in English.\r\n\r\nPerson to contact\r\nTuomas Helin, Project Group Manager\r\nTel: +358 40 700 4983\r\nEmail: tuomas.helin@wartsila.com",
