				"kuvausteksti" : "Kaiku HR is specialized in personnel leasing, outsourcing and recruitment. It is very important for us to find an inspiring and motivating job for the candidate or otherwise well-fitting task for his/ her current life situation. We believe that a motivated and inspired employee grants the success for our customer. \r\n\r\nWe are looking for Spare Part Engineer/ Technician to our customer company at Olkiluoto.\r\n\r\n\r\nDescription:\r\n\r\n- Assess maintenance and commissioning data to initiate spare parts and consumable orders in due time\r\n- Review and search for items in warehouse inventories\r\n- Search for technical/quality documentation in databases/folders\r\n- Follow-up of the purchase requests and purchase orders\r\n- Provide the documentation of the spare parts for maintenance reports and other work orders\r\n- Generatee purchase requests and technical requisition files\r\n- Coordinate the required inspections of the spare parts\r\n- Prepare the pick-up and handover of required spare parts\r\n\r\nRequirements:\r\n\r\n- Engineering degree/diploma with and emphasis on Mechanical Engineering (or similar) or experienced Technician with and Mechanical or Electromechanical background\r\n- Understanding of technical documentation for power plant components\r\n- General understanding of mechanical, electrical and instrumentation technology\r\n- Computer literacy in MS-Office\r\n- First experience with specifications and design documents (Construction Plans) are favorable. Exposure to facets of either maintenance, commissioning, quality, warehousing, procurement, or spare parts is mandatory.\r\n\r\nSkills required:\r\n- English (fluent)\r\n- French/Germany is considered a plus\r\n\r\nThe positions will be filled as soon as suitable candidates are found, so apply today by sending your CV and application.",
