				"kuvausteksti" : "Vaadin provides technology, tools, and services for software developers who create web based business oriented applications. Vaadin Framework is a Java web application development framework that is designed to make creation and maintenance of high quality web-based user interfaces easy.\r\nWe believe in open source, transparency, and that the best user experience wins. We've been in the business for over 15 years and are operating with positive cash flow. Today we have more than 140 people working with us globally with our HQ office in Turku, Finland, and additional offices in Helsinki, Berlin, and Silicon Valley.\r\nOur framework is currently adopted by more than 100,000 developers, and the user base has grown significantly in recent years, due to the explosion in mobile and other applications. We have customers all over the globe, with the vast majority in Europe and North America.\r\n\r\nVaadin is growing rapidly and we're looking for you to join our marketing team in helping us drive our leads and online sales channels. You'll be working in a team of three, driving the commercial adoption of our tools and services. You are familiar with funnel management, progressive profiling, gated content creation and master storytelling in a highly technical environment. Familiarity with Hubspot's workflows and campaign analytics is seen as a plus.\r\nYou will be collaborating closely with our sales team in driving high quality leads as well as online purchases.\r\nYour immediate colleagues include our Developer relations team, analytics responsible, graphical artist as well as partners and other experts inside the company.\r\nIf you're eager to monetize the open source business and have proven experience from international marketing, then this is your place to be!\r\n\r\nWE EXPECT THAT YOU\r\n-have at least 5 years of experience from marketing in an international product company,\r\n-are experienced and fluent in writing articles in English that drive to an action,\r\n-are able to relocate to Turku, Finland.\r\nExperience from SEO and Social Media attribution is seen as a big plus.\r\n\r\nWe're a young and dynamic team with a good work-life balance. You'll get to choose your own tools from hardware to software - we'll do anything to make you succeed! Besides being young we also have perks such as 10% of your time being available to be into your personal projects that help Vaadin move forward, lunch coupons, sports vouchers, game nights, movie nights, BBQs etc. If you need help in relocating to Turku, we'll help you all the way.\r\n\r\nCandidates will be contacted as they apply, and the position will be fulfilled as soon as a suitable candidate is found. \r\nSend your resume and application today!\r\n\r\nFor questions or more info don't hesitate to contact the hiring manager Fredrik Rönnlund, VP of Marketing, fredu@vaadin.com",
