				"etatyo" : false,
				"kuvausteksti" : "Want to do something interesting? Tired of working in a boring software project you don't really care about? Come work at Leiki! We are a growing and profitable company which offers text analysis and recommendation SaaS using our own unique ontology-based product. Business is booming and we are expanding rapidly in Europe and USA, so we need more people! Right now we are looking for a new\r\n\r\nSystem administrator\r\n\r\nfor our Helsinki office. Sure, there will be the usual daily tasks consisting of updates, documentation and maintenance as always - but you can also expect to work with interesting challenges due to new features, ever increasing efficiency requirements and varied international customers. Leiki also has a flat & flexible organization, where everybody from newcomer to CEO can give input on how to do things better, be it project methodology or a new algorithm. If this sounds good to you and you have the right skills, we want to hear from you!\r\n\r\nAt the moment we are looking for an experienced sysadmin who preferably is also happy to help with Java development tasks as needed. Your primary duties consist of managing our ever-increasing number of servers and applications running on them as well as ensuring everything is properly automated, monitored and documented. If you are willing to pitch in with occasional IT support duties around the office, it is appreciated, and any experience with Java profiling (memory/performance) is considered a big asset.\r\n\r\nApplicants should have:\r\n3+ years of industry experience.\r\nStrong experience in managing Linux servers.\r\nStrong experience in some of the following: cloud services, container/configuration management such as Docker or Puppet, TCP/IP networking or clustered services.\r\nExperience in SQL and databases.\r\nFamiliarity with some of the following: Jenkins, Tomcat, Apache, MySQL, Hibernate, Spring, JUnit, TestNG, Maven, ELK stack, Git, Atlassian software, nginx, DNS, computer hardware.\r\nProficiency in written and spoken English and good general communication skills.\r\n\r\nWe also appreciate:\r\nRelevant degree (such as M.Sc.).\r\nExperience in developing server-side Java applications.\r\nExperience in unit testing.\r\nInterest and skills in some of the following: algorithm design, distributed computing, machine learning or text analysis.\r\nFamiliarity with Internet technologies (HTTP, (X)HTML, JSP/servlets, JavaScript and similar).\r\n \r\nCheck out what we are all about at www.leiki.com!\r\n \r\nSend a short application with CV and preferred salary to jobs@leiki.com as soon as possible, latest by November 30th. If you have any questions about the position, please contact CTO Tomi Päiväniemi: tomi.paivaniemi@leiki.com.",
