				"kuvausteksti" : "Nordic Service Group is looking for 2 new positive team players to work as service engineers. You will be responsible of medical and/or laboratory equipment service. Our new colleagues have active and positive attitude on working. You are open for new challenges and continuously want to develop yourself. Jobs are mainly done in Finland but can also be performed in other Nordic countries. You will be part of Finnish service team reporting to service manager of Finland.\r\n\r\nFor the positions your optimal location could be in the close to the cities of: Tampere, Jyväskylä or Kuopio. In this position you will work independently and from home office.\r\n\r\nYour primary responsibilities are:\r\ndo equipment service consisting of \r\n\r\ninstallations\r\n\r\nupgrades\r\n\r\nrepairs\r\n\r\npreventive maintenance\r\n\r\ntechnical consultancy\r\n\r\nenhance customer satisfaction through high level service and communication\r\n\r\n\r\nWe wish from you\r\n\r\nyou can be experienced service engineer or a young gun showing your passion to learn\r\n\r\noutgoing personality and good communication skills\r\n\r\ncustomer oriented\r\n\r\ninterest on electronics and getting pleasure when making equipment work\r\n\r\nelectronical, biomedical, biochemical or service engineer education\r\n\r\nFinnish as native language and fluent oral and written on English (Swedish/Norwegian/Danish can be an advantage)\r\n\r\nwillingness to travel\r\n\r\n\r\nNSG offers\r\nNSG is strongly growing company and market leader on its field. Customers vary from the biggest healthcare companies globally to big hospitals and laboratories until smaller private clinics locally. You will have the position seeing Finnish and global healthcare sector on very wide perspective.\r\n\r\nFor further information please call country manager Teemu Valkonen phone 010-397 5403\r\n\r\nEmail your application and CV with your salary request to tva@nordicservicegroup.com \r\nMark your application NSG/Service engineer",
