				"kuvausteksti" : "Wärtsilä Marine Solutions enhances the business of its marine- and oil & gas -industry customers by providing innovative products and integrated solutions that are safe, environmentally sustainable, efficient, flexible, and economically sound. Being a technology leader, and through the experience, know-how and dedication of its personnel, Wärtsilä is able to customise solutions that provide optimal benefits to its customers around the world.\n\nPosition Description\nDelivery Centre Vaasa (DCV) is now looking for two (2) Development Experts to strengthen the Tools & Equipment team. \n\nOur team is a part of DCV's Pilot Delivery Unit which as an organization is responsible for co-ordinating, securing manufacturability and manufacturing new or upgraded products. We are responsible for securing functioning tool solutions. Our responsibility area incorporates everything from special hand tools to large lifting equipment and complex hydraulic tools controlled by computer. We find or develop solutions, prepare requirements for acquired equipment and maintain existing design/data. We also support different stakeholders in tool related studies, acquisitions, projects or questions. \n\nWe offer you a youthful team and an interesting position with a possibility to learn widely about Wärtsilä products and business. \n\nThe position will be located in Vaasa, Finland. \n\nResponsibilities \n- Coordinate tool development projects; secure that the developed solutions are available on time, are functional, safe and fulfil legal requirements \n- Support stakeholders in tool related studies or expertise questions \n- Define and prepare technical specifications for acquired equipment and ensure that offered solutions fulfil the requirements \n- Participate in product development projects and give support in an expert role. \n\nRequirements \n- B.Sc. or M.Sc. in Engineering (or other proven technical ability) \n- 3 years of working experience with design/development projects \n- Knowledge of NX / Teamcenter (or other similar design program)\n- Knowledge of Machinery Directive and applied standards \n- Systematic and organized way of working, good problem solving skills \n- Good communication and team working skills \n- Fluency in Finnish and English \n- Expertise in strength calculation, welding, hydraulics or any other traditional engineering area is taken into account as a notable advantage. \n\nPerson to contact\nSami Lehtonen, Manager, Tools & Equipment \nTel: +358 40 3507411 \nEmail: sami.lehtonen@wartsila.com",
