				"kuvausteksti" : "SOURCING MANAGER\n\nOutotec provides leading technologies and services for the Sustainable use of Earth's natural resources. As the global leader in minerals and metals processing technology, we have developed many breakthrough technologies over the decades for our customers in metals and mining industry. We also provide innovative solutions for industrial water treatment, the utilization of alternative energy sources and the chemical industry. Outotec shares are listed on NASDAQ OMX Helsinki. www.outotec.com\n\nAt Outotec we are passionate about building innovative and sustainable solutions that fulfill world's growing need for natural resources. We are continuously entering new markets and businesses, which creates interesting opportunities for personal and professional growth in our multinational work environment.\n \nJoin the team of Outotec professionals as a Sourcing Manager working in our Global Supply - Global Component Sourcing. In Global Component Sourcing you will manage Sourcing activities in component categories globally. Majority of the scope of Component Sourcing is related to commercial/3rd party components, yet also a great variety of manufactured parts and complete systems may form part of your portfolio. These universal categories also drives you to work with across Outotec technologies, having a network of product and business owners, supply chain professionals, engineers and suppliers across all continents.\n\nWe are looking for a motivated and self-oriented person with strong background of defining and implementing Category Strategies in a global and technology driven environment. You do not need to be an engineer, but general interest to technology, learning ability, logical thinking and strong analytical approach will be mandatory. Needless to say, we expect the members in our team to be strong in change management, networking and negotiating, and to stand the pressure at times in a changing business environment. \n\nThe position will be permanent, full time, and based in Espoo or Lappeenranta, with reasonable amount of travelling. You will report to the Head of Global Component Sourcing\n.\nAs Sourcing Manager, You will:\n\nManage your own component category portfolio\nManage strategic Suppliers, negotiating Frame Agreements and continuous improvement initiatives\nDefine and implement Category Strategies\nMaintain and improve cost competitiveness or our products\nSupport operations in critical Supplier and Supply Chain topics\nManage strategic supplier co-operation relationships & performance, and establish Frame Agreements and pricelists\nDefine component strategies, key suppliers, prioritization and action plan in own responsibility area.\nProtect Outotec IPR in Sourcing dimension including R&D activities\n\nTo succeed, you will need:\n\nSuitable Engineering or Commercial degree\nMinimum 5 years of experience in Global Sourcing and managing Sourcing Category\nSkills to analyze Supply Base, to define Strategies and to implement Strategies into practices end to end\nExperience in leading and performing international business negotiations\nAbility to work with others in a matrix from a range of cultures within a diverse political, economic, technical and social environment.\nSufficient technology, process and services business understanding\nGood skills in SAP, MS Office programs & experience using PDM tools & systems\nSelf-motivated approach and ability to work independently\nFluent spoken and written English, other languages are an asset",
