				"kuvausteksti" : "Kakslauttanen Arctic Resort is one of Finland's best-known and most talked about travel destinations. This family business, founded in 1974, is located in Saariselkä, Lapland. Kakslauttanen hosts around 30,000 visitors each year, the majority of them from abroad. The guests include several high-profile visitors, media and international filming crews. Among others, Kakslauttanen has served as the location for Ralph Lauren and Vogue fashion shoots, the new TV show from Top Gear creators, The Grand Tour, Sports Illustrated as well as hundreds of travel programmes. During the winter season, the hotel employs over 100 people from 25 different countries. The working language at the hotel is English.\r\n\r\nKakslauttanen Arctic Resort is looking for skilled, experienced and service-oriented Night Receptionists for next winter season. Employment will commence in November 2017 and last until March or April 2018.\r\nAs winter is the peak season, working days can be very busy. Applicants should possess the ability to work quickly and cope with pressure. A hotel receptionist is the first friendly face guest see and he/she will make guests feel welcome, manage room bookings and deal with requests that guests make during their stay. The receptionist also needs to be professional at all times, be able to look after several things at once and always stay calm, sometimes under pressure.\r\n\r\nThe role will involve:\r\n- Checking guests in and out\r\n- Assisting and guiding guests\r\n- Booking activities, arranging transport, and so on\r\n- Answering emails and phone calls\r\n- Supporting staff with other tasks around the resort as required\r\n\r\nDesired qualifications, skills, and experience:\r\n- Fluent in written and spoken English. Other languages are considered an advantage.\r\n- Relevant educational background\r\n- Experience of working in an international hotel\r\n- Experience of working with hotel reservation system\r\n- An proactive attitude and excellent customer service skills\r\n- Ability to work independently\r\n- A driving license",
