				"kuvausteksti" : "We are looking to hire Souvenir Shop and Customer Service agent.\r\nYour main tasks will include:\r\n-Ensure that store is clean, safe, presentable and well stocked for customers\r\n-Generate and maintain daily, weekly and monthly sales reports\r\n\r\nThe applicant must have the following:\r\n-Strong and high standard experience in retail market\r\n-Capable of handling cash register with accurate reports and accountable for Souvenir shop\r\n-General knowledge of computerized inventory control system\r\n-Excellent customer service skills, exhibiting a friendly, engaging personality\r\n-Multitasking skills and ability to assist in other service departments as and when needed\r\n-Driver's license\r\n-2-3 years of work experience in relevant field\r\n\r\nKakslauttanen Arctic Resort is one of Finland's best-known and most talked about travel destinations. This family business, founded in 1974, is located in Saariselkä, Lapland. Kakslauttanen hosts around 30,000 visitors each year, the majority of them from abroad. The guests include several high-profile visitors, media and international filming crews. Among others, Kakslauttanen has served as the location for Ralph Lauren and Vogue fashion shoots, the new TV show from Top Gear creators, The Grand Tour, Sports Illustrated as well as hundreds of travel programmes. During the winter season, the hotel employs 100 people from 25 different countries. The working language at the hotel is English.\r\nWe offer a chance for a unique international life and work experience in the middle of Lapland's wilderness. With us, you'll be involved in developing our business as well as yourself.",
