				"kuvausteksti" : "Hexagon Manufacturing Intelligence helps industrial manufacturers develop the disruptive technologies of today and the life-changing products of tomorrow. As a leading metrology and manufacturing solution specialist, our expertise in sensing, thinking and acting - the collection, analysis and active use of measurement data - gives our customers the confidence to increase production speed and accelerate productivity while enhancing product quality.\n \nHexagon Manufacturing Intelligence is part of Hexagon, a leading global provider of information technologies that drive quality and productivity across geospatial and industrial enterprise applications.\n \nHexagon (Nasdaq Stockholm: HEXA B) has approximately 18,000 employees in 50 countries and net sales of approximately 3.1bn EUR. Learn more at www.hexagon.com \n\nWe are searching for an independent and proactive\n\nMaintenance Engineer\n\nTo join our team in Helsinki, Finland. You are responsible for the maintenance and calibration of our 3D-coordinate measuring machines. Our customers are located all around Finland so you will be travelling most of the time: approximately four days out of five. You can organize your calendar independently and also have a clear area of responsibility. \n\nTo succeed in this role, you should have\n\n- an Engineering degree (preferably from mechanical engineering)\n- previous working experience from technical support or maintenance\n- technical orientation and ability to learn new systems and programs easily.\n\nWe also appreciate an independent, proactive and detail-oriented way of working. You should also be fluent in Finnish and English.\n\nWe offer you an interesting opportunity to self-organize your work in an international environment, within different kind of customers from small machinery producers to listed companies. We also provide you a thorough on-boarding, modern working tools and a car-benefit.\n\nIf you want to join our supportive, easygoing team, please send your CV and application in English latest by 23.11.2017. www.personnel.fi/avoimet-tyopaikat \n\nPersonnel's Research Consultant Elina Koljonen tel. +358 50 340 9778 is happy to give you more information about the role on Thursday the 16th of November between 1pm and 3pm.",
