				"kuvausteksti" : "On behalf of our client, an international software company,  we are looking for a candidate to fill the position of a Commercial Marketing Program Manager to be located in Espoo. You will support local executions and support in driving the commercial business segments. Your main responsibility is to manage the local marketing projects, plan and collaborate with key internal and external stakeholders. Projects are reported on a monthly basis. The Commercial Marketing Program Manager will drive local content marketing projects based on key themes defined for the Finnish market, run specific local digital campaigns and help maintain local digital presences.\n\nWe are looking for a person who has experience in Commercial Marketing project/campaign management, Content/Editorial Marketing and Marketing Analytics and also Marketing Automation capabilities. You need the ability to analyze marketing performance. The success factor with be to understand the customers needs and behaviour. To succeed in this position you need good teamwork skills, you should be very self-motivated and proactive with the ability to take ownership and control of work. You will need fluent English and Finnish.\n\nBachelor or Master's degree in Marketing and 3-5 years of relevant experience.\n\nYou will be working in an international company with diverse tasks. We offer you a fixed-term employment until the end of June 2018 with a possible extension. Besides your local team you get access to a vast international network that offers you support and opportunities to learn and develop yourself. Apply for this position as soon as possible by filling out an application form and attach your CV with a salary request at www.vmp.fi\n\nVMP Varamiespalvelu is a Finnish personnel service company that has almost 30 years of experience in developing the sector, and specialises in staffing services and recruitment in all sectors. We provide employment for 14,000 people in over 3,000 client companies annually. VMP has been granted the Private Employment Agencies Association's certification. www.vmp.fi",
