				"kuvausteksti" : "Citec is expanding its engineering activities in the minerals and metals industry. We are now looking for skilled Chief Process Electrification Engineers to work for us in Helsinki area. As a Chief Process Electrification Engineer, you will be managing the process electrification design scope and lead the electrical engineering team within the projects.\n\nWe are looking for an enthusiastic, customer oriented person with experience in leading engineering projects, who is ready to be part of growing business and developing the relationship with our valued customers.\n\nYour main tasks will be:\n\n-Leading and managing the design for process electrification from MV/LV substation to electrical consumer via electrical MCC's and panels including cable management and race ways.\n-Conducting electrical basic and detail design in process electrification area for process and mining industry including electrical equipment specifications.\n-Securing the design quality in projects via checking and approving\n-Providing technical support for the project team and sales\n-Acting as the main contact within own discipline towards the customer\n-Developing new solutions in our customer projects\n-Coordination and cooperation with other disciplines' project teams\n-Capability to lead people including good communication skills, team-spirit and driving attitude\n\nQualifications:\n\n-M.Sc. or B.Sc. in electrical engineering\n-At least 8 years working experience of process electrification in industrial projects\n-At least 3 years of design experience of process electrical systems from substation to LV electrical consumers\n-Technical knowledge of LV switchgears, motor control cabinets (MCC'c), variable frequency drives (VFD's), cables and cable raceways\n-Knowledge of electrical IEC standards, ATEX directives and machine/process safety\n-Experience in minerals and metals industry\n-Knowledge of design tools, such as Autocad, ePlan, PDMS, E3D\n-Cooperative and customer orientated way of working\n-Good communication skills in Finnish and English\n-Capability to lead people including good communication skills, team-spirit and driving attitude\n\nWe offer you:\n\n-Interesting and challenging work in both domestic and international projects\n-International and flexible work environment\n-Skilled colleagues and friendly atmosphere\n\nWould you like to join our team of professionals? For more information please contact Head of Electrical & Automation Engineering, Timo Wolff +358 50 4320 321 or Manager, Electrical and Automation Engineering, Rickard Nygård +358 50 4283 862. Read more and apply via www.citec.com/careers, Citec needs your expertise!",
