				"kuvausteksti" : "Citec is expanding its engineering activities in the minerals and metals industry. We are now looking for skilled Chief Instrumentation & Automation Engineers to work for us in Helsinki area. In this role, you will be managing the instrumentation and automation design scope and lead the electrical engineering team within the projects.\n\nWe are looking for an enthusiastic, customer oriented person with experience in leading engineering projects, who is ready to be part of growing business and developing the relationship with our valued customer.\n\nMain responsibilities:\n\n-Leading and managing the field instrumentation design for process from DCS system to instrument via junction boxes including cable management\n-Conducting the instrumentation basic design for process and mining industry including instrumentation specifications\n-Securing the design quality in projects via checking and approving\n-Providing technical support for the project team and sales\n-Acting as the main contact within own discipline towards the customer\n-Developing new solutions in our customer projects\n-Coordination and cooperation with other disciplines' project teams\n-Capability to lead people including good communication skills, team-spirit and driving attitude\n\nQualifications:\n\n-M.Sc. or B.Sc. in electrical engineering\n-At least 8 years of working experience of instrumentation in process industry\n-At least 3 years of design experience for field instrumentation\n-Technical knowledge of DSC/PLC platforms, process measurements, process instrument equipment and cables\n- Knowledge of Instrumentation IEC standards, ATEX directives and machine/process safety\n-Knowledge of design tools, such as Autocad, ePlan, PDMS, E3D\n-Experience in minerals and metals industry\n-Cooperative and customer orientated way of working\n-Good communication skills in Finnish and English\n-Capability to lead people including good communication skills, team-spirit and driving attitude\n\nWe offer you:\n\n-Interesting and challenging work in both domestic and international projects\n-International and flexible work environment\n-Skilled colleagues and friendly atmosphere\n\nWould you like to join our team of professionals? For more information please contact Head of Electrical & Automation Engineering, Timo Wolff +358 50 4320 321 or Manager, Electrical and Automation Engineering Rickard Nygård +358 50 4283 862. Read more and apply via www.citec.com/careers, Citec needs your expertise!",
