				"kuvausteksti" : "The Adecco Group, based in Zurich, Switzerland, is the world's leading provider of HR solutions. With over 31,000 FTE employees and more than 5,500 offices, in over 60 countries and territories around the world, Adecco Group offers a wide variety of services, connecting more than 600,000 colleagues with over 100,000 clients every day. The services offered fall into the broad categories of temporary staffing, permanent placement, outsourcing, consulting and outplacement. The Adecco Group is a Fortune Global 500 company.\n\nWe are now looking for Spare Parts Engineer for our international client on OL3 Site in Olkiluoto, Eurajoki. The job starts as soon as the right candidate is found and lasts for 12 months.\n\n\nCriterions:\n\n- Engineering degree/diploma with an emphasis on Mechanical Engineering (or similar) or experienced Technician with a Mechanical or Electromechanical background\n- Understanding of technical documentation for power plant components\n- General understanding of mechanical, electrical and instrumentation technology\n- Computer literacy in MS-Office\n- Good communicator\n- Experience with warehousing and related software is beneficial\n- Understanding of quality documentation and certificates is beneficial\n- Fluent in written and spoken English\n\n\nResponsibilities:\n\n- Assess maintenance and commissioning data to initiate spare parts and consumable orders in due time\n- Review and search for items in warehouse inventories\n- Generate Purchase Requests and technical Requisition Files\n- Follow-up of the Purchase Requests and Purchase Orders\n- Coordinate the required inspections of the spare parts\n- Generate Issue Notes to receive parts from the warehouse\n- Provide the documentation of the spare parts for maintenance reports and other work orders\n- Prepare the pick-up and handover of required spare parts\n\nWe're offering you the possibility to work with an international company where you can use and develop your skills. Please apply for the \"Spare Parts Engineer\" position by registering at www.adecco.fi. Attach your English CV to the application. For more information, please contact Senior HR Consultant Eerika Jantunen +35846 875 0111 or eerika.jantunen@adecco.fi.",
