				"kuvausteksti" : "Citec is expanding its engineering activities in the minerals and metals industry. We are now looking for skilled Senior Structural Engineers to work for us in capital area. As a Senior Structural Engineer, you should have solid experience in the steel and/or concrete structures and modern 3D design tools.\n\nMain responsibilities:\n\n    Acting as Senior Structural Engineer in domestic and international projects\n    Securing that the customer requirements are met in the project\n    Mentoring structural engineers in the design work\n\nQualifications:\n\n- B.Sc. of M.Sc. in Civil/Construction Engineering\n- 5 years of experience in structural engineering, both steel and concrete structures\n- Experience in modern 3D design tools\n- A- or AA- FISE qualification within structural engineering is seen as a benefit, but not necessary\n- Experience in minerals and metals industry is seen as a benefit\n- Architecture design experience is seen as a benefit\n- Experience in BIM is seen as a benefit\n- Good communication skills in Finnish and English\n- Customer focused and proactive way of working\n\nWe offer you:\n\n- Interesting and challenging work in both domestic and international projects\n- International and flexible work environment in a growing company\n- Skilled colleagues and friendly atmosphere\n\nWould you like to join our team of professionals? For more information please contact Head of Civil Engineering, Joakim Ingves +358 50 322 3126. Read more and apply via www.citec.com/careers by 12th November, Citec needs your expertise!",
