				"kuvausteksti" : "Kekkilä Group is a manufacturer and marketer of high quality growing substrates, fertilizers and garden items for consumers, professional growers and landscapers. Growing is our passion and we want to grow together with our customers and consumers. \n\nWe are looking for a skilled Supply Planner to join our growth journey\n\nEfficiency is your key driver and bringing structure to complex surrounding motivates you. You understand the importance of excellent supply planning and can spread your knowledge throughout the organization. It is important that you have already gained some experience from supply planning with the educational background from economical or technical studies. Having experience from international business is a plus.\n\nYou will be responsible of tactical operational planning of the professional substrates from multiple production sites located in Finland and Estonia. Tasks main focus is on balancing out capacity planning with demand to ensure efficiency in factories.\n\nYour responsibilities also include:\n- establishing strong relationships with production site personnel and working cross-functionally with sales and product teams and category leads \n- willingness and desire to become an expert in Cognos Planning Analytics, and other company tools to improve overall performance\n- product cost calculation process together with finance and controlling\n- steering of packing materials inbounding to factories and supporting the supply of finished goods\n- Identifying and driving systemic improvements to reduce supply chain costs\n- taking the initiative to identify, lead, and establish continuous improvement practices \n\nMain skills needed in the position:\n- Knowledge and understanding of supply chain planning and inventory management \n- Knowledge of multiple aspects of production planning and SC including capacity planning, manufacturing, material lead times and quality requirements.\n- Previous production planning and supply chain experience \n- Bachelor's degree with 3+ years working in operations environment, direct operations planning or equivalent experience, ideally in Consumer Package Goods industry \n- Strong Excel, MS Word, and project skills plus experience utilizing ERP software such as Microsoft DAX and Microsoft Cognos environment \n- Experience in collaboration and influencing cross functional teams and production sites \n- Well organized with excellent and effective follow-up skills \n- Ability to work on multiple priorities, meet deadlines, and set priorities while maintaining flexibility in a fast-paced environment \n- Fluent English, location TBD, but preferably Vantaa, willingness to travel\n- Adaptiveness to change\n- For more information, please contact Juha Järvinen; Manager, Group planning and QEHS, tel. +358 20 790 4858 or Jukka Merta; SC Director, tel. +358 20 790 4869.\n\nPlease fill in your application and CV together with a salary indication by 24th of November.",
