				"kuvausteksti" : "Android Developer\n\nWould you like to be part of transformative and agile work environment, where your opinion matters?\n\nIf yes, you will get the opportunity to learn and grow while creating cutting-edge apps and solutions for customers within the fintech and transit domain.\n\nWhat we offer:\n\nYou will join a growing community of Android developers within a company characterized by flexibility, team achievement, entrepreneurial drive and integrity. In different projects, you will become a central contributor across the development process, while sparring and collaborating with skilled IT-professionals.\n\nHere you will be part of a passionate and dynamic team with great colleagues, engaging in hackathons, Friday bars, and monthly events such as wine tastings, movies and foosball tournaments.\n\nBecause your professional growth and personal well-being is a priority, we offer participation in knowledge conferences and certification programs, onsite weekly massage and a great lunch scheme with daily healthy food options.\n\nYour responsibilities:\n\n    Deliver fantastic Android apps to costumers and the users\n    Write beautiful, flexible and maintainable code optimized for Android\n    Collaborate with designers and project managers to create UX oriented and first-class solutions\n    Engage and participate in defining strong APIs and integrate against middleware services\n    Drive and maintain highest quality from implementation to end user experience. \n\nRequired skills:\n\n    A strong understanding of object oriented programming and design patterns\n    A \"best practices\" approach and a passion for code quality and craftsmanship\n    Experience with Unit testing, TDD, debugging and bug reporting\n    Experience with version control (GIT) and continuous integration\n    Experience with design and use of RESTful web service APIs\n    Deep knowledge of Java, Android SDK and building apps for a wide range of devices\n    Deep knowledge of Activity and Fragment life-cycles, Android's threading model and view hierarchies\n    Fluent in Activities, Fragments, CursorAdapters, ContentProviders, creating custom views and animations.\n    Experience working with Google support libraries and app deployment to Google Play store\n\nDesired skills:  \n\n    Experience with MVP architecture, RxJava, Realm, Retrofit, Dagger and Espresso libraries.\n    Experience with Photoshop, Sketch, Affinity Designer, SQLite, technical documentation\n    Work experience with Atlassian, JIRA, Confluence, Stash and Bamboo.\n\nAbout you:\n\nWe imagine that you are an English speaking, self-motivated individual, able to work and take decisions in as a team and independently. You should be confident working with Android Studio, Gradle scripts and build variant/flavors configuration.\n\nFor further information:  Contact Maria Olesen, phone: +45 29720979 or e-mail: maria@execute.dk\n\nhttps://app.jobmatchprofile.com/7chdas",
