				"kuvausteksti" : "iOS Developer\n\nWould you like to be part of transformative and agile work environment, where your opinion matters?\n\nIf yes, you will get the opportunity to learn and grow while creating cutting-edge apps and solutions for customers within the fintech and transit domain.\n\nWhat we offer:\n\nYou will join a growing community of iOS developers within a company characterized by flexibility, team achievement, entrepreneurial drive and integrity.\n\nHere you will be part of a passionate and dynamic team with great colleagues, engaging in hackathons, Friday bars, and monthly events such as wine tasting, movies and foosball tournaments.\n\nBecause your professional growth and personal well-being is a priority, we offer participation in knowledge conferences and certification programs, onsite weekly massage and a great lunch scheme with daily healthy food options.\n\nYour responsibilities\n\nAs part of a project you will be a central contributor across the development process, from early concept to finished product.\n\nWe are passionate about great user experience and you will collaborate with other developers, designers and project managers to advocate the end-user and ensure our apps are easy and intuitive to use.\n\nThe position requires you to be self-driven and, depending on your experience, you will take responsibility for individual features or lead a project to ensure best practices and delivery of high quality code.\n\n    Write SOLID, testable and maintainable code\n    Document and unit test your code to deliver high quality\n    Take part in developing and ensuring best practices across our team\n    Maintain highest quality from implementation to end user experience\n\nRequired skills:\n\n    2+ years of iOS development\n    A solid foundation in either Swift or Objective C\n    A strong understanding of OOP and design patterns\n    Experience with networking, multithreading and data persistence\n    Experience with Cocoa standard components, UIKit, AutoLayout\n\nDesired skills:\n\n    Experience with CoreData, unit testing and TDD\n    Experience with build servers and Fastlane\n    Previous experience with project leadership is also a plus\n\nAbout you:\n\nWe imagine that you have focus on usability, visual appeal, an end-user approach and are a self-driven individual with a passion for best practices and code craftsmanship.\n\nFor further information: \n\nContact Maria Olesen, phone: 29720979 or e-mail: maria@execute.dk\n\nhttps://app.jobmatchprofile.com/66q6y3",
