				"kuvausteksti" : "N-PRO Resources Oy Ltd is a staffing and recruiting company belonging to Nipromec Group focusing mainly on needs of our customers in the fields of energy, industry and offshore.\n\nWe are now looking for a Commercial officer for the painting team for our client in Olkiluoto. Work starts as soon as possible and estimated duration is about 11 months.\n\nThe Commercial Officer reports directly to the Painting Manager of OL3. The role is mainly driven by supporting the site managers for purchasing materials and services.\n\nMain Responsibilities:\n-Summarizing requests for materials and service in live with the purchasing processes.\n-Requesting for prices at different local and international suppliers.\n-Production of approval documents for purchase of material.\n-Communication and organization for the supply of materials.\n-Placing of work orders after approval by management.\n-Cooperation with storage keeper to update the stock of material.\n-Quality inspection of the received material, documentation and archiving of those documents.\n-Issuance of chemical permit.\n-Documentation and archiving of material and staff list.\n-Handling and documentation for the supply of PPE to the respective contractors.\n-Participation in team meetings and presentation of key values of the work.\n-Support of the Painting Manager for reporting of cost and effort inside the team towards the management.\n-Reporting of weekly/monthly effort values.\n\nGeneral and technical background expected:\n-Office person with ability to drive processes for the purchase of material and consumables for the execution of painting works.\n\nSkills required:\n-Minimum 3 years of experience in office work in large projects.\n-Good knowledge of MS Office programs.\n-Self- organizing skills. \n-Good comunicational skills and positive attitude.\n-Flexibility regarding working hours and breaks.\n-Specific nuclear project experience is not necessary.\n-Good reporting writing skills.\n-Fluent English (both written and spoken) required, Finnish and/or German is an advantage.\n\nPosition is filled as soon as suitable candidate is found. To apply please send application and CV with salary request to info@n-pro.fi . For more information please go to www.n-pro.fi",
