				"kuvausteksti" : "N-PRO Resources Oy Ltd is a staffing and recruiting company belonging to Nipromec Group focusing mainly on needs of our customers in the fields of energy, industry and offshore.\n\nWe are now looking for a Chemistry Technician for our client in Olkiluoto.  Work starts in as soon as possible and estimated duration is 12 months.\n\nThe Chemistry Technician tasks includes:\n-Chemical surveillance of the nuclear and conventional circuits of the nuclear power plant.\n-Taking samples from the different fluid and gas circuits.\n-Analysis of the samples in the laboratory.\n-Following the chemistry handbook.\n-Secure the chemical parameters om the technical specification.\n-Documentation of the chemical surveillance.\n-Presentation of fluid system.\n-Supervision of the nuclear waste handling.\n\nGeneral and technical background expected:\n-Chemical technician degree.\n-5 years' experience om radiological chemistry of a running nuclear power plant with pressurized water reactor.\n-Experience in laboratory work in a running nuclear power plant.\n-Knowledge of all chemical laboratory methods needed in a nuclear power plant.\n-Basic knowledge of EPR technology.\n-Knowledge in pressurized water reactor technology and chemistry.\n-Fluent English. Ability with French, German or Finnish would be a plus;\n\nSkills required:\n-MS Office programs.\n-Knowledge of all chemical and radiological laws, guidelines (Finnish national and European).\n\nWork in controlled zone:\n-Work in radiological controlled zone is mandatory.\n-Radiological category A working capability.\n\nPosition is filled as soon as suitable candidate is found. To apply please send application and CV with salary request to info@n-pro.fi . For more information please go to www.n-pro.fi",
