				"kuvausteksti" : "Nipromec Oy Ltd is a global consulting and engineering company operating in energy-, industry- and offshore fields. \n\nWe are looking for a NSSS & BNI Test Analysis Engineer for our client working on the Olkiluoto 3 project. Work starts as soon as possible, estimated duration is until 15.09.2018.\n\nWithin OL3 project, inside Commissioning Department and under Technical Commissioning manager responsibility, the main duties of the Test Analysis Engineer are:\n\n-Support Commissioning Documentation validation through RFA (Ready For Application) process for NSSS and BNI.\n-Test Reports analysis for NSSS and BNI.\n-Assist Technical event analysis.\n-Provide support to the NSSS and BNI commissioning branches for the analysis of new design and field changes.\n-leading the follow-up of the commissioning deviations recorder during the commissioning activities in support of the NSSS and BNI commissioning branches.\n\nHe/she will support if needed the SCI52 NI/SCI53 team for the issuance of the test reports of the SCI52NI and SCI53NI upon request of the technical commissioning branch manager.\n\nSkills required:\n-Graduated from Mechanical, Process or general engineering school.\n-At least 1 or 2 years' experience in nuclear power plant or working period within nuclear project. Oil & Gas experience can also be considered.\n-PWR technology and EPR technology knowledge would be a plus. \n-System design experience would be a plus.\n-MS Office knowledge.\n-Document writing capacity.\n-Versatile, adaptable, rigorous, good interpersonal skills, client and result oriented, attention to detail.\n-Fluent in English. Ability with German and/or French and/or Finnish is beneficial.\n\nBasic work organization is a 5 (five) days per week. Possible adaptation according to project activity (weekend work, shift work, on duty work).\n\nPosition is filled as soon as suitable candidate is found. To apply please send application and CV with salary request to info@n-pro.fi . For more information please go to www.nipromec.com",
