				"kuvausteksti" : "Winter season as a guide in Northern Lapland! A whole different working experience far away in North! \r\nWe are looking for energetic and cheerful guides with lots of positive attitude to work in the area of Inari-Saariselkä, Lapland during the next winter season. \r\nIf you want to experience something unique and mystical, Lapland is the right place for you. Lapland is exceptional: geographically, spiritually and any other way you can imagine. The heart of mystical nature can always be found in Lapland. Even though the world would be changing, the Aurora Borealis, stars in the sky, midnight sun and the polar night remain the same. Witnessing the magical Northern Lights dancing up above is once-in-a-lifetime experience for many. Why wouldn't you be a part of creating magical experiences in Lapland? For more reasons to work in Lapland you can read at http://rekrytointi.inarisaariselka.fi/. \r\n\r\nAs the winter is the peak season, working days can be very busy. Applicants should possess the ability to work quickly and cope with pressure. The candidate must be ready to share his/her keen interest in magical Lapland through invigorating stories and engaging activities. The guide must have a charismatic personality and excellent communication skills. \r\n\r\n\r\nDesired qualifications, skills and experience: \r\n-Strong customer service skills and background \r\n-Fluent in written and spoken English. Other languages are considered an advantage. \r\n-Team working skills and resistance to pressure \r\n-Previous experience of seasonal work \r\n-Proactive attitude and motivation \r\n-Flexibility regarding the working hours \r\n-Ability to work independently \r\n-Driving license (B) \r\n-Experience and ability to be in nature \r\n\r\nOther: \r\n-Experience of working as a tour guide or safari guide \r\n-Skills to deal with the group of customers \r\n-Level 2 First Aid Course (or preparedness/willingness to submit the course) \r\n-Hygiene passport \r\n-Knowledge of the area \r\n\r\n\r\nWe offer a great seasonal position in a truly international hospitality business in Lapland. You will work in the middle of the most unique nature in Lapland wilderness where you are surrounded by the beauty of Finnish forests. Together with other employees you have an exceptional chance to create the magic of Lapland. Accommodation will be provided. \r\n\r\nEmployment will mainly commence in November and lasts until the end of March 2018. We also offer longer and shorter working periods. Depending on the location of the resort the season might last e.g. from August to May. We can discuss about different opportunities better and find a suitable position for you! Working hours may be either part-time or full-time. \r\n\r\n\r\nMore information\r\n\r\nIf you got interested send us your application through our system with attached CV and the contact details of your reference by 24.11.2017. We only consider applications submitted via Opteam system. Apply soon because we will fill the position right after finding the suitable candidates. Apply via this link: https://careers.fi/opteam/add_application.cgi?job_id=1408&language=uk \r\n\r\nFor more information please contact: \r\nOpteam Lapland Office; lappi@opteam.fi, +35810 8500 554 (no text messages) \r\nJyry Lehtoniemi, Recruitment consultant, jyry.lehtoniemi@opteam.fi, +35850 413 1220. Mika Rauhala, Sales Manager, mika.rauhala@opteam.fi, tel.+358400355159, \r\nBefore calling, please take in consideration Finnish time zone (UTC/GMT +2). Please leave your call request via text message. All applications will be treated confidentially. \r\n\r\nPLEASE NOTE THAT WE CANNOT TAKE ANY APPLICATIONS BY EMAIL! \r\n\r\n\"Working with Opteam \r\nThe world of work is changing rapidly and no longer meaning the same for everyone. Some people are seeking a steady career progression, permanent employment and solid professional skills in the field of their choice. Others want to slog away to fund that next surfing holiday or find work that accommodates the demands of family or studies. It takes all sorts. The most important thing is to achieve a balance between life and work. \r\nOpteam offers a range of work options. Temporary work is convenient when opting for harmonising work with the demands of a personal life, or to gain experience and skills working in various companies. We also serve our clients by directly recruiting skilled staff for permanent and temporary positions. With us you can boost your skills through a wide range of training courses.\"",
