				"kuvausteksti" : "Early Morning Delivery In Vihti and Nurmijärvi\n\nWhat is EarlyBird? \n\nEarlyBird is a happy group of Independent Distributors.  EarlyBird is Sanoma's own delivery service where anyone can take part in a carrier and do it on their own terms. Our goal is to expand by 2020 as one of the largest distribution agents in Uusimaa.\n\nThere are about 50 freelancers or entrepreneur who's working in the EarlyBird delivery service. We take care of the early morning delivery of newspapers and magazines.  Our main product is Helsingin Sanomat 7 days / week, but we also deliver Aamuposti, Länsi-Uusimaa, Etelä-Suomen Sanomat, Kauppalehti and HBL newspapers and weekly magazines e.g. Me Naiset, Rakennuslehti and ET-Magazine.\n\nWe are seeking for Vihti and Nurmijärvi Area\nEARLYBIRD CARRIER\n\nThe newspapers and any other products to be delivered will be delivered to pick-up boxes at 00-01 am for the carriers to pick up. The duty of a carrier is to deliver newspapers to subscribers by 6:30 am on weekdays, 7:00 am on Saturdays and 7:30 am on Sundays in the selected delivery district. \n\nIt has been estimated that the completion of one delivery task (district) takes around 1.5 hours. The estimated time may be longer for the most demanding districts. Carrier can do as much work as he wants: one to four routes each night and the area coordinator will assist our carriers in all situations.\n\nIf you are:\nOver 18 years old, used to work at night and value independent work, this may be your opportunity!  The delivery is done with your own car and you also need a smartphone for electric delivery book. You can schedule your working days eg. Weekdays or weekends or if you prefer, also 7 days a week is possible.  \nRead more about delivery work at www.earlybird.fi/basic-info and leave your application electronically. \n\nIf you are interested, fill the application https://www.earlybird.fi/application/",
