				"kuvausteksti" : "Type: Fulltime or part-time, permanent\nRecommended background: Flexible\nWorking hours: Negotiable\nRequested starting date: As soon as possible, negotiable\nLocation: Korkeavuorenkatu 35, Helsinki\nApplication DL: ASAP, 19.11.2017\n\nAre you a passionate learner of modern JavaScript front-end frameworks? You don't shy away from touching the back-end either? Lääketietokeskus is now looking for a Junior Software Developer to join their team!\n\nLääketietokeskus provides drug information, training and business intelligence services for healthcare and pharmaceutical industry. Company is known of Pharmaca Fennica® drug data database that includes also pharmacogenomic decision support for the benefit of healthcare professionals and patients. We are responsible for managing the Nordic Vnr-service and provide ePrescription pharmaceutical database for the Social Insurance Institution (Kela).\n\nOne of our latest services, Pharmaca Fennica mobile application has topped medical category at both app stores with more than 30,000 downloads. Our Lääkeinfo.fi website is one of the most popular medicine information websites for patients in Finland with almost 9 million page views per year.\n\nLääketietokeskus is now looking for a Junior Software Developer to join their team! As a Junior Software Developer at Lääketietokeskus you will work with the development of web applications and pharmaceutical databases. You will build digital drug information services targeted at the pharmaceutical industry, healthcare professionals and patients. You will particularly be involved in the development of information solutions and interfaces. \n\nAs an ideal candidate, you have knowledge of web development through your studies and/or work experience. Even though you'll mostly be working with front-end, we hope that you don't shy away from touching the back-end either. To succeed in this role, you are able to solve problems, passionate about learning new things and have an open-minded attitude. \n\nAt Lääketietokeskus you will be joining a team of four software developers. You also collaborate with Lääketietokeskus' software development partners. \n\nWe look for:\n\nExperience with modern JavaScript front-end frameworks and front-end development\nKnowledge of object-oriented languages (e.g. Java, Csharp, )\nKnowledge of relational databases\nProactive attitude and motivation to learn\nRelevant educational background (e.g. computer science)\nFluency in English or Finnish\n\nLääketietokeskus offers: \n\nA relaxed and flexible working environment where employee well-being is key\nA flat organization culture, where you are given responsibility yet the freedom to carry out your tasks the way you think is best\nAn opportunity to grow as a developer in a supportive environment and a thorough induction to the role\nGreat employee benefits (sports, public transport and lunch coupons etc.) \nA modern office in the center of Helsinki\n\nSounds good? Please send your CV and application letter in PDF form to: https://apply.atalent.fi/laaketietokeskus-junior-software-developer-11-2017 no later than 19.11. 2017. If you have a GitHub profile or equivalent, please also link that to your application! We go through applications already during the application period, so we encourage you to act fast!\n\nYou can familiarize with Lääketietokeskus at https://www.laaketietokeskus.fi/en. For further questions and more information about the position, you can contact Topi Hanhela (040 518 0792) on Thu 9 Nov at 10-11 o'clock or Wed 15 Nov at 14-15 o'clock. For enquiries about the recruitment process please approach aTalent's Recruitment Manager Emma Toivola (+358 50 304 5809, emma.toivola(at)atalent.fi).",
