				"kuvausteksti" : "Adecco Group is the world's leading provider of workforce solutions. Adecco Finland Oy has been in operation since 1997. Our company is authorized by the Private Employment Agencies' Association of Finland. Hundreds of professionals in various fields are employed through us each day in jobs ranging in duration from a few days to several years. We also recruit professionals for our client companies.\n\nWe're currently looking for Spare Part Team Support for our international client in the OL3 Site in Eurajoki. The job starts as soon as the suitable candidate is found and last approximately 2 months, possibly longer depending on our client's need.\n\nExpected background & Skills:\n\nUnderstanding of technical documentation\nGeneral understanding of mechanical, electrical and instrumentation technology\nIT-Skills: MS Office\nLanguage skills: Fluent in English\n\nResponsibilities:\n\nAssess maintenance and commissioning data to initiate spare parts and consumable orders in due time\nReview and search for items in warehouse inventories\nSearch for technical/quality documentation in databases/folders\nFollow-up of the purchase requests and purchase orders\nProvide the documentation of the spare parts for maintenance reports and other work orders\n\nWe are offering you a possibility to take an insight on a major industrial project in Finland. You'll be part of an active and professional team and you'll be able to gain experience in a multi-cultural environment.\n\nPlease apply for the Spare Part Team Support position by registering at www.adecco.fi. Attach your English CV to the application. For more information please contact HR Consultant Eerika Jantunen +35846 875 0111.",
