				"kuvausteksti" : "Experis is the global leader in professional resourcing and project based workforce solutions. We attract, assess and place specialist professional talent, connecting the passion of individuals with the ambition of business. We specialize in providing professional opportunities across IT and Engineering, Finance and Accounting, Sales, Marketing, Communications and HR. We deliver high-demand talent for mission-critical positions to clients in over 50 countries. Experis is part of ManpowerGroup, the world leader in innovative workforce solutions. \n\n\nWe are looking for a R&D Project Planner to an international ICT company for a fixed term agreement starting ASAP and ending 30.6.2018 with a possible extension. The selected person shall work as an Experis consultant at our clients premises.\n\nIn this role you need to organize, plan, monitor, report and prioritize of R&D activities and prototyping product manufacturing in highly technical R&D environment'.\n\nYour days will be filled with:\n\n-        Maintain and plan schedules \n\n-        Keep project resources on track\n\n-        Provide regular project updates\n\n-        Maintain contact with project staff\n\n-        Support and drive prioritization between different projects and staff - ensure clarity for the team\n\n-        Generally, makes sure all activities are done on time with minimum amount of time wasted of technical staff\n\nExperience:\n\n-        Any previous work on or with an advanced manufacturing hardware preferred\n\n-        Proven track record of coordinating and planning projects and execution (Mandatory) on highly complex R&D environment\n\n-        Experience from material stock management and logistics are preferred\n\n-        Bachelor's degree or higher education ( Optics / Manufacturing studies preferred )\n\n-        Fluent English language skills (mandatory) Finnish preferred\n\nAs a person you are:\n\n-        Self-motivated with the ability to take personal ownership of issues\n\n-        Demonstrated capability to rationalize and prioritize different work tasks at R&D environment\n\n-        Capability to influence different kind of persons while creating energy\n\nContinuous improvement thinking\n\nInterested? Please apply ASAP by registering your CV or send your CV directly to tessi.reispakka@fi.experis.com\n\nFor more information please contact Consultant Tessi Reispakka, 040 183 7863",
