				"kuvausteksti" : "Nipromec Oy Ltd is a global consulting and engineering company operating in energy-, industry- and offshore fields. \n\nWe are looking for a Chemical Engineer at OIO for our client working on the Olkiluoto 3 project. Work starts as soon as possible, estimated duration is until 31.12.2018.\n\nMain tasks:\n-Chemical surveillance of the nuclear and conventional circuits of the nuclear power plant.\n-Following the chemistry handbook.\n-Guarantee the chemical parameters in the technical specification.\n-Documentation of the chemical surveillance.\n-Optimization of the resin use.\n-Optimization of the lithium use.\n-Preservation of fluid systems.\n-Planning and supervision of the nuclear water handling.\n-Leading and training of the chemical and laboratory teams.\n\nWork in controlled zone:\n-Work in radiological controlled zone is mandatory.\n-Radiological category A working capability.\n\nTechnical and special Requirements:\n-Chemical Engineer degree.\n-5 years' experience in radiological chemistry of a running nuclear power plant with pressurized water reactor.\n-Experience in laboratory work in a running nuclear power plant.\n-Knowledge of all chemical laboratory methods needed in a nuclear power plant.\n-Leadership skills and experience.\n-Basic knowledge of EPR technology.\n-Deep knowledge in pressurized water reactor technology and chemistry.\n-Fluent English required. French, German and/or Finnish appreciated.\n\nSkills required:\n-MS Office programs.\n-Knowledge of all chemical and radiological laws, guidelines (Finnish national and European).\n\nPosition is filled as soon as suitable candidate is found. To apply please send application and CV with salary request to info@n-pro.fi . For more information please go to www.nipromec.com.",
