				"kuvausteksti" : "CUSTOMER FOCUSED & PROACTIVE?\nWE WANT TO HEAR MORE ABOUT YOU\n\nManager, Product Safety and Liability Prevention\n\nSandvik Mining and Rock Technology (SMRT) is a business area of the Sandvik Group and a leading supplier of equipment and tools, services, support and technical solutions for the mining industry and specialist sectors such as quarrying, tunneling, demolition, dimensional stone, recycling and the civil engineering industry. SMRT's offering covers drilling and mechanical cutting, loading and hauling, crushing and screening, demolition and recycling, and various solutions to increase automation. In 2016 the annual sales amounted to about SEK 31 093 M, with around 14 000 employees.\n \nProduct Area Rock Drills and Technologies is responsible for the development of new technologies and high technology products for all Product Areas (PA), including rock drills and automation, as well as common research and engineering services. We are now looking for a motivated and committed Manager, Product Safety and Liability Prevention. In this role, you report to the Director of Engineering Services in Product Area Rock Drills and Technologies. This is a permanent position and based in Tampere, Finland.\n\nJob Profile\nSafety is one of Sandvik's core values and driver of our corporate culture \"safety first\". As responsible for Product Safety, you have a strategic role and your main responsibilities include:\n Leading the product safety strategy development and execution in alignment with all PAs within SMRT, ensuring Sandvik's products meet the highest levels of safety and compliance with safety regulations in all market areas with clear focus on liability prevention \n Driving and further developing the Product Safety Network. \n Managing a team of product safety experts providing services to the Automation and Rock Drills business units, as well as supporting safety engineering across PAs.\n Managing the further development of product safety knowledge area, sharing best practices.\n Monitoring market, regulations and competitors' development.\n Driving the internal communication and keeping the spot light on product safety.\n Leading global safety standardization projects and regulations development. \n Driving SMRT interests in external safety regulations development organizations.\n Own the product safety incident database and process, safety engineering project model, environmental engineering project model, and safety regulations development roadmap. \n\nYour Profile\nThe ideal candidate holds a MSc. degree in Engineering and has eight or more years' experience in driving safety or compliance related areas in international environment. Experience in the heavy machinery industry is preferred, as well as solid knowledge and experience of risk assessment methods, mobile machinery and a good understanding of the relevant safety standards and technology. \n\nThe role requires strong verbal and written communication skills in English and extensive international travelling.  To succeed in this role, the candidate must be self-motivated and a good team player who can bring product safety to the spotlight and have very strong interpersonal skills to establish effective and constructive collaboration. \n\nWe offer you an interesting role in an international business environment as well as opportunities for your professional development.\n\nSandvik is a high-tech and global engineering group offering advanced products and services that enhance customer productivity, profitability and safety. We hold world-leading positions in selected areas - tools for metal cutting, equipment and tools for the mining and construction industries, stainless materials, special alloys, metallic and ceramic resistance materials as well as process systems. In 2016, the Group had about 43,000 employees and sales of about 82 billion SEK in more than 150 countries.",
