				"kuvausteksti" : "Normet is known for its hands-on attitude, entrepreneurial spirit, agile decision making and results-driven business culture. While current position holder is moving to new challenges we are now looking for a new hard-working Operative Purchaser to buy parts, components and materials for Normet production.\n\nYou work in a 5 operative purchaser team in close cooperation internally with strategic purchasers, production, engineering, supply chain and quality functions. Externally the most important stakeholders are suppliers and outsourced service providers. Your tasks include preparation and sending out of purchase orders to suppliers and controlling of on time material supply from order placement to delivery until supplier invoice process is completed. In addition you monitor open purchase orders, price development, supplier quality issues and claim handling. \n\nThe candidates are expected to have knowledge and understanding about sourcing and purchase processes, how to interact with suppliers and in general how supply chain is working. Negotiation and communication skills also in English and sufficient IT skills (especially ERP and PDM) are good competences. Ability to stand hectic job environment and work conscientiously, precisely and independently are valuable strengths to the position. Most importantly positive mindset and pro-active way of working are valued and appreciated. The job location is in Iisalmi and you report in this role to Team Leader, Material Planning and Operative Purchasing. \n\nWe offer you a dynamic and positive working environment with devoted professionals and excellent possibilities for professional growth in our global organization.\n\nPlease send your resume and application letter in English with salary request no later than 24th November 2017 at  www.mercuriurval.fi, ref. FI-11720. For further information, please contact Mercuri Urval's consultant Sanna Aikio +358 40 7179796.\n\nNormet is a global, fast growing and innovative technology company with a passion to offer continuous improvement to underground construction and mining processes for increased safety, productivity and profitability. Normet services its clients by providing complete technical solutions that create value through saving costs and shortening process cycle times. From conception to production to application, their solutions are developed based on the welfare of people and on the care of the environment. Normet has become one of the market leaders in its product segments globally. Normet's headquarters are located in Iisalmi, Finland and it operates globally with over 1000 business professionals in 42 locations in 28 countries. Normet Group's turnover in 2016 totalled over EUR 200 million. Please, see www.normet.com.",
