				"kuvausteksti" : "?Strip away modern technology and what you?ll find is our one true asset - a diverse multicultural group of talented and motivated people.?\nLuxus Worldwide is a global marketing technology and digital design agency. We create value-adding digital marketing solutions at the intersection of business insight, design and technology. Our clients appreciate that we don?t just plan and build the solutions - we stay in to operate, optimize and further develop them. \nWith people in Helsinki, Helsingborg, London, Singapore, Sydney and Dallas we can truly call ourselves a multicultural company which we believe gives a unique perspective both to our clients and Luxus as a company. \nOur people are characterized as strategic thinkers, business minded problem solvers and fun-loving team players. If this resonates with you and you wish to join our growing team in Helsinki, we are now looking for a:\nSenior Full-stack Web Developer\nYour work is to be a part of Luxus Site Development team, together with other back-end and front-end developers and coders. Being experienced, a proactive team player, as well as good at working independently, you play a crucial part in our web and software development projects.  \nYour ability to carry out creative software development with an experimental mind-set together with wanting to make things happen is the key to success in this position. Problem solving skills with a solid track record of success in similar positions are needed.  \nYou have a proof of previous successful projects as well as the capabilities of the following: \n? Strong knowledge and experience in HTML, CSS, JavaScript \n? Familiarity with React, Angular (both versions), Scss, Bootstrap 4, Node.js, Express,   Grunt, Gulp, Bower, Pug (Jade), InVision, Contentful, in addition to an up to date knowledge of new development tools as they become available. \n? Linux / Unix, and managing basic web components (Apache, Nginx, Mongo, etc).\n? Security and optimization - Information architecture \n? Application development frameworks \n? A deep understanding of web and mobile technologies \n? Familiarity with the principles of Agile software development \n? Ability to cope with tight deadlines \n? Customer oriented attitude and sociable nature \n? Full working proficiency in English (Finnish is a plus)\nYou are responsible for\n? Server-side programming (Node.js, React/redux server side rendering) \n? Software architecture \n? JavaScript programming \n? Shell Scripting / Linux server management \n? Software development planning\n? CDN management \nWe value that you know the ins and outs of web technologies (HTML, CSS, JS, REST, JSON) and have worked with different kinds of libraries and platforms for creating amazing web projects. You can specify, design and implement a web based application from end to end. \nYou also possess a clean programming style, document your work and are capable to abstract your ideas to create well organized code. \nYou have work experience of minimum 3-5 years in a senior developer or architect role. Experience in a leadership role and multi-vendor projects is a bonus.\nAs a person you are self-driven but also a team player. You know how to think from the client?s perspective and you?re not afraid of asking for help. Great communication skills are essential to be able to manage stakeholders.\nWe offer a truly multicultural working environment with 11 nationalities working in Helsinki alone. Our clients provide extremely interesting projects that keep the learning curve healthy along the way. We are eager to help our colleagues and we communicate daily through Slack. Our team is relaxed but professional? and we also know how to have fun!\n\nOperaria Oy assists us in the application process. Save your application and CV with your salary request by 12.11.2017 via the link below. For inquiries, please contact Mikael Rinne, Operaria Oy tel. +358 40 7554847",
