				"kuvausteksti" : "We are looking for a R&D Project Planner to work for our client, an international software company in Espoo. As a R&D Project Planner you will need to organize, plan, monitor, report and prioritize R&D activities and prototyping product manufacturing in highly technical R&D enviroment. Your tasks will be to maintain and plan schedules, keep project resources on track, provide regular project updates, support and drive prioritization between different projects and staff and generally make sure all activities are done on time.\n\nRequirements in this position is previous work on or with advanced manufacturing hardware. Proven track record of coordinating and planning projects and execution in highly complex R&D enviroment. Also experience from material stock management and logistics are preffered. You need good communication and teamwork skills in English. We are looking for a very self-motivated person with the ability to take personal ownership of issues. To succeed in this position you must have the capability to rationalize and prioritize different work tasks at R&D environment.\n\nThe job requires a Bachelor's degree or higher education, preffered in optics or manufacturing. Fluent English skills, Finnish is a plus.\n\nYou will be working in an international company with diverse tasks. We offer you a fixed-term employment until the end of June 2018 with a possible extension. Besides your local team you get access to a vast international network that offers you support and opportunities to learn and develop yourself. Apply for this position as soon as possible by filling out an application form and attach your CV with a salary request at www.vmp.fi\n\nVMP Varamiespalvelu is a Finnish personnel service company that has almost 30 years of experience in developing the sector, and specialises in staffing services and recruitment in all sectors. We provide employment for 14,000 people in over 3,000 client companies annually. VMP has been granted the Private Employment Agencies Association's certification. www.vmp.fi",
