				"kuvausteksti" : "We are hiring! \n\nWebhelp Nordic is looking for new talent to join our Technical Support Tier 1 Team. Supporting an exciting global consumer technology brand, you will be a member of the Technical customer support team with plenty of potential to kick off your career. Our goal is to have fun while delivering amazing support for our customers. Why not come join us!\n\nAs a Technical Support Advisor - you are a motivated and enthusiastic individual with great passion for technology. As a problem solver, you are looking for a challenge in inventive work environment. Prior experience in technical or phone support is not required but looked as an advantage. What means the most to us is that you are eager to learn new, able to truly listen our customers and oriented to make their day by providing the highest level of customer care. We support you by providing world class training for your new role at the very beginning of your employment but also throughout your career with us!\n\nAs part of your role, you will answer inbound calls from customers in an efficient and timely manner. You will troubleshoot quickly and efficiently, providing information and solutions to customers and do so with the highest standards of professional customer service. You will be supporting customers from Finland and internationally, both in Finnish and English languages. \n\nResponsibilities\nProvide first line support to customer enquiries \nInvestigate, resolve or escalate issues to Tier 2, senior support\nWorking with internal systems you will document each call via a client ticket system\nMaintain and support quality and statistical standards, KPIs\nWorking as part of a team, you will work to both individual and group targets\n\nRequirements\nFluent in English and Finnish, both written and spoken.\nPrior customer service experience. History working in call centers/phone support is looked as an advantage\nBasic understanding and interest in consumer based electronics\nExcellent verbal and written communications skills\nStrong problem solving and resolution skills\nExcellent listening, probing and de-escalation skills\nBe passionate about learning new concepts, technology and processes\n\nTo be our Super Hero:\nYou are passionate about delivering exceptional customer service\nYou thrive to build strong relationships with customers \nYou work well within a team and can motivate other team members\nYou are self-motivated with a great level of initiative\nYou are committed to continuous development\nThrive to take pride in your work \n\nDoes this sound like you? Go ahead and submit your application today! http://www.webhelp.com/en-gb/careers/\n\nOrientation day will be held on 5th/January/2018. Position to be filled is with full time contract. Recruitment process includes capability tests which first will be sent to you within 24h from submitted application. Team Manager Annamari Kolehmainen (Annamari.kolehmainen@nordic.webhelp.com) will be happy to answer any questions you might have!\n\nWebhelp is a leading Contact Center provider internationally with about 35.000 employees. Webhelp Nordic currently operates within the Nordic countries and Latvia with 1800 employees. We are committed to our people and thrive diversity and individual growth in everyday bases. Any level of discrimination is not welcome within our organization- rather we celebrate our differences. We believe in feedback and open communication to share knowledge and support business development. We guarantee high quality coaching and training and encourage and support our employees to find the best individual career development path with us.",
