				"kuvausteksti" : "We not only have ambitious goals but also a clear agreement on how to achieve them: For us, the means are as important as the ends. Whatever your role at ABB, you can be sure you are helping to create a better world. From building sustainable power plants in remote corners of the world, or improving safety for workers in automotive factories, to developing new technologies to combat pollution, the work we do touches the lives of millions.\n\nWe are looking for a Project Manager at ABB Oy, Motors and Generators unit in Helsinki. In this position, you will lead synchronous machines factory deliveries, including operations such as engineering, purchasing, and manufacturing. As a Project Manager, you will monitor KPIs such as on-time delivery at project milestones, quality, and cost. You will be responsible for customer communication and negotiations, and develop customer relationships with key customers. We offer you a broad view of the engineered-to-order delivery process for international businesses, and further career opportunities in, for example, sales management.\n\nWe require a B.Sc. or M.Sc. in mechanical or electrical engineering. A few years' experience in electrical machines is appreciated, as well as experience in developing co-operation with customers. The job requires knowledge of engineering tasks and quality systems such as ISO 9001, and skill in interpreting technical drawings and specifications. Because the Project Manager is responsible for the schedule, a good sense of time and problem-solving skills are needed. You are customer-oriented, and a motivating team player with good negotiation skills. A good command of Finnish and English is required; other language skills are an advantage. You are familiar with common office tools. Knowledge of SAP is beneficial. The position requires 10-20 travelling days per year.",
