				"kuvausteksti" : "Unicef is looking for face-to-face fundraisers for our morning and evening teams in Helsinki!\n\nI have one question for you!\n \nSurely you're interested in a job where you can develop yourself, save children's lives and work with the best people you can imagine? Wonderful! Here at Unicef that's exactly what you'll do, because right now we are looking for new face-to-face fundraisers to work with us. As a face-to-face fundraiser you are an integral part of the organization's backbone: you recruite monthly donors and by doing that you ensure that children everywhere get the vital help they need. Unicef always makes sure that the support from monthly donors reaches the children who need it the most. Right now those children are, for example, the ones living in war-ravaged Syria.\n \nWhat are we offering you, then?\n \nWell, our face-to-face fundraisers have:\n\n- A competitive wage: 12-13€/hour (+ 9% vacation compensation)\n- Opportunities to advance in their carees and develop their skills: our F2F Manager, our F2F-coordinators, our F2F-promoters and our team leaders have all started out as face-to-face fundraisers. When you work for us, you will be able to advance along with your skills.\n- Flexible working hours: you can book your own shifts (3-6 shifts of 4-6 hours per week). \n\nOur day team in works from 10-18 in 4-6hour shifts. Our evening team in Helsinki works from 16-20.\n\nAs a face-to-face fundraiser you'll develop amazing communication skills: you can convince anybody and you won't be left speechless in any situation. We have a motivating fundraising goal, and thanks to that goal, you'll always know how many children got to school with the donations you attained. You also get to challenge yourself: our best fundraisers get to participate on our caravan trips and on our trade fair events and show what they are made of. To prepare you for the job we, of course, provide you with a three-day training that is paid for. The icing on the cake is that as you develop, you can advance in your career. With us at Unicef you are a part of an inspiring group with a common goal: to save the lives of as many children as possible.\n \nAnd what do we wish from you?\n \nAs a Unicef face-to-face fundraiser you get to be yourself at work and convince people by using your persona.\n\nIn addition to that we ask for:\n\n- Plenty of ambition to develop and advance\n- Ability to convince people\n- Target-oriented mindset\n\nCome and work with us! Apply at: https://www.unicef.fi/unicef/avoimet-tyopaikat/\n\nThis is how Azin, a team leader and a face-to-face fundraiser with us since 2009, describes her job:\n\n\"Unicef has given me the opportunity to go to school when I was little. Now I want to give back and help, I want to ensure that other children all over the world are given the opportunity to education as well. Unicef has a good work atmosphere: the work is so important, and very different every day, which means that you constantly learn new wonderful things. Unicef appreciates what I do, and makes sure that everybody feels good at work, which of course increases my motivation and inspires to do more!\"\n\nUNICEF works in 190 countries and territories to save children's lives. To defend their rights. To help them fulfill their potential. And we never give up. UNICEF, for every child.",
