				"kuvausteksti" : "Stora Enso is a leading provider of renewable solutions in packaging, biomaterials, wooden constructions and paper on global markets. Our aim is to replace fossil based materials by innovating and developing new products and services based on wood and other renewable materials. We employ some 25 000 employees in more than 35 countries, and our sales in 2016 were EUR 9.8 billion. Stora Enso shares are listed on the Helsinki and Stockholm stock exchanges. storaenso.com\n\nPackaging Solutions division develops fibre-based packaging, and operates at every stage of the value chain from pulp production, material and packaging production to recycling. Our solutions serve leading converters, brand owners and retailer customers helping to optimise performance, reduce total costs and enhance sales.\n\nStora Enso Division Packaging Solutions is now looking for a\n\nMaster Planner\n\nfor Containerboard supply from Heinola mill\n\nAre you looking for an exciting opportunity to challenge yourself?\n\n\nAs Master Planner for our virgin-fiber Containerboard mill you will have the ownership and responsibility for demand and supply balance of the mill - in practical terms that means that you are in charge of us keeping our promises to customers. Sounds like a tough challenge? Well it is! You will work with defined processes to keep the order confirmation process alive and work towards avoiding overbooking situation. In case of overbooking, you will make priorities based on customer classification and in tight cooperation with sales. \n\nYou will balance the demand, supply and inventory with the agreed targets to ensure efficient stock rotation, while keeping the service to customers at a reliable level. Any hick-ups need to be voiced in the organization and mitigating actions initiated without hesitation, to ensure that we keep our promises.\n\nIn this role you will lead mill Supply Chain team consisting of professionals of production planning, logistics, dispatching and internal material flow. You will report to Manager, Sales & Operations Planning and Production Planning and work in close contact with production, sales, customer service and Stora Enso Logistics. Location of the position can be any Stora Enso mill site or office.\n\nWe are looking for these qualifications when selecting for this role:\n\n- Master's degree Supply Chain Management or equivalent\n- Deep knowledge of Sales & Operations Planning process\n- Knowledge of Fenix (order handling system) will be an advantage\n- Customer focused attitude\n- Ability to make quick and clear decisions even with incomplete information, which may includ tough choices or considerable risks\n- Ability to work productively, despite high pressure \n- Structured and systematic approach \n- Excellent, proven leadership skills; ability to inspire, motivate and empower\n- Skills to network, communicate and gain commitment from various stakeholders\n- Highly self motivated and independent working style, ability to take initiative and work under own direction\n- Fluency in both written and spoken English. Finnish language will be considered an advantage\n- Ability to travel\n\nWould you see yourself in this key position in the Containerboard supply chain team? Yes? Click on \"Apply\" and submit your application!\n\nThe application period ends 24 November 2017.",
