				"kuvausteksti" : "Senior Lecturer, Electrical and Automation Engineering\n(The application period has been extended to November 15th 2017, previous applications will be taken into account in the selection.)\n\nThe duties involve teaching and developing courses in the field of automation technology in collaboration with other staff members. Competence in electrical power engineering is seen as an asset. Typical course application areas include automation fundamentals, process and manufacturing automation, production simulation, electrical power applications and automation of consumer products. Research and development projects with our partners in the industry play an essential role in this position.\n\nWe expect you to have an appropriate university degree and a strong industrial background including practical experience, teamwork skills, and extensive business contacts. Development our industrial contacts and internal processes is a natural part of the duties. We appreciate an energetic and self-driven attitude to develop our pedagogical issues both in teaching and as to the electrical and automation laboratory environments here. We expect you to be able to conduct lectures both in English and in Finnish. A Master of Science in Engineering is the minimum requirement degree.\n\nThe working location is mainly Valkeakoski.\n\nThe qualification requirements for senior lecturer for University of Applied Sciences level in Finland are in accordance with decree 1129/2014 § 17. A senior lecturer is also required to have pedagogical studies (60 credits or 35 cource credits). Qualification requirements in Finnish: Sen lisäksi, mitä asetuksessa ammattikorkeakouluista (1129 / 2014) 17 §:ssä on säädetty ammattikorkeakoulun opettajien kelpoisuusvaatimuksista, vaaditaan opettajalta, että hänellä on suoritettuna vähintään 60 opintopisteen tai vähintään 35 opintoviikon laajuiset opettajan pedagogiset opinnot.",
