				"kuvausteksti" : "N-PRO Resources Oy Ltd is a staffing and recruiting company belonging to Nipromec Group focusing mainly on needs of our customers in the fields of energy, industry and offshore.\n\nWe are looking for a Fire Safety Officer for our client working on the Olkiluoto 3 project. Work starts as soon as possible, estimated duration is 8 months.\n\nThe Fire Safety Officer's tasks included, but are not limited to:\n-Strict follow up of application and compliance within site rules, national standards and legislation.\n-Reporting and recording of actions and deviations.\n-Active communication with contractor's personnel, their guidance and instructing.\n-Rescue trainings and tests with site personnel.\n-Follow up and updating daily fire protection tasks (exit ways, signalization).\n-Reporting daily to team leader.\n-Manage the fire safety inspection on site with the contractors. Follow up corrective actions defined during the inspection.\n-Closely work with supervisors and team (construction / commissioning to have the knowledge on the coming activities (anticipation) and involve them in the daily safety.\n-Animate the safety in the team (construction/commissioning) through visit on spot, training, lessons learned.\n\nGeneral and technical background expected:\n-Technical experience in fire protection and prevention on industrial environment or on construction site (hot works, welding, lifting, etc.).\n\nSkills required:\n-Good knowledge of Finnish Rescue and Chemical and Occupational Health and Safety Regulation, applicable standards.\n-Good knowledge of Finnish Rescue service and related operations (HÄKE) structure.\n-Holder of Hot Work license.\n-Experienced on industrial, ship yard, construction site - fire protection.\n-Skilled to write reports, records and instruction, procedure.\n-Comfortable in speaking in public (especially when giving training and eventually leading meetings).\n-Knowledge of Microsoft Office.\n-Knowledge of automatic systems (extinguishing, alarm) or experience in electrical, mechanical risks linked to industrial activities or commissioning activities will be the best.\n-Fluent English and Finnish required.\n\nPosition is filled as soon as suitable candidate is found. To apply please send application and CV with salary request to info@n-pro.fi or fill in an application at www.n-pro.fi.",
