				"kuvausteksti" : "Nipromec Oy Ltd is a global consulting and engineering company operating in energy-, industry- and offshore fields. \n\nWe are looking for Radiation Protection Engineer for our client working on the Olkiluoto 3 project. Work starts as soon as possible, estimated duration is 12 months.\n\nAssessment of the N-16 source team from the measured gamma dose rates\nPrepare methodology, perform calculations for the installation of the detectors, procure the detectors, participate to installation of the detectors, monitor the results (extrapolation) and perform the reporting to the project and customer.\nEvaluate potential of changes in zoning and predicted service lifetimes to be implemented only after commissioning feedback becomes available.\nConfirmation of radiation zoning, including assessment of potential hot spots close to buildings openings (SCP RAD).\nSupport the overall project in demonstrating that contractual requirements are met.\nInitiate corrective actions in case of deviations, the candidate will coordinate the handling of CR/DCR if any related to radiation shielding.\nParticipate in review and testing of equipment required during commissioning.\nSupport the commissioning for execution of the client's part of commissioning dose rate measurements.\nTroubleshoot and perform analysis activities during commissioning.\nOptional, review all test reports related to radiation protection.\n\nGeneral and technical background expected\n-Knowledge in radiation protection technology.\n-Experience in nuclear safety and/or system engineering.\n-EPR design basis knowledge.\n\nTechnical:\n-Adherence to access requirements in controlled area and sign posting.\n-use of radiation protection software.\n-Knowledge of radiation protection products such as Mirion products would be a plus.\n-Establishment and/or review of system test procedures.\n\nSkills required:\n-Engineering level degree in nuclear or radiological engineering.\n-Experience in nuclear power plant operations.\n-At least one significant experience in testing or commissioning activities related to radiation protection.\n-Knowledge or source term characteristics.\n-Knowledge of the applicable licensing requirements.\n-Capacity of organization and managing daily activities involving several disciplines.\n-Excellent relational and communication skills.\n-Rigorous especially for adherence to procedures in force on site including configuration management.\n-Aware of safety and security aspects.\n\n\nPosition is filled as soon as suitable candidate is found. To apply please send application and CV with salary request to info@n-pro.fi or fill in an application at www.nipromec.com",
