				"kuvausteksti" : "Nipromec Oy Ltd is a global consulting and engineering company operating in energy-, industry- and offshore fields. \n\nWe are now looking for Instrumentation Designer for I&C Field for a project in Olkiluoto. Work starts as soon as possible and estimated duration is 6 months.\n\nJob description:\n- Analyze of the correct functioning of the instrumentation, troubleshooting\n- Implementation of requests from installation and commissioning group from I&C systems engineering and its sub suppliers\n- Implementation of Field Change activities related to instrumentation\n\n- Handling of all activities related to I&C instrumentation design and modifications including cabling, sensing line piping, hook-ups etc.\n- Modification and adaptation of all I&C instrumentation related documents like Measuring racks drawings, sensor or transmitter drawings, wiring and termination drawings, I&C instrumentation detailed design\n- Adapting Construction plan documentation needed for equipment, valves and instrumentation\n- Adapting I&C documentation\n- Support for commissioning and calibration documentation\n\nThe instrumentation designer implements the design changes of reviews the correctness of documentation, databases and configuration management related to his scope. Two years of engineering experience at design, erection and/or commissioning of I&C or instrumentation systems, preferred in nuclear power plants, but also on conventional plants, oil rigs, chemical factories. OL3 experience would be advantage.\n\nTasks:\n- Modification implementation into I&C and equipment documentation, issue, follow up, approval and documentation\n- Design adaptations due to installation or commissioning hardware findings\n- clarification of technical issues with the other disciplines, if necessary\n- Reporting: provide input to the different weekly/monthly reports\n- Reporting to Instrumentation Task Leader\n\nGeneral and Technical background expected:\nGood knowledge of the conventional instrumentation and special cabling for a nuclear power plant inside and outside of the containment\n\nSkills required:\n- Good knowledge in I&C and instrumentation\n- Reliable\n- Organized\n- Experience in technical design activities\n- Good relationship\n- team work\n- tools (VPE, PDMS), basic knowledge\n- Office software, good knowledge\n- Working with databases, lists, Documentum\n- Engineering degree\n- good level of English, other languages beneficial\n\nPosition is filled as soon as suitable candidate is found. To apply please send application and CV with salary request to info@n-pro.fi . For any further information, you might require please go to www.nipromec.com",
