				"kuvausteksti" : "Nipromec Oy Ltd is a global consulting and engineering company operating in energy-, industry- and offshore fields. \n\nWe are now looking for Mechanical PTW Officers (2) for a project in Olkiluoto. Work starts as soon as possible and estimated duration until 31.12.2018.\n\nTasks:\n-Technical clarification of work orders / permits to test and creation and validation of block-ings / simulations.\n-Execution of blockings and simulations.\n-Oversee in-field operator teams for establishing safe work conditions (equipment's align-ment, depressurizing, de-energizing, locking and tagging).\n-Coordinate activities with operating, construction, installation and commissioning units.\n-Prepare permit to work documentation and ensure strict compliance.\n\nGeneral and technical background expected:\n-Mechanical engineering degree or experienced technician.\n-5 years' experience in nuclear power plants.\n-5 years' experience with mechanical work orders and blockings.\n-Detailed knowledge about the mechanical process documentation.\n-Ability to work on the different process diagram, isometrics, preparation of solution and sup-port for inventories in the field.\n-General understanding of mechanics, thermodynamics, fluid mechanics and measure-ment/instrumentation technology.\n-General understanding in electrical technology.\n-Computer literacy n MS Office. Ability to is the different project data bases, software etc.\n-Fluent English required. Ability with French, German or Finnish is a plus.\n\nSkills required:\n-Knowledge about EPR technology.\n-Work experience in permit to work offices.\n\nPosition is filled as soon as suitable candidate is found. To apply please send application and CV with salary request to info@n-pro.fi . For any further information, you might require please go to www.nipromec.com",
