				"kuvausteksti" : "Nipromec Oy Ltd is a global consulting and engineering company operating in energy-, industry- and offshore fields. \n\nWe are now looking for Field Instrumentation Commissioning Technician / Engineer for a project in Olkiluoto. Work starts as soon as possible and estimated duration is 9 months.\n\nThe summary of the field instrumentation commissioning technician/engineer tasks consists in:\n-Performing on-site baseline measurements on different kind of valves (valves with electrical or hydraulic actuator, solenoid valves, safety valves, chick valves) and vibration measurements on safety related and operational pumps.\n-Execution of field tests / loop checks on different type of sensors / measurement chains ac-cording to commissioning instructions of diagnostic systems.\n\nUnder the authority of the diagnostic systems commissioning section leas, the field instrumentation commissioning technician/engineer will be in charge of following tasks:\nPrepare the field task\nPerform the field task\nTest evaluation and result documentation\nFor valve baseline measurements\nFor test execution, according to commissioning instruction\nReporting\nGeneral and Technical background expected:\n\nSkills required:\n-Experience in preparation of measurement setups on valves, actuators and sensors.\n-Experience in loop checks and measurement chain calibration.\n-Experience in analysis of signals resulting from measurements on valves, actuators and vibration sensors.\n-Capacity of troubleshooting.\n-Good relational and communication skills.\n-Analysis and synthesis skills.\n-Ability to work in an international team.\n-Aware of HSE and IT security aspects.\n-Fluent English, other languages beneficial.\n\nTools:\n-Proficient with MS Excel reporting (pivot tables, statistics,).\n-Experience with OL3 engineering tools (COEDM 1.4, OPMS, AIMS, CMS,). is a plus.\n\nPosition is filled as soon as suitable candidate is found. To apply please send application and CV with salary request to info@n-pro.fi . For any further information, you might require please go to www.nipromec.com",
