				"kuvausteksti" : "We are looking to recruit a kennels manager to manage our kennels of approximately 84 Alaskan huskies in Lapland. \r\nWe operate husky sled tours to tourists in the winter - mainly from the UK. The job will involve managing all aspects of the kennels and being involved in their day-to-day maintenance, including: looking after the health and wellbeing of the dogs; running friendly and informative sled tours with the tourists; cutting trails in the land for the tours; cleaning the kennels daily and feeding the dogs; maintenance work such as repairing wooden kennels; breeding the dogs; keeping proper records of the dogs' health; ordering dog foods and budgeting. \r\nThe successful candidate should: have at least 10 years of experience in a similar role; have experience of working with dogs' vet issues and wellbeing; have experience of working with tourists and offering tourist services; be willing to work in a very remote location in the Lapland wilderness; speak fluent English; have experience of working in an Arctic environment.",
