				"kuvausteksti" : "PENTAIR OVERVIEW\nPentair plc (NYSE: PNR) is a global company dedicated to building a safer, more sustainable world. Pentair delivers industry leading products, services and solutions that help people make the best use of the resources they rely on most. Its technology moves the world forward by ensuring that water is plentiful, useful and pure, and that critical equipment and those near it are protected. With 2016 revenues of $4.9 billion, Pentair employs approximately 19,000 people worldwide.\n\nELECTRICAL SEGMENT OVERVIEW\nA high-performance electrical business focused on improving utilization, lowering costs and maximizing customer uptime. Its industrial enclosures, fastening systems and thermal management technologies help protect sensitive equipment, buildings and critical processes and help keep people safe. Strategic business units include Enclosures, Thermal Management, and Electrical & Fastening Solutions.  Electrical generated approximately $2.1 billion in sales in 2016.\n\nAREA SALES REPRESENTATIVE, West and South-West of Finland \nReporting to: Country Sales Manager - Finland\nBased from home office, a new exciting job opportunity has arisen for a Sales Person for our Pentair Thermal commercial and residential business in West and South-West of Finland.\n\nJob Summary:\nThis position is an external consultative sales role mostly within commercial and residential business. This role will involve selling heating mats and cables, electrical floor heating systems, frost protection solutions for pipes, gutters and ramps. Main customers are electrical and sanitary wholesalers, A&E houses, installers and occasionally end customers.\nThrough daily direct customer visits, this role will promote innovative solutions to both existing and new customers. \nBy actively supporting the development of the country sales strategy and its implementation this role is expected to deliver sustainable and profitable growth for commercial and residential Pentair Thermal application business.\nThis candidate will be responsible for giving trainings, active participation at exhibitions and help customers to choose and use Pentair Thermal products. \n\nMain Duties and Responsibilities:\nMeet or exceed the sales revenue and GOI targets for the region. Country plan is the guide line.\nActively support the development and implementation of a country based growth plan, aligned to the regional initiatives. \nPlan and execute daily customers visits in West and South-West of Finland. \nIdentify projects in the residential and commercial market and secure strong specifications and customer relationships. \nDeliver trainings, Certified PRO seminars, exhibitions and lunch & learns within the region. Key focus customers are electrical and sanitary wholesalers, installers and A&E houses.\nPlan activities in a smart way, provide sales forecasts, and activity reports in CRM. Maintain projects list in CRM database, ensuring regular follow up on all open sales prospects and quotations.\nBe a team player within the country and global organization whilst working cooperatively with Country Sales Manager and other operational areas of the business to deliver outstanding results.\n\nJob requirements:\nHighly motivated and self-driven individual, focused on achieving results.\nWorking from home office, there should be space for samples and marketing material\nHave good interpersonal & communication skills and be a team player\nNative Finnish Language with reasonable written and spoken English.\nPreferably located around Turku or Tampere on the West and South-West side of Finland\nThe position will require extensive daily travel and nights away\nDriving license\nPreferred\nBasic knowledge of electric, Ohms law\nBasic knowledge of electrical heat tracing or low voltage electrical power distribution will be an advantage\nExperience of using Microsoft Office and CRM\nCompetencies:\nIntegrity and Trust\nCustomer Focus\nManage Vision and Purpose\nDrive for results\nBusiness Acumen\nNegotiating\nCommunication\nTeam Player",
