				"kuvausteksti" : "As an Outdoor Instructor, you will be responsible for delivering a range of fun and exciting Arctic activities. From taking families by reindeer sleigh to see Father Christmas in his hideaway log cabin, to guiding a team of snowmobiles down a frozen river in search of the Northern Lights, out Instructors are key in creating memories of magical holidays.\r\n\r\nYou will be responsible for ensuring an excellent standard of service to clients, including providing appropriate briefings on activity content and safety. Utilising your knowledge of H&S, activity planning and risk assessments, you will ensure delivery of all activities is done safely.\r\n\r\nNo two days are alike in the Arctic, and so bundles of energy and a sense of fun will ensure you are able to meet every challenge.\r\n\r\nYou will be expected to be 'hands-on' and willing to help with pre-opening activity bases, ongoing trail maintenance and snow clearing during slack time between client activities.\r\nDrivers license needed.",
