				"kuvausteksti" : "Do you want to be part of a cutting edge team developing the future of transport? Are you ready to be part of a fun and challenging startup journey? Would you like to be involved in major projects that influence how future modes of transport combine, particularly car-sharing? If the answer is yes, apply now\n\nABOUT THE ROLE\n\nAcademic Work is looking for a front-end developer to our client company.\n\nThis job is a staffing position, which means that you will be employed by Academic Work and work as a consultant at Shareit Blox Car.\n\nJOB DUTIES\n\nOur client company is developing the market for mobility and transport services with their online portal for car-sharing. Our client's goal is to make car-sharing easier and contribute towards a major green shift in car-sharing as an integral part of Mobility as a Service. Shareit Blox Car has built a global network and they aim to use it to grow internationally.\n\nThis position suits you who wants to be a part of an exciting startup based in Helsinki.\n\nTechnologies used in the team: JavaScript, CSS, React, React Native, Bootstrap, Python, SQL\n\nWE ARE LOOKING FOR\n\nOur ideal candidate has a relevant educational background and some experience in the IT field and agile software development practices (e.g. summer jobs). You have good skills in JavaScript and CSS. You are eager in becoming an expert in React Native and mobile development or maybe you already have some experience with React Native/React. Our ideal candidate is willing to learn and have strong motivation to grow as a developer.\n\nApply for this position if you have:\n\n-Relevant academic background\n-Good skills in JavaScript and CSS\n-Some experience in the IT field and agile software development practices (e.g. summer jobs)\n-Good communication skills and fluent English skills\n-A desire for growth and improvement!\n\nFluency in Finnish is seen as an advantage. It is also seen as an advantage if you have experience from React, React Native or Bootstrap.\n\nIf you have your own free time projects or school projects (e.g. on Github) that would be relevant in this position, please make sure you include those in your application.\n\nGo ahead and apply already today, since we fill the position as soon as we find a suitable candidate!\n\nIn this position you will be employed by Academic Work and we take care of all the legal responsibilities of an employer such as salary payments, insurances and health care. It is important for us that you feel well and perform in your job. Your consultant manager will be in regular contact with you during the assignment and guides you on your career. Academic Work is an authorized staffing and recruitment agency and our employees are extremely satisfied, something that we are very proud of. We are here to help you succeed!\n\nINFORMATION ON THE APPLICATION PROCESS\n\nTo apply for the job click on \"Apply here\" below. Remember to attach your CV into your application! We only handle applications through our website but if you have questions about the position you can reach us via email hel03@academicwork.fi. Please write the advert ID in the subject and paste the advert link in the mail. We are ongoing screening and contacting candidates so make sure to send your application as soon as possible. Please notice that the advert can be removed before eventual last dates on our external advertising pages. When the advert is being removed it's either due to that the processes is finished or because we have many qualified applications and are continuing in the selection/interview phase.\n\nWe are the Home of the Young Professionals. We are experts in recruitment and staffing university students, recently graduated and professionals in the beginning of their career. You can be employed by us as a consultant in one of our client companies or be recruited directly to our client via our recruitment co-operation. You can read more about us at When employed at Academic Work you will have your own dedicated Consultant Manager, whose role is to answer your questions, support your career development and ensure you enjoy your place of work.\n\nINFORMATION ABOUT THE COMPANY\n\nShareit Blox Car Oy is developing the market for mobility and transport services with their online portal for car-sharing. Their goal is to make car-sharing easier and contribute towards a major green shift in car-sharing as an integral part of Mobility as a Service.",
