				"kuvausteksti" : "Senior Research Fellow in International Business, University of Oulu Business School\n\nThe University of Oulu is an international scientific community with 16 000 students and approximately 3 000 employees. The University is a multidisciplinary institute with modern research and study facilities. It operates in close contact with international educational and research institutes.\n\nThe following position is open at the University of Oulu Business School:\n\nSenior Research Fellow in International Business \n\nThe position is located at the Department of Marketing, Management and International Business. Senior Research Fellow is expected to conduct independent high-quality scientific research as a member of a research group in Management and International Business. The main focus of the research in the groups are in organizational entrepreneurship with focus on new business creation and innovation in international context, and strategic practices in relation to strategic management, networking and responsible business. Senior Research Fellow will teach and supervise theses in the Master's Programme in International Business Management. Senior Research Fellow is also expected to apply funds for research from external sources, and contribute to the development of teaching. Occasional administrative and university-level duties are included in the position.\n\nThe person appointed for the position is required to have a relevant Doctoral degree and ability to teach, supervise and interact in English and operate in a modern university infrastructure within the frame of 1624 hours/ year as specified in the work plan. The person should have strong research orientation, high quality publication record and active participation in research collaboration especially in international scientific community. The person should have a good teaching record, and interest in teaching development. She/he is expected to participate in building up and managing externally funded research projects. \n\nSalary\n\nThe salary of the appointed Senior Research Fellow will be set at level of 6 or 7 the national salary scale for the teaching and research staff of Finnish universities. In addition to this basic salary, supplementary remuneration will be given for personal achievement and performance, the sum rising to a maximum of 46.3% of whatever salary scale (6-7) is set for the post. The salary is in practice roughly 4079 -4937€ per month, depending on the appointee's qualification and experience. \n\nApplication together with all the relevant documents (detailed below) should be submitted electronically by Thursday, 30 November 2017. \n\nThe position is filled as of 1 March 2018 or as soon as possible thereafter, and is filled until 31 December 2022. There is a trial period of 4 months for this position. \n\nFurther details can be obtained from Professor Tuija Mainela,tel. 0294 482595, tuija.mainela(at)oulu.fi or Personnel Manager Kimmo Spets, tel. 0294 483819, kimmo, spets(at)oulu.fi \n\nThe following documents should be included in the application: \n1.Curriculum vitae in English (max. 4 pages).\n2.Publication list grouped as follows: (1) articles in refereed scientific journals; (2) articles in edited books, (3) articles in refereed conference proceedings; (4) scientific monographs, and (5) other scientific publications.\n3.Short description of the research merits relevant to the position and a short  presentation of research plans and aspirations (max 4 pages).\n4.Shortdescription of the teaching merits orteaching portfolio (max. 4 pages).\n5.Maximum of 5 publications (delivered in electronic format), which the applicant wants to be acknowledged in evaluation of her/his qualifications and merits in relation to the job.",
