				"kuvausteksti" : "Channel Marketing Manager Europe\r\n \r\nPowervision Robot (www.powervision.me) since its inception in 2010 has had the mission to innovate the future focusing on artificial intelligence (AI), robotics, and big data. Powervision has been a market leader in commercial UAV-related products and services including smart drones, data visualization and forecasting, virtual reality and augmented reality. Beyond its headquarters in Beijing, China, Powervision has international offices in Helsinki, Silicon Valley, Boston, Perth, Frankfurt, Shanghai, and Shenzhen.\r\n \r\nPowervision is looking for a Channel Marketing Manager to join our European team based in Espoo, Finland. Your main responsibility will be to independently ensure the Powervision brand is presented according to the brand guidelines and the company's high standards in stores, at trade fairs and expos, and throughout distributors across the European region, focusing on key markets like UK, Germany, France, Netherlands, Italy, and Spain. Powervision is growing rapidly worldwide, and our European marketing team is now looking for you to improve our visibility. The products you will be working with are consumer drones and robots, for both air and water.\r\n \r\nWe are looking for a person that is used to work in a fast-changing environment, has great prioritising skills and can work efficiently, both independently and as a proactive team member.\r\n\r\nKey Responsibilities:\r\nTrade partner relations\r\nIndependently plan and create Powervision's in-store presence\r\nDevelop and cooperate with distributors on the plan for marketing the products\r\nOrganise and participate in marketing events and fairs across Europe\r\nMonitor and evaluate competitor POS activity to gain and present actionable insights \r\nAdvocating for the brand amongst key retailing partners\r\nCreation and deployment of sales force training materials\r\nDevelop business cases for offers/promotions\r\n \r\nRequirements:\r\n3+ years of experience, a plus if it's in consumer electronics \r\nBachelor's degree in marketing, communications, advertising or related field.\r\nExperience in planning and deploying POS materials at big scale\r\nKnowledge of the retail and consumer electronics industry in Europe\r\nGood organisational skills and an eye for detail\r\nExperience in cross-cultural working environment is a plus\r\nPassionate about technology and drones in particular (desirable)\r\nEnglish as working language, German, Spanish, Italian, French or Russian a definitive advantage \r\nGlobal and growth mindset\r\n \r\nWhat we offer you\r\nFront seat in a growing, innovative global company\r\nPossibility to influence the company marketing strategies\r\nSpace to express creativity and develop the own marketing skills\r\nPossibility to travel\r\nCompetitive salary\r\n \r\nWe are interviewing immediately suitable candidates and the role will be filled as soon as the right profile is found. What are you waiting for?! Send us your cover letter and CV as soon as possible to: europe@powervision.me.\r\nWebsite: www.powervision.me",
