				"kuvausteksti" : "Wärtsilä Services supports its customers throughout the lifecycle of their installations by optimising efficiency and performance. The company's service network of approximately 11,000 professionals in 160 global locations is unmatched in the industry, delivering services to more than 12,000 customers every year. The portfolio of services - from spare parts to complete operational, maintenance, and optimisation services - is constantly being developed, not only to improve the availability of customers' installations, but to support them in growing their businesses.  Wärtsilä is committed to providing high quality, expert support, and the availability of services in the most environmentally sound way possible, whenever, wherever.\n\nWärtsilä Training Services is looking for a (Senior) Instructor, Electrical Systems. Title and responsibilities of the employee depends on the experience level. \n\nYour responsibilities in this job will mainly consist of providing technical training for internal and external customers, as well as participating in the training content material production process. Additionally, you will be responsible for maintaining and developing practical training environment and facilities. In this position you would be a part of a passionate training team, supporting and developing the team within areas of your own expertise. \n\nThe position is located in Turku, Finland. \n\nB.Sc. or M.Sc. in Electrical Engineering, Mechatronics or an equivalent education is needed for this job. The behaviours we wish you would have are openness and flexibility to promote building of customer relations and teamwork. In this position, self-management skills are also needed to perform and act independently on different tasks. The job includes travelling a few weeks per year. A desired skill is also good command of English and good skills in communication and documentation. \n\nWorking experience in the field and / or experience in training is considered as a strong merit. We also highly appreciate experience in Operation and Maintenance of Wärtsilä engines, Power Plant and / or Ship Power technology, Commissioning work, or LNG and / or environmental technology. \n\nContact person to give further information:\nMikko Issakainen \nTel. +358403567348 \nEmail: mikko.issakainen@wartsila.com",
