				"kuvausteksti" : "ADB SAFEGATE is a leading provider of solutions that boost efficiency, improve safety, raise environmental sustainability and reduce operational costs for airports. The company partners with airports to explore their current situations, identify bottlenecks and jointly solve them through integrated solutions that address airport operations from approach to departure. These solutions tackle every aspect of traffic handling and guidance, from approach, runway and taxiway lighting, to tower-based traffic control systems, to intelligent gate and docking automation. ADB SAFEGATE has more than 900 employees in more than 20 countries and operates in more than 175 countries, serving more than 2,500 airports.\n\n CUSTOMER SALES REPRESENTATIVE\n\n This role is well matched for a technical person, who enjoys being a link between customers, sales and other internal departments. You thrive in an international company and find being a crucial part of overall customer satisfaction highly meaningful. Airport environment and being part of it's functionality is part of the charm: Your input enables airports (in this case Helsinki-Vantaa) to operate more safely, efficiently and sustainably.\n\n What it's about / Job Description\n\n As Customer Service Representative your mission is  to support e.g. Sales Managers with technical assistance providing high quality service during the commissioning of the ADB Safegate equipment on site, troubleshooting any issues with our products or systems and following-up of the sales process from A to Z.Your main task is to contribute to customer satisfaction by being the first contact when information is needed by e.g. handling services requests and claims in time and looking for the best solution for both the customer and the company. This acquires process handling and keeping the customers up to date on a regularly basis. You visit Airport Maintenance Managers to better define their needs. In addition to helping customers, your know-how is needed in supporting and training other Customer Relation Representatives worldwide and also being consulted by sales when it comes to the preparation and handling of maintenance contracts. You reclaim ADB Safegate's customer promise by providing top notch customer service every day.\n\n Desirable skill-set\n\n - Technical background: Industrial engineer or equivalent by experience\n - Commercial sensitivity and driven by customer satisfaction\n - Sense for initiative\n - Ability to build relationships and will to help people by problem-solving and top notch service\n - Good oral and written communications skills: English (Nr 1 priority), Finnish, Russian language is an absolute asset\n \n\n What's in it for me?\n\n You get to combine your technical expertise with your people skills and do so in a communal working environment, where there are no two days alike and you have all the support for your professional growth. You will receive training on ADB SAFEGATE equipment and standard.  Despite the size of the organisation, you enjoy the benefits of a rather compact team here in Finland. The office in Vantaa is shared with 15+ employees that gather around for breakfast and change of thoughts and  share a game of badminton every week.\n\n Intrigued? Please send your CV and application via the link below by 26th of November the latest. Do note, that we are in contact with suitable candidates already during this period and will fill the position as soon as a match is found. For more information please contact Rainmaker Recruitment Consultant \nAnna Martinsen p. 044 755 3902 on Thu 16.11 or Tue 21.11. between 13-15.",
