				"kuvausteksti" : "The European Chemicals Agency (ECHA) is the driving force among regulatory authorities in implementing the EU's groundbreaking chemicals legislation for the benefit of human health and the environment as well as for innovation and competitiveness. ECHA helps companies to comply with the legislation, advances the safe use of chemicals, provides information on chemicals and addresses chemicals of concern.\n\n\nOur client, European Chemicals Agency (ECHA) is looking for an ADMINISTRATIVE ASSISTANT (Unit A2) for fixed term period until 31/03/2018. The start date will be agreed with the selected candidate but we hope that you are able to start the assignment as soon as possible. The work environment is very international and youthful and the office is located in Helsinki city center. The position is filled as soon as the suitable candidate is found.\n\nGeneral description: Assist the Regulatory Advice and HelpNet Secretariat in its work.\n\nDuties:\n\n1. As member of the regulatory advice team, provide regulatory advice to stakeholders, thereby;\n\n- Ensuring quality in terms of content and timeliness\n\n- Proactively seeking information necessary to respond to enquiries\n\n- Contributing to the high level of performance for the entire ECHA Helpdesk\n\n- Act as back-up for team members\n\n2. As member of the regulatory advice team:\n\n- Act as a focal point in the unit for your area of expertise, identifying upcoming developments relevant for the ECHA Helpdesk\n\n- Proactively informing peers and national helpdesks on developments, and sharing knowledge with them\n\n- Engage in review and revision of published FAQs and Q&As\n\n- Support in the organisation of one-to-one sessions at ECHA events\n\n3. Provide secretarial and administrative services to the unit:\n\n- Assist in the organization of the unit work\n\n- Interact proactively with colleagues within and outside the Unit\n\n- Respond pro-actively to ad hoc tasks\n\n- Ensure that documents/signataires submitted for signature have correct layout\n\n- Preparation of Remedy-requests to ICT Helpdesk and Corporate Services\n\n- Submit Remedy-requests to ICT Helpdesk and Corporate Services on behalf of the Head of Unit and the unit staff\n\n- Support the Head of Unit and bring up issues to his attention\n\n4. Reflect ECHA's values and people principles in your day-to-day workplace interactions with colleagues and stakeholders\n\nRequirements:\n\n- Successful completion of post-secondary level education attested by a diploma\n\n- Minimum one (1) year of professional experience relevant to the job\n\n- Ability to write and to communicate clearly and efficiently in spoken and written English \n\n- Ability to work in a multicultural environment\n\n- Specific competencies: knowledge and experience with REACH and CLP legislations will be an asset\n\n- Drafting skills and Helpdesk experience will be an asset\n\nBefore appointment, successful applicants will be asked to produce an official document indicating that they do not have a criminal record.\n \nWe offer you an interesting, multicultural working environment and a chance to develop you skills.\n\nApply for this job with your registered EUROPASS CV and cover letter by clicking \"Hae/Apply\" on Manpower's website www.manpower.fi.\n\nManpower is the global leader in contingent and permanent recruitment workforce solutions. It is part of ManpowerGroup, the world leader in innovative workforce solutions. Manpower Finland is an authorized private employment agency with branches across the nation. Its combination of global reach and local expertise allows for greater flexibility and agility to respond to changing business needs, providing unique value to clients and candidates through permanent, temporary and contract positions.",
