				"kuvausteksti" : "ADB SAFEGATE is a leading provider of solutions that boost efficiency, improve safety, raise environmental sustainability and reduce operational costs for airports. The company partners with airports to explore their current situations, identify bottlenecks and jointly solve them through integrated solutions that address airport operations from approach to departure. These solutions tackle every aspect of traffic handling and guidance, from approach, runway and taxiway lighting, to tower-based traffic control systems, to intelligent gate and docking automation. ADB SAFEGATE has more than 900 employees in more than 20 countries and operates in more than 175 countries, serving more than 2,500 airports.\n\n CONTRACT SALES ADMINISTRATOR\n\n This versatile role as sales team support is a match for a service-minded person who enjoys giving back-up and coordinating. You thrive in an international company where you get to have your language skills in use and find being a crucial part of overall customer satisfaction highly meaningful. You are the one \nto turn to when questions arise regarding sales orders or processes. Your input ensures customer satisfaction and by doing so, enable airports \n(in this case Helsinki-Vantaa) to operate more safely, efficiently and sustainably.\n\n What it's about / Job Description\n\n As Contact Sales Administrator your mission is to contribute to the objectives of the Sales Department by anticipating customer needs and giving priority to customer satisfaction. Your territory is order process handling from order intake till expedition and ensuring the delivery times. Effective communication with customers as well as colleagues in all order related issues is your main task. You report regularly to the manager the status of pending orders (backlog) \nin order to identify the financial and operational issues. In addition, you work cooperatively within ADB Safegate organization and outside the territory \nto promote sales goals.\n\n Desirable skill-set\n\n You have experience in similar role and have a customer minded approach in everything you do. You show initiative and reliability - you simply get things done. \nYou are able to view things in global perspective and have a focus on result and quality. Good oral and written language skills are necessary: English (Nr 1 priority) and Finnish. Russian language is seen as an absolute advantage. Knowledge about AGL technologies, experience in use of quotation tool and SAP (SD Module) are welcomed as well, but not top priority.\n\n What's in it for me?\n\n You get to work in a communal working environment in an international organization where you have all the support for your professional growth. Despite the size of the organisation, you enjoy the benefits of a rather compact team here in Finland. The office in Vantaa is shared with 15+ employees that gather around for breakfast and change of thoughts and share a game of badminton every week.\n\n Intrigued? Please send your CV and application via the link below by 26th of November the latest. Do note, that we are in contact with suitable candidates already during this period and will fill the position as soon as a match is found. For more information please contact Rainmaker's Recruitment Consultant Anna Martinsen p. 044 755 3902 on Thu 16.11 or Tue 21.11. between 13-15.",
